(30,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The initial time of employment is considered the orientation and training period. This period usually lasts approximately 90 <span style=\"border:none\">days; however, it can be extended at our discretion.</span></span></span></span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n',	2,	'Orientation and Training Period-non-MT',	'ORIENTATION AND TRAINING PERIOD',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"Non-MT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:14:56',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	10,	0),
(31,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">We refer to your initial time of employment as the orientation and training period, although many entities use the term probationary period. The orientation&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">and training period usually lasts approximately 90 days; however, it can be extended at our discretion.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	2,	'Orientation and Training Period-MT',	'ORIENTATION AND TRAINING PERIOD',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:15:58',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	11,	0),
(32,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>We must keep certain personnel records in order to comply with legislated record keeping a<span>nd reporting requirements. Many of these records you will be asked to complete upon employment. These records are confidential and only made available to authorized personnel. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>The physical safety and privacy of personnel records must be secured at all time<span>. Therefore, files are locked and/or contain special computer access codes. Entry to the files is strictly limited to authorized personnel on a need-to-know basis. If you access your own, or a co-worker&rsquo;s, confidential employee file without authorization<span>, you may be subject to disciplinary action up to and including termination.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">You, along with previous </span></span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>employees, may inspect and copy certain documents in your personnel file. We reserve the right to determine which documents you may inspect at any given<span> time in accordance with any law. These inspections are limited to no more than twice in a 12 month period. A request for an appointment to review the file must be submitted in writing using the </span></span></span></span><span><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Request to Review Personnel File Form</span></span></em></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	2,	'Personnel Records-non-MA VA',	'PERSONNEL RECORDS',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"AL\",\"AK\",\"AZ\",\"AR\",\"CA\",\"CO\",\"CT\",\"DE\",\"DC\",\"FL\",\"GA\",\"HI\",\"ID\",\"IL\",\"IN\",\"IA\",\"KS\",\"KY\",\"LA\",\"ME\",\"MD\",\"MI\",\"MN\",\"MS\",\"MO\",\"MT\",\"NE\",\"NV\",\"NH\",\"NJ\",\"NM\",\"NY\",\"NC\",\"ND\",\"OH\",\"OK\",\"OR\",\"PA\",\"RI\",\"SC\",\"SD\",\"TN\",\"TX\",\"UT\",\"VT\",\"WA\",\"WV\",\"WI\",\"WY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:18:52',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	14,	0),
(33,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Please park in the designated areas for employees. Remember to lock your car. W<span style=\"border:none\">e will not be responsible for damage or theft to personal </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">vehicles</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> <span style=\"border:none\">or property.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	2,	'Parking',	'PARKING',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:20:18',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	17,	0),
(34,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you use your own vehicle for managing any of your work duties, you will be required to provide proof of a valid driver&rsquo;s license&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">and adequate insurance coverage. Documentation showing proof of both is to be given to us each time your license or insurance is renewed.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You are <span style=\"border:none\">not to text or use cell phones <span style=\"border:none\">and other electronic devices while you are driving for business-related<span style=\"border:none\"> reasons. If it is necessary to use any wireless communication instrument, you must have a hands-free device or pull over.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	2,	'Use of Private Vehicle',	'USE OF PRIVATE VEHICLE',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:21:11',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	18,	0),
(35,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You will be provided a schedule for your workdays and hours.&nbsp;We reserve the right to<span style=\"border:none\"> increase or decrease your workdays and hours as needed. You are responsible for being available for work when required. </span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You are not permitted to work on your own initiative before or after scheduled working hours or during unpaid meal periods or paid rest breaks (if applicable).</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Unexpected emergencies and changes in planned procedures may occasionally make it necessary to work beyond the scheduled work hours. When overtime is required, you will be notified as much in advance as possible.&nbsp;When required,<span style=\"border:none\"> we may assign employees to jobs other than their usual assignments.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Exchanging Hours</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;please do not exchange hours with another employee without prior approval. Authorization will not be granted unless it can be accomplished without overtime.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Hours of Work',	'HOURS OF WORK',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:25:57',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	0,	0),
(36,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You must complete and sign a time record reflecting actual hours worked each day, either electronically or on paper, whether you are paid salaried or hourly. Any mistakes or omissions on the attendance record are to be reported immediately, and we will make the necessary corrections. No other employee is permitted to enter your time for you. Likewise, do not register another employee&#39;s time even if requested to do so.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustified\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Please enter all paid time off on your attendance record during the pay period in which it occurred.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustified\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustified\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11\"><span style=\"text-decoration:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance records are legal documentation of hours worked and must not be destroyed, falsified, defaced or removed from the premises.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Attendance Records',	'ATTENDANCE RECORDS',	'none',	'2017-10-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:27:10',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	1,	0),
(37,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You will be provided information regarding the payday schedule. Wages are paid according to the designated schedule unless you are notified in advance of a change. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If a payday cannot occur due to an office or bank closure, you will be paid on the last workday immediately&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">preceding the closure. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Please review your paycheck for errors. If you find a mistake, report it immediately so it can be corrected. To prevent misunderstandings later, any discrepancies must be reported within 30 days after receiving the check,<span style=\"border:none\"> or we will assume that no error has occurred.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You are responsible for your individual paycheck after it has been received. Please report a lost payroll check within 24 hours so we can initiate the &ldquo;stop-payment&rdquo; process.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Pay Schedule',	'PAY SCHEDULE',	'none',	'2017-10-26 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:28:01',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	3,	0),
(38,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">From your </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11\"><span style=\"text-decoration:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">actual commencement</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> of duties until the end of your workday, except for time spent at lunch, constitutes time worked</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. <span style=\"border:none\">Prepping the work area<span style=\"border:none\">, clean<span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">-up time, <span style=\"border:none\">and <span style=\"border:none\">employee meetings in the beginning or during the day are also time worked. Arriving early, leaving late, or preliminary time spent in attending to personal matters such as grooming, changing clothes (unless required by the nature of the job)<span style=\"border:none\">, are not considered time worked. Do not sign in until you are ready to go to work. Likewise, do not work after you have signed off. For purposes of calculating overtime, time worked does not include paid time off.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'What Constitutes Time Worked',	'WHAT CONSTITUTES TIME WORKED',	'none',	'2017-10-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:30:56',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	4,	0),
(39,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">When the doctor is away from the office and therefore not seeing patients, your presence may or may not be required depending on <span style=\"border:none\">our<span style=\"border:none\"> workload and staffing needs. You will be informed of the schedule while the doctor is away as soon as possible<span style=\"border:none\">. <span style=\"border:none\">When <span style=\"border:none\">you are not required to work, your time off will be unpaid unless you have available paid time off to use.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'When Doctor Is Away',	'WHEN THE DOCTOR IS AWAY',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"doptional\",\"voptional\",\"moptional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:31:58',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	5,	0),
(40,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Absenteeism</strong>&mdash;it is important that we have adequate staff to handle the workload at all times. Therefore, any unexcused absence from work, regardless of the reason, is unacceptable and constitutes an unsatisfactory work record. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Tardiness</strong>&mdash;we expect you to be on time and ready to begin work according to your schedule. Unexcused lateness, regardless of the reason, is not acceptable and reflects poorly on your work performance. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">In case of an unexpected absence or tardiness, please notify us as soon as possible. Ideally, notification will occur 1-2 hours before your shift is scheduled to begin. Depending on the circumstances and applicable laws, failing to call-in or follow proper call-in procedures may subject you to disciplinary action up to and including termination. &nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Please call every day during an absence unless otherwise agreed upon. Absences longer than 1 week are converted to a leave of absence.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Excessive tardiness and/or absences may be subject to disciplinary action up to and including termination.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Exceptions to this attendance policy will be made for any situation that is covered by law.</span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Attendance Punctuality',	'ATTENDANCE AND PUNCTUALITY',	'none',	'2019-04-11 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:33:36',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	9,	0),
(41,	'<p>You may be asked to be available on an on-call basis during your non-work hours due to potential unique staffing needs including, but not limited to, emergencies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Though you are on-call, you will be able to use your free time effectively for your own purposes except for when you must respond to calls if/when they come in. In doing so, you must manage them appropriately and professionally at all times, regardless of when or where you are taking the calls.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be paid for all calls that you manage, as well as any other work duties you perform as a result of the calls. The compensation provided may be at a different rate than your normal wage, and you will be notified in advance of any rate change in effect. Your work time while on call will count towards your total working hours for the day/week and will be used to calculate overtime, if applicable. Please track the time you spend performing work duties related to taking calls so that we may pay you accordingly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you find that being on call is impeding on your free time in some way, please let us know so that we may correct our procedures.</p>\r\n',	3,	'On Call Hours',	'ON-CALL HOURS',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 02:34:27',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'disabled',	11,	0),
(42,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">When you work more than 40 hours in a workweek, you will be paid overtime&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">in accordance with the federal Fair Labor Standards Act. At no time&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">will compensatory time off (comp time)<span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;be provided in-lieu-of overtime payments. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Definition of a Workweek</span></span></b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;we define the workweek as Sunday<span style=\"border:none\"> starting at midnight <span style=\"border:none\">through Saturday at 11:5<span style=\"border:none\">9P.M. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Overtime </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">will be calculated at <span style=\"border:none\">1 &frac12; times<span style=\"border:none\"> your regular hourly rate of pay, regardless of method of payment (hourly, daily, or salary). Daily or salary compensation will be converted into an hourly rate for overtime<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;calculation purposes.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">If you qualify and are </span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">classified as an exempt employee, you </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">will not be provided with overtime pay.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Overtime is based on hours worked, not hours paid. Therefore, any paid time off taken in association with any provided&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">benefits <span style=\"border:none\">is<span style=\"border:none\"> not considered when calculating overtime.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime is to be authorized in advance.&nbsp;</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You are not permitted to work more than your regularly scheduled hours without prior approval and may not work <span style=\"border:none\">at<span style=\"border:none\"> your own initiative before or after scheduled&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">working hours or during non-paid meal periods or breaks. Violation of this policy may result in disciplinary action, up to and including <span style=\"border:none\">termination<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Overtime Pay-non-AK-CA-CO-NV',	'OVERTIME PAY',	'none',	'2018-09-11 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"AL\",\"AZ\",\"AR\",\"CT\",\"DE\",\"DC\",\"FL\",\"GA\",\"HI\",\"ID\",\"IL\",\"IN\",\"IA\",\"KS\",\"KY\",\"LA\",\"ME\",\"MD\",\"MA\",\"MI\",\"MN\",\"MS\",\"MO\",\"MT\",\"NE\",\"NH\",\"NJ\",\"NM\",\"NY\",\"NC\",\"ND\",\"OH\",\"OK\",\"OR\",\"PA\",\"RI\",\"SC\",\"SD\",\"TN\",\"TX\",\"UT\",\"VT\",\"VA\",\"WA\",\"WV\",\"WI\",\"WY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 03:20:23',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	12,	0),
(43,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">When you work more than<span style=\"border:none\"> 8 hours in a day and/or more than 40 hours in a workweek, you will be paid overtime in accordance with both state and federal regulations. At no ti<span style=\"border:none\">me will compensatory time off (comp&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">ti<span style=\"border:none\">me) be provided in-lieu-of overtime payments.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Definition of a Workweek</span></span></b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;we define the workweek as Sunday starting at <span style=\"border:none\">midnight<span style=\"border:none\"> through Saturday at 11:59P.M. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Overtime </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">will be calculated at&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">1 &frac12; <span style=\"border:none\">times your regular hourly rate of pay, regardless of method of payment (hourly, daily, or salary<span style=\"border:none\">). Daily or salary compensation will be converted into an hourly rate for overtime calculation purposes.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Overtime is not paid twice for the same hours. Only hours worked at straight time apply to the weekly 40 hour limit. This prevents &ldquo;pyramiding&rdquo; of<span style=\"border:none\"> overtime, where you earn overtime on top of overtime already paid. Once you have been paid overtime for hours worked over the daily requirement, if applicable, those overtime hours do not count toward the weekly 40 hour limit.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">If you qualify and are </span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">classified as an exempt employee, you </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">will not be provided with overtime pay.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Overtime is based on hours worked, not hours paid. Therefore, any paid time off taken in association with any provided benefits <span style=\"border:none\">is<span style=\"border:none\"> not considered when calculating overtime<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime is to be authorized in advance.&nbsp;</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You are not permitted to work more than your regularly scheduled hours without prior approval and may not work <span style=\"border:none\">at<span style=\"border:none\"> your own initiative before or after scheduled working hours or during non-paid meal periods or breaks<span style=\"border:none\">. Violation of this policy may result in disciplinary action, up to and including <span style=\"border:none\">termination<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Overtime Pay-CA-AK',	'OVERTIME PAY',	'none',	'2018-09-11 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"AK\",\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 03:22:19',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	13,	0),
(44,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">When you work more than <span style=\"border:none\">12<span style=\"border:none\"> hours in a day and/or more than 40 hours in a workweek, <span style=\"border:none\">you will be paid overtime in accordance with both state and federal regulations. At no time will compensatory time off (comp time) be provided in-lieu-of overtime payments.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Definition of a Workweek</span></span></b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;we define the workweek as Sunday starting at midnight through&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">Saturday at 11:59P.M. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Overtime </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">will be calculated at 1 &frac12; times your regular hourly rate of pay, regardless of method of payment (hourly, daily, or salary). Daily or salary compensation will be converted into <span style=\"border:none\">an hourly rate for overtime calculation purposes.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Overtime is not paid twice for the same hours. Only hours worked at straight time apply to the weekly 40 hour limit. This prevents &ldquo;pyramiding&rdquo; of overtime, where you earn overtime on top of overtime already&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">paid. Once you have been paid overtime for hours worked over the daily requirement, if applicable, those overtime hours do not count toward the weekly 40 hour limit.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">If you qualify and are </span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">classified as an exempt employee, you </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">will not be provided&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">with overtime pay.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Overtime is based on hours worked, not hours paid. Therefore, any paid time off taken in association with any provided benefits <span style=\"border:none\">is<span style=\"border:none\"> not considered when calculating overtime.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime is to be authorized in advance.&nbsp;</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You are not permitted&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">to work more than your regularly scheduled hours without prior approval and may not work at your own initiative before or after scheduled working hours or during non-paid meal periods or breaks. Violation of this policy may result in disciplinary action<span style=\"border:none\">, up to and including <span style=\"border:none\">termination<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Overtime Pay-CO',	'OVERTIME PAY',	'none',	'2018-09-11 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 03:23:23',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	14,	0),
(45,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you earn less than 1 &frac12; times the minimum wage rate, w<span style=\"border:none\">hen you work more than <span style=\"border:none\">8<span style=\"border:none\"> hours in a day and/or more than 40 hours in a workweek, you will&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">be paid overtime in accordance with both state and federal regulations. <span style=\"border:none\">If you earn more than 1 &frac12; times the minimum wage rate, you will be paid overtime when you work more than 40 hours in a workweek in accordance with federal regulations. <span style=\"border:none\">At no time will&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">compensatory time off (comp time) be provided in-lieu-of overtime payments.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Definition of a Workweek</span></span></b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;we define the workweek as Sunday starting at midnight through Saturday at 11:59P.M. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Overtime </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">will be calculated at <span style=\"border:none\">1 &frac12; times your regular hourly rate of pay, regardless of method of payment (hourly, daily, or salary). Daily or salary compensation will be converted into an hourly rate for overtime calculation purposes.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Overtime is not paid twice for the same hour<span style=\"border:none\">s. Only hours worked at straight time apply to the weekly 40 hour limit. This prevents &ldquo;pyramiding&rdquo; of overtime, where you earn overtime on top of overtime already paid. Once you have been paid overtime for hours worked over the daily requirement, if applicable<span style=\"border:none\">, those overtime hours do not count toward the weekly 40 hour limit.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">If you qualify and are </span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">classified as an exempt employee, you </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">will not be provided with overtime pay.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Overtime is based on hours worked, not hours paid. Therefore, any pa<span style=\"border:none\">id time off taken in association with any provided benefits are not considered when calculating overtime.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime is to be authorized in advance.&nbsp;</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You are not permitted to work more than your regularly scheduled hours without prior approval and may not work&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">at your own initiative before or after scheduled working hours or during non-paid meal periods or breaks. Violation of this policy may result in disciplinary action, up to and including discharge.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Overtime Pay-NV',	'OVERTIME PAY',	'none',	'2018-09-11 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 03:24:46',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	15,	0),
(46,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">State and federal&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">taxes will be withheld from your paycheck in accordance with state and federal laws.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You are required to fill out a </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Withholding Exemption Certificate (W-4</span></span></i></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">)</span></span></i></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Form </span></span></i></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">on or before the day you begin work. If you fail to fill out a Form W-4, we are required to withhold the maximum amount of tax. A Form W-4 remains in effect until a new amended form is submitted by you. An amended Form W-4 will be made effective by the first payroll period ending approximately 30&nbsp;days after you submit the form</span></span></span>.</p>\r\n',	3,	'Payroll Deductions',	'PAYROLL DEDUCTIONS',	'none',	'2017-10-26 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 03:26:22',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	16,	0),
(47,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">We do not pay wages or salaries in advance. Exceptions may be made for extreme emergencies or circumstances on a case-by-case basis at our discretion. If you wish to request a pay advance, you may submit the </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Request <span style=\"border:none\">for Salary Advance Form</span></span></span></i></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. Please do so at least 2 weeks in advance.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Pay Advances',	'PAY ADVANCES',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 03:27:25',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	17,	0),
(48,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Your position may require&nbsp;licensure or certification. In such cases, maintaining valid and current licensure or certification is a condition of employment and is your responsibility<span style=\"border:none\">.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">For the purposes of recertification, any continuing education requirement must be managed, planned and scheduled by you. Please arrange to attend courses during hours you are not scheduled to work.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Upon completion of recertification, please provide&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">us with a copy of the renewed license. We assume no responsibility if you become delinquent in the number of units needed for recertification and, consequently, lose your license.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Recertification',	'RECERTIFICATION',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 03:29:50',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	21,	0),
(49,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-CT under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CT\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:32:58',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	117,	1),
(50,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-CT over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CT\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:33:51',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	118,	1),
(51,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be given a Leave of Absence to attend jury service. If you work full-time and you have been employed for more than 90 days and you work 30 or more hours per week, you will be paid your regular wages for the first 5 days of jury duty service, or any part thereof.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-CT',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:34:52',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	324,	1),
(52,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:14pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with any other authorized breaks, whether paid or unpaid, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-GA under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"GA\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:37:40',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	125,	1),
(53,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with any other authorized breaks, whether paid or unpaid, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-GA over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"GA\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:38:35',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	126,	1),
(54,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages, less the amount paid by the court, will be paid while on jury duty. Please submit a copy of the compensation received from the jury service for our payroll records. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-GA',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"GA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:44:22',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	329,	1),
(55,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When you have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day, you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide up to 2 hours of time off to vote. We may specify when the time off will be taken. Voting time is unpaid.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-GA',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"GA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:45:20',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	381,	1),
(56,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\">We are an E-Verify employer. E-Verify is an internet-based system that compares information from the </span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Employment Eligibility&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">Verification Form</span></span></span></i></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> (I-9)</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:#252525\"> you completed upon hire to data from the <i>U.S. Department of Homeland Security</i> and <i>Social Security Administration</i> records. This process will confirm your employment eligibility and comply with federal and state immigration laws.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	2,	'E-Verify-GA',	'E-VERIFY',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"GA\"]',	11,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:46:36',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	26,	0),
(57,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-ID under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ID\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:49:34',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	132,	1),
(58,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-ID over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ID\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:50:26',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	131,	1),
(59,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-ID',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ID\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-11 05:51:24',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	332,	1),
(60,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The 1994 Uniformed Services Employment and Reemployment Rights Act (USERRA), guarantees that if you are placed on active military duty, including Army, Navy, Air Force, Marine Corps, Coast Guard, and their<span style=\"border:none\"> reserves, you will be re-employed when you return to civilian life again.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">USERRA requires prompt reemployment. What is considered &quot;prompt&quot; generally depends on the circumstances and duration of the military leave, while some exceptions do apply. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Those <span style=\"border:none\">returning to work must be reinstated to the same position and benefits to which they would have been entitled if continuously employed. This includes seniority, seniority-tied increases in benefit earning rates, pay raises based on longevity, and promotion<span style=\"border:none\">s based on longevity or length of service that they were reasonably certain to have achieved.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">We will provide military leave in accordance with USERRA rules and regulations. Please talk to us if you need, or think you will need, military leave.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'USERRA',	'UNIFORMED SERVICES EMPLOYMENT AND REEMPLOYMENT RIGHTS ACT',	'none',	'2017-08-24 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 00:52:55',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	240,	1),
(61,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are bereaved by the death of a family member, you may be provided a leave of absence. Unless there are extenuating circumstances, you must request and get approval for the leave in advance. The<span style=\"border:none\"> amount of time off provided is at our discretion and is based, in large part, on the staffing needs at the time of the request. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">After you have successfully completed the orientation and training period, you may be eligible for compensation for the wages<span style=\"border:none\"> lost while on the leave. Time paid for bereavement leave will not be counted as hours worked for computing overtime. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Compensation is provided according to the following provisions:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustified\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Regular Full-Time Employees:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Up to a total of ______ workdays* when a death<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;occurs in your immediate family.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Up to a total of ______ workdays* when the death of a relative occurs in your family.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustified\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Regular Part-Time Employees:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Up to a total of ______ workdays* when a death occurs in your immediate family.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Up to a total of ______ workdays* when the death of a relative occurs in your family.<span style=\"border:none\"> </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">*A workday constitutes the number of hours you would have worked had you not been off for bereavement leave.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustified\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Immediate family</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> i<span style=\"border:none\">s defined as father, mother, sister, brother, legal spouse, domestic partner, son, daughter, step-parents, step-siblings, father-in-law, mother-in-law, grandparents, and grandchildren (whether related by blood, adoption, or marriage).</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Relative</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> is defined as brother-in-law, sister-in-law, daughter-in-law, son-in-law or a relative residing as a regular household member in the home of the employee.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Bereavement Leave non-NY',	'BEREAVEMENT LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-07-20 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"AL\",\"AK\",\"AZ\",\"AR\",\"CA\",\"CO\",\"CT\",\"DE\",\"DC\",\"FL\",\"GA\",\"HI\",\"ID\",\"IL\",\"IN\",\"IA\",\"KS\",\"KY\",\"LA\",\"ME\",\"MD\",\"MA\",\"MI\",\"MN\",\"MS\",\"MO\",\"MT\",\"NE\",\"NV\",\"NH\",\"NJ\",\"NM\",\"NC\",\"ND\",\"OH\",\"OK\",\"OR\",\"PA\",\"RI\",\"SC\",\"SD\",\"TN\",\"TX\",\"UT\",\"VT\",\"VA\",\"WA\",\"WV\",\"WI\",\"WY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:04:13',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	51,	1),
(62,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">To help secure your future retirement, we offer a retirement plan. We will provide you with the plan documents at the time you become eligible to participate. Please see the Plan Administrator for more information.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Retirement Plan',	'RETIREMENT PLAN',	'none',	'2017-08-24 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:04:55',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	54,	1),
(63,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">After completing the orientation and training period, you may receive the following veterinary benefits for up to 4 personal pets. Veterinary benefits cover the type of professional treatment we normally provide.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Regular Full-Time Employees</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;a</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> <u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </u>percent courtesy discount on veterinary services including dental, X-ray, surgeries, exams, hospitalization, professional fees, boarding, office visits, etc. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Regular Full-Time Employees</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;a</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> <u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </u>percent courtesy discount on laboratory work, dispensed drugs, flea products, pet products, etc.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Regular Full-Time Employees</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;a</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> <u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </u>percent courtesy discount on pet diet foods such as Science Diet, Prescription Diet, etc., and on baths and grooming performed by groomer.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Regular Part-Time Employees</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;a</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> <u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </u>percent courtesy discount on veterinary services including dental, X-ray, surgeries, exams, hospitalization, professional fees, boarding, office visits, etc. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Regular Part -Time Employees</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;a</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> <u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </u>percent courtesy discount on laboratory work, dispensed drugs, flea products, pet products, etc.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Regular Part -Time Employees</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;a</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> <u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </u>percent courtesy discount on pet diet foods such as Science Diet, Prescription Diet, etc., and on baths and grooming performed by groomer.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Up to <u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </u>&nbsp;pets will receive the following dog vaccinations: rabies, DHLP, parvovirus and kennel cough; and/or cat vaccinations; FVRCP, calicivirus and FELV once a year free of charge.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">After <u>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </u>&nbsp;months of employment, up to 2 pets will receive a free dental prophylaxis.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The discount applies to treatment rendered during the time of employment only and ends upon termination of employment. It does not apply to pets of relatives or friends.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">In order to receive the above discounted benefits, you must pay for the services at the time they are rendered. In addition, payment for services or products must be received and properly recorded by someone other than you.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You are responsible for all charges incurred when outside specialists or consultants are brought in for care on your pets.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Normal admittance, record keeping and checkout procedures will be followed at all times.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">There is no charge for the above treatment if you have veterinary insurance covering such fees. If you have insurance, you are required to use it.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Pet Care Benefits',	'PET CARE BENEFITS',	'none',	'2017-08-23 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"voptional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:11:44',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	7,	1),
(64,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">We believe that all requests for information concerning current or former employees should be handled in a consistent and appropriate manner. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Before a<span style=\"border:none\">ny information will be provided regarding a current or previous employee, the </span></span></span><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Authorization to Give References</span></span></i></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Form</span></span></i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, or one that is equivalent from a prospective employer, must be signed by the individual in question. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">In responding to other employers&#39; re<span style=\"border:none\">quests for employment information about a former employee without a signed release, we will provide only the individual&#39;s start and end date of employment, title of position held, and a description <span style=\"border:none\">of the<span style=\"border:none\"> job performed<span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">All written, oral, or informal requests for information about current or former employees are to be referred to _________________. Consequently, you may not provide (either on or off-the-record, formally or informally) any employment-related information<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;regarding current or former employees to any person or entity.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">By following this policy, we can ensure that any information released is authorized and accurate.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	7,	'Reference Requests',	'REFERENCE REQUESTS',	'none',	'2017-10-06 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:13:22',	'2018-03-07 03:26:56',	'enabled',	2,	0),
(65,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">We are eager to learn of <span style=\"border:none\">conditions that may be causing problems for you on the job. Such conditions cannot be corrected unless you make them known. A problem may involve work conditions, policies, or anything else that prevents a fair and productive work environment. You are encouraged&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">to inform us when a problem arises so that we can address and resolve it as quickly as possible. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Please report your problem/concern, preferably in writing using our </span></span><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Problems/Concerns Form,</span></span></i></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> to ______________________ </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">as soon as possible</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> after you be<span style=\"border:none\">come aware of the situation. Please be as clear as possible. Once a report is received, we will investigate the circumstances and </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">reach a resolution, which will be shared with you</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">If you are dissatisfied with the resolution of the investigation, you should&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; border: none;\">file a written appeal. You will not be subject to any form of retaliation or discipline for pursuing a problems/concerns complaint.</span></p>\r\n',	6,	'Problem Resolution Procedure',	'PROBLEM RESOLUTION PROCEDURE',	'none',	'2017-08-24 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:15:54',	'2019-12-18 23:18:19',	'enabled',	0,	0),
(66,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you have a right to request a breastfeeding accommodation. Please make your request for an accommodation with your direct manager/supervisor. We will respond to your request as soon as possible, and, if applicable, we will inform you in writing if we are unable to comply. Should you believe that any of your rights have been violated, you have a right to file a complaint with the Labor Commissioner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Each time you have a need to breastfeed and/or express milk, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-CA under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:20:51',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	114,	1),
(67,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you have a right to request a breastfeeding accommodation. Please make your request for an accommodation with your direct manager/supervisor. We will respond to your request as soon as possible, and, if applicable, we will inform you in writing if we are unable to comply. Should you believe that any of your rights have been violated, you have a right to file a complaint with the Labor Commissioner.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Each time you have a need to breastfeed and/or express milk, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. &nbsp;</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-CA over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:26:10',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	113,	1),
(68,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-CA',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:27:35',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	322,	1),
(69,	'<p>When your shift exceeds 5 hours, you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes after no more than 5 hours of work. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. There are 2 exceptions: 1) You may (with our permission) voluntarily agree to waive the right to a meal period, provided the work day is no more than 6 hours; 2) A paid working meal period may be permitted if the nature of the work does not permit you to be released from duty. The latter should occur infrequently. For both exceptions, you must sign the <em>On Duty Meal Period/Meal Period Waiver Form</em>.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-CA',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:28:13',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	291,	1),
(70,	'<p><!--[if supportFields]><b style=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span></span></b><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'>xe &quot;Rest Break&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><bstyle=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></span></b><![endif]-->You receive an uninterrupted, duty-free paid rest break of 10 minutes at approximately the middle of every four hours (or major portion thereof) of work. The breaks may not be combined and added to the lunch period, nor can they be waived to shorten the work day. We ask that you take your breaks when they will not negatively affect client/customer service.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The number of breaks you are allowed to take depends on your schedule. The table below explains what you can expect to receive:</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong>Hours of Work</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p><strong># of Rest Breaks</strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">0 &ndash; 3.5</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">0</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">3.5 &ndash; 6</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">1</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">6.0 &ndash; 10.0</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">2</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">10.0 &ndash; 14.0</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">3</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">14.0 &ndash; 18.0</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\">4</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n',	4,	'Rest Breaks-CA',	'REST BREAKS',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:32:44',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	310,	1),
(71,	'<p>If you suffer from a non-work-related illness or injury, you may be entitled to State Disability Insurance (SDI). SDI provides low cost disability protection if an illness or injury not caused by the job prevents you from working. A small percentage of your wages, up to the prevailing maximum, is deducted each pay period to finance this mandatory insurance. To initiate a claim, telephone the nearest State Disability office to request the necessary forms. During the waiting period before disability payments begin, you can take earned and unused sick leave. This will help to compensate for any lost wages during the waiting period.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Disability Insurance-CA',	'STATE DISABILITY INSURANCE',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:34:17',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	281,	1),
(72,	'<p>When you have sufficient time available during non-work hours when the polls are open on Election Day, you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have sufficient time available, we will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide as much time as needed to vote, but only a maximum of 2 hours will be paid. The time off will be scheduled at the beginning or ending of the regular work shift, whichever allows the most free time to vote during the hours the polls are open. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-CA',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:35:22',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	379,	1),
(73,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas, as feasible, for this purpose for up to 2 years after the birth of a child. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when possible. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk unless doing so would create an undue hardship to the business. This additional time off must be mutually agreed upon by you and us.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-CO under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:37:46',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	115,	1),
(74,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas, as feasible, for this purpose for up to 2 years after the birth of a child. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when possible. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This additional time off must be mutually agreed upon by you and us.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-CO over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:38:31',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	116,	1),
(75,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. You will be paid regular wages, not to exceed $50 per day, for the first 3 days of service or any part thereof.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-CO',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:39:32',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	323,	1),
(76,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When your shift exceeds 5 hours, </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. A paid working meal period may be permitted if the nature of the work does not permit you to be released from duty.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-CO',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2018-04-06 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:40:09',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	292,	1),
(77,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">You receive a paid rest break of 10 minutes at approximately the middle of every 4 hours of work. The breaks may not be combined and/or added to the lunch period, nor can they be waived to shorten the work day. We ask that you take your breaks when they will not negatively affect client/customer service. For insurance purposes, we ask that you remain on the premises during rest breaks.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Rest Breaks-CO',	'REST BREAKS',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:40:45',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	311,	1),
(78,	'<p>When you have 3 or more consecutive non-work hours available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day (typically 7:00 a.m. to 7:00 p.m.), you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 3 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide up to 2 hours of paid time off to vote. We may specify when the time off will be taken, unless you request time off to be taken at the beginning or ending of the regular work shift. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-CO',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-09-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:41:21',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	380,	1),
(79,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-DE under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DE\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:43:20',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	120,	1),
