(81,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-DE',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DE\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:44:45',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	327,	1),
(82,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request and on the advice of your<span style=\"border:none\"> treating physician.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical</span></b> <span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Certification</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability-DE',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DE\"]',	4,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:49:19',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	79,	1),
(83,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-FL under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"FL\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:53:29',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	124,	1),
(84,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-FL over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"FL\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:54:12',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	123,	1),
(85,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. &nbsp;Wages will not be paid while on the leave of absence.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-FL',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"FL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-12 01:55:08',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	328,	1),
(88,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">It is important for you to understand our feelings about what we do and what motivates us because we will ask you to contribute to the letter and spirit of the animal-centered, and client-centered, care we deliver.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Small animal care has changed dramatically in the last few years. Coupled with technology, new procedures, and heightened public credibility, veterinary science has found ways to bring a new, higher level of health to our patients, more comfortably than ever before. Therefore, more people use our services.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Our business is built on our patients and their &ldquo;people&rdquo;.</span></u></b><b> </b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">How we treat each animal in our care, individually and clinically, is a real factor in client trust. It&rsquo;s really up to all of us to create an atmosphere where trust can grow.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Our job is good medicine, education, caring and respect for our patients and health care team. Our clients recognize this effort. That&rsquo;s what makes a vital veterinary service provider.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Working with animals takes a special perspective and special skills. For one, we have the welfare of a different species at heart, as do our clients. Nearly everyone in veterinary science begins with compassion and understanding. There are stresses in the clinic, however, that can try your sympathies. Sometimes the work is dirty, sometimes emotional, sometimes physically exhausting. A strong stomach is a good thing to have, especially in the face of an animal&rsquo;s pain.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We cannot save every animal that comes to us for care. We give it our best effort, always. The reality is not just medical, it&rsquo;s economic too&ndash;&ndash;a client may not be able to afford the most elegant medical option. Because of this, the job takes personal grit.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The rewards for anyone who loves animals are there every day, so we always try to keep our objective clear: to provide the best veterinary care we can.</span></span></p>\r\n',	1,	'Our Philosophy-Vet',	'OUR PHILOSOPHY OF DELIVERING VETERINARY CARE',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"voptional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 01:59:41',	'2017-09-19 22:22:31',	'enabled',	4,	0),
(89,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with any other authorized breaks, whether paid or unpaid, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-HI under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 02:06:55',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	128,	1),
(90,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with any other authorized breaks, whether paid or unpaid, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-HI over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 02:07:41',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	127,	1),
(91,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-HI',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 02:08:34',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	330,	1),
(92,	'<p>When you have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours (excluding lunch or rest periods) available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day, you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide up to 2 hours of paid time off to vote. Presentation of a voter&rsquo;s receipt may be requested. Failure to provide the requested receipt may result in a deduction of wages paid for the time off allowed for voting purposes. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-HI',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 02:09:23',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	382,	1),
(93,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time may run concurrently with any break time already provided to you, if applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable paid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-IL under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2018-11-06 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	5,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 02:10:56',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	135,	1),
(94,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time may run concurrently with any break time already provided to you, if applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable paid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-IL over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2018-11-06 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 02:11:42',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	134,	1),
(95,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us within 10 days of the date of issuance of the summons to you. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-IL',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 02:12:40',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	333,	1),
(96,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When your shift is or exceeds seven and a half hours, </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">you will be scheduled for a meal period of at least 20 minutes no later than 5 hours after beginning work. If the meal period is less than 30 minutes, it will be paid. If it is 30 minutes or more and you are duty-free, it will be unpaid. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-IL',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 02:13:23',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	295,	1),
(97,	'<p>If you have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day, you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide 2 hours of paid time off to vote. We may specify when the time off will be taken. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-IL',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 02:14:31',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	384,	1),
(98,	'<p>If you have been employed for at least six (6) months as a full-time employee and wish to donate blood, you may be eligible for a paid leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With prior approval, you may use up to one (1) hour to donate blood every 56 days in accordance with appropriate medical standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to provide proof of the blood donation.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Blood Donation-IL',	'BLOOD DONATION LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	51,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 02:15:50',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	69,	1),
(99,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-IN under 25',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IN\"]',	1,	24,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:36:59',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	137,	1),
(100,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. If possible, we will also provide a storage space for keeping milk that has been expressed until the end of the work day. If no storage space can be provided, we will allow you to bring your own portable storage device for keeping the expressed milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-IN over 25',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IN\"]',	25,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:37:52',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	136,	1),
(101,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-IN',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IN\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:38:37',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	334,	1),
(102,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-IA under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IA\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:40:11',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	129,	1),
(103,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-IA over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IA\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:41:04',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	130,	1),
(104,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-IA',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:42:04',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	331,	1),
(105,	'<p>If you have 3 or more consecutive non-work hours available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day, you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 3 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior written request by you before Election Day, provide paid time off to vote. Time off will be added to the shift, at our discretion, such that when all time off is added together it totals 3 consecutive hours during the hours the polls are open. Wages, which would otherwise have been earned, will be paid. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-IA',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:43:08',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	383,	1),
(106,	'<p>If you are a veteran, you may be provided with time off on Veteran&rsquo;s Day, November 11, if you would otherwise be scheduled to work. Please provide written request of the need for time off at least 1 month in advance of Veteran&rsquo;s Day. When requesting time off, you must also provide us with a federal certificate of release or discharge from active duty, or a similar document, for the purpose of determining your eligibility for this time off. You should receive notification as to whether or not the time off taken will be paid at least 10 days prior to the holiday. Multiple requests from veterans for time off on this holiday may result in our inability to grant the time off to everyone depending on staffing needs. Time off may also be denied if allowing the time would cause significant economic or operational disruption.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Veterans Day-IA',	'VETERANS DAY HOLIDAY',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:44:02',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	42,	1),
(107,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-KS',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KS\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:45:18',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	335,	1),
(108,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-KS under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KS\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:46:03',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	139,	1),
(109,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-KS over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KS\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:48:10',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	138,	1),
(110,	'<p>If you have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day, you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior written request by you before Election Day, provide paid time off to vote. Time off will be added to the shift (excluding lunch periods), at our discretion, such that when all time off is added together it totals 2 consecutive hours during the hours the polls are open. Wages, which would otherwise have been earned, will be paid. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-KS',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KS\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:48:49',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	385,	1),
(111,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-KY under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KY\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:51:31',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	140,	1),
(112,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-KY over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KY\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:52:16',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	141,	1),
(113,	'<p>You will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes between the 3rd and 5th hour of work. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. A paid working meal period may be permitted if the nature of the work does not permit you to be released from duty. This should occur infrequently and you must sign the <em>On Duty Meal Period/Meal Period Waiver Form</em>.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-KY',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:53:02',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	296,	1),
(114,	'<p>When you receive a court-ordered appearance notice or are called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be given a Leave of Absence to attend court or jury service. Wages will not be paid while on the leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty or other court-ordered appearance.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-KY',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:53:52',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	336,	1),
(115,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">You will receive a paid rest break of 10 minutes at approximately the middle of every 4 hours of work. The breaks may not be combined and/or added to the lunch period, nor can they be waived to shorten the work day. We ask that you take your breaks when they will not negatively affect customer service. For insurance purposes, we ask that you remain on the premises during rest breaks.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Rest Breaks-KY',	'REST BREAKS',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:54:42',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	312,	1),
(116,	'<p>We will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide reasonable time off to vote. Time off will be added to the shift such that when all time off is added together it totals 4 consecutive hours during the hours the polls are open. We may specify when the time off will be taken. Voting time is unpaid.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-KY',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-16 03:55:24',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	386,	1),
(117,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">This manual is a reference for you and us. It is a summary of personnel policies, procedures and employee benefits. It is designed to be a working guide&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">for the administration of a consistent and fair personnel program. Please read it carefully. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">The policies herein are intended to: </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Prevent misunderstandings that might arise from unwritten policies, inconsistently applied policies, or lack of proper communications</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Eliminate the need to make hasty decisions in matters of personnel policies</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Assure uniformity and fairness in the administration of policies</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Communicate the rights and responsibilities of all</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The policies described are not an expressed or <span style=\"border:none\">implied contract of employment and do not in any way imply or create any rights, contractual or otherwise. We reserve the right to modify, suspend, rescind, interpret and administer any of the policies, procedures, terms, conditions, and language of any or<span style=\"border:none\"> all parts of this manual. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">This policy manual replaces all earlier policy manuals and takes precedence over all memoranda and oral descriptions of personnel policies, practices, and procedures. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Upon hire, you will be asked to sign the </span></span><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Policy Manual Acknowledgement<span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;Form</span></span></span></span></span></i></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> once you have had an opportunity to read and familiarize yourself with its contents. You will be informed of any revisions to these policies as they occur during employment, and you will be asked to sign a copy of the </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Updated Policy Manual<span style=\"border:none\"> Acknowledgement Form</span></span></span></i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">This Personnel Policy Manual is our property. Please do not remove any hardcopy versions from the premises.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you have any questions, please feel free to ask.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	1,	'About the Manual',	'ABOUT THE MANUAL',	'none',	'2018-05-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"AL\",\"AK\",\"AZ\",\"AR\",\"CA\",\"CO\",\"CT\",\"DE\",\"DC\",\"FL\",\"GA\",\"HI\",\"ID\",\"IL\",\"IN\",\"IA\",\"KS\",\"KY\",\"LA\",\"ME\",\"MD\",\"MA\",\"MI\",\"MN\",\"MS\",\"MO\",\"MT\",\"NE\",\"NV\",\"NH\",\"NJ\",\"NM\",\"NY\",\"NC\",\"ND\",\"OH\",\"OK\",\"OR\",\"PA\",\"RI\",\"SD\",\"TN\",\"TX\",\"UT\",\"VT\",\"VA\",\"WA\",\"WV\",\"WI\",\"WY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 01:50:32',	'2018-05-29 22:36:44',	'enabled',	1,	0),
(118,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Our goal is to provide each patient with the finest care in a professional environment that inspires trust and confidence. We therefore encourage you to share your ideas, opinions, and feelings so we can be sure to keep the channels of communication open.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Our business must be managed efficiently and profitably if we are to continue serving our community with quality treatment. We invite and appreciate your contributions and suggestions toward greater efficiency. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:left\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><strong><span><span><span>We strive:</span></span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">To help our patients achieve the highest level of health possible</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">To be committed to excellence in all our services to the patient</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">To treat the patient&#39;s&nbsp;needs with the highest level of care, skill, and comfort</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">To change, grow, and evolve with our profession and society</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">To enhance the lives of all those with whom we come in contact</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">To maintain a safe and healthy environment for our patients and ourselves</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">To be part of the solution of any conflict or problem solving, to share our ideas and feelings, and to confront any issue in a win-win manner in order to maintain office harmony and teamwork</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">To foster an environment that supports and encourages all of the above</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	1,	'Our Philosophy',	'OUR PHILOSOPHY',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"doptional\",\"moptional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 01:52:12',	'2020-02-21 15:46:23',	'enabled',	3,	0),
(119,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">We believe that <span style=\"border:none\">our<span style=\"border:none\"> strength and future growth depends directly upon the contributions made by you. We also know that high productivity and efficiency depend on individual job satisfaction and happiness.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustified\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">In our effort to implement fair and effective <span style=\"border:none\">personnel policies, we pledge to:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Hire people based on their qualifications and potential work-related contributions </span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Provide you with avenues for addressing job-related concerns</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Recognize you individually and as a valuable member of the team</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Maintain safe and healthy working conditions</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Ensure you&nbsp;know where you stand regarding your work performance and extend guidance and assistance as needed</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Provide a competitive compensation package based largely on industry standards in the community and the quality of your work performance</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Welcome your input and suggestions</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustified\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Your responsibilities are to:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Be professional and honest in all business dealings </span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Keep all business and proprietary information in strictest confidence</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Give a productive day&#39;s work commensurate with your individual skills and abilities</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Be friendly and courteous to others</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Adhere to office policies</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Address complaints or grievances through the established problem resolution procedure discussed later in this manual</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustified\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">We<span style=\"border:none\"> assume responsibility to:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Schedule hours of work </span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Make changes in the work schedule as needed</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Change work assignments or job classifications as needed</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Change policies as needed, taking into consideration internal circumstances, competitive forces, and economic conditions</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Dismiss, assign, supervise and discipline as necessary</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Decide and act whenever it is in the best interest of everyone involved</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	1,	'Employer Employee Relations',	'EMPLOYER-EMPLOYEE RELATIONS',	'none',	'2017-10-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 01:54:23',	'2018-03-29 22:51:08',	'enabled',	5,	0),
(120,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The federal &ldquo;Personal Responsibility and Work Opportunity Reconciliation&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">Act&rdquo; (PRWORA) requires all states to operate a child support enforcement program. Under PRWORA, we must report new hires to the state within 20 days of hiring. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The following information will be reported, as required:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Your full first and last name,<span style=\"border:none\"> social security number, home address and start of work date</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Our name, address, account number, and federal employer identification&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">n<span style=\"border:none\">umber</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	2,	'New Hire Reports',	'NEW HIRE REPORTS',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 01:59:04',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	8,	0),
(121,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>You are requested to help keep our records up-to-date by informing us of any changes in personal information. In order for us to keep the records updated, please report any of the following changes when they occur:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Name</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Home address&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Telephone numbers</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Email address</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Number of dependents (a new Form W-4 must be completed within 10 days of the change)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Marital status</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Education (courses completed and other training or skills acquired)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Military status (if appropriate)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Physical or other l<span>imitations</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Beneficiary designations for insurance, disability, pension, and profit-sharing plans</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Person(s) to notify in case of an emergency</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	2,	'Personal Data Changes',	'PERSONAL DATA CHANGES',	'none',	'2019-11-01 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 02:03:14',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	16,	0),
(122,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:justify\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><strong><span><span style=\"font-weight:normal\"><span>There are times when unusual circumstances occur which<span> result in an unforeseen closure and prevent you from working. This may be caused by:</span></span></span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Extreme weather</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Global pandemics, or other viral outbreaks</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Civil disturbances</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Bomb threats</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Health hazards</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Equipment or material breakdowns</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Power outages</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Other unexpected obstacles or emergency conditions beyond ou<span>r control </span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Unless an emergency closing is announced, you are expected to report to work during these times. However, please use your own discretion in deciding whether or not you can commute safely to work. Please follow proper call-in procedures if you choose&nbsp;<span>to remain at home during this time.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Non-Exempt Employees</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;any time off taken will be without pay, unless we make an exception at our discretion. You may have the option of using any paid time off you have earned to substitute for unpaid time.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Exemp<span>t Employees</span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span><span>&mdash;</span></span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>we will decide on a case-by-case basis whether the time off taken will be paid or unpaid. This is determined in large part on the circumstances upon which the time off occurred. If it is unpaid, you may have the option of using any paid time of<span>f you have earned to substitute for unpaid time.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Unforeseen Closures',	'UNFORESEEN CLOSURES',	'none',	'2020-03-12 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 02:04:50',	'2020-03-12 16:22:36',	'enabled',	8,	0),
(123,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">We firmly believe educational development is important in order to increase your competence in your present job assignment and to <span style=\"border:none\">prepare for future advancement.</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&nbsp;All courses must be approved in advance, and compensation will be determined in accordance with state and federal laws for each continuing education event.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Wages</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">&ndash;&ndash;</span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">y</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">ou will be compensated wages for time spent in seminars or training programs as required by federal and/or state law. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Expenses</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">&ndash;&ndash;expense&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">reimbursement for the continuing education event that has been agreed upon will be determined at our discretion and in accordance with state and federal<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;minimum wage laws. Types of expenses to be considered may include:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Travel (mileage, airfare, etc.)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Meals</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Accommodations</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Tuition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Supplies</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Instead of a dollar-for-dollar reimbursement, you may be allowed a per-diem amount to cover daily expenses. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The <em>Continuing&nbsp;</em></span></span><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Education Agreement to Reimburse Expenses Form</span></span></span></i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> must be completed and signed prior to attending a continuing education event.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Within 30<span style=\"border:none\"> <span style=\"border:none\">days of the course completion, please submit the following for reimbursement of the agreed upon expenses:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Evidence of completion of the course </span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Copies of receipts for incurred expenses</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Copies of certificates and units earned will be maintained in your personnel file.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Travel Time<span style=\"font-weight:normal\">&ndash;&ndash;</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">you will be compensated wages for applicable travel time to and from seminars or training programs as required by federal and/or state law.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Different Capacity Work Rate</span></strong><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">&ndash;&ndash;</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">non-exempt employees may be paid a separate straight-time rate of pay for dissimilar types of work performed during the same workweek. Traveling to or attending seminars or training programs are considered dissimilar types of work from the work conducted during a normal workday. The time may therefore be paid at a different rate from your regular rate of pay while attending such seminars or workshops.</span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Continuing Education-non CA',	'CONTINUING EDUCATION',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"AL\",\"AK\",\"AZ\",\"AR\",\"CO\",\"CT\",\"DE\",\"DC\",\"FL\",\"GA\",\"HI\",\"ID\",\"IL\",\"IN\",\"IA\",\"KS\",\"KY\",\"LA\",\"ME\",\"MD\",\"MA\",\"MI\",\"MN\",\"MS\",\"MO\",\"MT\",\"NE\",\"NV\",\"NH\",\"NJ\",\"NM\",\"NY\",\"NC\",\"ND\",\"OH\",\"OK\",\"OR\",\"PA\",\"RI\",\"SC\",\"SD\",\"TN\",\"TX\",\"UT\",\"VT\",\"VA\",\"WA\",\"WV\",\"WI\",\"WY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 02:07:56',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	19,	0),
(124,	'<p>We firmly believe educational development is important. Employees are encouraged to take educational courses or training to increase their competence in the present job assignment and to prepare for future advancement. All courses must be approved in advance to be eligible for compensation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Wages</strong><br />\r\nWhen attending an agreed upon course, you will be compensated wages for time spent in lectures, meetings or training programs as required by state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Expenses</strong><br />\r\nWhen attending an agreed upon course, all expenses, except meals, will be reimbursed in accordance with state laws. Types of expenses may include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Travel (mileage, airfare, etc.)</li>\r\n	<li>Accommodations</li>\r\n	<li>Tuition</li>\r\n	<li>Supplies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Instead of a dollar-for-dollar reimbursement, you may be allowed a per-diem amount to cover daily expenses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The <em>Continuing Education Agreement to Reimburse Expenses Form</em> must be completed and signed prior to attending a continuing education event.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Within 30-days of the course completion, please submit the following for reimbursement:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Evidence of completion of the course</li>\r\n	<li>Copies of receipts for incurred expenses</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Copies of certificates and units earned will be maintained in your personnel file.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Travel Time</strong><br />\r\nTravel to and from an agreed upon course will be compensated in accordance with state laws.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Different Capacity Work Rate</strong><br />\r\nNon-exempt employees may be paid a separate straight-time rate of pay for dissimilar types of work performed during the same workweek. Traveling to or attending a seminar or workshop are considered dissimilar types of work than the work conducted during a normal workday. The time may therefore be paid at a different rate from your regular rate of pay while attending such seminars or workshops.</p>\r\n',	3,	'Continuing Education-CA',	'CONTINUING EDUCATION',	'none',	'2015-09-16 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 02:09:26',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	20,	0),
(125,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>We offer an incentive or bonus pay program for all of our staff. You will be provided with details of the program when you become eligible to participate.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>In order to receive incentive or bonus pay, you must meet all eligibility criteria as described in the details provided to you, including being employed through the full term of the bonus or incentive period.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">In addition, if you have been on an unpaid leave of absence or other unpaid time off for disciplinary reasons during the period, you will not earn bonus pay.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Incentive or Bonus Pay',	'INCENTIVE OR BONUS PAY',	'none',	'2017-10-31 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 02:11:06',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	49,	1),
(126,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">When a regular full-time employee is hired as a result of your referral and recommendation during your employment, you will receive a referral bonus of $____________. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">When a regular part-time employee is hired <span style=\"border:none\">as a result of your referral and recommendation during your employment, you will receive a referral bonus of $____________. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">In order to be eligible for the bonus, you must have submitted your referral before we place the job posting&nbsp;or take other recruiting&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">measures.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The bonus will be split in half. You will receive &frac12; of the bonus at the time the new employee is hired, and the remaining balance will be paid after the new employee has completed 90 days of continuous service.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'New Employee Referral Bonus',	'NEW EMPLOYEE REFERRAL BONUS',	'none',	'2017-10-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 02:12:06',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	50,	1),
(127,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">A leave of absence may be granted if you are temporarily unable to work due to an illness or disability, including pregnancy or pregnancy-related conditions, or if you choose to take time off work to fulfill personal obligations due to an exceptional or emergency nature.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">after completing 6 months of employment, <span><span><span>you may request a leave of absence. Exceptions to the length of service requirement will be considered at our discretion.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Request for a Leave of Absence</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;a request for a leave of absence must be<span> submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance, or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please use the </span></span></span></span><span><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Request for a Leave Absence Form</span></span></em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>If the reason for the leave is due to an illness or a disability, you must include medical certification <span>from your health care provider </span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">verifying the need for leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Your desire to return to work and a date of return must be agreed upon in writing. We reserve the right to approve or deny any request for a leave of absence.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Length of Leave</span></strong></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted for a reasonable period of time based on the facts of the situation. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Reporting on Progress</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;you are required to report directly to us on your status and your continued intention to return to work a minimum of every 30<span> days.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Salary and Benefits</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may be required to use any paid time off benefit available. If so, the paid time off will run concurrently with the leave of absence.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage. If applicable, you will be notified of your continuation coverage rights. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>When you return from leave, benefits will <span>again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Reinstatement to Work</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;so that your return to work can be properly scheduled, please provide at least 30 days advance notice in writing of the date you intend to return<span> to work. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>If you take a leave of absence because of an illness or disability, you must provide a note from your physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties with or without restrictions. Please use the </span></span><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span><span>Medical Release <span>t<span>o Work Form</span></span></span></span></span></em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Upon returning from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits, unless a comparable position no longer exists.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Termination</span></strong></span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> of Employment</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;your employment may end if any of the following occurs:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>If you accept outside or supplemental employment while being on a leave of absence</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>If the purpose for requesting th<span>e leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>If the request for a leave of absence was denied and you take time off anyway</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Leave of Absence',	'LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2019-10-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"AL\",\"AK\",\"AZ\",\"AR\",\"CA\",\"CO\",\"CT\",\"DE\",\"DC\",\"FL\",\"GA\",\"HI\",\"ID\",\"IL\",\"IN\",\"KS\",\"KY\",\"LA\",\"ME\",\"MD\",\"MA\",\"MI\",\"MN\",\"MS\",\"MO\",\"MT\",\"NE\",\"NV\",\"NH\",\"NJ\",\"NM\",\"NY\",\"NC\",\"ND\",\"OK\",\"OR\",\"PA\",\"RI\",\"SC\",\"SD\",\"TN\",\"TX\",\"UT\",\"VT\",\"VA\",\"WA\",\"WV\",\"WI\",\"WY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 02:16:10',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	61,	1),
(128,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11\"><span style=\"text-decoration:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you work full-time, you may be eligible to </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">receive severance pay upon separation according to the following table:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:500px;\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>&nbsp;Years of Service</strong></span></span></td>\r\n			<td><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>&nbsp;Severance Pay</strong></span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;3 to 4 years</span></span></td>\r\n			<td><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;_____ week**</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;4 or more years</span></span></td>\r\n			<td><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;_____ weeks**</span></span></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">** A &quot;week&quot; constitutes the number of hours worked in your average work week.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you will become eligible after 3 years of continuous service when the reason for <span style=\"border:none\">the separation is:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">A permanent separation initiated by us due to a lack of work (layoff)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Elimination of the job or position without an offer of another suitable position that does not require relocation of residence</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Merger with, or acquisition by, another <span style=\"border:none\">owner or organization for which you do not continue employment. The written termination notice must be given to the seller before the date of transfer of ownership or within 10 days after you become aware of the transfer. Unless the sales contract reads otherwise<span style=\"border:none\">, the seller incurs the expense of the severance pay</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Your inability to satisfactorily perform the responsibilities of the job function through no fault of your own (as determined by us)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Non-Eligibility</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you are not eligible for severance pay if your<span style=\"border:none\"> separation is for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">You are terminated from employment for reasons other than a lay-off</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">If laid off for a period of less than 6 months</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Voluntary resignation</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Elimination of the job or position (if another suitable position, no<span style=\"border:none\">t requiring relocation of residence, is offered and you choose not to accept it, you will be considered to have left voluntarily)</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Merger with, or acquisition, by another owner or organization, if employment is continued or reinstated without an extended break<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;by the new owner</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">When you retain your position (or a like position) after being hired without an extended break by another employer practicing within the same facility</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">We reserve the right to make exceptions to this policy and provide severance pay al<span style=\"border:none\">though no such pay is required. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Severance pay is based on your regular hourly rate, excluding any other type of pay such as overtime, incentive or bonus pay.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	7,	'Severance Pay',	'SEVERANCE PAY',	'none',	'2019-02-14 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 22:32:48',	'2019-02-15 01:05:37',	'enabled',	3,	1),
(129,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>It is our policy to provide a work environment&nbsp;<span>that is free from any form of discrimination or harassment. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Harassment can take many forms: written, verbal and non-verbal, and can occur with any type of medium: phone, email, texting, social networking, etc. In all cases, jokes, name calling, discrimination, or harassment is prohibited at all times. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Sexual harassment includes but is not limited to: verbal, physical, or visual behavior of a sexual nature; graphic or suggestive comments about an individual&#39;s dress or body, or actual or perceived&nbsp;<span>sexual orientation; making unwanted sexual advances and requests for sexual favors where either (1) submission to such conduct is made an explicit or implicit term or condition of employment; (2) submission to or rejection of such conduct by an individual&nbsp;<span>is used as the basis for employment decisions affecting such individual; or (3) such conduct has the purpose or effect of substantially interfering with an individual&#39;s work performance or creating an intimidating, hostile, or offensive working environment<span>. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Any incident of discrimination or harassment, including threats, intimidation, and assault, must be reported immediately to your direct supervisor, or </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">any other company supervisor/manager</span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">. Please submit this information in writing; you may use the <em>Report of Harassment or Discrimination Form</em>. </span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>The report should state the time, place, type of harassment or discrimination, person or persons involved, and the name of any possible witnesses. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>A prompt investigation will be conducted as discreetly as possible<span>. Confidentiality will be maintained to the degree feasible given the need to investigate and act upon allegations made. Only those with a need to know about such a report will be advised of its existence. The person or persons accused of prohibited<span> conduct will have an opportunity to explain the conduct in question. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Any person who has been found in violation of this policy shall be subject to appropriate disciplinary action including letters of reprimand, suspension, demotion, termination, and the<span> possibility of civil liability. It is your responsibility to conscientiously follow this policy.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">If you are dissatisfied with the resolution of the investigation, you should file a written appeal. You will not be subject to any form of retaliation or discipline&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">for pursuing a report of harassment or discrimination.</span></p>\r\n',	6,	'Harassment & Discrimination non-CA NY OR',	'ANTI-HARASSMENT AND DISCRIMINATION',	'none',	'2019-04-11 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"AL\",\"AK\",\"AZ\",\"AR\",\"CO\",\"CT\",\"DE\",\"DC\",\"FL\",\"GA\",\"HI\",\"ID\",\"IL\",\"IN\",\"IA\",\"KS\",\"KY\",\"LA\",\"ME\",\"MD\",\"MA\",\"MI\",\"MN\",\"MS\",\"MO\",\"MT\",\"NE\",\"NV\",\"NH\",\"NJ\",\"NM\",\"NC\",\"ND\",\"OH\",\"OK\",\"PA\",\"RI\",\"SC\",\"SD\",\"TN\",\"TX\",\"UT\",\"VT\",\"VA\",\"WA\",\"WV\",\"WI\",\"WY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-17 22:36:12',	'2019-12-18 23:18:19',	'enabled',	4,	0),
(130,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-LA under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"LA\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:23:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	143,	1),
(131,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-LA over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"LA\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:24:09',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	142,	1),
(132,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. You will be paid regular wages for the first day of service or any part thereof.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-LA',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"LA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:24:53',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	337,	1),
(133,	'<p>School and day-care activities leave can be taken to attend, observe, or participate in conferences or classroom activities that are directly related to your children and cannot reasonably be scheduled during non-work hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A school is defined as any accredited public or private educational institution serving children of compulsory attendance age. A child day-care center is defined as a licensed facility providing day-care to seven or more children or a school authorized by the local school board to provide a child day-care program.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&ndash;&ndash;to qualify, you must be a parent or legal guardian of a child under the maximum age for compulsory school attendance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;you must give reasonable notice of your need to take leave for school and day-care activities and must make a reasonable effort to schedule the leave so as not to unduly disrupt operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave will be granted for up to 16 hours in a 12 month period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&ndash;&ndash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave.</p>\r\n',	4,	'SCHOOL ACTIVITIES-LA',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"LA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:25:48',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	246,	1),
(134,	'<p>Pregnancy leave is provided to you when you are temporarily unable to work due to a disability caused by pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a written request from your healthcare provider that you be transferred to a less strenuous or hazardous position, we will do our best to accommodate you. If accommodation is not possible, and you are not able to continue your normal job responsibilities, you may be asked to go on pregnancy leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please use the <em>Leave Of Absence Application Form</em> for this purpose.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Healthcare Professional&rsquo;s</strong><strong> Certification</strong>&mdash;any request for a pregnancy-related leave must be accompanied with a certified healthcare professional&rsquo;s certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.75in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.75in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><br />\r\n<strong>Reporting on Progress</strong>&mdash;you are required to report directly to us every 30 days on your health status and your intent to return to work.<strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;a leave of absence will be granted for a period of up to 6 weeks. If the initial period of approved absence needs to be extended due to medical complications related to pregnancy, the leave can be extended up to a total of 4 months pending written verification from a certified healthcare professional.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may use any earned paid time off to run concurrent with the pregnancy leave. Benefits are not earned during the leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during pregnancy leave. When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pregnancy Leave of Absence Ends When</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You are released for full or partial duty. You must provide a physician&rsquo;s statement in writing indicating your fitness to return to work</li>\r\n	<li>We receive satisfactory medical evidence that you are unable to return to work</li>\r\n	<li>You directly or indirectly inform us (for example, by accepting employment elsewhere, moving out of state, etc.) that you do not intend to return to work</li>\r\n	<li>You have been on a medical leave of absence for the approved time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Returning from Pregnancy Leave</strong>&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;you must provide a completed <em>Medical Release to Work</em> <em>Form</em>, or an equivalent note from your healthcare provider, verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. This must be received on or before the date you are scheduled to return from leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits, unless a comparable position no longer exists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</li>\r\n	<li>If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Leave-LA',	'PREGNANCY LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"LA\"]',	25,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:29:43',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	100,	1),
(135,	'<p>You may be eligible for a paid leave of absence if you wish to donate your bone marrow to another person.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligible Employees</strong>&mdash;you must work an average of twenty (20) or more hours per week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;up to forty (40) hours of paid leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Written verification</strong>&mdash;medical verification from a physician may be required to confirm the purpose and length of each leave requested by you to donate bone marrow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least thirty (30) days in advance, or as soon as possible for unforeseeable events.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that work can be properly scheduled.&nbsp; Upon returning from leave you will be reinstated to the position held before the leave began, or a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Bone Marrow-LA',	'BONE MARROW DONATION LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"LA\"]',	20,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:31:20',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	70,	1),
(136,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas, as feasible, for this purpose for up to 3 years after the birth of a child. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when possible. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This additional time off must be mutually agreed upon by you and us.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-ME',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ME\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:32:41',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	148,	1),
(137,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-ME',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ME\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:33:39',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	340,	1),
(138,	'<p>When your shift exceeds 6 hours, you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. You may (with our permission) voluntarily agree to waive the right to a meal period, provided the work day is no more than 6 hours. Exceptions to this policy may be made if fewer than 3 employees are on duty at any one time and&nbsp;the nature of the work done by you allows frequent breaks during the work day. &nbsp;</p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-ME',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ME\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:34:16',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	298,	1),
(139,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of violence, assault, sexual assault, stalking or other violence-related crimes, or have a child, parent or spouse who is a victim of violence, assault, sexual assault, stalking or other violence-related crimes, you will be provided with reasonable and necessary unpaid leave from work. Leave from work is available so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Prepare for and attend court proceedings</li>\r\n	<li>Receive medical treatment or attend to medical treatment for a victim who is your child, parent or spouse</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain necessary services to remedy a crisis caused by violence, assault, sexual assault, stalking or other violence-related crimes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Family relationship verification may be requested by us and can be satisfied by a statement from you, a birth certificate, a court document, or other similar documentation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unpaid leave from work may not be provided if any of the following are deemed applicable:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We would sustain undue hardship from your absence</li>\r\n	<li>The request for leave is not communicated to us within a reasonable time under the circumstances</li>\r\n	<li>The requested leave is impractical, unreasonable, or unnecessary based on the facts then made known to us</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-ME',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ME\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:35:50',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	270,	1),
(140,	'<p>Military family leave is for when you are the spouse, domestic partner, or parent of a person who is a resident of the state and is deployed for military service for a period lasting longer than 180 days. For purposes of this policy, deployed for military service means active military duty with the state military forces, or the United States Armed Forces, including the National Guard and Reserves, whether pursuant to orders of the Governor or the President of the United States, when the duty assignment is in combat theater or in an area where armed conflict is taking place. If you are in this situation, you may be provided a leave of absence as outlined below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;up to 15 days of leave, per deployment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualified Employee</strong>&mdash;you may be qualified for leave if all of the following are satisfied:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You have been employed for at least 12 months</li>\r\n	<li>You have worked at least 1,250 hours during the 12 month period immediately preceding the commencement of the leave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualified Leave Periods</strong>&mdash;you may take a leave of absence during one or more of the following periods:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The 15 days immediately prior to deployment</li>\r\n	<li>Deployment, if the military member is granted leave</li>\r\n	<li>The 15 days immediately following the period of deployment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notification</strong>&mdash;if the leave consists of 5 or more consecutive days, you must give at least 14 days notice of the intended date upon which the leave will begin. If the leave consists of less than 5 consecutive days, you must give us as much advanced notice as possible. When able, you must consult with us to schedule the leave so as to not unduly disrupt our operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;we may require certification from the proper military authority to verify your eligibility for leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;leave is unpaid.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be able to continue health insurance benefits, if applicable, at your own expense for the duration of the leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement Rights</strong>&mdash;you will be reinstated to your position held prior to taking leave, or to a position with equivalent seniority status, pay, benefits, and other terms and conditions of employment unless a comparable position no longer exists due to business necessity.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Leave-ME',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ME\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:37:18',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	232,	1),
(141,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business..</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-MD under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2018-01-24 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:38:52',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	147,	1),
(142,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-MD over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:39:33',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	146,	1),
(143,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-MD',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:40:18',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	339,	1),
(144,	'<p>If you have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day, you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide 2 hours of paid time off to vote. You must furnish proof that you have voted. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-MD',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:40:57',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	387,	1),
(145,	'<p>If you have family members in the military, you may be provided a leave of absence as outlined below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualified Employee</strong>&mdash;to qualify for leave, you must have worked: 1) At least 12 months, 2) At least 1,250 hours in the 12 months immediately preceding the request for leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;1 day of unpaid leave. You may take leave on the day that one of your immediate family members is leaving for, or returning from, active duty outside of the United States as a member of the United States military.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Immediate Family Member defined</strong>&mdash;spouse, parent, stepparent, child, stepchild, or sibling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying that the leave is being taken appropriately (e.g. the immediate family member&rsquo;s military order).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave is without pay. If you choose, you may use any paid time off benefits available at the time the leave is taken.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Leave-MD',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:42:10',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	231,	1),
(146,	'<p>You will be provided an unpaid parental leave as outlined below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;to qualify for unpaid parental leave, you must have been employed at least 12 months and worked 1,250 hours during the previous 12 months as of the date that the requested parental leave begins.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&mdash;you can take family leave for:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The birth of a child</li>\r\n	<li>The placement of a child with you for adoption or foster care</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. You may begin taking parental leave immediately without prior notice following a premature birth, unexpected adoption, or unexpected foster placement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We may deny the request if it is necessary to prevent substantial and grievous economic injury to the operations of our business, and we will notify you before you begin taking leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted for 6 weeks during any 12 month period.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may choose to use any earned paid time off to run concurrently with parental leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) prepayment before the leave, 2) pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. Failure to pay your share of the health insurance premium may result in a loss of coverage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Other benefits are not earned during leave. Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during parental leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. When you return from family leave, you will be restored to the former position held prior to the leave, or to an equivalent position with equivalent benefits, pay, and other terms and conditions of employment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end when:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Denial of reinstatement is necessary to prevent substantial and grievous economic injury to the operations of our business, and we notify you at the time that we determine this</li>\r\n	<li>We have just cause for terminating your employment</li>\r\n	<li>When you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return without notification to us</li>\r\n	<li>When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Parental Leave-MD',	'PARENTAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	15,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:44:17',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	223,	1),
(147,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-MA under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:45:35',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	145,	1),
(148,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-MA over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:46:13',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	144,	1),
(149,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. You will be paid regular wages for work hours missed during the first 3 days of service or any part thereof.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-MA',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:46:54',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	338,	1),
(150,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">You may be able to take unpaid leave to participate in school activities directly related to your son&rsquo;s or daughter&rsquo;s educational advancement, such as parent-teacher conferences or interviews at new schools.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Eligibility</strong>&ndash;&ndash;to qualify, you must have completed 1 year of continuous employment and have worked at least 1,250 hours.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;you must give at least 7 days advance notice of an anticipated need for leave. If the need for leave is unexpected, you must give as much notice as practicable.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave will be granted for up to 24 hours in a 12 month period. You can take leave on an intermittent basis or reduced work schedule.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">You may be required to supply signed, written certification of your need for leave. Certification is sufficient if it states the date on which leave will be taken, the purpose for which leave is needed, and the duration of the leave. For anticipated leave, certification will be required at the time or within 2 business days of submitting leave requests. For unanticipated leave, certification will be required within 2 business days after leave is taken or as soon as reasonably possible.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\">Salary and Benefits<span style=\"font-weight:normal\">&ndash;&ndash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you may be required to use any earned paid time off&nbsp;for school&nbsp;activities.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'SCHOOL ACTIVITIES-MA over 50',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:48:03',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	247,	1),
(151,	'<p>You may be provided an unpaid parental leave as outlined below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&ndash;&ndash;to qualify for leave, you must have been employed as a full-time employee for 3 calendar months prior to taking the leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted for up to 8 weeks*.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*Any 2 employees employed by us at the same time are entitled to 8 weeks of parental leave in aggregate for the reasons stated below for the same child.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When applicable, parental leave will be counted against any family and medical leave entitlements required by federal law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&mdash;you can take parental leave for:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The birth of a child</li>\r\n	<li>The placement of a child with you for adoption</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The definition of child generally means a child under age 18, but can include a child under the age of 23 if the child is mentally or physically disabled.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 2 weeks in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reporting on Progress</strong>&mdash;you are required to report directly to the employer every 30 days on your health status and your intent to return to work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may use any earned paid time off to run concurrent with the parental leave. Benefits are not earned during the leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any earned paid time off used during parental leave. When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you return from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of seniority, pay or service credits, unless we can show that a comparable position no longer exists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</li>\r\n	<li>If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Parental Leave-MA',	'PARENTAL LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	6,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:49:55',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	222,	1),
(152,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">If you report to work at the beginning of your work shift that is 3 hours or more but are sent home early, you will be paid for actual hours worked or a minimum of 3 hours of pay, whichever is greater, at your regular rate.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Pay for time not worked is excluded when computing overtime.</span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Reporting Time Pay-MA',	'REPORTING TIME PAY',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:51:33',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	7,	0),
(153,	'<p>You will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes after no more than 6 hours of work. The following are situations in which you will be paid for the meal break:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The nature of the work does not permit you to be released from duty, and you have worked through your meal break. This should occur infrequently and only after receiving permission from us first.</li>\r\n	<li>We request that you remain on the premises during your meal break. &nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-MA',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:52:10',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	297,	1),
(154,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12px;\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of abusive behavior, abuse, domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, or have a family member who is a victim of abusive behavior, abuse, domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, you may be allowed to take up to 15 days of leave from work in any 12 month period so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek legal or law enforcement assistance or remedies, including preparing for and participating in protective order proceedings or other civil or criminal legal proceedings</li>\r\n	<li>Appear in court</li>\r\n	<li>Secure housing</li>\r\n	<li>Seek or obtain medical treatment</li>\r\n	<li>Acquire counseling</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain services from a victim services provider</li>\r\n	<li>Attend child custody proceeding or address other issues directly related to the abusive behavior against you or your family member</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You are required to exhaust all paid time off available to you prior to taking unpaid leave under this policy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take time off under this policy, you must give us reasonable advance notice of your intention to take leave. If there is threat of imminent danger to you or your family member&rsquo;s health or safety, you are not required to provide advance notice of leave provided that you notify us within 3 workdays that the leave was taken or is being taken for this purpose. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to provide certification that you or your family member is a victim of abusive behavior, abuse, domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking and the time off is for one of the purposes outlined above. If required, certification must be provided within a reasonable time after it has been requested. You can provide certification through one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A police report or statement of a victim or witness provided to police, including a police incident report, documenting the abusive behavior complained of by you or your family member</li>\r\n	<li>A protective order, order of equitable relief or other documentation issued by a court of competent jurisdiction</li>\r\n	<li>A document under the letterhead of the court, provider or public agency which you attended for the purposes of acquiring assistance</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation that the perpetrator of the abusive behavior against you or your family member has: admitted to sufficient facts to support a finding of guilt of abusive behavior; or has been convicted of, or has been adjudicated a juvenile delinquent by reason of, any offense constituting abusive behavior</li>\r\n	<li>Medical documentation of treatment for you or your family member</li>\r\n	<li>A sworn statement, signed under the penalties of perjury, provided by a counselor, social worker, health care worker, member of the clergy, shelter worker, legal advocate or other professional who has assisted you or your family member in addressing the effects of the abusive behavior</li>\r\n	<li>A sworn statement, signed under the penalties of perjury, from you attesting that you have been the victim of abusive behavior or are the family member of a victim of abusive behavior.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Any documentation provided to us may be maintained in your employment record but only for as long as required for us to make a determination as to whether you are eligible for leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information the employee provides confidentially. Information will not be disclosed without your express permission, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-MA over 50',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:53:25',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	271,	1),
(155,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crime, or have a minor child who is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crime, you may be allowed to take time off from work based on office staffing so that you can obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare of the victim or your child.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take time off under this policy, you must follow our usual time-off request procedures, unless an emergency prevents you from doing so. When the need for time off is urgent and unforeseeable, you must provide documentation upon return to work that supports your reason for being absent from the workplace.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You can provide documentation through one or more of the following:</li>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you were a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Court protection order separating you from the perpetrator of an act of domestic violence or sexual assault, or other evidence from the court or prosecuting attorney that you have appeared in court</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation from a medical professional, domestic violence advocate or advocate for victims of sexual assault, health care provider, or counselor that you were undergoing treatment for physical or mental injuries or abuse resulting in victimization from an act of domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-CO under 50',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:55:51',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	256,	1),
(156,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have been employed for 12 months or more and are victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crimes, you will be provided with up to 3 days of leave in any 12 month period. Leave from work is available so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek a civil protection order to prevent domestic abuse</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain medical care or mental health counseling, or both, for you or for your children to address physical or psychological injuries resulting from the act of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crimes</li>\r\n	<li>Make your home secure from the perpetrator of the act of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crimes, or seek new housing to escape said perpetrator</li>\r\n	<li>Acquire legal assistance to address issues arising from the act of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crimes and attending and preparing for court-related proceedings arising from said act or crime</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Prior to taking the leave, you must exhaust available paid time off benefits, if applicable. After doing so, leave will be unpaid.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take leave under this policy, you must provide appropriate advance notice of the need for leave except in cases of imminent danger to your health and safety.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to verify that you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crimes. If required, verification must be provided in a timely manner. You can provide verification through one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you were a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crime</li>\r\n	<li>Court protection order separating you from a perpetrator of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crime</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation that you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crime from a domestic violence advocate or advocate for victims of sexual assault, an attorney, a member of the clergy, or a medical professional</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-CO over 50',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 06:57:19',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	257,	1),
(157,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">You should make a reasonable attempt to schedule academic activities outside regular work hours. In the event this is not possible, you may be provided time off without pay to participate in your children&rsquo;s academic activities.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Eligibility</strong>&ndash;&ndash;you can take time off for academic activities involving your child if you are a parent or legal guardian of a child enrolled in public or private school or in a nonpublic home-based education program.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave can be taken:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">To attend a parent-teacher conference</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">To attend a meeting related to: special education services, response to intervention, dropout prevention, attendance, truancy, or disciplinary issues</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;a request for school activities leave must be submitted in writing at least 1 calendar week in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Supporting documentation verifying the academic activity will be required at the time the request is made.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave will be granted for up to 18 hours per school year. Leave taken in any 1 month shall not exceed 6 hours. Leave may not be taken in increments of more than 3 hours at any one time.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">If you work part-time, you will be eligible for a prorated amount of leave based on the percent of a full-time employee&rsquo;s schedule that you work.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&ndash;&ndash;a school activities leave for non-exempt employees is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'SCHOOL ACTIVITIES-CO over 50',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:01:09',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	243,	1),
(158,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When your shift is or exceeds 7 &frac12; hours, you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes sometime after the first 2 hours of work and before the last 2 hours of work. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. Exceptions to this policy will be made if:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Compliance would adversely affect public safety </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Only one person may perform the duties of a position </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We have fewer than five employees on a shift at one location (the exception would only apply to that shift)</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Our operation requires that you be available to respond to urgent conditions, and you are compensated for the meal period</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-DE',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DE\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:02:37',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	294,	1),
(159,	'<div>\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crime, or have a minor child who is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crime, you may be allowed to take time off from work based on office staffing so that you can obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare for you or your child.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take time off under this policy, you must follow our usual time-off request procedures, unless an emergency prevents you from doing so. When the need for time off is urgent and unforeseeable, you must provide documentation upon return to work that supports your reason for being absent from the workplace.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You can provide documentation through one or more of the following:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">A police report indicating that you were a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Court protection order separating you from the perpetrator of an act of domestic violence or sexual assault, or other evidence from the court or prosecuting attorney that you have appeared in court </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Documentation from a medical professional, domestic violence advocate or advocate for victims of sexual assault, health care provider, or counselor that you were undergoing treatment for physical or mental injuries or abuse resulting in victimization from an act of domestic violence or sexual assault</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-FL under 50',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"FL\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:04:00',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	260,	1),
(160,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you have been employed for 3 months or more and are a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault, or have a family/household member who is a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault, you will be provided with up to 3 days of leave in any 12 month period. Leave from work is available so that you can:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Seek an injunction for protection against domestic violence or an injunction for protection in cases of repeat violence, dating violence, or sexual violence</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Obtain medical care or mental health counseling, or both, for you or a family/household member to address physical or psychological injuries resulting from the act of domestic violence or sexual assault</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Obtain services from a victim services organization, including, but not limited to, a domestic violence shelter or program or rape crisis center as a result of the act of domestic violence or sexual assault </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Make your home secure from the perpetrator of the domestic violence or sexual assault or seek new housing to escape said perpetrator</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Acquire legal assistance to address issues arising from the act of domestic violence or sexual assault or attend and prepare for court-related proceedings arising from the act of domestic violence or sexual assault</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Prior to taking the leave, you must exhaust paid time off benefits, if applicable. After doing so, leave will be unpaid. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take leave under this policy, you must provide appropriate advance notice of the need for leave except in cases of imminent danger to the health and safety of you or family/household member.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You may be required to verify that you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crimes. If required, verification must be provided in a timely manner. You can provide verification through one or more of the following:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">A police report indicating that you or family/household member was a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Court protection order separating you or family/household member from a perpetrator of domestic violence or sexual assault</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Documentation that you or family/household member is a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault from an attorney, a member of the clergy, or a medical or other professional</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-FL over 50',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2017-08-28 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"FL\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:05:04',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	261,	1),
(161,	'<p>You may be eligible for Temporary Disability Insurance (TDI) if one of the following occurs and prevents you from being able to work:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Pregnancy, or pregnancy-related medical conditions</li>\r\n	<li>Non-work-related Illness or injury</li>\r\n	<li>Organ donation, or medical conditions caused by organ donation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A small percentage from your wages, up to the prevailing maximum, may be deducted each pay period to finance this mandatory insurance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please contact us, or other designated personnel, to learn more or to initiate a claim.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Disability Insurance-HI',	'TEMPORARY DISABILITY INSURANCE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:06:42',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	285,	1),
(162,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have been employed for at least 6 months and are a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault, or have a minor child who is a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault, you will be provided with up to 5 days of leave per calendar year. Leave from work is available so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek medical attention for you or your minor child to recover from physical or psychological injury or disability caused by domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain services from a victim services organization</li>\r\n	<li>Acquire psychological or other counseling</li>\r\n	<li>Temporarily or permanently relocate</li>\r\n	<li>Take legal action, including preparing for or participating in any civil or criminal legal proceeding related to or resulting from the domestic violence or sexual assault, or other actions to enhance the physical, psychological, or economic health or safety of you or your minor child or to enhance the safety of those who associate with or work with you</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Leave will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take leave under this policy, you must provide reasonable advance notice of the need for leave except in cases of imminent danger to the health and safety of you or your minor child.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you are the victim of domestic violence or sexual assault and seek to take leave for medical attention to recover from physical or psychological injury or disability caused by domestic violence or sexual assault, you must provide:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A certificate from a health care provider estimating the number of leave days necessary and the estimated commencement and termination dates of leave required by you</li>\r\n	<li>Prior to your return to work, a medical certificate from your health care provider attesting to your condition and approving your return</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you take leave for non-medical reasons, you must provide certification within a reasonable period after it has been requested by us. In this case, the certification is a signed statement that you or your minor child is a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault and the leave is for one of the purposes outlined above. A failure to provide the certification may result in the leave not being job-protected and affecting your attendance record.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-HI under 50',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:08:26',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	262,	1),
(163,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have been employed for at least 6 months and are a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault, or have a minor child who is a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault, you will be provided with up to 30 days of leave per calendar year. Leave from work is available so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek medical attention for you or your minor child to recover from physical or psychological injury or disability caused by domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain services from a victim services organization</li>\r\n	<li>Acquire psychological or other counseling</li>\r\n	<li>Temporarily or permanently relocate</li>\r\n	<li>Take legal action, including preparing for or participating in any civil or criminal legal proceeding related to or resulting from the domestic violence or sexual assault, or other actions to enhance the physical, psychological, or economic health or safety of you or your minor child or to enhance the safety of those who associate with or work with you</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Leave will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid sick time benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take leave under this policy, you must provide reasonable advance notice of the need for leave except in cases of imminent danger to the health and safety of you or your minor child.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you are the victim of&nbsp;domestic violence or sexual assault and seek to take leave for medical attention to recover from physical or psychological injury or disability caused by domestic violence or sexual assault, you must provide:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A certificate from a health care provider estimating the number of leave days necessary and the estimated commencement and termination dates of leave required by you</li>\r\n	<li>Prior to your return to work, a medical certificate from your health care provider attesting to your condition and approving your return</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you take leave for non-medical reasons and the leave does not exceed 5 days, you must provide certification within a reasonable period after it has been requested by us. In this case, the certification is a signed statement that you or your minor child is a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault and the leave is for one of the purposes outlined above.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the leave exceeds 5 days per calendar year, then you must provide certification by one of the following methods:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A police or court record related to the domestic violence or sexual assault&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>A signed written statement from an employee, agent, or volunteer of a victim services organization, from your attorney or advocate, from a minor child&rsquo;s attorney or advocate, or a medical or other professional from whom you or your minor child has sought assistance related to the domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A failure to follow the applicable certification procedure may result in the leave not being job-protected and affecting your attendance record.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-HI over 50',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:09:46',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	263,	1),
(164,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-MS',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MS\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:11:09',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	344,	1),
(165,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-MS under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MS\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:11:52',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	156,	1),
(166,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-MS over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-10-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MS\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:12:29',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	155,	1),
(167,	'<p>We are an E-Verify employer. E-Verify is an internet-based system that compares information from the <em>Employment Eligibility Verification Form</em> (I-9) you completed upon hire to data from the <em>U.S. Department of Homeland Security</em> and <em>Social Security Administration</em> records. This process will confirm your employment eligibility and comply with federal and state immigration laws.</p>\r\n',	2,	'E-Verify-MS',	'E-VERIFY',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MS\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:13:11',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	22,	0),
(168,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-ND under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ND\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:14:37',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	161,	1),
(169,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-ND over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ND\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:15:15',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	162,	1),
(170,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-ND',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ND\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:15:56',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	347,	1),
(171,	'<p>When your shift exceeds 5 hours, you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes. We may deny unpaid meal periods if fewer than 2 employees are on duty at any one time. You may (with our permission) voluntarily agree to waive the right to a meal period at anytime. You will need to sign the <em>On Duty Meal Period/Meal Period Waiver Form</em>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-ND',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ND\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:16:32',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	301,	1),
(172,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">You are expected to go to the polls before or after regular working hours. When your regular schedule conflicts with voting during the time the polls are open, we will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide a reasonable amount of time off to vote. We may specify when the time off will be taken. Voting time is unpaid.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-ND',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-09-17 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ND\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-18 07:17:05',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	390,	1),
(173,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-NC',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NC\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 00:46:25',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	346,	1),
(174,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crimes, or have a minor child who is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crimes, you may take time off from work so that you can obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare of you or your child.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take time off under this policy, you must follow our usual time-off request procedures, unless an emergency prevents you from doing so. When the need for time off is unforeseeable, you must provide documentation upon return to work that supports your reason for being absent from the workplace.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-NC',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NC\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 00:47:57',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'disabled',	272,	1),
(176,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-NC under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NC\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 00:49:36',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	160,	1),
