(184,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-MO',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MO\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:13:35',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	343,	1),
(185,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you have 3 or more consecutive non-work hours available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day, you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 3 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide up to 3 hours of paid time off to vote. We may specify when the time off will be taken. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-MO',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MO\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:14:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	389,	1),
(186,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-MN under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:15:42',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	152,	1),
(187,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-MN over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:16:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	151,	1),
(188,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">When called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-MN',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:17:20',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	342,	1),
(189,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">When your shift is or exceeds 8 hours, you will be scheduled for sufficient time to eat a meal. If the period is 30 minutes or less in duration, it will be paid. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-MN',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:18:05',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	299,	1),
(190,	'<p>You may be eligible to take leave to attend school, preschool, or day-care conferences or activities involving a dependent child when these activities or conferences cannot be scheduled during non-work hours. This time can also be used to observe day-care, special education, or preschool services or programs provided these cannot be scheduled during non-work hours.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&ndash;&ndash;to qualify, you must be a parent of a child, whether biological, adopted, or foster, who is younger than 18, or who is younger than 20 and is still attending secondary school. In addition, you must work at least half of what we consider to be full-time employment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;when the need for leave is foreseeable, you must give us reasonable advance notice and make a reasonable effort to schedule leave so as to avoid unduly disrupting work operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave will be granted for up to 16 hours in any 12 month period, per child.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&ndash;&ndash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave.</p>\r\n',	4,	'SCHOOL ACTIVITIES-MN',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:18:54',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	248,	1),
(191,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Time to use the nearest restroom is provided within each 4 consecutive hours of work.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Rest Breaks-MN',	'REST BREAKS',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:20:15',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	313,	1),
(192,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">You will be provided an unpaid parental leave as outlined below.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;to qualify for unpaid parental leave, you must have worked: 1) At least 12 consecutive months immediately preceding the request for leave, and 2) A weekly average number of hours equivalent to 1/2 of a full-time position in your job classification in the 12 months immediately preceding the request for leave.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&mdash;you can take parental leave for:&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Prenatal care, or incapacity due to pregnancy, childbirth, or related health conditions</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The birth of a child</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The placement of a child with you for adoption</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The definition of child generally means a child under age 18, but can include a child under age 20 who still attends secondary school.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted for up to 12 weeks for the birth or adoption of a child. The leave shall begin at a time requested by you with the following criteria:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">The leave generally must begin within 12 months following the birth or adoption</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">When a child must remain in the hospital longer than the mother, the leave must begin within 12 months after the child leaves the hospital &nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Intermittent </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;with our agreement, you can return to part-time work during parental leave.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may choose to use any earned paid time off to run concurrently with parental leave.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Health insurance benefits, if applicable, will remain in force during the leave period but you will be responsible for the full amount of the premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) Prepayment through increased payroll deductions before the leave (when the need for the leave is foreseeable), 2) Through separate payments directly to us as the premiums become due each month. Please let us know your decision before the leave begins. Failure to pay your share of the health insurance premium may result in a loss of coverage.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Other benefits are not earned during leave. Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during parental leave.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">Seniority, accumulated prior to leave, is not lost during parental leave.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. If the leave period has been longer than 1 month, reasonable advance notice is defined as at least 2 weeks.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">When you return from parental leave, you will be restored to your former position with your original pay, plus any automatic adjustments to the pay scale implemented during the leave. If, due to business necessity, the former position in no longer available, you will be reinstated to a position with comparable duties, hours, and pay.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">When you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px;\">When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Parental Leave-MN',	'PARENTAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	21,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:22:18',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	224,	1),
(193,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">If you have family members in the military, you may be provided a leave of absence as outlined below:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Leave to Attend Military Ceremonies or Events</strong>&mdash;if you are a spouse, parent, or child of a military service member, you may attend the following kinds of events relating to the military service to which you are invited, or otherwise called upon to attend, by proper military authorities:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Departure or return ceremonies for deploying or returning military personnel or units</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Family training or readiness events sponsored or conducted by the military</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Events held as part of official military reintegration programs</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\">You must provide reasonable notice to us when requesting time off. We will provide a reasonable amount of unpaid time off to you not to exceed 2 consecutive days, or 6 days in a calendar year.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Leave for Military Personnel Injured or Killed in Active Service</strong>&mdash;you will be provided up to 10 working days of unpaid leave if you are a parent, child, grandparent, sibling, or spouse of a service member of the United States armed forces who has been injured or killed while engaged in active service. You must give as much notice in advance as possible of the need for leave.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>Leave to Attend Military Ceremonies for Extended Family</strong>&mdash;you may be provided with unpaid leave to attend a send-off or homecoming ceremony for a mobilized service member. The service member must have been ordered into active service in support of a war or other national emergency. For purposes of this leave, you must be a grandparent, legal guardian, sibling, grandchild, fianc&eacute;, or fianc&eacute;e, of the service member. Leave provided to you is limited to the actual time necessary for you to attend the ceremony and is not to exceed 1 day&rsquo;s duration in any calendar year. Leave will only be provided if it won&rsquo;t unduly disrupt our operations.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Leave-MN',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:23:16',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	233,	1),
(194,	'<p>If you are able to go to the polls before or after regular working hours, you are requested to do so. If that is not possible, you will be provided with time off necessary to appear at your polling place, cast a ballot, and return to work the day of that primary or election. Please give advance notice that time off during working hours is needed for appropriate scheduling purposes. We reserve the right to coordinate your time to vote in order to minimize disruption or ensure proper staffing. Time off for voting will be paid. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-MN',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:23:57',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	388,	1),
(195,	'<p>You may be eligible for a paid leave of absence if you wish to donate your bone marrow to another person.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligible Employees</strong>&mdash;you must work an average of 20 or more hours per week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;up to 40 hours of paid leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Written verification</strong>&mdash;medical verification from a physician may be required to confirm the purpose and length of each leave requested by you to donate bone marrow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that work can be properly scheduled.&nbsp; Upon returning from leave you will be reinstated to the position held before the leave began, or a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Bone Marrow-MN',	'BONE MARROW DONATION LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	20,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:25:07',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	71,	1),
(196,	'<p>Under the <em>Minnesota Wage Disclosure Protection</em> law, you have the right to tell any person the amount of your own wages. You will not be retaliated against for disclosing your own wages. Your remedies under the <em>Wage Disclosure Protection</em> law are to bring a civil action against us and/or file a complaint with the Minnesota Department of Labor and Industry&nbsp;at (651) 284-5070 or 1-800-342-5354.</p>\r\n',	3,	'Wage Disclosure-MN',	'WAGE DISCLOSURE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:26:15',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	18,	0),
(197,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-MI under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MI\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:41:36',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	149,	1),
(198,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-MI over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MI\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:42:19',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	150,	1),
(199,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When you receive a subpoena or request to appear in court because you are a victim or a victim representative or are called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You will be given a Leave of Absence to attend court or jury service. Wages will not be paid while on the leave of absence.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty or other court-ordered appearance.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-MI',	'JURY DUTY/VICTIM RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:43:04',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	341,	1),
(202,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking, or have a family/household member who is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking, you will be provided with up to 12 workweeks of leave in any 12 month period. Leave from work is available so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek medical attention for, or recover from, physical or psychological injuries resulting from domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking to you or your family/household member</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain services from a victim services organization for you or your family/household member</li>\r\n	<li>Acquire psychological or other counseling for you or your family/household member</li>\r\n	<li>Participate in safety planning, temporarily or permanently relocating, or taking other actions to increase the safety of you or your family/household member from future domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking or to ensure economic security&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain legal assistance or remedies to ensure the health and safety of you or your family/household member, including preparing for or participating in any civil or criminal legal proceedings related to or derived from domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Leave will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time. If applicable, your time off will run concurrently with any leave available under the Federal Family and Medical Leave Act.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before the leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are 2 payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. Failure to pay your share of the health insurance premium may result in a loss of coverage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take leave under this policy, you must provide at least 48 hours&rsquo; advance notice of your intention to take leave, unless providing such notice is not practicable. When the need for leave is unforeseeable, you must provide certification to us within a reasonable time after the absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to verify that you or your family/household member is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking and the leave is for one of the purposes outlined above. If required, verification must be provided in a timely manner. You can provide verification through one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A sworn statement by you</li>\r\n	<li>A police or court record&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation from an employee, agent, or volunteer of a victim services organization, an attorney, a member of the clergy, or a medical or other professional from whom you or your family/household member has sought assistance in addressing domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking and the effect of the violence</li>\r\n	<li>Other corroborating evidence</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to in writing by you or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-IL over 50',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:51:32',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	266,	1),
(203,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">You may be provided time off without pay to participate in your children&rsquo;s school activities.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Eligibility</strong>&ndash;&ndash;to qualify, you must have been working for us at least half-time for at least 6 consecutive months immediately before the leave and must have exhausted all earned paid time off you are granted, except for sick leave and disability leave, if applicable.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave can be taken to attend or participate in school conferences or classroom activities related to your children, if such activities cannot be scheduled during non-work hours.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">For school activities leave purposes, a child must be:</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Your biological, adopted, or foster child, a stepchild, or a legal ward</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Enrolled in a primary or secondary public or private school in Illinois or a state that borders Illinois</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;a request for school activities leave must be submitted in writing at least 7 days in advance. If the need for leave is due to an emergency, you must give at least 24 hours&#39; advance notice. You must attempt to schedule leave so as not to unduly disrupt work operations.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave will be granted for up to 8 hours per year, but no more than 4 hours in any 1 day. Upon completion of the school activities leave, you must provide verification of parental participation in a specific school activity (the documentation can be obtained from school administrators).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&ndash;&ndash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you can choose, but are not required, to make up time taken off work for school activities on a different day or different shift at our direction. A good-faith effort will be made to allow you to make up time off for school activities leave. Make up time will be paid at your regular rate.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Applicable benefits will continue to be earned while on leave.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Exceptions</strong>&ndash;&ndash;at our discretion, school activities leave may be denied to you if granting leave would result in more than 5 percent of the workforce or 5 percent of the workers on a shift taking school activities leave at the same time.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'SCHOOL ACTIVITIES-IL over 50',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:52:41',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	245,	1),
(204,	'<p>Military family leave is for when you are the spouse, parent, child, or grandparent of a person called to military service lasting longer than 30 days with the State or United States pursuant to the orders of the Governor or the President of the United States. If you are in this situation, you may be provided a leave of absence as outlined below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;up to 15 days of leave during the time federal or state deployment orders are in effect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualified Employee</strong>&mdash;you may be qualified for leave if all of the following are satisfied:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You have been&nbsp; employed for at least 12 months</li>\r\n	<li>You have worked at least 1,250 hours during the 12 month period immediately preceding the commencement of the leave</li>\r\n	<li>You have exhausted all earned paid time off, personal leave, and any other leave that may be granted to you, except sick leave and disability leave, if applicable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notification</strong>&mdash;if the leave consists of 5 or more consecutive days, you must give at least 14 days notice of the intended date upon which the leave will begin. Where able, you shall consult with us to schedule the leave so as to not unduly disrupt our operations. If the leave consists of less than 5 consecutive days, you must give us as much advance notice as possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;we may require certification from the proper military authority to verify your eligibility for military family leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;this leave is unpaid.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be able to continue applicable benefits (such as health insurance) at your own expense for the duration of the leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement Rights</strong>&mdash;you will be reinstated to your position held prior to taking leave, or to a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Leave-IL 15 to 49',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	15,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:54:04',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	228,	1),
(205,	'<p>Military Family Leave is for when you are the spouse, parent, child, or grandparent of a person called to military service lasting longer than 30 days with the State or United States pursuant to the orders of the Governor or the President of the United States. If you are in this situation, you may be provided a leave of absence as outlined below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;up to 30 days of leave during the time federal or state deployment orders are in effect. The total number of days provided to you may be reduced by the number of days provided for &ldquo;qualifying exigency leave&rdquo; under the federal Family and Medical Leave Act, if applicable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualified Employee</strong>&mdash;you may be qualified for leave if all of the following are satisfied:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You have been&nbsp; employed for at least 12 months</li>\r\n	<li>You have worked at least 1,250 hours during the 12 month period immediately preceding the commencement of the leave</li>\r\n	<li>You have exhausted all earned paid time off, personal leave, and any other leave that may be granted to you, except sick leave and disability leave, if applicable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notification</strong>&mdash;if the leave consists of 5 or more consecutive days, you must give at least 14 days notice of the intended date upon which the leave will begin. Where able, you shall consult with us to schedule the leave so as to not unduly disrupt our operations. If the leave consists of less than 5 consecutive days, you must give us as much advance notice as possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;we may require certification from the proper military authority to verify your eligibility for military family leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;this leave is unpaid.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be able to continue applicable benefits (such as health insurance) at your own expense for the duration of the leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement Rights</strong>&mdash;you will be reinstated to your position held prior to taking leave, or to a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Leave-IL over 50',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 01:55:24',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	229,	1),
(206,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Military family leave is </span>for when you are the spouse, parent, grandparent, child, or sibling of a person called to active duty for a period lasting longer than 89 days. For purposes of this policy, active duty means the armed forces of the United States or the National Guard. <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are in this situation, you may be provided a leave of absence as outlined below<span style=\"border:none\">:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Length of Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">up to 10 days of military family leave during the time federal or state deployment orders are in effect. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Qualified Employee</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be qualified for leave if all of the following are satisfied:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You have been employed for at least 12 months</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You have worked at least 1,500 hours during the 12 month period immediately preceding the commencement of the leave</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You are</span> the spouse, parent, grandparent, child, or sibling of a person called to active duty </span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Qualified Leave Periods</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may take a leave of absence during 1 or more of the following periods:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">During the 30 days before the active duty orders are in effect</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">During a period in which the person ordered to active duty is on leave while active duty orders are in effect</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">During the 30 days after the active duty orders are terminated</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Notification</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you must provide written notice, including a copy of the active duty orders if available, at least 30 days before the date on which you intend to begin leave. If the active duty orders are issued less than 30 days before the date the requested leave is to begin, you must provide as much advance notice as possible. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;we may require certification from the proper military authority to verify your eligibility for leave. If requested, a failure to provide certification will result in the leave being denied and any absence unexcused.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Salary and Benefits</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;leave is unpaid. You may elect or, at our discretion, we may require, you to substitute any earned paid time off, except medical or sick leave (if applicable), for any part of the 10 day period of leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You will be able to continue applicable benefits (such as health insurance) at your own expense for the duration of the leave.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Reinstatement Rights</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you will be reinstated to your position held prior to taking leave, or to a position with equivalent seniority status, pay, benefits, and other terms and conditions of employment unless a comparable position no longer exists due to business necessity. </span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Leave-IN over 50',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IN\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:00:58',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	230,	1),
(207,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault, or have a minor child who is a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault, you may be allowed to take time off from work based on office staffing so that you can obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare of you or your child.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take time off under this policy, you must follow our usual time-off request procedures, unless an emergency prevents you from doing so. When the need for time off is urgent and unforeseeable, you must provide certification to us within 48 hours after the beginning of the unscheduled absence.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can provide documentation through one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you were a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Court protection order separating you from the perpetrator of an act of domestic violence or sexual assault, or other evidence from the court or prosecuting attorney that you have appeared in court</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation from a medical professional, domestic violence advocate or advocate for victims of sexual assault, health care provider, or counselor that you were undergoing treatment for physical or mental injuries or abuse resulting in victimization from an act of domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-KS under 4',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KS\"]',	1,	3,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:03:34',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	268,	1),
(208,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault, or have a minor child who is a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault, you may take time off from work so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare of you or your child</li>\r\n	<li>Seek medical attention for injuries caused by domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain services from a domestic violence shelter, program, or rape crisis center as a result of domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Make court appearances in the aftermath of domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take time off under this policy, you must give us reasonable advance notice of your intention to take time off, unless advance notice is not feasible. When the need for time off is unforeseeable, you must provide certification to us within 48 hours after the beginning of the unscheduled absence. When the need for leave is foreseeable, you must provide documentation to support taking time off under one of the purposes outlined above within 48 hours after returning from the requested time off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can provide certification through one or more of the following:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you were a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Court protection order separating you from the perpetrator of an act of domestic violence or sexual assault, or other evidence from the court or prosecuting attorney that you have appeared in court</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation from a medical professional, domestic violence advocate or advocate for victims of sexual assault, health care provider, or counselor that you were undergoing treatment for physical or mental injuries or abuse resulting in victimization from an act of domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-KS over 4',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KS\"]',	4,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:04:39',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	269,	1),
(209,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Because of the overwhelming evidence that smoking is dangerous and injurious to a person&#39;s health, you are encouraged not to smoke. However, we recognize that the decision to smoke or not to smoke is a personal one.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">State law prohibits smoking in all enclosed areas of places of employment. Therefore, smoking, or carrying the scent of having smoked, whether it is cigarettes, cigars, pipes, e-cigarettes, or any other form, is prohibited within the premises at all times. If you wish to smoke, you must smoke outdoors. While smoking, you must remain 10 feet away from any door, open window or air intake leading into any enclosed area of our business.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">This policy is for the health and safety of everyone. Refer to the <em>Appearance </em>policy for additional information regarding smoking.</span></p>\r\n',	6,	'SMOKING-KS',	'SMOKING',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KS\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:05:30',	'2019-12-18 23:18:19',	'enabled',	18,	0),
(210,	'<p>Adoption leave is available to you when you are temporarily unable to work due to adoption of a child under age 7.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing as early as possible. Please use the <em>Leave Of Absence Application Form</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;a leave of absence will be granted for a period of up to 6 weeks.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may take any earned paid time off to run concurrent with adoption leave. Paid time off benefits are not earned during the leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual). When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Returning from Adoption Leave</strong>&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits, unless a comparable position no longer exists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</li>\r\n	<li>If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Adoption Leave-KY',	'ADOPTION LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:09:49',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	221,	1),
(211,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. If you work full-time, wages, less the amount paid by the court, will be paid for the first 5 days of jury duty or any part thereof. Please submit a copy of the compensation received from the jury service for our payroll records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you would not have earned regular wages had you not been serving as a juror and if you would not have worked more than one-half of a shift that extends into another day had you not been serving as a juror on that day, you will not be paid.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-DC over 10',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	11,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:11:24',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	325,	1),
(212,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-DC under 10',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	1,	10,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:12:10',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	326,	1),
(213,	'<p>If you are a parent, you may be provided time off without pay to participate in your children&rsquo;s school activities. The term parent is defined to include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The natural mother or father of a child</li>\r\n	<li>Anyone who has legal custody of a child or acts as a child&#39;s guardian</li>\r\n	<li>An aunt, uncle, or grandparent of a child</li>\r\n	<li>Anyone who is married to the parent of a child</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave can be taken to attend or participate in any school-related event. A school-related event is defined as any activity sponsored by a school or associated organization, such as a parent-teacher association, and includes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A student performance, such as a concert, play, or rehearsal</li>\r\n	<li>The sporting game or practice of a school team</li>\r\n	<li>A meeting with a teacher or counselor</li>\r\n	<li>Any similar type of activity that directly involves the parent&#39;s child as a participant or as a subject, but not as a spectator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;a request for school activities leave must be submitted in writing at least ten (10) days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave will be granted for up to 24 hours per year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&ndash;&ndash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave. Seniority and applicable benefits will continue to be earned while on leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Exceptions</strong>&ndash;&ndash;at our discretion, school activities leave may be denied if the granting of such leave would disrupt operations and make production or service delivery unusually difficult.</p>\r\n',	4,	'SCHOOL ACTIVITIES-DC',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2017-10-23 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:13:14',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	244,	1),
(214,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with any other authorized breaks, whether paid or unpaid, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-DC under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:51:43',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	121,	1),
(215,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with any other authorized breaks, whether paid or unpaid, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-dc over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:52:34',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	122,	1),
(216,	'<p>When your shift is or exceeds 7 &frac12; hours, you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. Exceptions to this policy will be made if:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Complying with this requirement would endanger public safety</li>\r\n	<li>The duties of your position can only be performed by you</li>\r\n	<li>We employ less than five employees on that shift at that one business location (this only applies to that particular shift)</li>\r\n	<li>Our operation requires that you be available to respond to urgent conditions, and that you are compensated for the meal period</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-CT',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:55:18',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	293,	1),
(217,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic or family violence resulting in physical harm, bodily injury or assault, or an act of threatened violence that constitutes fear of imminent physical harm, bodily injury or assault between family or household members, you may be allowed to take time off from work based on office staffing so that you can obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare of the victim or your child.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take time off under this policy, you must follow our usual time-off request procedures, unless an emergency prevents you from doing so. When the need for time off is urgent and unforeseeable, you must provide documentation upon return to work that supports your reason for being absent from the workplace.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can provide documentation through one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you were a victim of domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Court protection order separating you from the perpetrator of an act of domestic violence or sexual assault, or other evidence from the court or prosecuting attorney that you have appeared in court</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation from a medical professional, domestic violence advocate or advocate for victims of sexual assault, health care provider, or counselor that you were undergoing treatment for physical or mental injuries or abuse resulting in victimization from an act of domestic violence or sexual assault</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-CT under 3',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CT\"]',	1,	2,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:56:54',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	258,	1),
(218,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic or family violence resulting in physical harm, bodily injury or assault, or an act of threatened violence that constitutes fear of imminent physical harm, bodily injury or assault between family or household members, you will be provided with paid or unpaid leave in any calendar year so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek medical care or psychological or other counseling for physical or psychological injury or disability</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain services from a victim services organization</li>\r\n	<li>Relocate due to family violence</li>\r\n	<li>Participate in any civil or criminal proceeding related to or resulting from family violence</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Leave includes paid leave which may include, but is not limited to, vacation time, personal days off or other paid time off benefits. Unpaid leave shall be limited to 12 days during any calendar year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to use leave under this section and it is foreseeable, you must provide 7 days advance notice prior to the date such leave is to begin. If your need for such leave is not foreseeable, you are required to give notice of such intention as soon as practicable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to provide us a signed written statement certifying that the leave is for a purpose authorized under this section.&nbsp; You may also be asked to provide one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Police or court record related to the family violence</li>\r\n	<li>A signed written statement that you are a victim of family violence from you or an agent of a victim services organization, an attorney, an employee of the Judicial Branch&#39;s Office of Victim Services or the Office of the Victim Advocate, or a licensed medical professional or other licensed professional from whom you have sought assistance with respect to the family violence</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, or if required by federal or state law, or if necessary to protect your safety in the workplace.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-CT over 3',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CT\"]',	3,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 02:58:04',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	259,	1),
(219,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, you may take time off from work so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare of you or your child.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any applicable paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take time off under this policy, you must give us reasonable advance notice of your intention to take time off, unless advance notice is not feasible. When the need for time off is unforeseeable, you must provide certification to us within a reasonable time after the absence.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can provide certification through one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you were a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking.</li>\r\n	<li>Court protection order separating you from the perpetrator of an act of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, or other evidence from the court or prosecuting attorney that you have appeared in court.</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation from a medical professional, domestic violence advocate or advocate for victims of sexual assault, health care provider, or counselor that you were undergoing treatment for physical or mental injuries or abuse resulting in victimization from an act of domestic violence, sexual assault or stalking.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have disclosed your status as a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, we will, upon request, provide reasonable accommodation to ensure your safety while at work. We shall work together with you to quickly determine what, if any, accommodation we can make that will not create an undue hardship on the business. Such accommodation may include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Transfer, reassignment, modified schedule, changed work telephone, changed work station, installed lock</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance in documenting domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking that occurs in the workplace</li>\r\n	<li>An implemented safety procedure or another adjustment to a job structure, workplace facility, or work requirement in response to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, or referral to a victim assistance organization.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If, at some point, circumstances change and you determine you need a new accommodation, please inform us as soon as possible. Also, please let us know when you no longer need the accommodation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-CA under 25',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	1,	24,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 03:00:48',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	254,	1),
(220,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, you may take time off from work so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare of you or your child.</li>\r\n	<li>Seek medical attention for injuries caused by domestic violence, sexual assault or stalking.</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain services from a domestic violence shelter, program, or rape crisis center as a result of domestic violence, sexual assault or stalking.</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain psychological counseling related to an experience of domestic violence, sexual assault or stalking.</li>\r\n	<li>To participate in safety planning and take other actions to increase safety from future domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, including temporary or permanent relocation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any applicable paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take time off under this policy, you must give us reasonable advance notice of your intention to take time off, unless advance notice is not feasible. When the need for time off is unforeseeable, you must provide certification to us within a reasonable time after the absence.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can provide certification through one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you were a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking.</li>\r\n	<li>Court protection order separating you from the perpetrator of an act of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, or other evidence from the court or prosecuting attorney that you have appeared in court.</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation from a medical professional, domestic violence advocate or advocate for victims of sexual assault, health care provider, or counselor that you were undergoing treatment for physical or mental injuries or abuse resulting in victimization from an act of domestic violence, sexual assault or stalking.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have disclosed your status as a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, we will, upon request, provide reasonable accommodation to ensure your safety while at work. We shall work together with you to quickly determine what, if any, accommodation we can make that will not create an undue hardship on the business. Such accommodation may include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Transfer, reassignment, modified schedule, changed work telephone, changed work station, installed lock</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance in documenting domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking that occurs in the workplace</li>\r\n	<li>An implemented safety procedure or another adjustment to a job structure, workplace facility, or work requirement in response to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, or referral to a victim assistance organization.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If, at some point, circumstances change and you determine you need a new accommodation, please inform us as soon as possible. Also, please let us know when you no longer need the accommodation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-CA over 25',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	25,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 03:02:15',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	255,	1),
(221,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are a parent, guardian, stepparent, foster parent, or grandparent of, or a person who stands in loco parentis to, a child that is enrolled in a licensed day-care facility or a school (from kindergarten through grade 12), you are eligible to take school activities leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Reasons for Leave</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;leave can be taken to:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Find, enroll, or re-enroll a child in a school or with a licensed child care provider</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Participate in activities at a child&#39;s day-care facility or school. </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Appear at the school when a child has been suspended or expelled</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Address a child care provider or school emergency</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Request for Leave</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;a request for school activities leave must be submitted in writing as early as possible. At our discretion, documentation from your child&#39;s school or day-care facility verifying participation in a specific activity on a particular date at a particular time may be required.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Length of Leave</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;leave will be granted for up to 40 hours per year. You are limited to 8 hours in a single month for the following reasons:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Find, enroll, or re-enroll a child in a school or with a licensed child care provider</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Participate in activities at a child&#39;s day-care facility or school</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Time off to appear at school at the request of the school for a child that has been suspended or expelled shall not be limited provided you give reasonable notice of the request. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Salary and Benefits</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'SCHOOL ACTIVITIES-CA over 25',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	25,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 03:03:29',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	242,	1),
(222,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">If you are the parent or guardian of a child who has been suspended from school, you will be provided time off without pay to appear at the school in connection with that suspension.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&mdash;school leave relating to a student&#39;s suspension can be taken whenever the school requests your appearance.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for school activities leave must be submitted in writing as early as possible.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;no limit applies to school leave relating to a student&#39;s suspension.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><strong>Other school activities</strong>&mdash;you must make a reasonable attempt to schedule other appointments for school activities outside regular work hours. However, at our discretion, you may be provided time off without pay to participate in other school or day-care activities, although it is not required by federal or state law. Please submit a request in writing at least seven days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Documentation from your child&#39;s school or day-care facility verifying participation in a specific activity on a particular date at a particular time may be required. You may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'SCHOOL ACTIVITIES-CA under 25',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	1,	24,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 03:04:46',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	241,	1),
(223,	'<p>You may be eligible for a leave of absence if you wish to donate an organ or your bone marrow to another person. To be eligible, you must have been employed for at least 90 days immediately preceding the beginning of leave. The following outlines the leave of absence available for each purpose:&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>O</strong><strong>rgan Donation (Paid Leave)</strong>&mdash;you may be given a paid leave of absence for up to 30 business days in any 1 year period, taken in 1 or more periods, for the purpose of donating an organ to another person. The 1 year period is measured from the date your leave begins and shall consist of 12 consecutive months.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>O</strong><strong>rgan Donation (Unpaid Leave)</strong>&mdash;if you exhaust your paid leave, you may be given an unpaid leave of absence for up to an additional 30 business days in any 1 year period, taken in 1 or more periods, for the purpose of donating an organ to another person. The 1 year period is measured from the date your leave begins and shall consist of 12 consecutive months.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Bone Marrow Donation (Paid Leave)</strong>&mdash;you may be given a paid leave of absence for up to 5 business days in any 1 year period, taken in 1 or more periods, for the purpose of donating bone marrow to another person. The 1 year period is measured from the date your leave begins and shall consist of 12 consecutive months.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Written Verification</strong>&mdash;if you need a leave for either of the above-listed reasons, you must provide written verification that you are an organ or bone marrow donor or that there is a medical necessity for the donation at the time the leave of absence is requested.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;as a condition of your initial receipt of bone marrow or organ donation leave, you must take up to 5 days of earned and unused paid time off for bone marrow donation and up to 2 weeks of earned and unused paid time off for organ donation.&nbsp; For the purposes of seniority, benefits, or other terms of employment, leave taken under this policy does not constitute a break in continuous service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If applicable, we shall maintain and pay for health insurance coverage for the full duration of the leave in the same manner the coverage would have been maintained if you had been actively at work during the leave period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that work can be properly scheduled.&nbsp; Upon returning from leave you will be reinstated to the position held before the leave began, or a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Bone Marrow-CA',	'ORGAN AND BONE MARROW DONATION LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 03:08:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	68,	1),
(224,	'<p>For those who have spouses in the military, you may be provided a leave of absence as outlined below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;up to 10 days of unpaid leave during a qualified leave period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualified Leave Period</strong>&mdash;the period during which the qualified service member is on leave from deployment during a period of military conflict.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualified Employee</strong>&mdash;you may be qualified for leave if all of the following are satisfied:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You are a spouse of a qualified service member</li>\r\n	<li>You work an average of 20 or more hours per week (independent contractors excluded)</li>\r\n	<li>You provide us with notice, within 2 business days of receiving official notice that the qualified service member will be on leave from deployment, of your intention to take a leave of absence</li>\r\n	<li>You submit written documentation to us certifying that the qualified service member will be on leave from deployment during the time the leave is requested</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualified Service Member</strong>&mdash;a qualified service member is any of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A member of the Armed Forces of the United States who has been deployed during a period of military conflict to an area designated as a combat theater or combat zone by the President of the United States</li>\r\n	<li>A member of the National Guard who has been deployed during a period of military conflict</li>\r\n	<li>A member of the Reserves who has been deployed during a period of military conflict</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&ldquo;Period of Military Conflict&rdquo;</strong>&mdash;a &ldquo;period of military conflict&rdquo; means either of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A period of war declared by the United States Congress</li>\r\n	<li>A period of deployment for which a member of a reserve component is ordered to active duty pursuant to either Sections 12301 and 12302 of Title 10 of the United States Code, or Title 32 of the United States Code</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Military Leave-CA',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	25,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 03:10:06',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	227,	1),
(225,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Safety shields are to be worn during clinical and/or laboratory procedures, as required by law. We will supply non-<span style=\"border:none\">prescription safety shields, or glasses, for your use.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	5,	'Safety Shields',	'SAFETY SHIELDS',	'none',	'2017-08-24 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"doptional\",\"voptional\",\"moptional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 05:37:46',	'2019-10-03 16:32:44',	'enabled',	1,	0),
(226,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If applicable, and as required by law, safety equipment like shields, glasses, gloves, and hard hats are to be worn. If required, we will supply non-prescription safety shields, or glasses, for your use.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	5,	'Safety Equipment',	'SAFETY EQUIPMENT',	'none',	'2017-08-24 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"coptional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 05:42:25',	'2019-10-03 16:32:44',	'enabled',	2,	0),
(227,	'<p>If you experience or witness an accident in which you or someone else sustains a personal injury or is exposed to occupational health hazards, regardless of how serious, immediately report the situation. Non-work-related injuries that might be aggravated on the job, or adversely affect job performance, are also to be reported. You may use the <em>Accident Report Form</em> for this purpose. Failure to report an accident or injury can result in a violation of legal requirements and can lead to difficulties in processing insurance and benefit claims.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your injury is such that we require you to seek medical attention, either on site or at a medical care facility, your time waiting for and receiving treatment will be paid during your normal work hours.</p>\r\n',	5,	'Accidents or Injuries',	'ACCIDENTS OR INJURIES',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-09-19 05:45:53',	'2019-12-17 21:11:47',	'enabled',	4,	0),
(228,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Separations are classified as either voluntary</span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> or involuntary.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Voluntar</span></span></span><strong><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">y</span></span></span></strong><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;a resignation initiated by you. Please submit your resignation in writing using the </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Notice of Resignation Form</span></span></i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Although you may resign, at any time, with or without cause or advance notice, we would appreciate that you provide at least two weeks&rsquo; <span style=\"border:none\">advance notice, whenever possible. However, we may find it inefficient, disruptive or undesirable to permit you to work for the duration of your notice, and we reserve the right to accelerate the effective date of your resignation at any given time. In-lie<span style=\"border:none\">u-of-notice pay may be provided at our discretion.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Involuntary</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;a separation initiated by us. This may be the result of:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Lack of work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Your inability to perform work duties satisfactorily </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Reorganization and/or relocation</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Your unprofessional conduct</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">The business&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">being<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;sold or acquired by another entity </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The above items are not intended to show all the possibilities that might result in involuntary release from employment. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Exit Interview</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you may be asked to complete an exit interview questionnaire&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">at the time of your departure.</span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:red\"><span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"border:none\">This questionnaire gives you a chance to communicate your views on your work, pay, benefits, management, and communication during your time of employment and is used for us to consider making improvements to our work environment<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Return of Property</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you resign, any property belonging to us must be returned on or before your last day of work. If your employment is involuntarily terminated, any property belonging to us must be returned immediately. Items&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">may include uniforms, keys, <span style=\"border:none\">cell phones and electronic devices, <span style=\"border:none\">manuals, equipment, etc. Your cooperation is appreciated. We reserve the right to take any legal action necessary to ensure our property is returned.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	7,	'Separation from Employment',	'SEPARATION FROM EMPLOYMENT',	'none',	'2019-01-10 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 03:18:27',	'2019-01-10 19:45:08',	'enabled',	0,	0),
(229,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are absent from work for 3 consecutive days without providing proper notification, we will consider you to have resigned. If you request time off that is denied and take time off anyway, or if you fail to return from an approved absence on th<span style=\"border:none\">e agreed upon date, or if you walk off the job during your shift, the absence is considered to be job abandonment and will be treated as a voluntary resignation.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Exceptions may be made to this policy if extenuating circumstances existed that resulted in </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; border: none;\">your inability to properly notify us of your absence.</span></p>\r\n',	7,	'Job Abandonment',	'JOB ABANDONMENT',	'none',	'2017-08-24 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 03:19:23',	'2017-09-19 23:14:40',	'enabled',	1,	0),
(230,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you, or any of your dependents, are covered by our group health plan, you or your dependents may be eligible for continuation of the coverage when it would otherwise be lost. Upon enrollment onto our plan, you and/or your dependents will be provided with information regarding your rights for continuation of coverage should an event occur that would make you or your dependents eligible. You and/or your dependents will also be notified of these rights and provided appropriate paperwork for continuation of coverage when an event occurs that would cause a loss of coverage. If elected, this coverage is paid for entirely by you or your dependents. Please let us know if you have any questions</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">.</span></span></p>\r\n',	7,	'Healthcare Continuation',	'HEALTHCARE CONTINUATION COVERAGE',	'none',	'2017-08-24 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 03:20:44',	'2018-02-08 17:50:39',	'enabled',	4,	1),
(231,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas, as feasible, for this purpose for up to 3 years after the birth of a child. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, when possible. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk unless doing so would create an undue hardship to the business. This additional time off must be mutually agreed upon by you and us.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-VT under 50',	'	BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	0,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:01:04',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	197,	1),
(232,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas, as feasible, for this purpose for up to 3 years after the birth of a child. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, when possible. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This additional time off must be mutually agreed upon by you and us.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-VT over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	50,	10000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:02:00',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	198,	1),
(233,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-VT',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:03:41',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	367,	1),
(234,	'<p>You may be provided time off without pay to participate in your children&rsquo;s school activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&ndash;&ndash;to qualify, you must have completed 1 year of continuous employment and have worked an average of at least 30 hours a week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave can be taken to participate in school activities, such as parent-teacher conferences, that are directly related to the academic educational advancement of your child, stepchild, foster child, or legal ward. The child, stepchild, foster child, or legal ward must live with you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;you must make a reasonable attempt to schedule appointments for school activities outside regular work hours. If that is not possible, a request for school activities leave must be submitted in writing at least 7 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave will be granted for up to 4 hours in a 30 day period, but no more than 24 hours in any 12 month period. You may be required to take school activities leave in a minimum of 2 hour segments.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Any short-term parental leave used for school activities reduces the amount of short-term leave allowed for other purposes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&ndash;&ndash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Leave for School Activities-VT',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	15,	1000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:05:28',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	253,	1),
(235,	'<p>Paid rest breaks are provided throughout the work period for you to use the restroom facilities as needed.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Rest Breaks-VT',	'REST BREAKS',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:06:26',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	316,	1),
(236,	'<p>You will be provided a reasonable opportunity to eat during the work period. The meal period may be scheduled for more or less than 30 minutes depending on our scheduling needs. Meal periods lasting 30 minutes or more in which you are completely relieved of your work duties will be unpaid.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-VT',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:07:16',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	307,	1),
(237,	'<p>You will be provided an unpaid family leave as outlined below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family leave, you must have worked for an average of at least 30 hours per week during a 12 month period.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&mdash;you can take family leave for:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your own serious illness</li>\r\n	<li>The serious illness of your child, stepchild or ward, who lives with you, foster child, parent, spouse or parent of your spouse</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&ldquo;Serious Illness&rdquo; means an accident, disease or physical or mental condition that:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Poses imminent danger of death</li>\r\n	<li>Requires inpatient care in a hospital</li>\r\n	<li>Requires continuing in-home care under the direction of a physician</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing as early as possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Medical</strong><strong> Certification</strong>&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need for leave due to a serious health condition.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.5in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 12 weeks during any 12 month period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may choose to use paid time off, not to exceed 6 weeks, in-lieu-of unpaid family leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. If you do not pay the total amount of the premium, coverage will discontinue until regular employment is resumed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Seniority, accumulated prior to leave, is not lost during a family leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during family leave. Benefits are earned for the full month in which you work at least 50 percent of the time. Paid time off counts as time worked.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you take a leave due to a personal serious health condition, you must provide a note from your treating physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. The note must also indicate if there are any restrictions pertaining to duties or the number of hours the employee can work. You may use the <em>Medical Release to Work Form</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits, unless a comparable position no longer exists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>When you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</li>\r\n	<li>When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</li>\r\n	<li>When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Family Leave-VT',	'STATE FAMILY LEAVE ',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	15,	1000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:12:55',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	225,	1),
(238,	'<p>You will be provided an unpaid parental leave as outlined below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid parental leave, you must have worked for an average of at least 30 hours per week during a 12 month period.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&mdash;you can take parental leave for:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The birth of your child</li>\r\n	<li>The initial placement of a child 16 years of age or younger with you for the purpose of adoption</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 6 weeks in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 12 weeks during any 12 month period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may use paid time off, not to exceed 6 weeks, in-lieu-of unpaid family leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. If you do not pay the total amount of the premium, coverage will discontinue until regular employment is resumed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Seniority, accumulated prior to leave, is not lost during a parental leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any earned paid time off used during parental leave. Benefits are earned for the full month in which you work at least 50 percent of the time. Paid time off counts as time worked.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits, unless a comparable position no longer exists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>When you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</li>\r\n	<li>When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</li>\r\n	<li>When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</li>\r\n	<li>If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Parental Leave-VT',	'STATE PARENTAL LEAVE ',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	10,	1000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:15:49',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	226,	1),
(239,	'<p>You shall have the right to take unpaid leave for the purpose of attending the annual town meeting provided it does not adversely impact essential business operations. You must notify us at least 7 days prior to the date of the town meeting you wish to attend. We will not discharge or in any other manner retaliate against you for exercising your right to attend the annual town meeting.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-VT',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:16:46',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	401,	1),
(240,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-VA under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VA\"]',	0,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:18:41',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	195,	1),
(241,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. </span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-VA over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VA\"]',	50,	1000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:19:39',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	196,	1),
(242,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When you receive a subpoena to appear in court or are called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You will be given a Leave of Absence to attend court or jury service. Wages will not be paid while on the leave of absence.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty or other court-ordered appearance.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-VA',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:20:52',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	366,	1),
(243,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 2 years after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-WA 14 to 50 ees',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	15,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:22:28',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	199,	1),
(244,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 2 years after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-WA over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	50,	1000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:25:21',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	200,	1),
(245,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-WA',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:26:37',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	368,	1),
(246,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When your shift exceeds five hours, </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30-minutes. The meal period will be scheduled after the second hour of work and before the fifth hour of work. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. You may (with our permission) voluntarily agree to waive the right to a meal period. A written agreement to waive the meal period may be required</span>.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-WA',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2018-03-20 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:28:37',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	308,	1),
(247,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">You receive a paid rest break of 10 minutes at approximately the middle of every 4 hours of work. The breaks may not be combined and added to the lunch period, nor can they be waived to shorten the work day. We ask that you take your breaks when they will not negatively affect customer service. For insurance purposes, we ask that you remain on the premises during rest breaks.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Rest Breaks-WA',	'REST BREAKS',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:29:30',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	317,	1),
(248,	'<p>Pregnancy leave is provided to you when you are temporarily unable to work due to a disability caused by pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a written request from your healthcare provider that you be transferred to a less strenuous or hazardous position, we will do our best to accommodate you. If accommodation is not possible, and you are not able to continue your normal job responsibilities, you may be asked to go on pregnancy leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please use the <em>Leave Of Absence Application Form</em> for this purpose.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Healthcare Professional&rsquo;s</strong><strong> Certification</strong>&mdash;any request for a pregnancy disability leave must be accompanied with a certified healthcare professional&rsquo;s certificate.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.5in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;the duration of leave will be decided on a case-by-case basis. Your physician will determine, based on the facts of the situation, how long you need to be on a leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intermittent </strong><strong>Leave/Reduced Work Schedule</strong>&mdash;is allowable when medically necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reporting on Progress</strong>&mdash;you are required to report directly to the employer every 30 days on your health status and your intent to return to work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may use any earned paid time off to run concurrent with the pregnancy leave. Benefits are not earned during the leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during pregnancy leave. When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pregnancy Leave of Absence Ends When</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"arrow\">\r\n	<li>You are released for full or partial duty. You must provide a physician&rsquo;s statement in writing indicating your fitness to return to work</li>\r\n	<li>We receive satisfactory medical evidence that you are unable to return to work</li>\r\n	<li>You directly or indirectly inform us (for example, by accepting employment elsewhere, moving out of state, etc.) that you do not intend to return to work</li>\r\n	<li>You have been on a medical leave of absence for the approved time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Returning from Pregnancy Leave</strong>&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that your return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;you must provide a completed <em>Medical Release to Work</em> <em>Form</em>, or an equivalent note from your healthcare provider, verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. This must be received on or before the date you are scheduled to return from leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or a similar position without loss of status, pay or service credits, unless a comparable position no longer exists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class=\"arrow\">\r\n	<li>If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</li>\r\n	<li>If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Leave-WA',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2015-10-13 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	8,	1000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:31:45',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	103,	1),
(249,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault or stalking, or have a family member who is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, you will be provided with reasonable leave from work. The leave can be taken intermittently or on a reduced schedule so that you can:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Seek legal or law enforcement assistance or remedies to ensure the health and safety of you or your family member including, but not limited to, preparing for, or participating in, any civil or criminal legal proceeding related to or derived from domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Seek treatment by a health care provider for physical or mental injuries caused by domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, or to attend to the health care treatment of your family member who is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Obtain, or assist a family member in obtaining, mental health counseling related to an incident of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking when you or your family member is a victim.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Participate in safety planning, temporarily or permanently relocate, or take other actions to increase the safety of you or your family member from future incidents of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Obtain services from a domestic violence shelter or program</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">For the purpose of this policy, &ldquo;family member&rdquo; is defined as:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Your spouse, child, parent, parent-in-law, grandparent</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">A person with whom you have a dating relationship</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Leave will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take leave, you must give us reasonable advance notice of your intention to take leave and must follow our usual time-off request procedures. However, when you cannot provide advance notice because of an emergency or unforeseen circumstance related to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, you or your designee must give notice no later than the end of the first day that you take leave.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take leave or request a safety accommodation under this policy, you may be required to verify that you or your family member is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking and that leave is taken for one of the reasons described above or that the safety accommodation requested is for the purpose of protecting you from domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking. If required, verification must be provided in a timely manner. When the need for time off is unforeseeable, you must provide verification to us within a reasonable time during or after the leave. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">You can provide verification through one or more of the following:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">A police report indicating that you or your family member was a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Court order protecting or separating you or your family member from the perpetrator of the act of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, or other evidence from the court or the prosecuting attorney that you or your family member appeared, or is scheduled to appear, in court in connection with an incident of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Documentation that you or your family member is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking from any of the following persons from whom you or your family member sought assistance in addressing the situation: an advocate for victims of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, an attorney, a member of the clergy, or a medical or other professional </span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Your own written statement that you or your family member is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking and that the leave was taken for one of the purposes outlined above or that the safety accommodation requested is for the purpose of protecting you from domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Family relationship verification may be made by a statement from you, a birth certificate, a court document, or other similar documentation</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you have disclosed your status as a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, we will, upon request, provide reasonable accommodation to ensure your safety while at work. We shall work together with you to quickly determine what, if any, accommodation we can make that will not create an undue hardship on the business. Such accommodation may include:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Transfer, reassignment, modified schedule, changed work telephone or email address, changed work station, installed lock </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">An implemented safety procedure or another adjustment to a job structure, workplace facility, or work requirement in response to actual or threatened domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If, at some point, circumstances change and you determine you need a new accommodation, please inform us as soon as possible. Also, please let us know when you no longer need the accommodation.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence-WA',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2018-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	1,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-14 04:48:34',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	280,	1),
(250,	'<p>Please see our policy on paid time off regarding the amount of paid time off available to you based on your employment category. This policy does not add paid time off benefits; rather it ensures flexibility in the use of your paid time off benefits.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may use any of your earned and available paid time off to attend to a child with a health condition that requires treatment or supervision, or to care for a spouse, registered domestic partner, parent, parent-in-law, or grandparent who has a serious health condition or an emergency health condition, and to care for children 18 years and older with disabilities. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following definitions apply for purposes of this policy: &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&ldquo;Registered Domestic Partners&rdquo; qualify if they are registered with the Office of the Secretary of State</li>\r\n	<li>&quot;Child&quot; means an adopted, biological, or foster child, a stepchild, a legal ward, or a child of a person standing in for a parent&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>&ldquo;Disabled child&rdquo; is a child who is &ldquo;incapable of self-care because of a mental or physical disability that limits 1 or more activities of daily living&rdquo;, no requirement that it be a chronic condition&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For time off to care for a child, the &ldquo;health condition&rdquo; must be:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A medical condition requiring treatment or medication that the child cannot self-administer</li>\r\n	<li>A medical or mental-health condition which would endanger the child&rsquo;s safety or recovery without the presence of a parent or guardian</li>\r\n	<li>A condition warranting treatment or preventive health care such as physical, dental, optical or immunization services, when a parent must be present to authorize the treatment</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For time off to care for a spouse, registered domestic partner, parent, parent-in-law, or grandparent, the serious or emergency health condition must:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Require an overnight stay in a hospital or other medical-care facility</li>\r\n	<li>Result in a period of incapacity or treatment or recovery following inpatient care</li>\r\n	<li>Be continuing treatment under the care of a health care services provider that includes any period of &nbsp;incapacity to work or attend to regular daily activities</li>\r\n	<li>Be demanding immediate action (emergency health condition)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You are eligible if you earn paid time off benefits as defined by the applicable policies set forth in the manual.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\nAll requirements regarding time off, reporting time off, and/or documentation, as outlined in the paid time off policies, are also applicable to this policy.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Flexible Leave-WA',	'FLEXIBLE LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-11-14 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:39:16',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	9,	1),
(251,	'<p>Military family leave can be requested by you if you are the spouse or domestic partner of a member of the Armed Forces of the United States, the National Guard, or the military reserve forces of the United States who has been notified of an impending call or order to active duty, or who has been deployed during a period of military conflict.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For purposes of this policy, a &ldquo;period of military conflict&rdquo; means a period of war declared by the United States Congress, declared by executive order of the President of the United States, or in which a reserve component of the Armed Forces of the United States is ordered to active duty pursuant to Title 32 of the United States Code or section 12301 or 12302 of Title 10 of the United States Code.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Leave may be provided per deployment after the military member has been notified of an impending call or order to active duty and before deployment, and when the military member is on leave from deployment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;up to 15 days of leave during the time federal or state deployment orders are in effect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qualified Employee</strong>&mdash;you are qualified for leave if you work 20 or more hours per week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notification</strong>&mdash;if you intend to take leave under this policy, you must provide us with notice of the intention to take leave within 5 business days of receiving the official notice of an impending call or order to active duty or of a leave from deployment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;we may require certification from the proper military authority to verify your eligibility for leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;leave is unpaid. However, you may elect to use any earned paid time off as part of the leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any earned paid time used during leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement Rights</strong>&mdash;you will be reinstated to your position held prior to taking leave, or to a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</p>\r\n',	4,	'MIlitary Leave-WA',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:40:32',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	239,	1),
(252,	'<p>You may be provided an unpaid family and medical leave as outlined below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family and medical leave, you must have worked: 1) At least 12 months (need not be consecutive), 2) At least 1,250 hours in the 12 months immediately before the leave is to commence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&mdash;family and medical leave is available for:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The birth, adoption, or foster placement of a child</li>\r\n	<li>Your own serious health condition (excluding pregnancy or pregnancy-related disabilities)</li>\r\n	<li>The serious health condition of your family member (spouse, child, parent, or state registered domestic partner of an employee)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A serious health condition is defined as an illness, injury, impairment, or physical or mental condition requiring inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential medical care facility or continuing treatment or supervision by a health care provider.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The definitions of &ldquo;parent&rdquo; and &ldquo;child&rdquo; cover biological, foster, step, and adoptive relationships; legal guardians or wards; and individuals charged with parental rights, duties, and responsibilities for a child. A child generally must be under 18; however, an adult dependent incapable of self-care due to mental or physical disability also qualifies as a child.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;when leave is foreseeable, you must request a leave at least 30 days in advance. However, if 30 days&#39; advance notice is impossible because of a change in circumstances or a medical emergency, you must give notice as soon as practicable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Medical</strong><strong> Certification</strong>&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need for leave due to your own or a family member&rsquo;s serious health condition. You must provide certification in a timely manner.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.5in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 12 workweeks during any 12 month period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intermittent </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;you may take your available family and medical leave on an intermittent basis when necessary. If you take intermittent or reduced-schedule leave for planned medical treatment, you must attempt to schedule the leave so as to minimize disruption to work operations. If you need such leave, you may be required to transfer temporarily into alternative positions with equivalent pay and benefits that better accommodate recurring periods of leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Interaction with Other </strong><strong>Leave</strong><strong> Mandates</strong>&mdash;unless you are disabled by a pregnancy-related medical condition, leave under state law runs concurrently with leave under the Federal Family and Medical Leave Act. Any leave taken in accordance with state-mandated pregnancy disability leave will not reduce the amount of family and medical leave available under state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may take any earned paid time off to run concurrent with the leave. Benefits are not earned during the leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy at the end of this manual).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any earned paid leave used during family and medical leave. When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Returning from Leave</strong>&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you take a leave due to a personal serious health condition, you must provide a note from your treating physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. The note must also indicate if there are any restrictions pertaining to duties or the number of hours the employee can work. You may use the <em>Medical Release to Work Form</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</li>\r\n	<li>When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</li>\r\n	<li>When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Family and Medical Leave-WA',	'STATE FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	50,	10000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:42:53',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'disabled',	217,	1),
(253,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-WV under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WV\"]',	0,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:44:55',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	204,	1),
(254,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-WV over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WV\"]',	50,	10000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:45:57',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	205,	1),
(255,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-WV',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WV\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:47:12',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	370,	1),
(256,	'<p>When your shift is or exceeds 6 hours, you will be scheduled for a meal period of at least 20 minutes. If the period is less than 30 minutes in duration, it will be paid. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. There are two exceptions: 1) You may (with our permission) voluntarily agree to waive the right to a meal period, provided the work day is no more than 7 hours; 2) A paid working meal period may be permitted if the nature of the work does not permit you to be released from duty. The latter should occur infrequently. For both exceptions, you must sign the <em>On Duty Meal Period/Meal Period Waiver Form</em>.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-WV',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WV\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:48:19',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	309,	1),
(257,	'<p>If you have 3 or more consecutive non-work hours available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day, you may not be entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 3 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior written request by you at least 3 days before Election Day, provide up to 3 hours of paid time off to vote. We may specify when the time off will be taken in order to avoid impairment or disruption of essential services. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In addition, if you are provided time off with pay and fail or neglect to vote, then the time provided for this purpose may be without pay and subject to salary and/or wage deductions.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-WV',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WV\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:49:32',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	404,	1),
(258,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breasfeeding-WI under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WI\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:51:06',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	203,	1),
(259,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breasfeeding-WI over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WI\"]',	50,	10000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:52:13',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	202,	1),
(260,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty-WI',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:53:18',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	369,	1),
(261,	'<p>We will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide up to 3 consecutive hours of unpaid time off to vote. We may specify when the time off will be taken.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting-WI',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:54:33',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	402,	1),
(262,	'<p>You may be provided an unpaid family and medical leave as outlined below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family and medical leave, you must have worked: 1) More than 52 consecutive weeks, 2) At least 1,000 hours in the preceding 52 week period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&mdash;you can take family and medical leave for:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Childbirth</li>\r\n	<li>Adoption or pre-adoption placement of a child</li>\r\n	<li>Your own serious health condition</li>\r\n	<li>The serious health condition of your child, spouse, or parent</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A serious health condition is defined as an illness, injury, impairment, or physical or mental condition requiring inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or nursing home or continuing treatment by a health care provider.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The definitions of parent and child cover biological, step, foster, adoptive, and in-law relationships, along with legal wards and guardians.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;if you expect to take leave for childbirth or adoption or for planned medical treatment or supervision of your own or a family member&#39;s serious illness, you must give us reasonable and practicable advance notice of the need for leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When requesting intermittent or reduced-schedule leave for planned treatment of your own illness or to care for a family member with a serious health condition, you must provide notice with reasonable promptness once they learn of the probable need for leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Medical</strong><strong> Certification</strong>&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need for leave due to your own or a family members&rsquo; serious health condition. You must provide this medical certification before starting family and medical leave, if possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.5in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;no more than 8 weeks of family leave and no more than 2 weeks of medical leave can be taken in any 12 month period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Family leave for childbirth, adoption, and care of family members with serious health conditions is limited to a combined total of 8 weeks in a 12 month period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Additional limits apply to the amount of leave allowed for particular purposes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Childbirth/Adoption </strong><strong>Leave</strong><strong>:</strong> Family leave of up to 6 weeks over a 12 month period is available to you for the birth or adoption of a child. The leave must begin within 16 weeks before or after the expected or actual date of a child&#39;s birth or adoption.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Leave</strong><strong> for Own Serious Health Condition:</strong> Medical leave of up to two (2) weeks in a twelve (12) month period is available to you when you are unable to work because of your own serious health condition.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Leave</strong><strong> for </strong><strong>Family</strong><strong> Member&#39;s Serious Condition:</strong> Family leave of up to two (2) weeks in a twelve (12) month period is available to care for a child, spouse, or parent with a serious health condition.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intermittent </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;you can take family and medical leave on an intermittent basis or a reduced work schedule for your own serious health condition to the extent such leave is medically necessary. You must schedule intermittent or reduced scheduled leave for childbirth, adoption, or care of family members with serious health conditions in a way that avoids unduly disrupting work operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;generally, the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may choose, but are not required, to substitute any earned paid time off for unpaid family and medical leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are 2 payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>During family and medical leave, you retain all employment benefits earned prior to the date the leave began. If you are using other forms of paid leave while on family and medical leave, you will earn employment benefits at the rate normally permitted during paid time off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you take a leave due to a personal serious health condition, you must provide a note from your treating physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. The note must also indicate if there are any restrictions pertaining to duties or the number of hours the employee can work. You may use the <em>Medical Release to Work Form</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On return from family and medical leave, you will be restored to your former position or to a position with equivalent compensation, benefits, work hours, and other terms and conditions of employment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</li>\r\n	<li>When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</li>\r\n	<li>When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</li>\r\n	<li>If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Family and Medical Leave-WI',	'STATE FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WI\"]',	50,	10000000,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 01:58:26',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	218,	1),
(263,	'<p>Because of the overwhelming evidence that smoking is dangerous and injurious to a person&#39;s health, you are encouraged not to smoke. However, we recognize that the decision to smoke or not to smoke is a personal one.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>State law prohibits smoking in all enclosed areas of places of employment. Therefore, smoking, or carrying the scent of having smoked, whether it is cigarettes, cigars, pipes, e-cigarettes, or any other form, is prohibited within the premises at all times. If you wish to smoke, you must smoke outdoors in designated smoking areas.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This policy is for the general health and safety of everyone. Refer to the <em>Appearance</em> policy for additional information regarding smoking.</p>\r\n',	6,	'Smoking-WI',	'SMOKING',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 02:01:12',	'2019-12-18 23:18:19',	'enabled',	17,	0),
(264,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-WY under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-10-14 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WY\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-10-15 02:03:16',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	207,	1),
