(322,	'<p>When you receive a subpoena to appear in court or are called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be given a Leave of Absence to attend court or jury service. Wages will not be paid while on the leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty or other court-ordered appearance.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Witness Duty SC',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"SC\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 07:58:31',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	360,	1),
(323,	'<p>You may be eligible for a paid leave of absence if you wish to donate your bone marrow to another person.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligible Employees</strong>&mdash;you must work an average of 20 or more hours per week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;the total length of the leave shall be determined by you and cannot exceed 40 hours for bone marrow donation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance, or as soon as possible for unforeseeable events.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Written Verification</strong>&mdash;medical verification from a physician may be required to confirm the purpose and length of each leave requested by you to donate bone marrow.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that work can be properly scheduled.&nbsp; Upon returning from leave you will be reinstated to the position held before the leave began, or a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Bone Marrow Leave SC',	'BONE MARROW DONATION LEAVE',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"SC\"]',	20,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 08:00:13',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	72,	1),
(324,	'<p>We are an E-Verify employer. E-Verify is an internet-based system that compares information from the <em>Employment Eligibility Verification Form</em> (I-9) you completed upon hire to data from the <em>U.S. Department of Homeland Security</em> and <em>Social Security Administration</em> records. This process will confirm your employment eligibility and comply with federal and state immigration laws.</p>\r\n',	2,	'E-Verify SC',	'E-VERIFY',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"SC\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 08:01:46',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	20,	0),
(325,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with any other authorized breaks, whether paid or unpaid, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding RI under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 08:09:44',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	184,	1),
(326,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with any other authorized breaks, whether paid or unpaid, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding RI over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 08:10:32',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	183,	1),
(327,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty RI',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 08:13:29',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	359,	1),
(328,	'<p>You may be provided time off without pay to participate in your children&rsquo;s school activities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&ndash;&ndash;to qualify, you must have completed 12 months of continuous employment and have worked an average of at least 30 hours per week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave can be taken to attend school conferences or other school-related activities involving your biological, adoptive, or foster child or legal ward.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;you must give at least 24 hours advance notice of an anticipated need for leave. Reasonable efforts must be made to schedule the leave so as to avoid undue disruption of operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&ndash;&ndash;leave will be granted for up to 10 hours in a 12 month period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&ndash;&ndash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave. Applicable benefits will continue to be earned while on leave.</p>\r\n',	4,	'School Activities-RI over 50',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 08:15:15',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	252,	1),
(329,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">If you suffer from a non-work-related illness or injury, you may be entitled to State Disability Insurance (SDI). SDI provides low cost disability protection if an illness or injury not caused by the job prevents you from working. A small percentage of your wages, up to the prevailing maximum, is deducted each pay period to finance this mandatory insurance. To initiate a claim, contact the nearest State Disability office to request the necessary forms. During the waiting period before disability payments begin, you can use earned and unused sick leave. This will help to compensate for any lost wages during the waiting period.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'State Disability Insurance RI',	'STATE DISABILITY INSURANCE',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 08:16:12',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	284,	1),
(330,	'<p>You will be scheduled for a paid meal period of at least 20 minutes within a 6 hour work shift, and an unpaid 30 minute meal period with an 8 hour work shift. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. Exceptions to this policy may be made if we employ less than 3 people on any shift at the worksite.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period-RI',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 08:16:59',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	305,	1),
(331,	'<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">If you report for work at the beginning of a work shift and are not given 3 hours of work to perform, or are sent home before performing any work, you will be paid a minimum of 3 hours of pay at your regular rate.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">This policy does not apply if you voluntarily report late or voluntarily leave before completing 3 hours of work. In that case, we will only pay you for actual hours of work. The reason for not working a minimum of 3 hours will be noted on your time records to ensure accurate records and compliance with the law.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Pay for time not worked is excluded when computing overtime.</span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Reporting Time Pay RI',	'REPORTING TIME PAY',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 08:18:48',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	6,	0),
(332,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">The Temporary Caregiver Insurance program provides wage replacement benefits to workers who take time off work to bond with a new child, or to care for a seriously ill child, spouse, domestic partner, parent, parent-in-law, or grandparent.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif; line-height:1.6\">The Temporary Caregiver Insurance program is part of the State Disability Insurance program and is administered by the State of Rhode Island.&nbsp; For more information or to request benefits, please contact the appropriate state office.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif; line-height:1.6\">Under the Temporary Caregiver Insurance program, you may be eligible for up to 4 weeks of wage replacement benefits within a specified benefit year. Wage replacement benefits may be subject to a waiting period. During the waiting period, you may use any paid time off benefit available, if applicable. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif; line-height:1.6\">Time off taken under the Temporary Caregiver Insurance program will run concurrently with other family and medical leave programs, if applicable. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif; line-height:1.6\">You must notify us, in writing, a minimum of 30 days prior to commencement of any time off taken under this program. If you fail to provide written intent within the specified time, it may result in a delay or reduction in benefits. Some exceptions may be provided in the event the time off is unforeseeable or the date of the time off changes for unforeseeable circumstances. </span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif; line-height:1.6\">Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the time off period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before time off began. Therefore, if you pay a portion of the premium, you are responsible for your share during the time off.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\">You will be restored to your position held prior to the time off or to one that is equivalent in terms of seniority, status, employment benefits, pay, and other terms and conditions of employment.</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Temp Caregiver Insurance RI',	'TEMPORARY CAREGIVER INSURANCE',	'none',	'2015-12-16 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2015-12-17 08:20:21',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	287,	0),
(339,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Diagnosis, care, or treatment of an existing health condition of, or preventive care for, you or your family member</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">To manage situations involved with being a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">For purposes of this policy, &ldquo;family member&rdquo; means:&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Child -&nbsp; a biological, foster, adopted, stepchild, legal ward, a child of a domestic partner, or a child of whom you stand in loco parentis</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Parent - means a biological, foster, adoptive, stepparent, or a legal guardian of you or your spouse or registered domestic partner, or a person who stood in loco parentis when you were a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Spouse, or registered domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Grandparent</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Grandchild</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Sibling</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all employees who work for us at least 30 <span style=\"border:none\">calendar <span style=\"border:none\">days within a y<span style=\"border:none\">ear. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">1 hour of paid leave is <span style=\"border:none\">accrued<span style=\"border:none\"> for every 30 hours worked<span style=\"border:none\">, including overtime,<span style=\"border:none\"> up to a maximum of 6 days* per year</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">*A day is defined as the equivalent of your normal work schedule at no less than 8 hours. For example, if you wo<span style=\"border:none\">rk 8.5 hours per day, 6 days of sick leave equals 51 hours. If you work 7 hours per day, 6 days of sick leave equals 48 hours. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until the 90</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><sup style=\"âvertical-align:\" top=\"\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">th</span></span></sup></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> calendar day following commencement of your<span style=\"border:none\"> employment. After you have completed the initial 90 days of employment, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave may be used in hourly increments, unless our payroll program will allow for smaller amounts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You may not use, in 1 year, m<span style=\"border:none\">ore than 3 days of sick leave.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;any accrued and unused sick will be carried over into the next 12 month cycle up to the 6 day cap. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends, for any reason, and you are rehired within a year of the date of separation, you<span style=\"border:none\">r previously unused accrued sick leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using sick leave provided you worked at least 90 days previously. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;when the use of paid sick leave is foreseeable<span style=\"border:none\">, you shall provide reasonable advance notice of the need to take sick leave. When it is not foreseeable, you shall provide us notice as soon as practicable. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">for the day or week.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">so we can be <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">sure to pay you on the next regularly scheduled payday after your sick leave was taken.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not accrued while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave CA Accrual',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-10-02 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-04 17:49:50',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	14,	1),
(340,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">P<span style=\"border:none\">aid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Diagnosis, care, or treatment of an existing health condition of, or preventive care for, you or your family member</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To manage situations involved with being a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:42.0pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<pre style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">\r\n<span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For purposes of this policy, &ldquo;family member&rdquo; means:&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></pre>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Child -&nbsp; a biological, foster, adopted, stepchild, legal ward, a child of a domestic partner, or a child of whom you stand in loco parentis</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Parent - means a biological, foster, adoptive, stepparent, or a legal guardian of you or your spouse or registered domestic partner, or a person who stood in loco parentis when you were a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Spouse, or registered domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Grandparent</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Grandchild</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span lang=\"X-NONE\" style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Sibling</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash; paid sick leave is provided to all employees who work for us at least <span style=\"border:none\">30 calendar days within a year<span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">3 days* of paid leave is provided at the beginning of each year. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"border:none\">I<span style=\"border:none\">f your employment ends, for any reason, and you are rehired within a year of the date of separation, </span></span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">you will be provided with 3 days* of sick leave upon rehire and each subsequent year thereafter.<span style=\"border:none\"> There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using <span style=\"border:none\">sick leave provided you worked at least 90 days previously.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">*A day is defined as the equivalent of your normal work schedule at no less than 8 hours. For example, if you work 8.5 hours per day, 3 days of sick leave equals 25.50 hours. If you work 7 hours <span style=\"border:none\">per day, 3 days of sick leave equals 24 hours. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you are not eligible to use your sick leave until the 90</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><sup style=\"âvertical-align:\" top=\"\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">th</span></span></sup></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> calendar day following commencement of your employment. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave may be used in hourly increments, unless our payroll program w<span style=\"border:none\">ill allow for smaller amounts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;unused sick leave is forfeited at the end of the 12 month cycle upon which a new set of 3 days is provided to you. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;when the use of paid sick leave is foreseeable, you shall provide reas<span style=\"border:none\">onable advance notice of the need to take sick leave. When it is not foreseeable, you shall provide us notice as soon as practicable. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the day or week.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance r</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">ecord so we can be <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">sure to pay you on the next regularly scheduled payday after your sick leave was taken.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if yo<span style=\"border:none\">u are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;earned and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave CA Lump Sum',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-08-04 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-04 17:50:49',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'disabled',	15,	0),
(343,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We comply with federal and state and local laws providing for nondiscrimination in employment against qualified individuals with disabilities as they may be applicable. We will provide reasonable accommodation for such individuals in accordance with these laws. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">It is our policy to: </span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Ensure that qualified individuals with disabilities are treated in a nondiscriminatory manner during the pre-employment process and in all conditions of employment if hired</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Administer medical examinations (a) to applicants only after conditional offers of employment have been extended, and (b) to employees only when justified by business necessity, such as for a second medical opinion or a fitness-for-duty exam, or as part of a voluntary annual physical examination program</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Keep all medical-related information confidential in accordance with the requirements of the ADA and retain such information in separate confidential files</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notify individuals with disabilities that we provide reasonable accommodation to qualified individuals with disabilities, by including this policy in the Employee Policy Manual and by posting the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission&#39;s poster on not discriminating against individuals with disabilities and other protected groups conspicuously throughout our facilities&nbsp; </span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><b style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Procedure for Requesting an Accommodation:&nbsp; </span></b><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt;\">Qualified individuals with disabilities must make requests for reasonable accommodation. We will then meet with the individual to interactively identify the precise limitations resulting from the disability and the potential accommodation we might be able to make.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\">It is important to consider the nature and cost of the accommodation, our overall financial resources, the effect on the other employees&rsquo; ability to perform their duties, and the overall impact on the business.</span></p>\r\n',	2,	'Disability Accommodation',	'ACCOMMODATION OF INDIVIDUALS WITH DISABILITIES',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-22 22:14:34',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	2,	0),
(344,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">The&nbsp;evaluation of your job performance is an ongoing process. Throughout your employment with us, we will evaluate your progress and address areas for improvement. If needed, we will plan for further training. As&nbsp;part of our performance management&nbsp;system, we may&nbsp;establish and commit to&nbsp;goals, for all employees or just you. The frequency of&nbsp;feedback on your overall performance&nbsp;may vary depending upon&nbsp;your&nbsp;length of service, job position, past&nbsp;performance, changes in job duties,&nbsp;and/or recurring performance problems.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Wage adjustments are discretionary,&nbsp;largely&nbsp;dependent upon&nbsp;our profitability,&nbsp;and&nbsp;based on&nbsp;your performance, increased skills, and individual contributions to&nbsp;our success.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	2,	'Performance Management',	'EMPLOYEE PERFORMANCE MANAGEMENT',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-22 22:26:45',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	12,	0),
(345,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You may b<span style=\"border:none\">e <span style=\"border:none\">asked<span style=\"border:none\"> to be available on an on-call basis during your non-work hours due to potential unique staffing needs including, but not limited to, emergencies. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Though you are <span style=\"border:none\">on-call, you will be able to use your free time effectively&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">for your own purposes except<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">for <span style=\"border:none\">when y<span style=\"border:none\">ou <span style=\"border:none\">must<span style=\"border:none\"> respond to calls if/when they come in<span style=\"border:none\">. In doing so, you must <span style=\"border:none\">manage them appropriately<span style=\"border:none\"> and professionally at all times<span style=\"border:none\">, regardless of when or where you are taking the calls<span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You will be paid for all calls that you manage, as well as<span style=\"border:none\"> any other work duties you perform as a result of the calls. The compensation provided may be at a different rate than your normal wage, and you will be notified in advance of any rate change in effect. Your work time while on call will count towards your <span style=\"border:none\">total working hours for the day/week and will be used to calculate overtime, if applicable. Please track the time you spend performing work duties related to taking calls so that we may pay you accordingly.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you find that <span style=\"border:none\">being on call is impeding on y<span style=\"border:none\">our free time<span style=\"border:none\"> <span style=\"border:none\">in some way, <span style=\"border:none\">please let us know so that we may correct our procedures.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'On-Call Hours',	'ON-CALL HOURS',	'none',	'2017-08-22 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-22 23:23:19',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	10,	0),
(346,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">It is in our best interest to grant Paid Time Off (PTO) to you for the purpose of rest and relaxation away from the demands of the job. Our intent is to provide adequate PTO hours to cover all of your time off needs, regardless of the reason. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">PTO is paid at your regular rate of pay as outlined in the benefit table below:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">PTO&nbsp;benefit for regular full-time employees:&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table class=\"Table\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:170.5pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"227\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After 1 year of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:2.05in; border-left:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"197\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ PTO hours accrued</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:170.5pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"227\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After 2 years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:2.05in; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"197\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ PTO hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:170.5pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"227\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After _____ years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:2.05in; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"197\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ PTO hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:170.5pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"227\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After _____ years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:2.05in; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"197\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ PTO hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"Arial11Boldcentered\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">PTO&nbsp;benefit for regular part-time employees:&nbsp; </span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table class=\"Table\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:170.5pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"227\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After 1 year of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:2.05in; border-left:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"197\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ PTO hours accrued</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:170.5pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"227\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After 2 years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:2.05in; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"197\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ PTO hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:170.5pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"227\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After _____ years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:2.05in; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"197\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ PTO hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:170.5pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"227\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After _____ years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:2.05in; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"197\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ PTO hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text3\" style=\"margin-right:.05in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">*Continuous service is broken if employment has been terminated or otherwise interrupted for a period of 30 days. Exceptions may be made at our discretion.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text3\" style=\"margin-right:.05in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"text3\" style=\"margin-right:.05in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><strong>Accruing PTO Benefits</strong>&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">PTO benefits are accrued monthly on a prorated basis.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><strong>Using Accrued PTO</strong>&mdash;while PTO is accrued monthly, <span style=\"color:black\">you are not eligible to use accrued PTO until after 12 months of continuous employment. You are required to use your PTO benefit within the year after which it has been accrued. Unused PTO will be paid out at the end of your anniversary year unless carried over with special permission. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><strong>PTO Approval</strong>&mdash;PTO requests must be submitted and approved in advance to ensure staffing needs are met. Therefore, p<span style=\"color:black\">lease submit your PTO request at least 4 weeks in advance. </span>Conflicting requests will be decided in favor of the person with the most seniority in that position. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><strong>Unexpected Absence</strong>&mdash;if a sudden illness or personal issue makes it impossible for you to request PTO in advance, you <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">must notify us of your absence no later than 1 hour before&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">the start of the workday</span></span></span></span>. <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">If circumstances are such that you cannot personally notify us, please have a relative or other responsible individual handle that for you within the required timeframe.&nbsp;Failure to follow this procedure will void the claim for <span style=\"border:none\">PTO and can be grounds for disciplinary action up to and including termination</span></span></span></span>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">During an absence because of illness, you are to notify us daily of progress unless otherwise agreed upon. </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Please give us advance notice of your return to work after an absence for an illness so that we can manage the schedule and staff accordingly</span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Physician&rsquo;s Statement</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;at our discretion, you may be required to bring a healthcare practitioner&rsquo;s certificate verifying your ability to return to work if you have been absent for a<span style=\"border:none\">n illness or injury</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><strong>Attendance Record</strong>&mdash;<span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">please be sure to include any PTO taken on your attendance record&nbsp;</span></span></span>so we can <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">pay you appropriately</span></span></span>.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employees Returning from Military Service</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you will be credited for seniority that would have been earned during such military service as if you had been continuously employed, but will not accrue PTO during the military leave.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;PTO is not included as hours worked when computing overtime hours for the week.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><strong>Leave of Absence</strong>&mdash;<span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">if you are unable to return to work d<span style=\"border:none\">ue to an illness within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Please review our </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Leave of Absence</span></span></i></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"> policy for more information.</span></span></span> No PTO is accrued while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><strong>Job Abandonment</strong>&mdash;if you fail to return from PTO on the scheduled date, the failure to return will be considered job abandonment and treated as a voluntary termination.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Pay of PTO Upon Termination</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;any accrued and unused PTO will be paid based on your regular hourly rate at the time of separation.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'PTO - CA IL MA',	'PAID TIME OFF',	'none',	'2018-08-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\",\"IL\",\"MA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-23 17:10:19',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	36,	1),
(347,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">It is in our best interest to grant vacation to you for the purpose of rest and relaxation away from the demands of the job. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Vacation time is paid at your regular rate of pay as outlined in the benefit table below:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Vacation benefit for regular full-time employees: </span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table class=\"Table\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:161.75pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"216\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After 1 year of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:156.35pt; border-left:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"208\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ vacation hours accrued</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:161.75pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"216\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After 2 years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:156.35pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"208\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ vacation hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:161.75pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"216\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After _____ years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:156.35pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"208\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ vacation hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:161.75pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"216\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After _____ years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:156.35pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"208\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ vacation hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"Arial11Boldcentered\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Vacation benefit for regular part-time employees: </span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table class=\"Table\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:solid windowtext 1.0pt\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:161.75pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"216\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After 1 year of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:156.35pt; border-left:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"208\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ vacation hours accrued </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:161.75pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"216\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After 2 years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:156.35pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"208\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ vacation hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:161.75pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"216\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After _____ years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:156.35pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"208\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ vacation hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:161.75pt; border-top:none; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"216\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">After _____ years of continuous service*</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt; width:156.35pt; border-top:none; border-left:none; border-right:solid windowtext 1.0pt; padding:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt\" valign=\"top\" width=\"208\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">_____ vacation hours accrued per year </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">* Continuous service is broken if employment has been terminated or otherwise interrupted for a period of 30 days. Exceptions may be made at our discretion.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Accruing Vacation Benefits</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">vacation benefits are accrued monthly on a prorated basis. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Using Accrued Vacation</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;while vacation benefits are accrued monthly, you are not eligible to use accrued vacation until after 12 months of continuous employment. You are required to use your vacation benefit within the year after which it has been accrued. Unused vacation will be paid out at the end of your anniversary year unless carried over with special permission. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Vacation Approval</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;vacation requests must be submitted and approved in advance to assure that staffing needs are met. Therefore, please submit your vacation request at least 4 weeks in advance. Conflicting requests will be decided in favor of the person with the most seniority in that position.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Employees Returning from Military Service</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you will be credited for seniority that would have been earned during such military service as if you had been continuously employed but will not accrue vacation during military leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Overtime</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;paid vacation time is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;n</span>o vacation benefit is accrued while on a leave of absence<span style=\"color:black\">. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Job Abandonment</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;if you fail to return from vacation on the scheduled date, the failure to return will be considered job abandonment and treated as a voluntary termination.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Vacation Pay Upon Termination</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;any accrued and unused vacation time will be paid based </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">on your regular hourly rate<span style=\"color:black\"> at the time of separation.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Vacation Benefits - CA IL MA',	'Vacation Benefits',	'none',	'2018-08-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\",\"IL\",\"MA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-24 17:39:43',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	38,	1),
(348,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>It is our policy to provide <span>a work environment that is free from any form of harassment or discrimination. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The law specifically provides protection from harassment or discrimination in employment because of:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Age (40 and over)</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Ancestry</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Color</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Religious Creed (including religious dress and grooming practices)</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Denial of Family and Medical Care Leave</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Disability (mental and physical) including HIV and AIDS</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Marital Status</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical Condition (cancer and genetic characteristics)</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Genetic Information</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Military and Veteran Status&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:1vpt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">National Origin (including language use restrictions)</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Race</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Sex (which includes pregnancy, childbirth, breastfeeding&nbsp;and medical conditions related to pregnancy, childbirth or breastfeeding)</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Gender, Gender Identity, and Gender Expression&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Sexual Orientation</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span>Supervisors, managers, co-workers, third parties, volunteers, unpaid interns, individuals in apprenticeship training programs, and independent contractors are all prohibited from harassing or discriminating others in the workplace at all times.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">Harassment can take many forms: written, verbal and non-verbal, and can occur with any type of medium: phone, email, texting, social networking, etc. In all cases, jokes, name calling, harassment or discrimination is prohibited at all times. </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>Sexual harassment includes but is n<span>ot limited to: verbal, physical, or visual behavior of a sexual nature; graphic or suggestive comments about an individual&#39;s dress or body, or actual or perceived sexual orientation; making unwanted sexual advances and requests for sexual favors.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Any incident of harassment or discrimination, including threats, intimidation, and assault, must be reported immediately to your direct supervisor, or </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">any other company supervisor/manager, <span>or you may contact the Department of Fair Employment and Housing. Though it&rsquo;s not required, we ask that you submit this information in writing; you may use the <em>Report of Harassment or Discrimination Form</em>. Verbal or written complaints </span><span><span><span>should state the time, place, type of harassment or discrimination, person or persons involved, a<span>nd the name of any possible witnesses. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Supervisors and managers must report employee complaints to their </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">direct supervisor, </span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">or </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">any other company supervisor/manager,<span><span><span> immediately upon receipt of a complaint that is made either verbally or in writing.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Once<span> a complaint or allegation is received, a </span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>fair, impartial, timely, and thorough investigation</span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span> will be conducted as discreetly as possible. Confidentiality will be maintained to the degree feasible given the need to investigate and act upon allegations made<span>. Only those with a need to know about such a complaint will be advised of its existence. However, the investigation itself may not remain completely confidential. This investigation will be documented and tracked for progress and will receive a timely closure<span>. Reasonable conclusions will be reached based on the evidence collected. If you are dissatisfied with the resolution of the investigation, you should file a written appeal.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Any person who has been found in violation of this policy shall be subject to appropriate disciplinary action including letters of reprimand, suspension, demotion, termination, and the possibility of civil liability. It is your responsibility to conscientiously follow this policy.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>You will not be subject to any form of retaliation<span> or discipline for pursuing a harassment or discrimination complaint or for participating in a harassment or discrimination investigation.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	6,	'Harassment & Discrimination - CA',	'ANTI-HARASSMENT AND DISCRIMINATION',	'none',	'2017-08-24 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-24 21:27:52',	'2020-02-12 17:57:17',	'enabled',	2,	0),
(349,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Once you have earned sick leave, you may use your personal sick leave benefit provided by us for absences due to an illness, injury, or medical appointment of your child, spouse, parent, grandchild, grandparent, or any dependents as shown on your most recent tax return, for reasonable periods of time as your attendance may be necessary, on the same terms upon which you are able to use sick leave benefits for your own illness, injury, or medical appointment. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Use of available sick leave due to an illness, injury, or medical appointment of your child, spouse, parent, grandchild, grandparent, or any dependents as shown on your most recent tax return is limited to five days per calendar year.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you must work at least 30 hours per week.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Definitions</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;for purposes of this policy, sick leave benefit means time away from work by an employee, due to his or her own incapacity, illness, or injury, for which the employee receives compensation.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave Act - GA',	'SICK LEAVE ACT',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"GA\"]',	25,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-29 20:31:17',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	39,	1),
(350,	'<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Pregnancy leave is provided to you when you are temporarily unable to work due to a disability caused by pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">With a written request from your healthcare provider that you be transferred to a less strenuous or hazardous position, we will do our best to accommodate you. If accommodation is not possible, and you are not able to continue your normal job responsibilities, you may be asked to go on pregnancy leave.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please use the <i>Leave Of Absence Application Form</i> for this purpose.<i> </i></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Healthcare Professional&rsquo;s Certification</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;any request for a pregnancy-related leave must be accompanied with a certified healthcare professional&rsquo;s certificate. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;as determined by your physician, a reasonable leave of absence will be granted based on your physical condition and job requirements. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reporting on Progress</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you are required to report directly to the employer every 30 days on your health status and your intent to return to work.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may use any earned paid time off to run concurrent with the pregnancy leave. Benefits are not earned during the leave. Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during pregnancy leave. When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual). </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Pregnancy Leave of Absence Ends When</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You are released for full or partial duty. You must provide a physician&rsquo;s statement in writing indicating your fitness to return to work</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We receive satisfactory medical evidence that you are unable to return to work</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You directly or indirectly inform us (for example, by accepting employment elsewhere, moving out of state, etc.) that you do not intend to return to work</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You have been on a medical leave of absence for the approved time </span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Returning from Pregnancy Leave</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you must provide a completed <i>Medical Release to Work</i> <i>Form</i>, or an equivalent note from your healthcare provider, verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. This must be received on or before the date you are scheduled to return from leave.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You will be reinstated to your former position or a position of comparable status and pay, without loss of accumulated service credits and privileges, unless business necessity makes this impossible or unreasonable.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Leave - MT',	'PREGNANCY LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-29 20:41:15',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	101,	1),
(351,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere</span><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding - OK over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OK\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-29 20:45:06',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	178,	1),
(352,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding - OK under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OK\"]',	0,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-29 20:46:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	177,	1),
(353,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty, unless you decide to use any eligible paid leave for the time off.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty - OK',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OK\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-29 20:48:45',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	356,	1),
(354,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you have 3 or more consecutive non-work hours available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day, you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 3 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior oral or written request by you, provide 2 hours of paid time off to vote. If 2 hours are insufficient due to length of travel to and from the polling place, sufficient paid time off for travel time will be granted. You must furnish proof that you have voted.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We may specify when the time off will be taken. At our discretion, your schedule may be changed such that 3 consecutive non-work hours are provided after polls open and before work begins or 3 consecutive non-work hours are provided after work ends and before polls close. Voting time that is paid is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting - OK',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OK\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-29 20:50:24',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	395,	1),
(355,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty - PA',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"PA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-29 21:02:03',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	358,	1),
(356,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding - PA over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"PA\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-29 21:03:38',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	182,	1),
(357,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding - PA under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-29 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"PA\"]',	0,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-29 21:06:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	181,	1),
(358,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding - NE under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NE\"]',	0,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 15:49:09',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	164,	1),
(359,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding - NE over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NE\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 15:50:12',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	163,	1),
(360,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. You will be paid your regular wages, less the amount paid by the court, while on jury duty. Please submit a copy of the compensation received from the jury service for our payroll records. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty - NE ',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NE\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 15:52:03',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	348,	1),
(361,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available after polls open or before polls close on Election Day, you are not entitled to time off to vote. If you do not have 2 or more consecutive non-work hours available, we will, upon prior written request by you before Election Day, provide paid time off to vote. Time off will be added to the shift, at our discretion, such that when all time off is added together it totals 2 consecutive hours during the hours the polls are open. Wages, which would otherwise have been earned, will be paid. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting - NE',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NE\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 15:53:07',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	391,	1),
(362,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Military family leave<b> </b></span>can be requested by you when you are the spouse or parent of a person called to military service lasting 179 days or longer with the State or United States pursuant to the orders of the Governor or the President of the United States. If you are in this situation, you <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">may be provided a leave of absence as outlined below:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Length of Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">up to 15 days of military family leave during the time federal or state deployment orders are in effect.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Qualified Employee</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be qualified for leave if all of the following are satisfied:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You have been employed for at least 12 months</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You have worked at least 1,250 hours during the 12 month period immediately preceding the commencement of the leave</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Notification</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;if the leave consists of 5 or more consecutive days, you must give at least 14 days notice of the intended date upon which the leave will begin.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;we may require certification from the proper military authority to verify your eligibility for leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Salary and Benefits</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;leave is unpaid.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You will be able to continue applicable benefits (such as health insurance) at your own expense for the duration of the leave.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Reinstatement Rights</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you will be reinstated to your position held prior to taking leave, or to a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment unless a comparable position no longer exists due to business necessity.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Leave - NE 15 - 49',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE ',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NE\"]',	15,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 15:55:40',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	234,	1),
(363,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Military family leave<b> </b></span>can be requested by you when you are the spouse or parent of a person called to military service lasting 179 days or longer with the State or United States pursuant to the orders of the Governor or the President of the United States. If you are in this situation, you <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">may be provided a leave of absence as outlined below<span style=\"border:none\">:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Length of Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">up to 30 days of military family leave during the time federal or state deployment orders are in effect.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Qualified Employee</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be qualified for leave if all of the following are satisfied:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You have been employed for at least 12 months</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You have &nbsp;worked at least 1,250 hours during the 12 month period immediately preceding the commencement of the leave</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Notification</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;if the leave consists of 5 or more consecutive days, you must give at least 14 days notice of the intended date upon which the leave will begin.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;we may require certification from the proper military authority to verify your eligibility for leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Salary and Benefits</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;leave is unpaid.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You will be able to continue applicable benefits (such as health insurance) at your own expense for the duration of the leave.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Reinstatement Rights</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you will be reinstated to your position held prior to taking leave, or to a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment unless a comparable position no longer exists due to business necessity.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Leave - NE over 50',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE ',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NE\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 15:58:10',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	235,	1),
(364,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with any other authorized breaks, whether paid or unpaid, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding - NM over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NM\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 16:34:55',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	170,	1),
(365,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us and shall run concurrently with any other authorized breaks, whether paid or unpaid, when applicable. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding - NM under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NM\"]',	0,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 16:36:03',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	169,	1),
(366,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty - NM',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NM\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 16:37:48',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	351,	1),
(367,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you have 2 consecutive hours after the polls open and before your shift is scheduled to begin and/or 3 consecutive hours after work before the polls close, you are expected to use those hours to vote. If that is not possible, we will, upon prior request by you, provide up to 2 hours of paid time off to vote. We may specify when the time off will be taken. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting - NM',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NM\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 16:40:09',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	392,	1),
(368,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are a victim of domestic violence, or have a minor child who is a victim of domestic violence, you will be provided with up to 14 days of leave in any calendar year. The leave can be taken intermittently for up to 8 hours in 1 day so that you can:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Obtain or attempt to obtain an order for protection or other judicial relief from domestic violence</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Meet with law enforcement officials, or consult with attorneys or the district attorney&rsquo;s victim advocates</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Attend court proceedings related to domestic violence of you or your minor child </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Leave will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take leave under this policy, you must give us reasonable advance notice, unless advance notice is not feasible. When the need for leave is unforeseeable, you must provide notice to us within 24 hours of commencing leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You may be required to verify that you or your minor child is a victim of domestic violence and the leave is for one of the purposes outlined above. If required, verification must be provided in a timely manner. You can provide verification through one or more of the following:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">A police report indicating that you or your minor child was a victim of domestic violence&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">A copy of an order of protection or other court evidence produced in connection with an incident of domestic violence </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">A written statement from an attorney representing you, a district attorney&rsquo;s victim advocate, a law enforcement official or a prosecuting attorney that you or your minor child appeared or is scheduled to appear in court in connection with an incident of domestic violence </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to in writing by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence - NM',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2017-08-30 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NM\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-08-30 16:46:15',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	276,	1),
(369,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is intended<span style=\"border:none\"> to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Your own mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; your own need for medical diagnosis, care, or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; your own need for preventive medical care;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Care of a family member with a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; care of a family member who needs medical diagnosis, care, or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; care of a family member who needs preventive medical care;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Closure of our place of business by order of a public official due to a public health emergency or your need to care for a child whose school or place of care has been closed by order of a public official due to a public health emergency, or care for oneself or a family member when it has been determined by the health authorities having jurisdiction or by a health care provider that you or your family member&#39;s presence in the community may jeopardize the health of others because of exposure to a communicable disease, whether or not you or your family member has actually contracted the communicable disease; or</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Absence necessary due to domestic violence, sexual violence, abuse or stalking, provided the leave is to allow you or your family member to obtain:</span></span></span></span>\r\n	<ol style=\"list-style-type:lower-alpha\">\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Medical attention needed to recover from physical or psychological injury or disability caused by domestic violence, sexual violence, abuse or stalking;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Services from a domestic violence or sexual violence program or victim services organization;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Psychological or other counseling;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Relocation or taking steps to secure an existing home due to the domestic violence, sexual violence, abuse or stalking; or</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Legal services, including but not limited to preparing for or participating in any civil or criminal legal proceeding related to or resulting from the domestic violence, sexual violence, abuse or stalking.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:42.0pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">For purposes of this policy, the term family member includes: </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A spouse</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A domestic partner</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">An employee&#39;s or a spouse&rsquo;s/domestic partner&#39;s biological, adopted, or foster child; stepchild or legal ward, a child to whom the employee stands <i>in loco parentis</i>, or an individual to whom the employee stood <i>in loco parentis</i> when the individual was a minor</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">An employee&rsquo;s or a spouse&rsquo;s/domestic partner&rsquo;s biological, foster, stepparent, or adoptive parent or legal guardian, or a person who stood <i>in loco parentis</i> when the employee or employee&rsquo;s spouse/domestic partner was a minor child</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">An employee&#39;s or a spouse&rsquo;s/domestic partner&#39;s biological, foster, adoptive, or step grandparent, grandchild, or sibling</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Any other individual related by blood or affinity whose close association with the employee is the equivalent of a family relationship</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all employees. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">1 hour of paid leave is </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">accrued</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> for every 30 hours worked up to a maximum of </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">24</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours per year. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;in 1 year, you may not use more than </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">24</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours<span style=\"border:none\"> of sick leave. You are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until the </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">90</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><sup><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">th</span></span></sup></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial 90 days of employment, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leav<span style=\"border:none\">e may be used in hourly increments, unless our payroll program will allow for smaller amounts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;up to </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">24</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours of accrued and unused sick leave during a 12 month period will be carried over into the next year. Sick time is capped at </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">24</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> h<span style=\"border:none\">ours per year.</span></span></span></span> &nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends, for any reason, and you are rehired within 9 months of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued sick leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using sick<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;leave provided you worked at least 90 days previously.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;when the use of paid sick leave is foreseeable, you shall</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> make a good faith effort to provide notice of the need for such time to us in advance. You shall make a reasonable effort&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">to schedule the use of earned paid sick time in a manner that does not unduly disrupt our operations. When the need for sick leave is not foreseeable, please follow our procedures for notification of unexpected time off (see the </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Attendance &amp; Punctuality</span></span></i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> <span style=\"border:none\">policy earlier in this manual for specific call-in procedures). </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave for more than 3 consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting the need for leave from your treating&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">physician. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">so we can be <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">sure to pay you appropriately.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;noti<span style=\"border:none\">ce of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave AZ Accrual under 14',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-10-02 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"AZ\"]',	1,	14,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 21:05:28',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	13,	1),
(370,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost <span style=\"border:none\">due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Your own mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; your own need for medical diagnosis, care, or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; your own need for preventive medical care;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Care of a family member with a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; care of a family member who needs medical diagnosis, care, or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; care of a family member who needs preventive medical care;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Closure of our place of business by order of a public official due to a public health emergency or your need to care for a child whose school or place of care has been closed by order of a public official due to a public health emergency, or care for oneself or a family member when it has been determined by the health authorities having jurisdiction or by a health care provider that you or your family member&#39;s presence in the community may jeopardize the health of others because of exposure to a communicable disease, whether or not you or your family member has actually contracted the communicable disease; or</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Absence necessary due to domestic violence, sexual violence, abuse or stalking, provided the leave is to allow you or your family member to obtain:</span></span></span></span>\r\n	<ol style=\"list-style-type:lower-alpha\">\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Medical attention needed to recover from physical or psychological injury or disability caused by domestic violence, sexual violence, abuse or stalking;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Services from a domestic violence or sexual violence program or victim services organization;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Psychological or other counseling;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Relocation or taking steps to secure an existing home due to the domestic violence, sexual violence, abuse or stalking; or</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Legal services, including but not limited to preparing for or participating in any civil or criminal legal proceeding related to or resulting from the domestic violence, sexual violence, abuse or stalking.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:42.0pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">For purposes of this policy, the term family member includes: </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A spouse</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A domestic partner</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">An employee&#39;s or a spouse&rsquo;s/domestic partner&#39;s biological, adopted, or foster child; stepchild or legal ward, a child to whom the employee stands <i>in loco parentis</i>, or an individual to whom the employee stood <i>in loco parentis</i> when the individual was a minor</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">An employee&rsquo;s or a spouse&rsquo;s/domestic partner&rsquo;s biological, foster, stepparent, or adoptive parent or legal guardian, or a person who stood <i>in loco parentis</i> when the employee or employee&rsquo;s spouse/domestic partner was a minor child</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">An employee&#39;s or a spouse&rsquo;s/domestic partner&#39;s biological, foster, adoptive, or step grandparent, grandchild, or sibling</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Any other individual related by blood or affinity whose close association with the employee is the equivalent of a family relationship</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all employees<span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">1 hour of paid leave is </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">accrued</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> for every 30 hours worked up to a maximum of </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">40</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours per year. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;in 1 year, you may not use more than </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">40</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours of sick leave. You are not eligible to use your accrued sick lea<span style=\"border:none\">ve until the </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">90</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><sup><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">th</span></span></sup></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial 90 days of employment, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave may be used in hourly increments, unless our payroll program wi<span style=\"border:none\">ll allow for smaller amounts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;up to </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">40</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours of accrued and unused sick leave during a 12 month period will be carried over into the next year. Sick time is capped at </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">40</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours per year.</span></span></span> &nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends, for any reason, and yo<span style=\"border:none\">u are rehired within 9 months of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued sick leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using sick leave provided you worked at least 90 days previously.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;when the use of paid sick leave is foreseeable, you shall</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> make a good faith effort to provide notice of the need for such time to us in advance. You shall make a reasonable effort to schedule the use of earned paid sick time in a manner that does&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">not unduly disrupt our operations. When the need for sick leave is not foreseeable, please follow our procedures for notification of unexpected time off (see the </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Attendance &amp; Punctuality</span></span></i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> policy earlier in this manual for specific call-in procedures). </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave for more than 3 consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting the need for leave from your treating physician. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is n<span style=\"border:none\">ot included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">so we can be <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">sure to pay you appropriately.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave AZ Accrual over 14',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-10-02 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"AZ\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 21:06:56',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	12,	1),
(371,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth<span style=\"border:none\">, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability CO',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CO\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 21:21:54',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	76,	1),
(372,	'<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:.5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Pregnancy leave is provided to you when you are temporarily unable to work due to a disability caused by pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">With a written request</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> from your healthcare provider that you be transferred to a less strenuous or hazardous position, we will do our best to accommodate you. If accommodation is not possible, and you are not able to continue your normal job responsibilities, you may be asked to go on pregnancy leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please use the <i>Leave Of Absence Application Form</i> for this purpose.<i> </i></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Healthcare Professional&rsquo;s</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;any request for a pregnancy-related leave must be accompanied with a certified healthcare professional&rsquo;s certificate. &nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash; as determined by your physician, a reasonable leave of absence will be granted based on your individual capacities and medical condition. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reporting on Progress</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you are required to report directly to us every 30 days on your health status and your intent to return to work.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may use any earned paid time off to run concurrent with the pregnancy leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see the continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual). </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Benefits are not earned during the leave. Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any earned paid time off used during pregnancy leave. When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Pregnancy Leave of Absence Ends When</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You are released for full or partial duty. You must provide a physician&rsquo;s statement in writing indicating your fitness to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We receive satisfactory medical evidence that you are unable to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You directly or indirectly inform us (for example, by accepting employment elsewhere, moving out of state, etc.) that you do not intend to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You have been on a leave of absence for the approved time</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Returning from Pregnancy Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you must provide a completed <i>Medical Release to Work</i> <i>Form</i>, or an equivalent note from your healthcare provider, verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. This must be received on or before the date you are scheduled to return from leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When you return from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position with equivalent pay and accumulated seniority, retirement, fringe benefits and other service credits, unless circumstances have changed so as to make it impossible or unreasonable to do so.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Leave CT',	'PREGNANCY LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CT\"]',	3,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 21:31:02',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	97,	1),
(373,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for 1 or more days for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Your own illness, injury,<span style=\"border:none\"> or health condition</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The medical diagnosis, care, or treatment of your mental or physical illness, injury, or health condition</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Preventative medical care for you</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Your child&rsquo;s or spouse&rsquo;s illness, injury, or health condition</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The medical diagnosis, care, or treatment<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;of your child&rsquo;s or spouse&rsquo;s mental or physical illness</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Preventative medical care for your child or spouse</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You need any of the following considerations related to being a victim of family violence or sexual assault:</span></span></span></span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Medical care or psychological or<span style=\"border:none\"> other counseling for physical or psychological injury or disability </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">To obtain services from a victim services organization</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">To relocate due to family violence or sexual assault</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">To participate in any civil or criminal proceedings related to or resulting fr<span style=\"border:none\">om family violence or sexual assault</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">For the purposes of this policy, the definition of an employee is: </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">An individual engaged as a &ldquo;service worker&rdquo; to the employer</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">For the purposes of this policy, the definition of a &ldquo;service worker&rdquo; is: </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">An employee primarily engaged in an occupation with one of the broad or detailed occupation code numbers and titles as defined by the federal Bureau of Labor Statistics Standard Occupational Classification system</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Includes, but is not limited to:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span>\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Dental Hygienists</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Dental Assistants</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Receptionists</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Secretaries and Administrative Assistants</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Insurance Claims Processing Clerks</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Office Clerks, general</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">For the purposes of this policy, the definition of a child is: </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A biological, adopted, or foster child</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A stepchild</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Legal ward of the employee</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A child for which the employee is standing in loco parentis</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Under eighteen years of age</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">Eighteen years of age or older and incapable of self-care because of a mental or physical disability</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">For the purposes of this policy, the definition of a spouse is: </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A husband or wife</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all service workers who have completed their 680 hour of employment.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Sick Leave Earned</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;1 hour of paid leave for every 40 hours worked in 1 hour increments up to a maximum of 40 hour<span style=\"border:none\">s per anniversary year. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you may not be entitled to use earned paid sick leave if you have not worked an average of 10 or more hours a week in the most recent complete anniversary quarter. Up to 40 hours of earned and unused sick leave m<span style=\"border:none\">ay be carried over into the next anniversary year. You may not use, in 1 year, more than the maximum hours allowed per year as described in the previous paragraph. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Make-up Time</span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours or<span style=\"border:none\"> shifts during the same or following pay period, in lieu of hours or shifts missed, and not use paid sick leave benefits. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if your need for paid sick leave is foreseeable, you must provide advance notice of the intention to use paid sick<span style=\"border:none\"> leave at least 7 days prior to the date the leave is to begin. If your need to take paid sick leave is not foreseeable, you must provide advance notice as soon as practicable. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave for 3 or more consecutive <span style=\"border:none\">days, you must bring in certification supporting the need for leave. Reasonable certification may include:&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">A signed document from a health care provider affirming the need for the specified number of days off</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">A court record or documentation signed by a representative&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">of a victim services organization, an attorney, a police officer or other counselor</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for the time<span style=\"border:none\"> out ill and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">so we can be</span></span> <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">sure to pay you for the day.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not <span style=\"border:none\">earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of an Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;after an illness, you need to give advance notice so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;earned and unused sick leave will not be paid at <span style=\"border:none\">the time of separation<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave CT over 50',	'PAID SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CT\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 21:36:02',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	17,	1),
(374,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, lactation or the need to express breast milk, or a related medical condition, you may be provided <span style=\"border:none\">with reasonable accommodation, upon request.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability CT',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 21:37:21',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	77,	1),
(375,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.25in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><em><b><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">NOTE: Applies to employers with 100 or more employees</span></span></b></em><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> <b><i>for each workday during each of 20 or more calendar weeks in the current or preceding calendar year</i></b></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You will be provided an unpaid family and medical leave as outlined below. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eligibility</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family and medical leave, you must have worked at least 6 consecutive months excluding any paid leave or authorized unpaid leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Reasons for Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you can take family and medical leave for the: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Birth or adoption of a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Serious health condition of your child, spouse, or parent</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A serious health condition is defined as a physical or mental condition that merits your care during the period of treatment or supervision by a health care provider and: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Requires inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential health care facility</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Involves continuing treatment by a health care provider</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The definitions of parent and child include biological, foster, step, and adoptive relationships, along with legal guardians or wards. A parent also can be a grandparent, parent-in-law, or grandparent-in-law. A child can be any age, not just a minor.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;when the need for family and medical leave is foreseeable, you must give at least 30 days advance, written notice of the expected birth, adoption, or serious medical condition. When it is not possible or practicable to give as much as 30 days notice, you must at least give verbal notice to us within 2 working days before family leave will be taken, and written notice to follow as soon as practicable. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need for leave due to a serious health condition of your own or the serious health condition of a covered family member. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For situations where the serious health condition is chronic and continuous, and you foresee the need for family leave in another 12 month period, you need to provide certification by the health care provider for each 12 month period of family leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">At our expense, you may be required to provide re-certification during the course of any 12 month period, but not more often than 30 days, if: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Circumstances described by the previous certification have changed significantly, e.g., the duration of the illness, the nature of the illness, and complications</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We received information that casts doubt upon your stated reason for the absence</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For purposes of confirming family relationships in granting family leave, we may require you to provide reasonable documentation or statement of the relationship. Reasonable documentation includes, but is not limited to, a court document, or a birth or marriage certificate.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 4 weeks during a 12 month calendar year as established by us. Unused leave cannot be accumulated. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Intermittent </span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you can take family and medical leave on an intermittent basis, when necessary. Since family leave can be taken intermittently and for less than a week, we may elect to convert the 4 week entitlement to an equivalent number of hours based on your current regular workweek as follows: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When you have a part-time regular workweek schedule, the amount of family leave entitlement is determined on a proportional or equivalent basis by comparing it with your normal work schedule</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When your regular workweek schedule varies, a weekly average of the hours worked over the 4 weeks prior to the beginning of family leave can be used to calculate your normal workweek</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We will determine the size of intermittent family leave increments based on the shortest period of time that our payroll system uses to account for use of leave, provided that the shortest incremental period is 1 hour or less.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We may offer to modify existing duties and conditions of regular jobs for you to take intermittent family leave to better accommodate the leave. We may also offer you a temporary transfer to available alternative positions for which you are qualified and which better accommodate intermittent periods of leave. The job modification or transfer will be permitted if: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You agree to either the job modification or transfer</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The transfer or modification is in compliance with any applicable federal or state laws</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The transfer or modified position has equivalent pay and benefits even if we must increase the pay and benefits of the alternative job in order to meet the equivalency</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Interaction with Other Legal Mandates</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;any substitution of paid sick leave for unpaid family and medical leave will not reduce your earned sick and available leave below the amount required by the state&#39;s temporary disability insurance law; however, any sick leave in excess of the minimum statutory equivalent for temporary disability benefits will be used.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When state law provides broader rights than the federal Family and Medical Leave Act requires, we will contact the federal Labor Department&#39;s Wage and Hour Division to determine whether state leave taken for such purposes can count against the federal leave entitlement.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;generally, the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid family and medical leave<span style=\"color:blue\">. </span>If we provide paid sick leave, then you are allowed to substitute up to 10 days of earned paid sick leave per year for unpaid family and medical leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual).</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during family and medical leave. Benefits are earned for the full month in which you work at least 50 percent of the time. Paid time off counts as time worked.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give reasonable advance notice, at least 2 business days, of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you take a leave due to a serious health condition of your own, you must provide a note from your treating physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. The note must also indicate if there are any restrictions pertaining to duties or the number of hours you can work. Please use the <i>Medical Release to Work Form</i>.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">On return from family and medical leave, you will be restored to your former position or to a position with equivalent pay, benefits, and other employment terms and conditions. <u>Exception</u>: You are not entitled to reinstatement when a layoff or workforce reduction during the leave period would have eliminated the original position if you had not been on leave. However, in this situation, you retain all rights, including seniority rights, under any applicable layoff and recall system.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Family Medical Leave HI',	'STATE FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	100,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 21:40:22',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	211,	1),
(376,	'<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:.5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Pregnancy leave is provided to you when you are temporarily unable to work due to a disability caused by pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">With a written request</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> from your healthcare provider that you be transferred to a less strenuous or hazardous position, we will do our best to accommodate you. If accommodation is not possible, and you are not able to continue your normal job responsibilities, you may be asked to go on pregnancy leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please use the <i>Leave Of Absence Application Form</i> for this purpose.<i> </i></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Healthcare Professional&rsquo;s</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;any request for a pregnancy-related leave must be accompanied with a certified healthcare professional&rsquo;s certificate. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;as determined by your physician, a reasonable leave of absence will be granted based on your physical condition and job requirements. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reporting on Progress</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you are required to report directly to us every 30 days on your health status and your intent to return to work.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may take any earned paid time off to run concurrent with the pregnancy leave. Benefits are not earned during the leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual). </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid leave used during pregnancy leave. When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Pregnancy Leave of Absence Ends When</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You are released for full or partial duty. You must provide a physician&rsquo;s statement in writing indicating your fitness to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We receive satisfactory medical evidence that you are unable to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You directly or indirectly inform us (for example, by accepting employment elsewhere, moving out of state, etc.) that you do not intend to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You have been on a medical leave of absence for the approved time</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Returning from Pregnancy Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you must provide a completed <i>Medical Release to Work</i> <i>Form</i>, or an equivalent note from your healthcare provider, verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. This must be received on or before the date you are scheduled to return from leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Upon returning from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or a position of comparable status and pay, without loss of accumulated service credits and privileges. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Leave HI',	'PREGNANCY LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 21:44:31',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	98,	1),
(377,	'<p>If you are prevented from working as a result of an illness, an injury, a disability caused by pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions, or some other serious health condition and you are enrolled in our group health plan, you may be able to continue your health insurance coverage while you are off work and unable to earn wages. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification verifying your inability to work due to a serious health condition.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:40.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive&nbsp;reproductive services</span></span></b></span></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance will continue for the period you are unable to work and earn wages, but shall not exceed 3 months after the initial month in which you are prevented from working and earning wages.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance will be provided at the same level and under the same conditions that existed prior to you being off work. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you will be responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while off work. You must maintain your portion of the premium payments; otherwise, coverage may be terminated.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Healthcare Continuation LOA HI',	'HEALTH CARE CONTINUATION COVERAGE FOR A LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 21:51:30',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	62,	1),
(378,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b>Medical Certification</b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability HI',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"HI\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 21:54:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	80,	1),
(379,	'<p>You may be entitled to time off without pay for the following reasons:&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your own physical or mental illness, injury, or medical condition that requires home care, professional medical diagnosis or care, or preventive medical care</li>\r\n	<li>Care for your child, parent, spouse, or parent of spouse, who is suffering from a physical or mental illness, injury, or medical condition that requires home care, professional medical diagnosis or care, or preventive medical care</li>\r\n	<li>Attend your routine medical and dental appointment or a routine medical and dental appointment for your child, spouse, parent, or parent of spouse</li>\r\n	<li>Address the psychological, physical or legal effects of domestic violence</li>\r\n	<li>Travel to and from an appointment, a pharmacy, or other location related to the purpose for which the time was taken</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Use of sick time for other purposes is not allowed and may result in disciplinary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following definitions apply for purposes of this policy:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Spouse = the meaning given to this term by the marriage laws of the commonwealth</li>\r\n	<li>Child = a biological, adopted, or foster child, a stepchild, a legal ward, or a child of a person who has assumed the responsibilities of parenthood</li>\r\n	<li>Parent = your biological, adoptive, foster or step-parent or that of your spouse, or other person who assumed the responsibilities of parenthood when you or your spouse was a child</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Benefit </strong><strong>Year</strong>&mdash;January 1 to December 31.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;unpaid sick leave is provided to all employees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Earning Sick Leave</strong>&mdash;1 hour of unpaid sick leave is accrued for every 30 hours worked up to a maximum of 40 hours per benefit year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Sick </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;you are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until the 90<sup>th</sup> calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial waiting period, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sick leave may be used in hourly increments, unless we have agreed to smaller amounts. You may not use, in 1 year, more than 40 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to use available sick leave to run concurrent with time off provided by other applicable leaves of absence addressed elsewhere in this manual.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sick leave cannot be used as an excuse to be late for work without an authorized purpose under this policy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may not use sick time if you are not scheduled to be at work during the period of use. You may not accept a specific shift assignment with the intention of calling out sick for all or part of that shift.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;up to 40 hours of unused sick time may be carried over into the following benefit year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your employment ends for any reason and you return to work for us within 1 year from the last date of work, you may use any unused accrued sick time that you had prior to the break in service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the break in service is 4 months or less, all unused sick time will be reinstated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the break in service is more than 4 months but not more than 12 months, all previously earned sick time will be reinstated provided you had 10 or more hours of sick time accrued and unused.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you worked for us at least 90 days prior to the break in service and you return to work within 12 months, you may use your sick time immediately. No additional waiting period will apply.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you did not work for us at least 90 days prior to the break in service and you return to work within 12 months, your previous time of employment will count towards your 90 day waiting period. For example, if you had worked 2 calendar months prior to the break in service, you need only work 1 more month (for a total of 90 days) before being able to use any accrued sick time. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Make-up Time</strong>&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours or shifts during the same or next pay period in lieu of hours or shifts missed and not have to use unpaid sick leave benefits. However, we cannot require you to work the extra hours or shifts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notice of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you need to be absent, late, or leave work early for purposes that are permissible under this policy, you must give advance notice, except in an emergency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Notice should be provided through our established system in a manner that you customarily use to communicate with us for absences or requesting leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the absence is foreseeable (for example, if you will be absent to attend a previously scheduled appointment), you must provide up to seven days&rsquo; advance notice, unless you learn of the need to use earned sick time within a shorter period of time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the absence is not foreseeable, you must provide notice at least 2 hours before the start of your shift. If 2 hours&rsquo; notice is not reasonable due to an accident or sudden illness, notice must be provided as soon as practicable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are going to be absent on multiple days, you or your surrogate (e.g., spouse, adult family member or other responsible party) must provide notice of the expected duration of the leave or, if unknown, provide notice of continuing absence on a daily basis, unless the circumstances make such notice unreasonable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;you may be required to bring in certification supporting the need for leave if:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You are absent from work for more than 24 consecutively-scheduled work hours</li>\r\n	<li>You are absent for three consecutively-scheduled work days</li>\r\n	<li>Your absence occurs within 2 weeks prior to your final scheduled day of work before termination of employment, except in the case of temporary workers</li>\r\n	<li>Your absence occurs after 4 unforeseeable and undocumented absences within a 3 month period</li>\r\n	<li>Your absence occurs after 3 unforeseeable and undocumented absences within a 3 month period (for employees age 17 and younger)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Required documentation must be submitted within 7 days of the absence. Additional time will be allowed for good cause shown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you fail to comply with our documentation requirements for use of unpaid sick time in a timely manner, we may deny future use of an equivalent number of hours of accrued sick time until the documentation is provided.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will never require further information about the details of a medical condition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Expectations Regarding Attendance</strong>&mdash;please remember that regular, reliable attendance and timeliness is expected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you commit fraud or abuse by engaging in an activity that is not consistent with allowable purposes for sick time, you may be subject to disciplinary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you exhibit a clear pattern of taking leave on days just before or after a weekend, vacation, or holiday, we may apply disciplinary action for misuse of earned sick time, unless you provide verification of authorized use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Leave of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employee&#39;s Return to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave MA under 10',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	1,	10,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:05:56',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	22,	1),
(380,	'<p>You may be entitled to time off with pay for the following reasons:&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your own physical or mental illness, injury, or medical condition that requires home care, professional medical diagnosis or care, or preventive medical care</li>\r\n	<li>Care for your child, parent, spouse, or parent of spouse, who is suffering from a physical or mental illness, injury, or medical condition that requires home care, professional medical diagnosis or care, or preventive medical care</li>\r\n	<li>Attend your routine medical and dental appointment or a routine medical and dental appointment for your child, spouse, parent, or parent of spouse</li>\r\n	<li>Address the psychological, physical or legal effects of domestic violence</li>\r\n	<li>Travel to and from an appointment, a pharmacy, or other location related to the purpose for which the time was taken</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Use of paid sick time for other purposes is not allowed and may result in disciplinary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following definitions apply for purposes of this policy:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Spouse = the meaning given to this term by the marriage laws of the commonwealth</li>\r\n	<li>Child = a biological, adopted, or foster child, a stepchild, a legal ward, or a child of a person who has assumed the responsibilities of parenthood</li>\r\n	<li>Parent = your biological, adoptive, foster or step-parent or that of your spouse, or other person who assumed the responsibilities of parenthood when you or your spouse was a child</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Benefit </strong><strong>Year</strong>&mdash;January 1 to December 31.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all employees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Earning Sick Leave</strong>&mdash;1 hour of paid sick leave is accrued for every 30 hours worked up to a maximum of 40 hours per benefit year.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Sick </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;you are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until the 90<sup>th</sup> calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial waiting period, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sick leave may be used in hourly increments, unless we have agreed to smaller amounts. You may not use, in 1 year, more than 40 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to use available sick leave to run concurrent with time off provided by other applicable leaves of absence addressed elsewhere in this manual.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sick leave cannot be used as an excuse to be late for work without an authorized purpose under this policy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may not use sick time if you are not scheduled to be at work during the period of use. You may not accept a specific shift assignment with the intention of calling out sick for all or part of that shift.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;up to 40 hours of unused sick time may be carried over into the following benefit year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your employment ends for any reason and you return to work for us within 1 year from the last date of work, you may use any unused accrued sick time that you had prior to the break in service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the break in service is 4 months or less, all unused sick time will be reinstated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the break in service is more than 4 months but not more than 12 months, all previously earned sick time will be reinstated provided you had 10 or more hours of sick time accrued and unused.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you worked for us at least 90 days prior to the break in service and you return to work within 12 months, you may use your sick time immediately. No additional waiting period will apply.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you did not work for us at least 90 days prior to the break in service and you return to work within 12 months, your previous time of employment will count towards your 90 day waiting period. For example, if you had worked 2 calendar months prior to the break in service, you need only work 1 more month (for a total of 90 days) before being able to use any accrued sick time. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Make-up Time</strong>&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours or shifts during the same or next pay period in lieu of hours or shifts missed and not have to use paid sick leave benefits. However, we cannot require you to work the extra hours or shifts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notice of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you need to be absent, late, or leave work early for purposes that are permissible under this policy, you must give advance notice, except in an emergency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Notice should be provided through our established system in a manner that you customarily use to communicate with us for absences or requesting leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the absence is foreseeable (for example, if you will be absent to attend a previously scheduled appointment), you must provide up to seven days&rsquo; advance notice, unless you learn of the need to use earned sick time within a shorter period of time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the absence is not foreseeable, you must provide notice at least 2 hours before the start of your shift. If 2 hours&rsquo; notice is not reasonable due to an accident or sudden illness, notice must be provided as soon as practicable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are going to be absent on multiple days, you or your surrogate (e.g., spouse, adult family member or other responsible party) must provide notice of the expected duration of the leave or, if unknown, provide notice of continuing absence on a daily basis, unless the circumstances make such notice unreasonable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;you may be required to bring in certification supporting the need for leave if:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You are absent from work for more than 24 consecutively-scheduled work hours</li>\r\n	<li>You are absent for three consecutively-scheduled work days</li>\r\n	<li>Your absence occurs within 2 weeks prior to your final scheduled day of work before termination of employment, except in the case of temporary workers</li>\r\n	<li>Your absence occurs after 4 unforeseeable and undocumented absences within a 3 month period</li>\r\n	<li>Your absence occurs after 3 unforeseeable and undocumented absences within a 3 month period (for employees age 17 and younger)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Required documentation must be submitted within 7 days of the absence. Additional time will be allowed for good cause shown.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you fail to comply with our documentation requirements for use of paid sick time in a timely manner, we may recoup the sick time paid from future wages.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will never require further information about the details of a medical condition.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Expectations Regarding Attendance</strong>&mdash;please remember that regular, reliable attendance and timeliness is expected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you commit fraud or abuse by engaging in an activity that is not consistent with allowable purposes for sick time, you may be subject to disciplinary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you exhibit a clear pattern of taking leave on days just before or after a weekend, vacation, or holiday, we may apply disciplinary action for misuse of earned sick time, unless you provide verification of authorized use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Overtime</strong>&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attendance </strong><strong>Record</strong>&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record so we can be sure to pay you appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Leave of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employee&#39;s Return to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</strong>&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave MA over 10',	'PAID SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	11,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:07:02',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	21,	1),
(381,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">You will be provided an unpaid family and medical leave as outlined below. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eligibility</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family and medical leave, you must have: 1) been employed for a total of at least 12 months (52 weeks) with us at any time prior to the commencement of leave, 2) worked at least 1,250 hours during the 12 month period immediately prior to the date of leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Reasons for Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you may be eligible to take family and medical leave for: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">The birth, adoption, or foster placement of a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Your own serious health condition (excluding pregnancy or pregnancy-related disabilities)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">The serious health condition of your family member (spouse, child or parent)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">A serious health condition is defined as an illness, injury (including, but not limited to, on-the-job-injuries), impairment, or physical or mental condition of the employee or a child, parent, or spouse of the employee that involves either inpatient care or continuing treatment, including, but not limited to, treatment for substance abuse.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">The definitions of &ldquo;parent&rdquo; and &ldquo;child&rdquo; cover biological, foster, step, and adoptive relationships; legal guardians or wards; and individuals charged with parental rights, duties, and responsibilities for a child. A child generally must be under 18; however, an adult dependent incapable of self-care due to mental or physical disability also qualifies as a child.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&ldquo;Spouse&rdquo; means a partner in marriage (including same-sex relationships) or a registered domestic partner.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you must give at least verbal notice of your need for leave, the expected start date of the leave and the anticipated duration of the leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When leave is foreseeable due to an expected birth, adoption, or foster placement of a child or a planned medical treatment, you must request a leave at least 30 days in advance. However, if 30 days&#39; advance notice is impossible because of a change in circumstances or a medical emergency, you must give notice as soon as practicable.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Medical</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need for leave due to your own or a family member&rsquo;s serious health condition. You must provide certification within 15 calendar days, unless obtaining certification within that deadline is impracticable. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 12 workweeks over a 12 month period. The minimum duration of leave for birth, adoption, or foster placement of a child is 2 weeks; however, we may grant up to 2 requests for shorter leave periods. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If we employ a married couple and both are eligible for leave, the family and medical leave for the birth, adoption, or foster care placement of a child is limited to 12 workweeks in a 12 month period between the two parents. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Intermittent </span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you can take your leave on an intermittent basis when necessary. When taking intermittent or reduced-schedule leave for planned medical treatment, you must attempt to schedule the leave so as to minimize disruption to work operations. When you need such leave, you may be required to transfer temporarily into alternative positions with equivalent pay and benefits that better accommodate recurring periods of leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Interaction with Other </span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Leave</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"> Mandates</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;unless you are disabled by a pregnancy-related medical condition, leave under state law runs concurrently with leave under the Federal Family and Medical Leave Act. Any leave taken in accordance with federal-mandated pregnancy disability leave will not reduce the amount of family and medical leave available to you under state law.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Leave</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"> taken under California&#39;s temporary disability benefit program runs concurrently with family and medical leave under state and federal laws, provided the leave meets the terms of all laws. If you are on family and medical leave, you can receive up to 6 weeks of state family temporary disability leave benefits when the qualifying conditions of both leave laws are met.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;generally, the leave of absence is without pay. However, you are required to use any earned paid time off benefit, except sick leave, as part of any leave. Use of paid sick leave is only required when the leave is granted for your own serious health condition. Any paid time off used will run concurrently with the family and medical leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are 2 payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Upon returning from leave, you retain all seniority earned before your leave began for purposes of layoff, recall, promotion, job assignment, and seniority-related benefits.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid leave used during family and medical leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;on return from leave, you will be restored to your former position or to a position with similar duties and responsibilities and equivalent status, benefits, pay, working conditions, privileges, and other terms and conditions of employment. Upon request, we will provide this guarantee of reinstatement in writing. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When we agree to a definite return date at the start of leave, you will be reinstated on that date. If the original return date changes during your leave, we will reinstate you within 2 business days after receiving notice of your readiness to return.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you take a leave due to a personal serious health condition, you must provide a note from your treating physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. You may use the <i>Medical Release to Work Form</i>.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">You do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Family Rights CA',	'CALIFORNIA FAMILY RIGHTS ACT',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:10:34',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	219,	1),
(382,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">Pregnancy leave is provided to you when you are temporarily unable to work due to a disability caused by pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a written request<!--[if supportFields]><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span>xe&quot;Reporting A Pregnancy&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></span><![endif]--> from your healthcare provider that you be transferred to a less strenuous or hazardous position, we will do our best to accommodate you. If accommodation is not possible, and you are not able to continue your normal job responsibilities, you may be asked to go on pregnancy leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong><!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span>xe &quot;Leave Of Absence Request&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></span><![endif]-->&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please use the <em>Leave of Absence Application Form</em> for this purpose.<em> </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Healthcare Professional&rsquo;s</strong><strong> Certification</strong>&mdash;any request for a pregnancy-related leave must be accompanied with a certified healthcare professional&rsquo;s certification.<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span> </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;as determined by your physician, a leave of absence for a reasonable period of time, up to 4 months*, will be provided, as needed, for the period of time you are actually disabled by pregnancy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*Four months of leave is defined as 17 1/3 weeks. The number of hours of leave you are entitled to in a 4 month period is calculated as 17 1/3 weeks multiplied by the number of hours you work in an average workweek. For example, if you average 12 hours in a workweek, you will have up to 208 hours of leave (17.3 x 12 = 207.6 hours). If you average 32 hours in a workweek, you will have up to 554.5 hours of leave. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pregnancy leave will be counted against any family and medical leave entitlements required by federal law. At the conclusion of leave due to disability, an additional 12 weeks of leave for childbirth may be available under the state family and medical leave, which applies to employers with 50 or more employees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intermittent </strong><strong>Leave/Reduced Work Schedule</strong>&mdash;is allowable when medically necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reporting on </strong><strong>Progress</strong>&mdash;you are required to report directly to us every 30 days on your health status and your intent to return to work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and </strong><strong>Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may take any earned paid time off to run concurrently with the pregnancy leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are 2 payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during pregnancy leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Pregnancy Leave of Absence Ends When</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You are released for full or partial duty. You must provide a physician&rsquo;s statement in writing indicating your fitness to return to work</li>\r\n	<li>You receive satisfactory medical evidence that you are unable to return to work</li>\r\n	<li>You directly or indirectly inform us (for example, by accepting employment elsewhere, moving out of state, etc.) that you do not intend to return to work with us</li>\r\n	<li>You have been on a leave of absence for the approved time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Returning from Pregnancy </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;you must provide a completed <em>Medical Release to Work</em> <em>Form</em>, or an equivalent note from your healthcare provider, verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. This must be received on or before the date you are scheduled to return from leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or a comparable position in terms of pay, location, job content and promotional opportunities, unless we can prove by a preponderance of evidence that no comparable position exists.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong><!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span>xe &quot;Voluntary Termination&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></span><![endif]-->&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>You do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</li>\r\n	<li>If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave&nbsp;ââââââ</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Leave CA',	'PREGNANCY LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	5,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:20:53',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	96,	1),
(383,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:justify\">When you show up to work a regularly scheduled workday but are then not put to work or are given less than half the usual or scheduled day&#39;s work, you will receive a minimum of 2 hours of pay or a maximum of 4 hours of pay depending on the length of the scheduled shift. The following chart will be used to determine the amount of pay legally required:</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:350px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Scheduled Hours</span></span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td>\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Reporting Time Pay Owed</span></span></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">10</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">4</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">9</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">4</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">8</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">4</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">7</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">3.5</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">6</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">3</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">5</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">2.5</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">4</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">2</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">3</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">2</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">2</td>\r\n			<td style=\"text-align:center\">2</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>Reporting Time Pay will also be provided if you are required to report to work a second time in any 1 workday and are given less than 2 hours of work on the second reporting. In this case, you will receive at least 2 hours of pay for the second appearance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are required to attend a meeting that has been scheduled in advance on a day you do not normally&nbsp;work, you will be paid for the entire duration of the meeting&nbsp;or Reporting Time pay, whichever is greater. In this case, Reporting Time Pay is based on the meeting&#39;s scheduled number of hours.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example, if the meeting is scheduled for 2 hours and lasts 1.5 hours, you will be paid for the actual duration of the meeting (i.e. 1.5 hours). This is because the meeting lasted at least half of the scheduled time. If the meeting is scheduled for 2 hours and lasts 45 minutes, you will be paid 1 hour (45 minutes of meeting attendance and 15 minutes of Reporting Time Pay). This is because the meeting lasted less than half of the scheduled time.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the meeting takes place during your regularly scheduled workday&nbsp;but requires you to return sometime after the end of your shift, then you will be paid for the entire duration of the meeting or 2 hours of Reporting Time Pay, whichever is greater.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These provisions do not apply to you:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<li>When you are on a paid standby status</li>\r\n	<li>When operations cannot begin due to threats to us or our property or when recommended by civil authority</li>\r\n	<li>When public utilities fail, such as water, gas, electricity, or sewer</li>\r\n	<li>When work is interrupted by an act of God or other causes not within our control</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Pay for time not worked is excluded when computing overtime.</p>\r\n',	3,	'Reporting Time CA',	'REPORTING TIME PAY',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:29:09',	'2019-11-20 08:01:32',	'enabled',	22,	0),
(384,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are a victim of an offense, you may be eligible for time off from work to appear in court to be heard at any proceeding, including any delinquency proceeding, involving a post-arrest release decision, plea, sentencing, post-conviction release decision, or any proceeding in which a right of the victim is at issue.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Applicable offenses include all of the following:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Vehicular manslaughter while intoxicated.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Felony child abuse likely to produce great bodily harm or a death.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Assault resulting in the death of a child less than eight years of age.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Felony domestic violence.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Felony physical abuse of an elder or dependent adult.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Felony stalking.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Solicitation for murder.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">A serious felony.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">A hit-and-run causing death or injury.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Felony driving under the influence causing injury.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Sexual assault.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any applicable paid time off benefit available at that time.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take time off under this policy, you must give us reasonable advance notice of your intention to take time off, unless advance notice is not feasible. When the need for time off is unforeseeable, you must provide certification to us within a reasonable period of time after the absence.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">You can provide certification through one or more of the following:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">A police report indicating that you were a victim of an offense specified above.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Court protection order separating you from the perpetrator of an offense specified above, or other evidence from the court or prosecuting attorney that you have appeared in court. </span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Documentation from a medical professional, domestic violence advocate or advocate for victims of sexual assault, health care provider, or counselor that you were undergoing treatment for physical or mental injuries or abuse resulting in victimization from an offense specified above.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Leave Appear in Court CA',	'LEAVE TO APPEAR IN COURT',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:31:11',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	372,	1),
(385,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">The Paid Family Leave Insurance (PFL) program provides wage replacement benefits to workers who take time off work to: &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Care for a seriously ill child, parent, parent-in-law, grandparent, grandchild, sibling, spouse or registered domestic partner</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Bond with a minor child within the first year of the child&rsquo;s birth or placement in connection with foster care or adoption</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">The PFL is part of the State Disability Insurance (SDI) program and is administered by the State of California Employment Development Department (EDD), not us. &nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We will provide </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">a brochure on PFL to new employees and employees requesting a leave of absence that qualifies under this program.&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">For more information or to file a claim, please contact the State of California.</span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">The PFL law is a monetary benefit, not a leave entitlement benefit. &nbsp;As such, it does not mandate that we provide time off or a leave of absence to you, even for the covered reasons listed above. You must follow all applicable time off and leave of absence policies as outlined in this manual. All time off or leave of absence requests are subject to our approval. For information about any leave of absence that may be available to you, please see the leave of absence policies.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">If you are not approved for time off or a leave of absence and you choose to take the time off anyway, your employment with us may be terminated. While employment may have ended, benefits under the PFL program may still be available to you.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Paid Family Leave Insurance CA',	'PAID FAMILY LEAVE INSURANCE',	'none',	'2017-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:32:47',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	289,	1),
(386,	'<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When called to serve on jury duty</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty OR',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:36:06',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	357,	1),
(387,	'<p>When your shift is 6 hours or more, you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes. If the work shift is at least 6 hours but less than 7 hours, the meal period will be scheduled between the 2nd and 5th hour worked. If the work period is more than 7 hours, the meal period will be scheduled between the 3rd and 6th hour worked. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. A paid working meal period may be permitted if the nature of the work does not permit you to be released from duty. This should occur infrequently and you must sign the <em>On Duty Meal Period/Meal Period Waiver Form</em>.</p>\n',	4,	'Meal Period OR',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2020-06-04 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:36:55',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	304,	1),
(388,	'<p style=\"margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You receive a paid rest break of 10 minutes </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">for every segment of 4 hours or major part thereof (2 hours and 1 minute through 4 hours) worked in one work period</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">. </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The rest period should be taken as nearly as possible in the middle of the work segment.&nbsp;Rest breaks are in addition to and separate from required meal periods.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The breaks may not be combined and/or added to the lunch period, nor can they be waived to shorten the work day. We ask that you take your breaks when they will not negatively affect customer service. For insurance purposes, we ask that you remain on office premises during rest breaks.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Rest Breaks OR',	'REST BREAKS',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:38:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	315,	1),
(389,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You may be eligible for: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Parental Leave&ndash;&ndash;must be completed within 12 months after birth or placement of the child:</span></span></span></span></span>\r\n\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To care for an infant </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To care for a newly placed adopted or foster child under 18 years of age</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To care for a newly placed or adopted child older than 18 years of age if the child is incapable of self-care because of a mental or physical condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Serious Health Condition Leave:</span></span></span></span></span>\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To recover from or seek treatment for your own non-pregnancy-related serious health condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To care for a family member with a serious health condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Sick Child Leave:</span></span></span></span></span>\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To care for your child&rsquo;s non-serious illness, injury, or other condition that requires home care. (Leave to care for a child with a non-serious injury or illness does not cover routine dental or medical appointments).</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Pregnancy Disability Leave:</span></span></span></span></span>\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To recover from or seek treatment for an illness, injury or condition related to pregnancy or childbirth that disables you from performing any available job duties offered by us</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Bereavement Leave&ndash;&ndash;must be completed within 60 days of the date on which you received notice of the death of a family member:</span></span></span></span></span>\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To attend the funeral or alternative to a funeral of the family member </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To make arrangements necessitated by the death of a family member</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 1.0in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To grieve the death of a family member</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The term family member includes: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A spouse</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A same-sex domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&#39;s or a domestic partner&#39;s biological, adoptive, or foster parent or child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A legal guardian or person with whom an employee has or had a parental relationship involving financial or day-to-day responsibility for a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&#39;s parent-in-law or the parent of an employee&#39;s same-sex domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&rsquo;s grandparents or grandchildren</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eligibility</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;to qualify for Parental Leave, you must have worked for us: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">At least 180 days immediately prior to taking leave</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To qualify for all other types of leave, you must have worked for us:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An average of 25 hours per week for at least 180 days immediately prior to taking leave</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;except for Bereavement Leave, a leave of absence may be granted for up to 12 weeks over a 12 month period. Leave may be extended as outlined below:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you take 12 weeks of Parental leave, you may be eligible for an additional 12 weeks of Sick Child Leave </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you take 12 weeks of Pregnancy Disability Leave, you may be eligible for an additional 12 weeks of leave for any applicable reason.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Two weeks of Bereavement Leave per family member death in any 1 year period is available provided that the total leave time does not exceed 12 weeks. If multiple deaths occur during the 1 year period, the leave shall not be taken concurrently. Unless an extension is available, as outlined above, all leave taken for Bereavement Leave counts towards the total amount of leave available in any 1 year. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If 2 family members are employed at the same time, leave cannot be taken concurrently without our approval. Exceptions to this rule will be made when: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">One family member needs to care for the other family member who has a serious health condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">One family member needs to care for a child&#39;s serious health condition while the other family member cares for his or her own serious health condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Both family members need to take Bereavement Leave </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Intermittent </span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;leave may be taken on an intermittent basis when medically necessary. If you take leave intermittently or on a reduced work schedule, you will only have the hours of leave taken counted against your total family and medical leave entitlement.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If no other option can accommodate intermittent or reduced-schedule leave, you may be transferred into an alternative position that has equivalent pay and benefits to accommodate the need for leave, if mutually agreed upon by both of us. If you agree to a transfer, you will be entitled to reinstatement to your original position as soon as your need for accommodation ends.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance. The following exceptions may be made:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You or your family member experience an unexpected serious health condition </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Your child has an unexpected illness, injury, or condition that requires home care</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Premature birth, or unexpected adoption or foster placement</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Death of a family member</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If one of the above exceptions occurs, you, or someone authorized to speak on your behalf, must give oral notice within 24 hours of starting leave and written notice within 3 days after returning to work.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:red\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you are required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification in any of the following situations:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The need for leave is due to your own serious health condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The need for leave is due to your family member&rsquo;s serious health condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We will provide you our <i>Medical Certification Form</i> for this purpose.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical Recertification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if the circumstances meriting leave have changed significantly or we have received information casting doubt on the stated reason for leave, you may be required to recertify your medical condition requiring leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If there are costs associated with obtaining certification or recertification that are not otherwise covered by insurance or other benefits, we will pay the expense. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;the leave of absence is generally without pay. You will be required to use any available paid time off benefit as part of the family and medical leave. </span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. If you do not pay the total amount of the premium, coverage will discontinue until regular employment is resumed.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during family and medical leave. Benefits are earned for the full month in which you work at least 50 percent of the time. Paid time off counts as time worked.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you take a leave due to a personal serious health condition, you must provide a note from your treating physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. The note must also indicate if there are any restrictions pertaining to duties or the number of hours you can work. You may use our <i>Medical Release to Work Form </i>or one that is equivalent. If there are costs associated with obtaining certification of fitness to work that are not otherwise covered by insurance or other benefits, we will pay the expense.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits, unless a comparable position no longer exists.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletindent\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletindent\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletindent\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletindent\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Family Medical Leave OR',	'STATE FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-10-20 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	25,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:41:29',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	215,	1),
(390,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are a victim of </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking<span style=\"color:black\">, or have a minor child who is a victim of </span>domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking<span style=\"color:black\">, you may be allowed to take time off from work based on staffing so that you can:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare of you or your child.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any applicable paid time off benefit available at that time.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take time off under this policy, you must give us reasonable advance notice of your intention to take leave, unless advance notice is not feasible.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">You may be required to provide certification that you or your minor child or dependent is a victim of domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault or stalking and the time off is for one of the purposes outlined above. If required, certification must be provided within a reasonable time after it has been requested. You can provide certification through one or more of the following:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">A police report indicating that you were a victim of </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking<span style=\"color:black\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Court protection order separating you from the perpetrator of an act of </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking<span style=\"color:black\">, or other evidence from the court or prosecuting attorney that you have appeared in court. </span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Documentation from a medical professional, domestic violence advocate or advocate for victims of sexual assault, health care provider, or counselor that you were undergoing treatment for physical or mental injuries or abuse resulting in victimization from an act of </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking<span style=\"color:black\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Safety Accommodation</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;we will make a reasonable safety accommodation when requested by you if you are a victim of domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking, unless it would impose an undue hardship on the operation of the business. Prior to making an accommodation, we may require certification as outlined above. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information the employee provides confidentially. Information will not be disclosed without your express permission, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence OR under 6',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	1,	5,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:43:33',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	279,	1),
(391,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are a victim of </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking<span style=\"color:black\">, or have a minor child who is a victim of </span>domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking<span style=\"color:black\">, you will be provided with reasonable leave from employment so that you can:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Seek legal or law enforcement assistance or remedies to ensure the health and safety of you or your minor child or dependent, including preparing for and participating in protective order proceedings or other civil or criminal legal proceedings related to domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking. </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Obtain medical treatment for or to recover from injuries caused by <span style=\"color:black\">domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking for you or your minor child or dependent.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Acquire, or to assist a minor child or dependent in acquiring, counseling from a licensed mental health professional related to an experience of domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking. </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Obtain services from a victim services provider for you or your minor child or dependent. </span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Relocate or take steps to secure an existing home to ensure the health and safety for you or your minor child or dependent. </span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Leave will be unpaid unless you choose to use any applicable paid time off benefit available at that time. We reserve the right to limit the amount of leave you may take if your leave creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take leave under this policy, you must give us reasonable advance notice of your intention to take leave, unless advance notice is not feasible.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">You may be required to provide certification that you or your minor child or dependent is a victim of domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault or stalking and the leave is for one of the purposes outlined above. If required, certification must be provided within a reasonable time after it has been requested. You can provide certification through one or more of the following:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">A police report indicating that you or your minor child or dependent was a victim of domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Court protection order or other evidence from a court or attorney that you appeared in or was preparing for a civil or criminal proceeding related to domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Documentation from an attorney, law enforcement officer, health care professional, licensed mental health professional or counselor, a member of the clergy, or victim services provider that you or your minor child or dependent was undergoing treatment or counseling, obtaining services or relocating as a result of domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Safety Accommodation</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">- we will make a reasonable safety accommodation when requested by you if you are a victim of domestic violence, criminal harassment, sexual assault, or stalking, unless it would impose an undue hardship on the operation of the business. Prior to making an accommodation, we may require certification as outlined above. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will not be disclosed without your express permission, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence OR over 6',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	6,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:44:53',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	278,	1),
(392,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Military family leave may be available if you are</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"> the spouse of a member of the Armed Forces of the United States, the National Guard, or the military reserve forces of the United States who has been notified of an impending call or order to active duty, or who has been deployed during a period of military conflict.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">For purposes of this policy, a &ldquo;period of military conflict&rdquo; means a period of war declared by the United States Congress, declared by executive order of the President of the United States, or in which a reserve component of the Armed Forces of the United States is ordered to active duty pursuant to Title 32 of the United States Code or section 12301 or 12302 of Title 10 of the United States Code.</span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Leave may be provided per deployment after the military member has been notified of an impending call or order to active duty and before deployment and when the military member is on leave from deployment.</span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">up to 14 days of leave during the time federal or state deployment orders are in effect. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Qualified Employee</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you are qualified for leave if you work 20 or more hours per week.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Notification</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;if you intend to take leave under this policy, you must provide us with notice of the intention to take leave within 5 business days of receiving the official notice of an impending call or order to active duty or of a leave from deployment.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;we may require certification from the proper military authority to verify your eligibility for leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;leave is unpaid. However, you may elect to use any paid time off as part of leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Reinstatement Rights</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you will be reinstated to your position held prior to taking leave, or to a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Family Leave OR',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	25,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-03 22:47:14',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	238,	1),
(393,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>This manual serves as a ready reference for you and us. It is a summary of personnel policies, procedures and employee benefits. It is designed to be a working guide for the administration of a consistent and fair personnel program. Please read it carefully. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:left\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span><span><span>The policies herein are intended to: </span></span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span>Prevent misunderstandings that might arise from unwritten policies, inconsistently applied policies, or lack of proper communications</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span>Eliminate the need to make hasty decisions in matters of personnel policies</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span>Assure uniformity and fairness in the administration of policies</span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span>Communicate the rights and responsibilities of all</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span><span>THE POLICIES DESCRIBED ARE NOT AN EXPRESSED OR IMPLIED CONTRACT OF EMPLOYMENT BETWEEN THE EMPLOYER AND THE EMPLOYEES AND DO NOT IN ANY WAY IMPLY OR CREATE ANY RIGHTS, CONTRACTUAL OR OTHERWISE. </span></span></span></u></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>We reserve th<span>e right to modify, suspend, rescind, interpret and administer any of the policies, procedures, terms, conditions, and language of any or all parts of this manual. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>This policy manual replaces all earlier policy manuals and takes precedence over all memoranda<span>&nbsp;and oral descriptions of personnel policies, practices, and procedures. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Upon hire, you will be asked to sign the </span></span></span><span><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Policy Manual Acknowledgment Form</span></span></em></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span> once you have had an opportunity to read and familiarize yourself with its contents. You will be inform<span>ed of any revisions to these policies as they occur during employment, and you will be asked to sign a copy of the </span></span></span></span><span><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Updated Policy Manual Acknowledgement Form</span></span></em></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>This Personnel Policy Manual is our property. Please do not remove any hardcopy versions from th<span>e premises.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>If you have any questions, please feel free to ask.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	1,	'About the Manual SC',	'ABOUT THE MANUAL',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"SC\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 20:44:58',	'2020-01-28 00:35:27',	'enabled',	2,	0),
(394,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Your own illness or injury</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Diagnostic, preventive, routine or therapeutic care for yourself</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">To care for a sick or injured parent, grandparent, spouse, child, brother, sister, parent-in-law, grandchild, or foster child, including helping that individual obtain diagnostic, preventive, routine, or therapeutic health treatment</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">To accompany your parent, grandparent, spouse, or parent-in-law to an appointment related to that individual&rsquo;s long-term care</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Absences due to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking, for yourself or your parent, grandparent, spouse, child, brother, sister, parent-in-law, grandchild, or foster child:</span></span></span></span></span>\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To obtain social or legal services</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To obtain medical care or counseling</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To relocate</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">To care for </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">parent, grandparent, spouse, child, brother, sister, parent-in-law, grandchild, or foster child because the school or business where that individual is normally located during your workday is closed for public health or safety reasons</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all employees</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> <span style=\"border:none\">who <span style=\"border:none\">work <span style=\"border:none\">an average of 18 hours p<span style=\"border:none\">er week <span style=\"border:none\">for<span style=\"border:none\"> 20 <span style=\"border:none\">or more <span style=\"border:none\">weeks in a 12 month period</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is not provided to those who:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Work on an intermittent<span style=\"border:none\">, or as needed,<span style=\"border:none\"> basis</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Have no expectation of continuing employment with us, such as temporary employees working for less than 20 weeks </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">1 hour of paid leave is accrued for every </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">52</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours worked up to a maximum of 24 hours </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">in a 12 month period through December 31, 2018 and up to a maximum of 40 hours in a 12 month period from December 31, 2018 and beyond</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">while sick leave begins accruing at the start of employment, <span style=\"border:none\">y</span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">ou are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">after one year <span style=\"border:none\">of employment.</span></span></span></span> </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave may be used</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> in hourly increments</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Group health insurance, if applicable, shall continue&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">during your use of sick leave at the same level and conditions that would otherwise exist <span style=\"border:none\">when<span style=\"border:none\"> you are normally working<span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave during a 12 month period will be carried over into the next year. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You may not use<span style=\"border:none\">, in one 12 month period, more than </span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">24 hours </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">of sick leave </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">through December 31, 2018 and more than 40 hours of sick leave from December 31, 2018 and beyond</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends involuntarily (i.e. you are discharged or laid off)</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, and you are rehired<span style=\"border:none\"> within </span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">12</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> months of the date of separation, </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">t</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">here will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for accruing and using sick leave provided you worked at least </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">one year</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> previously.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends voluntarily (i.e. you resigned)</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, and you are rehired within&nbsp;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">12</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> months of the date of separation, </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">you will be subject to the one year of employment </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">waiting period, upon rehiring, for accruing and using sick leave.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">we ask that you make reasonable efforts to avoid scheduling routine or preventive&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">health care during regular work hours. If you need to use paid sick leave, please notify us as soon as practicable of the intent to take<span style=\"border:none\"> sick time and provide the expected duration of your absence. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Make-up Time</span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you <span style=\"border:none\">may choose to work </span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">an equivalent number of hours as the number of hours for which you were absent in the same pay period and not use paid sick leave. As an alternative, </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">upon mutual consent by you and us</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, you may trade hours with another employee so that th<span style=\"border:none\">e other employee works during the hours you are absent and you work an equivalent number of hours in place of the other employee during the same<span style=\"border:none\"> pay period and not use paid sick leave. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">so we can be <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">sure to pay you appropriately.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are unable <span style=\"border:none\">to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave VT',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 20:47:31',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	33,	1),
(395,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">You or your family member&rsquo;s mental or physical illness, injury, or health condition</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Diagnosis, care, or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury, or health condition of, or preventive care for, you or your family member</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">When our place of business or your child&rsquo;s school or place of care is closed by order of a public official for any health-related reason</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">To manage situations involved with being a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking for you or your family member</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">For purposes of this policy, &quot;family member&quot; means:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Child - a biological, foster, adopted, stepchild, legal ward, or a child of whom you stand in loco parentis or are a de facto parent</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Parent - a biological, foster, adoptive, de facto, stepparent, or a legal guardian of you or your spouse or registered domestic partner, or a person who stood in loco parentis when you were a child</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Spouse or registered domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Grandparent</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Grandchild</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Sibling&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Eligibility</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">paid sick leave is provided to all employees</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">1 hour of paid leave is accrued for every </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">4</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">0 h</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">ours worked, including overtime</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;you are not eligible to use your sick leave until the 90th calendar day following commencement of your employment. </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">After you have completed the initial 90 days of employment, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Sick leave may be used in hourly increments.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">up to 40 hours of</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> accrued and unused sick<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;leave will be carried over into the next 12 month cycle. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends, for any reason, and you are rehired within a year of the date of separation, your </span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">previously unused accrued sick leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon <span style=\"border:none\">rehiring, for using sick leave provided you worked at least 90 days previously.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">when the use of paid sick leave is foreseeable, you shall provide reasonable advance notice, verbally or in writing, of the need to take sick leave. When possible, please provide notice at least 10 days in advance for scheduling purposes. When the use of paid sick leave is not foreseeable, you shall provide us notice, verbally or in writing, as soon as practicable</span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave for more than 3 consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in certification<span style=\"border:none\"> supporting the need for leave. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Prohibition on Retaliation</span></span></b><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">we do not retaliate against employees for any reason. Should you need to exercise your right<span style=\"border:none\"> to use paid sick leave <span style=\"border:none\">as <span style=\"border:none\">described <span style=\"border:none\">in this policy<span style=\"border:none\">, <span style=\"border:none\">you will not be subject to retaliation<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Overtime</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the day or week.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Attendance Record</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record so we can be sure to pay you on the next regularly scheduled payday after your sick leave was taken.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Employee&rsquo;s Return to Work</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Unused Sick Leave Upon Termination</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave WA',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-10-02 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 20:50:11',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	34,	1),
(396,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.5in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability WV',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WV\"]',	12,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 20:51:41',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	94,	1),
(397,	'<div class=\"WordSection1\">\r\n<div class=\"WordSection1\">\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"page:WordSection1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You may be eligible for a leave of absence if you wish to donate an organ or your bone marrow to another person. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"page:WordSection1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eligible Employees</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you must have been employed for more than 52 weeks and have worked at least 1,000 hours in the preceding 52-week period.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"page:WordSection1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;up to 6 weeks of leave in a 12 month period may be taken.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"page:WordSection1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any applicable paid time off benefit available at that time.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"page:WordSection1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Please make a reasonable effort to schedule the bone marrow or organ donation procedure so that it does not unduly disrupt our operations, subject to the approval of the health care provider of the bone marrow or organ donee</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">. Please give us advance notice of the bone marrow or organ donation in a reasonable and practicable manner.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"page:WordSection1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Written verification</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">medical verification from a physician may be required to confirm the purpose and length of each leave requested by you to donate an organ or bone marrow.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"page:WordSection1\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that work can be properly scheduled.&nbsp; Upon returning from leave you will be reinstated <span style=\"color:black\">to the position held before the leave began, or a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Bone Marrow WI',	'ORGAN AND BONE MARROW DONATION LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WI\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 20:55:52',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	75,	1),
(398,	'<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:.5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Pregnancy leave is provided to you when you are temporarily unable to work due to a disability caused by pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">With a written request</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> from your healthcare provider that you be transferred to a less strenuous or hazardous position, we will do our best to accommodate you. If accommodation is not possible, and you are not able to continue your normal job responsibilities, you may be asked to go on pregnancy leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please use the <i>Leave Of Absence Application Form</i> for this purpose.<i> </i></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Healthcare Professional&rsquo;s</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;any request for a pregnancy-related leave must be accompanied with a certified healthcare professional&rsquo;s certificate. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:40.5pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a leave of absence will be granted for a reasonable period of time, which will normally be construed as the period of the actual disability or 8 weeks, whichever is less. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reporting on Progress</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you are required to report directly to us every 30 days on your health status and your intent to return to work.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may use any earned paid time off to run concurrent with the pregnancy leave. Benefits are not earned during the leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual). </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during pregnancy leave. When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Pregnancy Leave of Absence Ends When</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You are released for full or partial duty. You must provide a physician&rsquo;s statement in writing indicating your fitness to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We receive satisfactory medical evidence that you are unable to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You directly or indirectly inform us (for example, by accepting employment elsewhere, moving out of state, etc.) that you do not intend to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You have been on a medical leave of absence for the approved time</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Returning from Pregnancy Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you must provide a completed <i>Medical Release to Work</i> <i>Form</i>, or an equivalent note from your healthcare provider, verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. This must be received on or before the date you are scheduled to return from leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We will endeavor to place you in your former position or in a position comparable in status and pay, subject to budgetary restrictions, our need to fill vacancies, and the ability to find qualified temporary replacements.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:40.5pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Leave IA',	'PREGNANCY LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IA\"]',	4,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 21:00:22',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	99,	1),
(399,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You may be provided an unpaid family and medical leave as outlined below. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eligibility</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family and medical leave, you must have worked at least 12 months. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Reasons for Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you can take family and medical leave for: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Childbirth</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Adoption of a child age 16 or younger</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Your own serious health condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Care of a family members&#39; (including domestic partners&rsquo;) serious health condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Donation of an organ for transplant</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Serious health conditions or death of your family members (including domestic partners) while on active duty with U.S. or Maine military forces</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A serious health condition is defined as an illness, injury, impairment, or physical or mental condition requiring inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential medical care facility or continuing treatment by a health care provider.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for emergency medical conditions. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need for leave due to a serious health condition of your own or the serious health condition of a covered family member.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.5in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 10 weeks over a 24 month period. The 24 month period is measured from the date your initial leave begins. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid family and medical leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual).</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during family and medical leave. Benefits are earned for the full month in which you work at least 50 percent of the time. Paid time off counts as time worked.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you take a leave due to a personal serious health condition, you must provide a note from your treating physician, or an accredited religious healer, verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. The note must also indicate if there are any restrictions pertaining to duties or the number of hours you can work. You can use the <i>Medical Release to Work Form</i> for this purpose.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Upon returning from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits, unless a comparable position no longer exists.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Family Medical Leave ME',	'STATE FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ME\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 22:03:58',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	212,	1),
(400,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You may be provided an unpaid family and medical leave as outlined below. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eligibility</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family and medical leave, you must have worked: 1) At least 12 months without a break in employment, 2) Full time for an average of at least 30 hours per week in the 12 months immediately preceding the request for leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Reasons for Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you can take family and medical leave for: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Childbirth</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Adoption of a child age 16 or younger</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The serious health condition of you or your family member</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A serious health condition is defined as a disabling physical or mental condition, impairment, injury, or illness requiring inpatient care in a hospital, nursing home, or hospice; or outpatient care requiring continuing treatment by a health care provider.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The definition of family member includes your parents, spouses, children, mothers-in-law, and fathers-in-law.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you must give at least 30 days&#39; advance written notice of the beginning and ending dates of leave for childbirth, adoption, or serious health conditions, unless advance notice is impossible because of a medical emergency. The notice must include a detailed description of the circumstances requiring leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need and probable duration of leave. You must provide this medical certification before starting family and medical leave, if possible. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 13 weeks over a 2 year period, beginning with the first day of leave taken. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;generally, the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may choose to use any paid time off as part of the leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You are entitled to any benefits earned before the start of leave, along with any benefits you would have received if you had not taken leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash; if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you take a leave due to a personal serious health condition, you must provide a note from your treating physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. The note must also indicate if there are any restrictions pertaining to duties or the number of hours the employee can work. You may use the <i>Medical Release to Work Form</i>.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">On return from parental and family medical leave, you will be restored to your former position or to a position with equivalent seniority, status, benefits, pay, service credits, and other terms and conditions of employment. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When you do not to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Family Medical Leave RI',	'STATE FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 22:08:42',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	216,	1),
(401,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, or you need to breastfeed/express milk, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">request.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Medical</span></span></b> <span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Certification</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you our <i>Medical Certification Form</i> for this purpose.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability RI',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	4,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 22:10:03',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	90,	1),
(402,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, you may be<span style=\"border:none\"> provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical</span></b> <span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Certification</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose.</span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services</span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability ND',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ND\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 22:37:58',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	85,	1),
(403,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crimes, or have a minor child who is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, stalking or other domestic violence-related crimes, you may take time off from work so that you can obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare of you or your child.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take time off under this policy, you must follow our usual time-off request procedures, unless an emergency prevents you from doing so. When the need for time off is unforeseeable, you must provide documentation upon return to work that supports your reason for being absent from the workplace.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence NC',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NC\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:15:04',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	274,	1),
(404,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You may be able to take leave to attend or otherwise be involved in your child&#39;s school activities.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&ndash;&ndash;if you are a parent or guardian or act as a parent of a school-aged child, you are eligible to take school activities leave.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Request for Leave</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&ndash;&ndash;you must give at least 48 hours advance notice of an anticipated need for leave. Leave must be taken at a time that is mutually agreeable by you and us.&nbsp; At our discretion, documentation from your child&#39;s school or day-care facility verifying participation in a specific activity on a particular date at a particular time may be required.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Length of Leave</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&ndash;&ndash;leave will be granted for up to 4 hours in a 12 month period. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Salary and Benefits</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&ndash;&ndash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'School Activities NC',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NC\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:16:39',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	249,	1),
(405,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation upon request and on the advice of your treating physician or certified&nbsp;doula.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship. In addition, the reasonable accommodation cannot result in:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Us creating additional employment that we would not have otherwise created</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">The termination of another employee</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Transferring an employee with more seniority than you </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Promoting any employee </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical</span></span></b> <span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Certification</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.5in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability MN',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	21,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:20:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	84,	1),
(406,	'<p>Please see our policy on paid time off regarding the amount of paid time off available to you based on your employment category. This policy does not add paid time off benefits; rather it ensures that you use your paid time off benefits appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may use your earned and available paid time off to attend to an illness of your child, parent, or spouse under the same conditions and policy rules that apply if you took time off for your own illness. If you have more than one paid time off benefit available, then you may elect the type and the amount of paid time off benefit to be used.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following definitions apply for purposes of this policy:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>&quot;Child&quot; means an adopted, biological, foster child, stepchild, or a legal ward who is under the age of 18, or over 18 and incapable of self-care due to a mental or physical disability</li>\r\n	<li>&quot;Parent&quot; means an adoptive, biological, foster parent, stepparent, legal guardian, or a person fulfilling a parental role (&ldquo;standing in loco parentis&rdquo;)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>You are eligible if you earn paid time off benefits as defined by the applicable policies set forth in the manual and are primarily employed in the state of Maryland.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\nAll requirements regarding time off, reporting time off, and/or documentation, as outlined in the paid time off policies, are also applicable to this policy.&nbsp;</p>\r\n',	4,	'Flexible Leave MD',	'FLEXIBLE LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-11-14 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:24:10',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	8,	1),
(407,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant and have a disability that is caused by or contributed to by pregnancy, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request, in any of the following ways:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Changing your job duties</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Changing your work hours </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Relocating <span style=\"border:none\">your work area</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Providing mechanical or electrical aids</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Providing a leave of absence</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\"> (please see our leave of absence policy for more information)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Transferring you to a less strenuous or less hazardous position</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you want to request a transfer to a less strenuous or less hazardous position, we shall make this accommodation provided your treating physician has advised the transfer. In addition, the transfer cannot result in:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Us creating additional employment that we would not have otherwise created</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">The termination of another employee</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Transferring an employee with more seniority than you </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Promoting any employee who is not qualified to perform the job</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical</span></span></b><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"> Certification</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose. The certification must include the date the reasonable accommodation became medically advisable, the probable duration of the reasonable accommodation, and an explanatory statement as to the medical advisability of the reasonable accommodation. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability MD',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:26:22',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	83,	1),
(408,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 18 months after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-OR under 11',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	1,	10,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:39:59',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	180,	1),
(409,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 18 months after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-OR over 11',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	11,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:40:41',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	179,	1),
(410,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border:none; font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You may be eligible to use your paid time off benefits, if applicable, for a leave of absence if you wish to donate your bone marrow to another person. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eligible Employees</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you must work an average of 20 or more hours per week.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;the total length of the leave shall be determined by you and cannot exceed the amount of paid time off you have available or 40 hours, whichever is less, for bone marrow donation.</span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance<span style=\"color:black\">, or as soon as possible for unforeseeable events.</span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Written verification</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">medical verification from a physician may be required to confirm the purpose and length of each leave requested by you to donate bone marrow.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that work can be properly scheduled.&nbsp; Upon returning from leave you will be reinstated to the position held before the leave began, or a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Bone Marrow OR',	'BONE MARROW DONATION LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:41:52',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	74,	1),
(411,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You may be provided with time off on Veteran&rsquo;s Day, November 11, if you are a veteran and you would otherwise be scheduled to work. In order to ensure this time off, you must give us at least 21 calendar days&rsquo; notice of your<span style=\"border:none\"> intent to be off on that day. We may require documentation showing that you are a veteran. Time off may be denied if allowing the time would cause significant economic or operational disruption, or undue hardship to the business.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If there are multiple re<span style=\"border:none\">quests from veterans for the time off, we may determine that we cannot accommodate everyone. If that is the case, we will do one of the following:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Deny time off to all veterans</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Deny time off to the minimum number of veterans needed by us to avoid significant&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">economic or operational disruption, or undue hardship</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you have been denied the time off for any reason and you have to work Veteran&rsquo;s Day, you may choose, with our prior approval, a single day off within the year as a replacement for the holiday you <span style=\"border:none\">missed and to honor your service.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You will receive notification at least 14 calendar days prior to the holiday as to whether or not the time off has been granted and if it will be paid.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Veterans Day OR',	'VETERANS DAY HOLIDAY',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:42:48',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	43,	1),
(412,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Mental or physical illness, injury or health condition, need for medical diagnosis, care or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition or need for preventive medical care</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For care of a family member with a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition, care of a family member who needs medical diagnosis, care or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition or care for a family member who needs preventive medical care</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To manage situations involved with being a victim of domestic violence, harassment, sexual assault, or stalking, or having a minor child who is the victim of domestic violence, harassment, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">In the event of a public health emergency</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For purposes of this policy, the term family member includes: </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A spouse</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A same-sex domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&#39;s or a domestic partner&#39;s biological, adoptive, or foster parent or child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A legal guardian or person with whom an employee has or had a parental relationship involving financial or day-to-day responsibility for a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&#39;s parent-in-law or the parent of an employee&#39;s same-sex domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&rsquo;s grandparents or grandchildren</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all employees. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">1 hour of paid leave is <span style=\"border:none\">accrued<span style=\"border:none\"> for every 30 hours worked up to a maximum <span style=\"border:none\">of 40 hours per year</span></span></span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;in 1 year, you may not use more than 40 hours of sick leave. You are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until the 91</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><sup style=\"âvertical-align:\" top=\"\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">st</span></span></sup></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">90 days of employment, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave may be used in hourly increments, unless our payroll program will allow for smaller amounts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;up to 40 hours of accrued and unused sick leave during <span style=\"border:none\">a 12 month period will be carried over into the next year.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick time is capped at 40 hours. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Unused sick leave <span style=\"border:none\">that is rolled over <span style=\"border:none\">will not affect an employee<span style=\"border:none\">&rsquo;s ability to accrue up to 40 hours each&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">year. <span style=\"border:none\">For example, an employee rolls over 20 hours of sick leave and accrues 20 more hours to a cap of 40 hours<span style=\"border:none\"> for the year<span style=\"border:none\">. If the employee uses 20 hours of sick time in that same year, s/he will begin to accrue <span style=\"border:none\">up to <span style=\"border:none\">20 more hours o<span style=\"border:none\">f sick time to total 40 hours of sick time actually accrued in the year.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"> </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends, for any reason, and you are rehired within 180 days of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued sick leave will be<span style=\"border:none\"> reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using sick leave provided you worked at least 90 days previously.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Make-up Time</span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours or shifts during the sa<span style=\"border:none\">me or next pay period in lieu of hours or shifts missed and not have to use paid sick leave benefits. However, we cannot require you to work the extra hours or shifts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;when the use of paid sick leave is foreseeable, you shall provide notice&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">of your intention to take sick time at least 10 days in advance. If the need for paid sick leave is unforeseeable, please provide notice as soon as practicable. We ask that you comply with our rules regarding notifying us of your absences and to make <span style=\"border:none\">an attempt to schedule the use of sick time in a manner that does not unduly disrupt our operations. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave for more than 3 consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">the need for leave from your treating physician. If the need for sick leave is foreseeable and will require you to be off for more than 3 consecutive days, you may be required to provide certification supporting the need for leave from your treating physician&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">prior to sick leave commencing. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">so on your attendance record s</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">o we can be <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">sure to pay you appropriately.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave OR Accrual 10 to 24 ees',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-10-02 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	10,	24,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:44:45',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	30,	1),
(413,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages th<span style=\"border:none\">at would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Mental or physical illness, injury or health condition, need for medical diagnosis, care or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition or need for preventive medical care</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For care of a family member with a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition, care of a family member who needs medical diagnosis, care or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition or care for a family member who needs preventive medical care</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For taking Family and Medical Leave as covered in our policy later in this manual </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To manage situations involved with being a victim of domestic violence, harassment, sexual assault, or stalking, or having a minor child who is the victim of domestic violence, harassment, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">In the event of a public health emergency</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For purposes of this policy, the term family member includes: </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A spouse</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A same-sex domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&#39;s or a domestic partner&#39;s biological, adoptive, or foster parent or child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A legal guardian or person with whom an employee has or had a parental relationship involving financial or day-to-day responsibility for a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&#39;s parent-in-law or the parent of an employee&#39;s same-sex domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&rsquo;s grandparents or grandchildren</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all employees. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">1 hour of paid leave is <span style=\"border:none\">accrued<span style=\"border:none\"> for every 30 hours worked up to a maximum of 40 hours<span style=\"border:none\"> per year</span></span></span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;in 1 year, you may not use more than 40 hours of sick leave. You are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until the 91</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><sup style=\"âvertical-align:\" top=\"\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">st</span></span></sup></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial 90 da<span style=\"border:none\">ys of employment, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave may be used in hourly increments, unless our payroll program will allow for smaller amounts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span> <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">up to 40 hours of accrued and unused sick leave during a 12 month<span style=\"border:none\"> period will be carried over into the next year.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick time is capped at 40 hours. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Unused sick leave <span style=\"border:none\">that is rolled over <span style=\"border:none\">will not affect an employee<span style=\"border:none\">&rsquo;s ability to accrue up to 40 hours each&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">year. <span style=\"border:none\">For example, an employee rolls over 20 hours of sick leave and accrues 20 more hours to a cap of 40 hours<span style=\"border:none\"> for the year<span style=\"border:none\">. If the employee uses 20 hours of sick time in that same year, s/he will begin to accrue <span style=\"border:none\">up to <span style=\"border:none\">20 more hours o<span style=\"border:none\">f sick time to total 40 hours of sick time actually accrued in the year.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"> </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends, for any reason, and you are rehired within 180 days of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued sick leave will be reinstate<span style=\"border:none\">d. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using sick leave provided you worked at least 90 days previously.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Make-up Time</span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours or shifts during the same or next<span style=\"border:none\"> pay period in lieu of hours or shifts missed and not have to use paid sick leave benefits. However, we cannot require you to work the extra hours or shifts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;when the use of paid sick leave is foreseeable, you shall provide notice of yo<span style=\"border:none\">ur intention to take sick time at least 10 days in advance. If the need for paid sick leave is unforeseeable, please provide notice as soon as practicable. We ask that you comply with our rules regarding notifying us of your absences and to make an attempt<span style=\"border:none\"> to schedule the use of sick time in a manner that does not unduly disrupt our operations. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave for more than 3 consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting the ne<span style=\"border:none\">ed for leave from your treating physician. If the need for sick leave is foreseeable and will require you to be off for more than 3 consecutive days, you may be required to provide certification supporting the need for leave from your treating physician prior&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">to sick leave commencing. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on yo<span style=\"border:none\">ur attendance record&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">so we can be <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">sure to pay you appropriately.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave OR Accrual over 25 ees',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-10-02 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	25,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:46:54',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	29,	1),
(414,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>You may be entitled to time off without pay for the following reasons<span>:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Mental or physical illness, injury or health condition, need for medical diagnosis, care or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition or need for preventive medical care</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>For care of a family member with a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition, care of a family member who needs medical diagnosis, care or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition or care for a family member who needs preventive medical care</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>To manage situations involved with being a victim of domestic violence, harassment, sexual assault, or stalking, or having a minor child who is the victim of domestic violence, harassment, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>In the event of a public health emergency</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>For purposes of this policy, the term family member includes: </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>A spouse</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>A same-sex domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>An employee&#39;s or a domestic partner&#39;s biological, adoptive, or foster parent or child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>A legal guardian or person with whom an employee has or had a parental relationship involving financial or day-to-day responsibility for a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>An employee&#39;s parent-in-law or the parent of an employee&#39;s same-sex domestic partner</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>An employee&rsquo;s grandparents or grandchildren</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;unpaid sick leave is provided to all employees. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;</span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>1 hour of unpaid leave is <span>accrued<span> for every 30 hours worked up to a maximum of 40 hours per year</span></span></span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;in 1 year, you may not use more than 40 hours of sick leave. You are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until the 91</span></span></span><span><sup><span style=\"font-size:7.0pt\"><span>st</span></span></sup></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span> <span>calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial 90 days of employment, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Sick leave may be used in hourly increments. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;up to 40 hours of accrued and unused&nbsp;<span>sick leave during a 12 month period will be carried over into the next year. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Sick time is capped at 40 hours. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Unused sick leave <span>that is rolled over <span>will not affect an employee<span>&rsquo;s ability to accrue up to 40 hours each&nbsp;<span>year. <span>For example, an employee rolls over 20 hours of sick leave and accrues 20 more hours to a cap of 40 hours<span> for the year<span>. If the employee uses 20 hours of sick time in that same year, s/he will begin to accrue <span>up to <span>20 more hours o<span>f sick time to total 40 hours of sick time actually accrued in the year.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>If your employment ends, for any reason, and you are rehired within 180 days of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued&nbsp;<span>sick leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using sick leave provided you worked at least 90 days previously.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Make-up Time</span></span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours<span> or shifts during the same or next pay period in lieu of hours or shifts missed and not have to use sick time. However, we cannot require you to work the extra hours or shifts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;when the use of sick leave is foreseeable, you shall provide&nbsp;<span>notice of your intention to take sick time at least 10 days in advance. If the need for sick leave is unforeseeable, please provide notice as soon as practicable. We ask that you comply with our rules regarding notifying us of your absences and to make a<span>n attempt to schedule the use of sick time in a manner that does not unduly disrupt our operations. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;if you are absent on sick leave for more than 3 consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting th<span>e need for leave from your treating physician. If the need for sick leave is foreseeable and will require you to be off for more than 3 consecutive days, you may be required to provide certification supporting the need for leave from your treating physician&nbsp;<span>prior to sick leave commencing. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;the time spent on sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence<span>. Sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave OR Accrual under 10 ees',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-10-02 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	1,	9,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:48:12',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	28,	1),
(415,	'<p style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.05in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you are a victim of a crime, you may be eligible for unpaid leave in order to assist in the prosecution and trial of the accused.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:5.0pt; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Eligible Employees</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you must have worked for us at least 25 hours per week for the 180 days immediately preceding the leave.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:5.0pt; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Request for Leave</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;please provide at least 3 days&rsquo; notice of the need for leave.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:5.0pt; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Documentation</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;please provide any applicable documentation that you have received from law enforcement agencies regarding the scheduled proceedings.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Wages</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;leave is unpaid unless you choose to use any available paid time off benefits during the time off.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Crime Victims Leave OR',	'CRIME VICTIM\'S LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-05 23:49:23',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	373,	1),
(416,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-OH under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OH\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:23:35',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	176,	1),
(417,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. Reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-OH over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OH\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:24:11',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	175,	1),
(418,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When called to serve on jury duty</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty OH',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OH\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:24:53',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	355,	1),
(419,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">A leave of absence may be granted if you are </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">temporarily unable to work due to an illness or disability, pregnancy and pregnancy-related conditions, or<span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"> if you choose to take time off work to fulfill personal obligations due to an exceptional or emergency nature.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">after completing 6 months of employment, <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">you may request a leave of absence</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Exceptions to the <span style=\"border:none\">length of service requirement will be considered at our discretion.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A Request for a Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;<span style=\"border:none\">a request for a leave of absence must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance, or as early as possible for unforeseeable&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">events. Please use the </span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Request for a Leave Absence Form</span></span></i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If the reason for the leave is due to an illness or a disability or </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">pregnancy and pregnancy-related conditions<span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">, you must include medical certification from your health care provider </span></span></span>verifying the need for leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition.</span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Your desire to return to work and a date of return must be agreed upon in writing. We reserve the right to approve or deny any request for a leave of absence.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Length of Leave</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted for a reasonable period of time based on the facts of the situation. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b>Intermittent </b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may take your leave on an intermittent or reduced schedule basis when necessary, at our discretion, based on the needs of the business. If you request intermittent leave or leave on a reduced schedule, we may require that you transfer to a temporary, alternative job for which you are qualified and that better accommodates the intermittent or reduced schedule leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Reporting on Progress</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;<span style=\"border:none\">you are required to report&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">directly to us on your status and your continued intention to return to work a minimum of every 30 days<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">the leave of absence is without pay. </span>However, <span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">you may be required to use any paid time off benefit available. If so, the paid time off will run concurrently with the leave of absence.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage. If applicable, you will be notified of your continuation coverage rights. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;<span style=\"border:none\">so that your return to work can be properly scheduled<span style=\"border:none\">, please provide at least 30 days advance notice in writing of the date you intend to return to work</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you take a leave of absence because of a medical condition, illness, disability, pregnancy and/or childbearing, you must provide a note from y<span style=\"border:none\">our physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties with or without restrictions. Please use the </span></span></span><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Medical Release </span></span></i></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">t</span></span></i></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">o Work Form</span></span></i></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Upon returning from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits, unless a comparable position no longer exists.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Termination</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> of Employment</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;your employment may end if any of the following occurs:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you accept outside or supplemental&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">employment while being on a leave of absence</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">If the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">If the request for a leave of absence was denied and you <span style=\"border:none\">took<span style=\"border:none\"> time off anyway</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"bulletedtext\" style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">When, <span style=\"border:none\">for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Personal LOA OH under 50',	'LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-18 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OH\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:29:06',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	64,	1),
(420,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You are expected to go to the polls before or after regular working hours. When your regular schedule conflicts with voting when the polls are open, we will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide a reasonable amount of time off to vote. We may specify when the time off will be taken. Voting time is unpaid.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting OH',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OH\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:29:47',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	396,	1),
(421,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you have a spouse or a child in the military, you may be provided a<span style=\"border:none\"> leave of absence as outlined below:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">up to 10 days, or 80 hours, whichever is less, of unpaid leave.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Eligible Employee</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;once per calendar year, you may be eligible for leave if all of the following are satisfied:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">You have been employed for at least 12 consecutive months and for at least 1,250 hours in the 12 months immediately preceding commencement of the leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">You are a parent, spouse, or a person who has or had legal custody of a person who is a member of the uniformed services and who is called into active duty in the uniformed services for a period longer than 30 days, or is injured, wounded, or hospitalized while serving on active duty in the uniformed services</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">You provide notice of your intention to take leave under this policy at least 14 days prior to taking leave if the leave is because of a call to active duty</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">You provide notice of your intention to take leave under this policy at least 2 days prior to taking leave if the leave is being taken because of an injury, wound, or hospitalization. If, however, the injury, wound, or hospitalization is critical or life-threatening, you may take leave without providing notice </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">The leave is no more than 2 weeks prior to or 1 week after the deployment date of your spouse, child, or ward or former ward</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">You no longer have any paid time off available other than sick or disability leave, if applicable</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to provide certification from the appropriate military authority to verify your eligibility for Military Family Leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;generally, the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may elect to use any available and applicable paid time off benefit as part of any leave. Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during Military Family leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;upon return from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or a position with equivalent seniority, benefits, pay, and other terms and conditions of employment.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Family Leave OH',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OH\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:30:57',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	237,	1),
(422,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You may be provided an unpaid family and medical leave as outlined below. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eligibility</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family and medical leave, you must have worked: 1) At least 12 months, 2) At least 1,000 hours in the 12 months immediately preceding the leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Exceptions</span></span></u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">:</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> you may be denied family and medical leave if: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You are salaried and rank among the highest-paid 5 percent of our workers or the 7 highest-paid workers, whichever group is larger</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The denial is necessary to prevent substantial and grievous economic injury to our operations</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Reasons for Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you can take family and medical leave for: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Childbirth</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Adoption of a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The serious health condition of your family member</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A serious health condition is defined as an illness, injury, impairment, or physical or mental condition requiring inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential medical care facility or continuing treatment by a health care provider.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;when the need to take leave for childbirth or adoption is foreseeable, you must give us reasonable and practicable advance notice. When you take intermittent or reduced-schedule leave for a family member&#39;s serious illness, you also must provide advance notice whenever reasonable and practicable, and you must attempt to schedule the leave to avoid unduly disrupting operations.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need for leave. Certification for childbirth or adoption must state the date of the child&#39;s birth or placement for adoption. You must provide this medical certification before starting family and medical leave, if possible.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 12 weeks over a 24 month period. Leave taken for the birth or adoption of a child can begin at any time within a year after the date of the birth or adoption.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Intermittent </span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you can take leave intermittently to care for a family member with a serious health condition or for the birth or adoption of a child. Intermittent leave taken for a family member&#39;s serious health condition cannot extend beyond a 12 month period for each episode.&nbsp;We may agree to an intermittent leave schedule for the birth or adoption of a child.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Reduced </span></span></u><u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">leave</span></span></u><u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> schedule</span></span></u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">: </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You can choose to take family and medical leave on a reduced schedule that extends over a period of up to 24 consecutive weeks. To take leave for the birth or adoption of a child on a reduced schedule, you must have our approval.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Interaction with Other </span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Leave</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Mandates</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;state family and medical leave is in addition to and does not abridge your leave rights under the state&#39;s temporary disability benefit law.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are 2 payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you take a leave due to a serious health condition of your own, you must provide a note from your treating physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. The note must also indicate if there are any restrictions pertaining to duties or the number of hours you can work. You may use the <i>Medical Release to Work Form</i> for this purpose.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Upon return from family and medical leave, you will be restored to your former position or to a position with equivalent seniority, status, employment benefits, pay, and other terms and conditions of employment.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you began family and medical leave before we determined that denial of leave is necessary, you must return to work within 10 workdays of receiving notice of the denial.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Exceptions</span></span></u><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you are returning from family and medical leave when a layoff during the leave period would have eliminated your position if you had not been on leave, you are not entitled to reinstatement. However, in this situation, you retain all rights under any applicable layoff and recall system.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Family Medical Leave OH',	'STATE FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OH\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:37:40',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	214,	1),
(423,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose after the birth of a child. Reasonable time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-NJ under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2018-03-20 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:38:25',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	168,	1),
(424,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose after the birth of a child. Reasonable time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk.&nbsp; Break times must be mutually agreed upon by you and us. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere</span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-NJ over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2018-03-20 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:39:08',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	167,	1),
(425,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>When called to serve on jury duty, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty NJ',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:39:48',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	350,	1),
(426,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you suffer from a non-work-related illness or injury, you may be entitled to State Disability Insurance (SDI). SDI provides low cost disability protection if an illness or injury not caused by the job prevents you from working. A small percentage of your wages, up to the prevailing maximum, is deducted each pay period to finance this mandatory insurance. To initiate a claim, contact the nearest State Disability office to request the necessary forms. During the waiting period before disability payments begin, you can use earned and unused sick leave. This will help compensate for any lost wages during the waiting period.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'State Disability Insurance NJ',	'STATE DISABILITY INSURANCE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:40:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	282,	1),
(427,	'<p>The Family Leave Insurance (FLI) program is a monetary benefit, not a leave entitlement benefit. As such, it does not mandate that we provide a leave of absence to you. Whether or not a leave of absence is available to you is determined by federal and/or state laws, or, if those are not applicable, discretionary policies we may have.&nbsp; Please see the leave of absence policies that are applicable to you elsewhere in this manual for more information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you have been granted a leave of absence and the leave meets the FLI eligibility requirements, then you have a right to file for benefits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Covered reasons for FLI are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Care for a family member with a serious health condition<strong> </strong>supported by a certification provided by a health care provider</li>\r\n	<li>Bond with a child<strong> </strong>during the first 12 months after the child&rsquo;s birth, or the first 12 months after the placement of a child for adoption or foster care with you</li>\r\n	<li>If you have a family or household member who is a victim of domestic violence or a sexually violent offense</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For more information or to file for benefits, please contact the New Jersey Department of Labor and Workforce Development. If you need assistance with this, please let us know.<span style=\"font-size:11pt\">&nbsp;âââââ</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Family Leave Insurance NJ',	'PAID FAMILY LEAVE INSURANCE',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:41:21',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	288,	1),
(428,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">If you report to work at the beginning of your work shift but are sent home early, you will be paid for actual hours worked or a minimum of 1 hour of pay, whichever is greater, </span></span><span class=\"A3\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">at your regular rate</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">. <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Pay for time not worked is excluded when computing overtime.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Reporting Time NJ',	'REPORTING TIME PAY',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:42:00',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	24,	0),
(429,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are a victim of domestic violence or a sexually violent offense or have a family or household member who is a victim of domestic violence or a sexually violent offense, you will be provided with up to 20 days of leave from work within 1 year of an incident of domestic or sexual violence. The leave can be taken intermittently or on a reduced schedule so that you can:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Seek medical attention for, or recovery from, physical or psychological injuries caused by domestic or sexual violence to you or your family or household member</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Obtain services from a victim services organization for you or your<span style=\"color:black\"> family or household member</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Obtain psychological or other counseling for you or your<span style=\"color:black\"> family or household member</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Participate in safety planning, temporarily or permanently relocating, or taking other actions to increase the safety of you or your family or household member from future domestic or sexual violence or to ensure economic security</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Seek legal assistance or remedies to ensure the health and safety of you or your family or household member, including preparing for, or participating in, any civil or criminal legal proceeding related to or derived from domestic or sexual violence</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Attend, participate in, or prepare for a criminal or civil court proceeding relating to an incident of domestic or sexual violence of which the individual, or the family or household member of the individual, was a victim</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Leave will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take leave under this policy, you must give us reasonable advance notice of your intention to take leave and must follow our usual time-off request procedures. However, when you cannot provide advance notice because of an emergency or unforeseen circumstance related to domestic or sexual violence, you or your designee must give notice no later than the end of the first day that you take leave.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">You may be required to verify that you or your family or household member is a victim of domestic or sexual violence and that leave is taken for one of the reasons described above. If required, verification must be provided in a timely manner. When the need for time off is unforeseeable, you must provide verification to us within a reasonable time during or after the leave. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">You can provide verification through one or more of the following:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">A domestic violence restraining order or other documentation of equitable relief issued by a court of competent jurisdiction</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">A letter or other written documentation from the county or municipal prosecutor documenting the domestic violence or sexually violent offense</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Documentation of the conviction of a person for the domestic violence or sexually violent offense</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Medical documentation of the domestic violence or sexually violent offense</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Certification from a certified Domestic Violence Specialist or the director of a designated domestic violence agency, or Rape Crisis Center, that you or your family or household member is a victim of domestic violence or a sexually violent offense</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Other documentation or certification of the domestic violence or sexually violent offense provided by a social worker, member of the clergy, shelter worker, or other professional who has assisted you or your family or household member in handling the domestic violence or sexually violent offenses</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency having authority over such matters, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence NJ over 25',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	25,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 20:43:07',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	275,	1),
(430,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request and on the advice of your treating physician.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical</span></b> <span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Certification</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services</span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability NJ',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:03:58',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	87,	1),
(431,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-NV under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:07:53',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	172,	1),
(432,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-NV over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:08:30',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	171,	1),
(433,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When called to serve on jury duty</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"> or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty NV',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:10:07',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	352,	1),
(434,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When your shift is or exceeds 8 hours, </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. A paid working meal period may be permitted if the nature of the work does not permit you to be released from duty. This should occur infrequently and you must sign the <i>On Duty Meal Period/Meal Period Waiver Form</i>.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period NV',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:10:49',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	302,	1),
(435,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We will not terminate, demote, suspend, or otherwise discriminate against anyone who takes time off to participate in their children&rsquo;s school activities. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Eligibility</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&ndash;&ndash;if you are a parent, guardian, or custodian of a child, you are eligible.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Reasons for Time Off</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To attend a conference requested by an administrator of the school attended by your child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To respond to an emergency involving your child while at school</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Request for Time Off</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&ndash;&ndash;you must give as much notice as practicable.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&ndash;&ndash;time off for school activities is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid time off. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'School Activities NV under 50',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:11:36',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	250,	1),
(436,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You may be provided time off without pay to participate in your children&rsquo;s school activities.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Eligibility</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&ndash;&ndash;if you are a parent, guardian, or custodian of a child, you can take time off to attend or participate in any school-related event involving your child.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Request for Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&ndash;&ndash;a request for school activities leave must be submitted in writing at least 5 school days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Supporting documentation verifying the school-related event may be required.&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Length of Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&ndash;&ndash;leave will be granted for up to 4 hours per school year, per child enrolled in public or private school. Leave must be taken in increments of at least 1 hour and at a time that is mutually agreeable by you and us. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If leave has been exhausted, parents, guardians, or custodians of a child will still be allowed to take time off to:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Attend a conference requested by an administrator of the school attended by your child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Respond to an emergency involving your child while at school</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&ndash;&ndash;a school activities leave is without pay. However, you may choose to substitute earned paid time off for unpaid school activities leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'School Activities NV over 50',	'LEAVE FOR SCHOOL ACTIVITIES',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:12:43',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	251,	1),
(437,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You receive a paid rest break of 10 minutes at approximately the middle of every 4 hours of work. The breaks may not be combined and/or added to the lunch period, nor can they be waived to shorten the work day. We ask that you take your breaks when they will not negatively affect customer service. For insurance purposes, we ask that you remain on the premises during rest breaks.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Rest Breaks NV',	'REST BREAKS',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:13:34',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	314,	1),
(438,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If sufficient time allows, you are expected to go to the polls before or after regular working hours. If that is not possible, we will, upon prior request by you before Election Day, provide paid time off to vote according to the following:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">1 hour of leave if the workplace is within 2 miles of the polling place where you vote</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">2 hours if the workplace is more than 2 but less than 10 miles from the polling place where you vote</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">3 hours if the workplace is more than 10 miles from the polling place where you vote</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We may specify when the time off will be taken. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting NV',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:14:19',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	393,	1),
(439,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a condition </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">that is </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">related</span></span></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">to </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">pregnancy</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, including childbirth,<span style=\"border:none\"> lactation or the need to express breast milk, o<span style=\"border:none\">r a related medical condition, </span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical</span></b> <span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Certification</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you with a form for this purpose. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.5in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services</span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability NV over 15',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:15:25',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	88,	1),
(440,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you are a victim of domestic violence, or have a family/household member who is a victim of domestic violence, you will be provided with up to 160 hours of leave in any 12 month period. Leave must be used within 12 months immediately following the date on which a situation of domestic violence occurred and may be taken consecutively or intermittently.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Leave from work is available so that you can:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For the diagnosis, care or treatment of a health condition related to an act which constitutes domestic violence committed against you or your <span style=\"color:black\">family/household </span>member </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To obtain counseling or assistance related to an act which constitutes domestic violence committed against you or your <span style=\"color:black\">family/household </span>member </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To participate in any court proceedings related to an act which constitutes domestic violence committed against you or your <span style=\"color:black\">family/household </span>member </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list -.05in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">To establish a safety plan, including, without limitation, any action to increase the safety of you or your <span style=\"color:black\">family/household </span>member from a future act which constitutes domestic violence </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Eligibility</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you must have been employed with us for at least 90 days.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Leave will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">If you need to take leave under this policy, you must provide at least 48 hours&rsquo; advance notice of your intention to take leave, unless providing such notice is not practicable. When the need for leave is unforeseeable, you must provide certification to us within a reasonable time after the absence. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">You may be required to verify that you or your family/household member is a victim of domestic violence and the leave is for one of the purposes outlined above. If required, verification must be provided in a timely manner. You can provide verification through one or more of the following:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A police report</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A copy of an application for an order for protection</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An affidavit from an organization which provides services to victims of domestic violence</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .2in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Documentation from a physician</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Accommodation</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">upon request, we will provide reasonable accommodation to ensure your safety while at work. We shall work together with you to quickly determine what, if any, accommodation we can make that will not create an undue hardship on the business. Such accommodation may include:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Transfer or reassignment</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Modified schedule</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Changed work telephone</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Changed work station</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Prior to making an accommodation, we may require documentation that confirms or supports the need of an accommodation. If, at some point, circumstances change and you determine you need a new accommodation, please inform us as soon as possible. Also, please let us know when you no longer need the accommodation.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to in writing by you or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence NV',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:17:19',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	277,	1),
(441,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas, as feasible, for this purpose for up to 3 years after the birth of a child. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when possible. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk unless doing so would create an undue hardship to the business. This additional time off must be mutually agreed upon by you and us.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-NY under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:35:33',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	174,	1),
(442,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas, as feasible, for this purpose for up to 3 years after the birth of a child. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when possible. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This additional time off must be mutually agreed upon by you and us.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-NY over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:36:13',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	173,	1),
(443,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence<!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span>xe &quot;Leave Of Absence&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></span><![endif]-->. You will be paid $40 a day or your regular daily wage, whichever is less, for the first 3 days of jury duty. Wages are paid only when you serve on jury duty on a regular scheduled workday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are subpoenaed to appear in court as a victim or as a witness, you will be given a Leave of Absence. You will not be paid while attending court in this manner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty NY over 10',	'JURY DUTY/WITNESS/VICTIM RIGHTS',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	10,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:37:23',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	354,	1),
(444,	'<p>When called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are called to serve on jury duty or as a witness, you will be given a Leave of Absence<!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span>xe &quot;Leave Of Absence&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></span><![endif]-->. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty or for attending court as a victim or witness.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty NY under 10',	'JURY/WITNESS DUTY',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	1,	9,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:38:13',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	353,	1),
(445,	'<p style=\"margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When your shift exceeds 6 hours and starts before 11:00am and continues through 2:00pm, </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes between 11:00am and 2:00pm. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. There are two exceptions: 1) You may (with our permission) voluntarily agree to waive the right to a meal period, provided the work day is no more than 6 hours; 2) A paid working meal period may be permitted if the nature of the work does not permit you to be released from duty. The latter should occur infrequently. For both exceptions, you must sign the <i>On Duty Meal Period/Meal Period Waiver Form</i>.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period NY',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:38:49',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	303,	1),
(446,	'<p>We will, upon prior request by you at least 2 days before Election Day, provide enough time off to enable you to vote. Wages, for up to 3 hours, will be paid. Voting time is not included for overtime calculation purposes.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unless other arrangements are mutually agreed upon, time off will be added to the beginning or end of the shift.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Not less than 10 working days before every election, we shall post conspicuously a notice setting forth the provisions of this section. Such notice shall be kept posted until the close of the polls on Election Day.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Voting NY',	'VOTING',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:39:28',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	394,	1),
(447,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you suffer from a non-work-related illness or injury, you may be entitled to State Disability Insurance (SDI). SDI provides low cost disability protection if an illness or injury not caused by the job prevents you from working. A small percentage of your wages, up to the prevailing maximum, is deducted each pay period to finance this mandatory insurance. To initiate a claim, contact the nearest State Disability office to request the necessary forms. During the waiting period before disability payments begin, you can take earned and unused sick leave. This will help to compensate for any lost wages during the waiting period.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'State Disability Insurance NY',	'STATE DISABILITY INSURANCE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:40:22',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	283,	1),
(448,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">If you report to work at the beginning of your work shift but are sent home early, you will be paid for actual hours worked or a minimum of 4 hours of pay, whichever is greater, </span></span><span class=\"A3\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">at your regular rate</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Pay for time not worked is excluded when computing overtime.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Reporting Time NY',	'REPORTING TIME PAY',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:41:06',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	25,	0),
(449,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Military family leave can be</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"> requested by you when you are the spouse of a person who is a member of the armed forces of the United States, National Guard, or Reserves who has been deployed during a period of military conflict to a combat theater or combat zone of operations. Such leave shall only be used when your spouse is on leave from the armed forces of the United States, National Guard, or Reserves while deployed during a period of military conflict to a combat theater or combat zone of operations. If you are in this situation, you <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border:none; font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">may be provided a leave of absence as outlined below:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">up to 10 days of leave during the time federal or state deployment orders are in effect.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">Qualified Employee</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you are qualified for leave if you work 20 or more hours per week. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;leave is unpaid.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">You will be able to continue applicable benefits (such as health insurance) at your own expense for the duration of the leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Reinstatement Rights</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you will be reinstated to your position held prior to taking leave, or to a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Military Family Leave NY',	'MILITARY FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	20,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:49:57',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	236,	1),
(450,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You <span style=\"border:none\">may be eligible for an unpaid leave of absence if you wish to donate blood or your bone marrow to another person. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eligible Employees</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you must work an average of 20 or more hours per week.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;t<span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">he following outlines the leave of absence avail<span style=\"border:none\">able for each purpose:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Blood</span></span></b></span><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\"> Donation</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">3 hours of leave in any 12 month period for an off-premises blood donation</span><span style=\"color:black\">. You may be required to provide proof of the blood donation</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Bone Marrow Donation</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;for each request, the amount of leave shall be determined by the physician and may not exceed 24 hours. <span style=\"color:black\">Medical verification from a physician may be required to confirm the purpose and length of each leave requested by you to donate bone marrow</span>&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance<span style=\"color:black\">, or as soon as possible for unforeseeable events.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"topic\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"topic\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\"><strong>Reinstatement to Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that work can be properly scheduled. Upon returning from leave you will be reinstated <span style=\"color:black\">to the position held before the leave began, or a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Bone Marrow NY',	'BLOOD AND BONE MARROW DONATION LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	20,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:52:03',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	73,	1),
(451,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you our <i>Medical Certification Form</i> for this purpose.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability NY',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	4,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:53:03',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	89,	1),
(452,	'<p>You will be provided paid family leave as outlined below.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility for Employee Working 20 Hours or More Per </strong><strong>Week</strong>&mdash;to qualify for paid family leave, you must have been employed at least 26 consecutive weeks preceding the first full day of family leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility for Employee Working less than 20 Hours Per </strong><strong>Week</strong>&mdash;to qualify for paid family leave, you must have worked at least 175 days preceding the first full day of family leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Time spent on paid time off can be counted toward your eligibility determination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paid family leave may be granted for the following reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The birth of a child*</li>\r\n	<li>The placement of a child for adoption or foster care*</li>\r\n	<li>Baby bonding*</li>\r\n	<li>To provide care or companionship to a spouse, domestic partner, child, parent, parent-in-law, grandparent, or grandchild due to the diagnosis or occurrence of a serious health condition</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>*Leave must be taken within one year of the occurrence of a qualifying reason.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A serious health condition is an illness, injury, impairment, or physical or mental condition that involves inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential health care facility; or continuing treatment or&nbsp;continuing supervision by a health care provider.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you and your spouse are both employed by us, only one of you at a time will receive Paid Family Leave to bond with the same child or care for the same family member.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;paid family leave benefits increase over a period of several years as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2020 = 10 weeks</li>\r\n	<li>2021 = 12 weeks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notification of </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;notification of time off taken under paid family leave must be submitted at least 30 days in advance, or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please submit your request to take Paid Family Leave to your manager.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intermittent </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;leave may be taken on an intermittent basis when necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;you may be required to provide appropriate documentation of the need for leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Paid Family Leave </strong><strong>Funding</strong>&mdash;this program is funded through an employee payroll tax that is determined by the state of New York.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Payments to you while on leave are based on a percentage of the &ldquo;New York State&rsquo;s Average Weekly Wage (NYSAWW),&rdquo; which is determined annually by the state of New York.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Paid Family Leave Insurance </strong><strong>Premiums</strong>&mdash;we maintain insurance to provide Paid Family Leave. Some or all of the cost of the premiums for this coverage may be deducted from your paycheck. We will notify you of this deduction, and you may be asked to sign a <em>Payroll Deduction Authorization</em> <em>Form</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Interaction with Other Leave </strong><strong>Mandates</strong>&mdash;you may not receive short-term disability and Paid Family Leave benefits at the same time. You may not take more than 26 combined weeks of short-term disability and Paid Family Leave in a 52-week period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are unable to work and qualify for workers&rsquo; compensation benefits, you may not use Paid Family Leave benefits at the same time as you are receiving workers&rsquo; compensation benefits. If you are receiving reduced earnings, you may be eligible for Paid Family Leave. Please check with us on eligibility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong>&mdash;health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) prepayment before the leave, 2) pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. Failure to pay your share of the health insurance premium may result in a loss of coverage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may choose to substitute any available paid time off to receive full wages during paid family leave. While on Paid Family Leave, you will not accrue paid time off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;when you return from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For more details about this policy, including how to apply for benefits, please ask your manager.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Paid Family Leave NY under 50',	'PAID FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:55:52',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	57,	1),
(453,	'<p>You will be provided paid family leave as outlined below.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility for Employee Working 20 Hours or More Per Week</strong><!--[if supportFields]><bstyle=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span></span></b><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'>xe&quot;Eligibility&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><bstyle=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></span></b><![endif]-->&mdash;to qualify for paid family leave, you must have been employed at least 26 consecutive weeks preceding the first full day of family leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility for Employee Working less than 20 Hours Per Week</strong><!--[if supportFields]><bstyle=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span></span></b><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'>xe &quot;Eligibility&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><bstyle=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></span></b><![endif]-->&mdash;to qualify for paid family leave, you must have worked at least 175 days preceding the first full day of family leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Time spent on paid time off can be counted toward your eligibility determination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paid family leave may be granted for the following reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The birth of a child*</li>\r\n	<li>The placement of a child for adoption or foster care*</li>\r\n	<li>Baby bonding*</li>\r\n	<li>To provide care or companionship to a spouse, domestic partner, child, parent, parent-in-law, grandparent, or grandchild due to the diagnosis or occurrence of a serious health condition</li>\r\n	<li>Active duty deployment for your spouse, domestic partner, child or parent, as defined in the Federal Family and Medical Leave (FMLA) policy regarding &ldquo;qualifying exigency&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>*Leave must be taken within one year of the occurrence of a qualifying reason.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A serious health condition is an illness, injury, impairment, or physical or mental condition that involves inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential health care facility; or continuing treatment or&nbsp;continuing supervision by a health care provider.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you and your spouse are both employed by us, only one of you at a time will receive Paid Family Leave to bond with the same child or care for the same family member.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>&mdash;paid family leave benefits increase over a period of several years as follows:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2020 = 10 weeks</li>\r\n	<li>2021 = 12 weeks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notification of </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;notification of time off taken under paid family leave must be submitted at least 30 days in advance, or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please submit your request to take Paid Family Leave to your manager.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intermittent </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;leave may be taken on an intermittent basis when necessary.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;you may be required to provide appropriate documentation of the need for leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Paid Family Leave </strong><strong>Funding</strong>&mdash;this program is funded through an employee payroll tax that is determined by the state of New York.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Payments to you while on leave are based on a percentage of the &ldquo;New York State&rsquo;s Average Weekly Wage (NYSAWW),&rdquo; which is determined annually by the state of New York.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Paid Family Leave Insurance </strong><strong>Premiums</strong>&mdash;we maintain insurance to provide Paid Family Leave. Some or all of the cost of the premiums for this coverage may be deducted from your paycheck. We will notify you of this deduction, and you may be asked to sign a <em>Payroll Deduction Authorization</em> <em>Form</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Interaction with Other Leave </strong><strong>Mandates</strong>&mdash;Paid Family Leave can be taken if you are eligible for time off under the provisions of the Family and Medical Leave Act (FMLA). Paid Family Leave will run concurrently with designated FMLA leave when the reason for leave qualifies under both Paid Family Leave and FMLA. If you are eligible, you must apply for both Paid Family Leave and FMLA.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may not receive short-term disability and Paid Family Leave benefits at the same time. You may not take more than 26 combined weeks of short-term disability and Paid Family Leave in a 52-week period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are unable to work and qualify for workers&rsquo; compensation benefits, you may not use Paid Family Leave benefits at the same time as you are receiving workers&rsquo; compensation benefits. If you are receiving reduced earnings, you may be eligible for Paid Family Leave. Please check with us on eligibility.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong>&mdash;health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) prepayment before the leave, 2) pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. Failure to pay your share of the health insurance premium may result in a loss of coverage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to use your available paid time off benefit during paid family leave. Unless time off under Paid Family Leave is concurrent with FMLA, you will not accrue paid time off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;when you return from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For more details about this policy, including how to apply for benefits, please ask your manager.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Paid Family Leave NY over 50',	'PAID FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 21:57:28',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	58,	1),
(454,	'<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-NH under 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NH\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:00:43',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	166,	1),
(455,	'<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-NH over 50',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NH\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:01:20',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	165,	1),
(456,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When called to serve on jury duty</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">, you are to submit a copy of the summons to us immediately. You are also required to submit certification from the court listing the actual days of service. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you are called to serve on jury duty, you will be given a Leave of Absence</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">. Wages will not be paid while on jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you are released before the end of the workday, you are to return to work for the balance of the day.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">We reserve the right to contact the court to request a release from jury duty.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Jury Duty NH',	'JURY DUTY',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NH\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:02:05',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	349,	1),
(457,	'<p style=\"margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">When your shift exceeds 5 hours, </span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">you will be scheduled for an unpaid meal period of at least 30 minutes. You may not work through a mandatory meal period or be allowed to shorten the work day by a corresponding period of time. There are two exceptions: 1) You may (with our permission) voluntarily agree to waive the right to a meal period, provided the work day is no more than 5 hours; 2) A paid working meal period may be permitted if the nature of the work does not permit you to be released from duty. The latter should occur infrequently. For both exceptions, you must sign the <i>On Duty Meal Period/Meal Period Waiver Form</i>.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Meal Period NH',	'MEAL PERIOD',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NH\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:02:35',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	300,	1),
(458,	'<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When you report to work at the beginning of your work shift but are sent home early, you will be paid for actual hours worked or a minimum of 2 hours of pay, whichever is greater,</span></span><span class=\"A3\" style=\"font-family:ProseAntique,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> at your regular rate</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">. This will not apply to those who report to work after we have made a good faith effort to inform you to refrain from reporting to work. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you report to work after our attempts to notify you were unsuccessful or if we are prevented from making notification for any reason, you shall perform whatever duties are assigned by us at the time you report to work.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Pay for time not work<span style=\"border:none\">ed is excluded when computing overtime.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	3,	'Reporting Time NH',	'REPORTING TIME PAY',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NH\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:03:14',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'enabled',	23,	0),
(459,	'<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:.5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Pregnancy leave is provided to you when you are temporarily unable to work due to a disability caused by pregnancy, childbirth, or related medical conditions.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">With a written request</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> from your healthcare provider that you be transferred to a less strenuous or hazardous position, we will do our best to accommodate you. If accommodation is not possible, and you are not able to continue your normal job responsibilities, you may be asked to go on pregnancy leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. Please use the <i>Leave Of Absence Application Form</i> for this purpose.<i> </i></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Healthcare Professional&rsquo;s</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;any request for a pregnancy-related leave must be accompanied with a certified healthcare professional&rsquo;s certificate. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;as determined by your physician, a reasonable leave of absence will be granted based on your physical condition and job requirements. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Intermittent </span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Leave/Reduced Work Schedule</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;is allowable when medically necessary.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reporting on Progress</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you are required to report directly to us every 30 days on your health status and your intent to return to work.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may use any earned paid time off to run concurrent with the pregnancy leave. Benefits are not earned during the leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage (see continuation policy, if applicable, at the end of this manual). </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during pregnancy leave. When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Pregnancy Leave of Absence Ends When</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You are released for full or partial duty. You must provide a physician&rsquo;s statement in writing indicating your fitness to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We receive satisfactory medical evidence that you are unable to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You directly or indirectly inform us (for example, by accepting employment elsewhere, moving out of state, etc.) that you do not intend to return to work</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You have been on a medical leave of absence for the approved time</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Returning from Pregnancy Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if you wish to return to work sooner than the date agreed upon at the start of the leave, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled. You will be reinstated no later than the agreed upon date or earlier if possible. However, business reasons may prevent us from having you return before the agreed upon date.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you must provide a completed <i>Medical Release to Work</i> <i>Form</i>, or an equivalent note from your healthcare provider, verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. This must be received on or before the date you are scheduled to return from leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You will be reinstated to your former position or a position of comparable status and pay, without loss of accumulated service credits and privileges, unless business necessity makes this impossible or unreasonable.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .75in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Leave NH',	'PREGNANCY LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NH\"]',	6,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:04:23',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	102,	1),
(460,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking, or have a family/household member who is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking, you will be provided with up to 4 workweeks of leave in any 12 month period. Leave from work is available so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek medical attention for, or recover from, physical or psychological injuries resulting from domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking to you or your family/household member</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain services from a victim services organization for you or your family/household member</li>\r\n	<li>Acquire psychological or other counseling for you or your family/household member</li>\r\n	<li>Participate in safety planning, temporarily or permanently relocating, or taking other actions to increase the safety of you or your family/household member from future domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking or to ensure economic security&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain legal assistance or remedies to ensure the health and safety of you or your family/household member, including preparing for or participating in any civil or criminal legal proceedings related to or derived from domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Leave will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before the leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are 2 payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. Failure to pay your share of the health insurance premium may result in a loss of coverage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take leave under this policy, you must provide at least 48 hours&rsquo; advance notice of your intention to take leave, unless providing such notice is not practicable. When the need for leave is unforeseeable, you must provide certification to us within a reasonable time after the absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to verify that you or your family/household member is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking and the leave is for one of the purposes outlined above. If required, verification must be provided in a timely manner. You can provide verification through one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A sworn statement by you</li>\r\n	<li>A police or court record&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation from an employee, agent, or volunteer of a victim services organization, an attorney, a member of the clergy, or a medical or other professional from whom you or your family/household member has sought assistance in addressing domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking and the effect of the violence</li>\r\n	<li>Other corroborating evidence</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to in writing by you or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence IL 14 and under',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	1,	14,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:06:36',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	264,	1),
(461,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking, or have a family/household member who is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking, you will be provided with up to 8 workweeks of leave in any 12 month period. Leave from work is available so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek medical attention for, or recover from, physical or psychological injuries resulting from domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking to you or your family/household member</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain services from a victim services organization for you or your family/household member</li>\r\n	<li>Acquire psychological or other counseling for you or your family/household member</li>\r\n	<li>Participate in safety planning, temporarily or permanently relocating, or taking other actions to increase the safety of you or your family/household member from future domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking or to ensure economic security&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain legal assistance or remedies to ensure the health and safety of you or your family/household member, including preparing for or participating in any civil or criminal legal proceedings related to or derived from domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Leave will be unpaid unless you choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before the leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are 2 payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. Failure to pay your share of the health insurance premium may result in a loss of coverage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take leave under this policy, you must provide at least 48 hours&rsquo; advance notice of your intention to take leave, unless providing such notice is not practicable. When the need for leave is unforeseeable, you must provide certification to us within a reasonable time after the absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to verify that you or your family/household member is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking and the leave is for one of the purposes outlined above. If required, verification must be provided in a timely manner. You can provide verification through one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A sworn statement by you</li>\r\n	<li>A police or court record&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation from an employee, agent, or volunteer of a victim services organization, an attorney, a member of the clergy, or a medical or other professional from whom you or your family/household member has sought assistance in addressing domestic violence, sexual assault, gender violence, or stalking and the effect of the violence</li>\r\n	<li>Other corroborating evidence</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to in writing by you or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon returning from leave you will be restored to the position held at the time leave began or to an equivalent position if the former position is no longer available due to the needs of the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence IL 15 to 49',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	15,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:07:32',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	265,	1),
(462,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth<span style=\"border:none\">, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request and on the advice of your treating physician.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship. In addition, the reasonable accommodation cannot result in:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Us creating additional employment that we would not have otherwise created</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">The termination of another employee</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Transferring an employee with more seniority than you </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Promoting any employee who is not qualified to perform the job</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical</span></span></b> <span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Certification</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose. The certification must include a description of the reasonable accommodation, the date the reasonable accommodation became medically advisable, and the probable duration of the reasonable accommodation. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability IL',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:08:54',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	81,	1),
(463,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you suffer the loss of child, you may be eligible for an unpaid leave of absence as outlined below:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Eligibility</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid child bereavement leave, you must have worked: 1) at least 12 months within the previous 7 years*, 2) at least 1,250 hours in the 12 months immediately preceding the request for leave.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">*Military service or other written agreements may extend this length of time</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">maximum of 2 weeks (10 working days) in a 12 month period.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\">In the event of the death of more than one child, you may be eligible for 2 weeks of bereavement leave per child up to a total of 6 weeks in a 12 month period. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\">Your time off may run concurrently with any leave available under the Federal Family and Medical Leave Act.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\">Substitution of paid time off benefits</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">&mdash;<span style=\"color:black\">you may choose to use any paid time off benefit available at that time in-lieu-of unpaid time off. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\">Reasons for Leave</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">&mdash;leave may be taken for the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">To attend the funeral or alternative to a funeral of a child</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">To make arrangements necessitated by the death of the child</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">To grieve the death of the child</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\">Leave must be completed within 60 days after the date on which you receive notice of the death of the child.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\">Definitions</span></span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">&mdash;for purposes of this policy, child is defined as your son or daughter who is a biological, adopted, or foster child; a stepchild; a legal ward; or a child of a person standing <i>in loco parentis</i>.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">Notification of Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">&mdash;you shall provide us with at least 48 hours&rsquo; advance notice of the need for child bereavement leave, unless providing such notice is not reasonable and practicable. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">We may ask that you provide reasonable documentation to support the need for leave. Such documentation may be:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">A death certificate</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">A published obituary </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Written verification of death, burial, or memorial services from a mortuary, funeral home, burial society, crematorium, religious institution, or government agency</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Child Bereavement IL',	'CHILD BEREAVEMENT LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:10:25',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	52,	1),
(464,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You may use your personal sick leave benefit provided by us for absences due to an illness, injury, or medical appointment of your child, spouse, sibling, parent, mother-in-law, father-in-law, grandchild, grandparent, or stepparent, for reasonable periods of time as your attendance may be necessary, on the same terms upon which you are able to use sick leave benefits for your own illness or injury. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Use of available sick leave due to an illness, injury, or medical appointment of your child, spouse, sibling, parent, mother-in-law, father-in-law, grandchild, grandparent, or stepparent is limited to the equivalent of the amount of sick leave benefit that is earned in a 6 month period. For example, if you earn 32 hours of sick leave in a 12 month period, sick leave under this Act is limited to 16 hours in year.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"topic\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:14pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Definitions</span><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">&mdash;for purposes of this policy, sick leave benefit means time accrued and available to you to be used as a result of absence from work due to personal illness, injury, or medical appointment.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave Act IL',	'SICK LEAVE ACT',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:12:57',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	40,	1),
(465,	'<p>Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your own physical or mental illness, injury, or medical condition</li>\r\n	<li>Your need to obtain professional medical diagnosis or care, or preventive medical care</li>\r\n	<li>Caring for a child, parent, spouse, domestic partner, or any other family member who has any of the conditions or needs for diagnosis or care described above</li>\r\n	<li>You or a family member needs any of the following considerations related to being a victim of stalking, domestic violence, or sexual abuse:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Acquire social or legal services</li>\r\n		<li>Seek medical attention to recover from physical or psychological injury or disability caused by domestic violence or sexual abuse</li>\r\n		<li>Obtain services from a victim services organization</li>\r\n		<li>Obtain psychological or other counseling</li>\r\n		<li>Temporarily or permanently relocate</li>\r\n		<li>Take legal action, including preparing for or participating in any civil or criminal legal proceeding related to or resulting from the domestic violence or sexual abuse</li>\r\n		<li>Take other actions to enhance the physical, psychological, or economic health or safety of you or your family member or to enhance the safety of those who associate or work with you</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For the purposes of this policy, the definition of a family member is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A spouse, including the person identified by you as your domestic partner</li>\r\n	<li>The parents of a spouse</li>\r\n	<li>Children, including foster children and grandchildren</li>\r\n	<li>The spouses of children</li>\r\n	<li>Parents</li>\r\n	<li>Your siblings</li>\r\n	<li>The spouses of your siblings</li>\r\n	<li>A child who lives with you and for whom you permanently assume and discharge parental responsibility</li>\r\n	<li>A person with whom you share or have shared, for not less than the preceding 12 months, a mutual residence and with whom you maintain a committed relationship</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Benefit </strong><strong>Year</strong>&mdash;January 1 to December 31.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;sick leave is provided to all employees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Earning Sick Leave</strong>&mdash;1 hour of sick leave is accrued for every 87 hours worked up to 3 days* per calendar year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*A day means the length of the employee&rsquo;s customary work day or work shift. For example, a customary work day or work shift of 8 hours means 3 days is 24 hours. A customary work day or work shift of 6 hours means 3 days is 18 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sick leave shall be earned in accordance with our established pay periods.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using </strong><strong>Sick Leave</strong>&mdash;you begin accruing sick leave upon hire, but you may not access the paid sick leave until 90 days of service is completed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may not use, in 1 calendar year, more than 3 days of sick leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;any accrued and unused sick leave during a 12 month period will be carried over into the next calendar year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your employment ends, for any reason, after you have completed 90 days of employment and you are rehired within 12 months of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued sick leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using accrued sick leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Make-up Time</strong>&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours or shifts during the same or next pay period in lieu of hours or shifts missed, and not have to use paid sick leave benefits. However, we cannot require you to work the extra hours or shifts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notice of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;you must make a reasonable effort to schedule paid sick leave in a manner that does not unduly disrupt daily operations. Paid leave shall be provided upon your written request. The request shall include a reason for the absence involved and the expected duration of the paid leave. If the paid leave is foreseeable, the request must be provided at least 10 days, or as early as possible, in advance of the paid leave. If the paid leave is unforeseeable, an oral request for paid leave shall be provided prior to the start of the work shift for which the paid leave is requested. In the case of an emergency, we must be notified prior to the start of the next work shift or within 24 hours of the onset of the emergency, whichever occurs sooner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave for 3 or more consecutive days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting the need for leave. Reasonable certification may include:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A signed document from a health care provider confirming your illness</li>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you were a victim of stalking, domestic violence, or sexual abuse</li>\r\n	<li>A court order</li>\r\n	<li>A signed statement from a victim and witness advocate, or domestic violence counselor affirming that you are involved in legal action related to stalking, domestic violence, or sexual abuse</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Overtime</strong>&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attendance </strong><strong>Record</strong>&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for the time out ill and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record so we can be sure to pay you for the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Leave of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not accrued while on a leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employee&#39;s Return to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;notice of your return to work after an illness needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick Leave upon </strong><strong>Termination</strong>&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave DC under 25',	'PAID SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	1,	24,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:15:32',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	18,	1),
(466,	'<p>Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your own physical or mental illness, injury, or medical condition</li>\r\n	<li>Your need to obtain professional medical diagnosis or care, or preventive medical care</li>\r\n	<li>Caring for a child, parent, spouse, domestic partner, or any other family member who has any of the conditions or needs for diagnosis or care described above</li>\r\n	<li>You or a family member needs any of the following considerations related to being a victim of stalking, domestic violence, or sexual abuse:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Acquire social or legal services</li>\r\n		<li>Seek medical attention to recover from physical or psychological injury or disability caused by domestic violence or sexual abuse</li>\r\n		<li>Obtain services from a victim services organization</li>\r\n		<li>Obtain psychological or other counseling</li>\r\n		<li>Temporarily or permanently relocate</li>\r\n		<li>Take legal action, including preparing for or participating in any civil or criminal legal proceeding related to or resulting from the domestic violence or sexual abuse</li>\r\n		<li>Take other actions to enhance the physical, psychological, or economic health or safety of you or your family member or to enhance the safety of those who associate or work with you</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For the purposes of this policy, the definition of a family member is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A spouse, including the person identified by you as your domestic partner</li>\r\n	<li>The parents of a spouse</li>\r\n	<li>Children, including foster children and grandchildren</li>\r\n	<li>The spouses of children</li>\r\n	<li>Parents</li>\r\n	<li>Your siblings</li>\r\n	<li>The spouses of your siblings</li>\r\n	<li>A child who lives with you and for whom you permanently assume and discharge parental responsibility</li>\r\n	<li>A person with whom you share or have shared, for not less than the preceding 12 months, a mutual residence and with whom you maintain a committed relationship</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Benefit </strong><strong>Year</strong>&mdash;January 1 to December 31.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;sick leave is provided to all employees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Earning Sick Leave</strong>&mdash;1 hour of sick leave is accrued for every 43 hours worked up to 5 days* per calendar year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*A day means the length of the employee&rsquo;s customary work day or work shift. For example, a customary work day or work shift of 8 hours means 3 days is 24 hours. A customary work day or work shift of 6 hours means 3 days is 18 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sick leave shall be earned in accordance with our established pay periods.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using </strong><strong>Sick Leave</strong>&mdash;you begin accruing sick leave upon hire, but you may not access the paid sick leave until 90 days of service is completed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may not use, in 1 calendar year, more than 5 days of sick leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;any accrued and unused sick leave during a 12 month period will be carried over into the next calendar year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your employment ends, for any reason, after you have completed 90 days of employment and you are rehired within 12 months of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued sick leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using accrued sick leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Make-up Time</strong>&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours or shifts during the same or next pay period in lieu of hours or shifts missed, and not have to use paid sick leave benefits. However, we cannot require you to work the extra hours or shifts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notice of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;you must make a reasonable effort to schedule paid sick leave in a manner that does not unduly disrupt daily operations. Paid leave shall be provided upon your written request. The request shall include a reason for the absence involved and the expected duration of the paid leave. If the paid leave is foreseeable, the request must be provided at least 10 days, or as early as possible, in advance of the paid leave. If the paid leave is unforeseeable, an oral request for paid leave shall be provided prior to the start of the work shift for which the paid leave is requested. In the case of an emergency, we must be notified prior to the start of the next work shift or within 24 hours of the onset of the emergency, whichever occurs sooner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave for 3 or more consecutive days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting the need for leave. Reasonable certification may include:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A signed document from a health care provider confirming your illness</li>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you were a victim of stalking, domestic violence, or sexual abuse</li>\r\n	<li>A court order</li>\r\n	<li>A signed statement from a victim and witness advocate, or domestic violence counselor affirming that you are involved in legal action related to stalking, domestic violence, or sexual abuse</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Overtime</strong>&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attendance </strong><strong>Record</strong>&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for the time out ill and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record so we can be sure to pay you for the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Leave of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not accrued while on a leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employee&#39;s Return to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;notice of your return to work after an illness needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick Leave upon </strong><strong>Termination</strong>&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave DC 25 to 99',	'PAID SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	25,	99,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:16:33',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	19,	1),
(467,	'<p>Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your own physical or mental illness, injury, or medical condition</li>\r\n	<li>Your need to obtain professional medical diagnosis or care, or preventive medical care</li>\r\n	<li>Caring for a child, parent, spouse, domestic partner, or any other family member who has any of the conditions or needs for diagnosis or care described above</li>\r\n	<li>You or a family member needs any of the following considerations related to being a victim of stalking, domestic violence, or sexual abuse:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Acquire social or legal services</li>\r\n		<li>Seek medical attention to recover from physical or psychological injury or disability caused by domestic violence or sexual abuse</li>\r\n		<li>Obtain services from a victim services organization</li>\r\n		<li>Obtain psychological or other counseling</li>\r\n		<li>Temporarily or permanently relocate</li>\r\n		<li>Take legal action, including preparing for or participating in any civil or criminal legal proceeding related to or resulting from the domestic violence or sexual abuse</li>\r\n		<li>Take other actions to enhance the physical, psychological, or economic health or safety of you or your family member or to enhance the safety of those who associate or work with you</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For the purposes of this policy, the definition of a family member is:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A spouse, including the person identified by you as your domestic partner</li>\r\n	<li>The parents of a spouse</li>\r\n	<li>Children, including foster children and grandchildren</li>\r\n	<li>The spouses of children</li>\r\n	<li>Parents</li>\r\n	<li>Your siblings</li>\r\n	<li>The spouses of your siblings</li>\r\n	<li>A child who lives with you and for whom you permanently assume and discharge parental responsibility</li>\r\n	<li>A p