make a reasonable effort to schedule paid sick leave in a manner that does not unduly disrupt daily operations. Paid leave shall be provided upon your written request. The request shall include a reason for the absence involved and the expected duration of the paid leave. If the paid leave is foreseeable, the request must be provided at least 10 days, or as early as possible, in advance of the paid leave. If the paid leave is unforeseeable, an oral request for paid leave shall be provided prior to the start of the work shift for which the paid leave is requested. In the case of an emergency, we must be notified prior to the start of the next work shift or within 24 hours of the onset of the emergency, whichever occurs sooner.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave for 3 or more consecutive days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting the need for leave. Reasonable certification may include:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A signed document from a health care provider confirming your illness</li>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you were a victim of stalking, domestic violence, or sexual abuse</li>\r\n	<li>A court order</li>\r\n	<li>A signed statement from a victim and witness advocate, or domestic violence counselor affirming that you are involved in legal action related to stalking, domestic violence, or sexual abuse</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information you provide confidentially. Information will only be disclosed if requested or consented to by you, as ordered by the court or administrative agency, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Overtime</strong>&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attendance </strong><strong>Record</strong>&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for the time out ill and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record so we can be sure to pay you for the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Leave of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not accrued while on a leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employee&#39;s Return to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;notice of your return to work after an illness needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick Leave upon </strong><strong>Termination</strong>&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave DC over 100',	'PAID SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	100,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:17:33',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	20,	1),
(468,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You will be provided an unpaid family and medical leave as outlined below. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"margin-right:.5in; text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"margin-right:.5in; text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family and medical leave, employees must have worked: 1) At least 12 months without a break in employment, and 2) At least 1,000 hours in the 12 months immediately preceding the request for leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Reasons for Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you can take family and medical leave for: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The birth, adoption, or foster placement of a child, or the placement of a child for whom you are assuming permanent parental responsibility</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Your own serious health condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The serious health condition of your family member</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A serious health condition is defined as a physical or mental illness, injury, or impairment requiring inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential health care facility or continuing treatment by a health care provider or other competent individual.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A family member is defined as: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Anyone to whom you are related by blood, legal custody, or marriage</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A child for whom you have permanent parental responsibility and who resides with you</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Anyone with whom you maintain a committed relationship and share, or have shared within the past year, a residence</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A committed relationship can be demonstrated by showing economic interdependence, such as joint tenancy, bank accounts, or loans; domestic interdependence, as reflected by a close or public association or an exclusive or a lengthy relationship; or other commitment made through a will, life insurance, or similar document.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. If the need for leave is foreseeable due to a planned course of medical treatment, you must attempt to schedule the leave to avoid unnecessary disruption. When you could not have anticipated the need for leave before the first day of absence, you must submit family and medical leave requests within 2 business days after the leave begins.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Medical</span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"> Certification</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need for leave due to a serious health condition of your own or the serious health condition of a covered family member.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.5in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 16 weeks over a 24 month period. The 24 month period is measured from the date your initial leave begins. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If 2 family members are employed at the same time, leave will be granted in one of the following ways, as agreed upon in advance: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A combined total leave of 16 workweeks in a 24 month period</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A combined total of 4 workweeks of leave taken simultaneously over a 24 month period</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Any leave taken for the birth, adoption, or placement of a child must occur within 12 months after the child&#39;s arrival with you.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Intermittent </span></span></b><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;leave for your own serious illness or to care for a family member who has a serious health condition can be taken on an intermittent basis when medically necessary. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If mutually agreed upon, you may reduce your work schedule to stretch the 16 weeks of total leave over a period of up to 24 consecutive weeks. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When you have a serious health condition, you may perform alternative work for the duration of the leave, if mutually agreed upon. The length of leave and reinstatement rights will remain the same. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may use paid time off under the following conditions:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .3in .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Earned paid time off (excluding sick leave) may be used for the purpose of childbirth, child adoption or placement, or care of a seriously ill family member </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .3in .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Paid sick leave may be used for your own serious health condition. Use of other paid time off benefits for your own serious health condition may be granted if mutually agreed upon </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. If you do not pay the total amount of the premium, coverage will discontinue until regular employment is resumed.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Seniority, accumulated prior to leave, is not lost during a family and medical leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid time off used during family and medical leave. Benefits are earned for the full month in which you work at least 50 percent of the time. Paid time off counts as time worked.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you take a leave due to a personal serious health condition, you must provide a note from your treating physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties. The note must also indicate if there are any restrictions pertaining to duties or the number of hours you can work. Please use the <i>Medical Release to Work Form</i>.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When you return from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\" style=\"font-family:Arial,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list .5in\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">If you accept outside or supplemental employment while on leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Family Medical Leave DC',	'STATE FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	20,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:21:04',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	210,	1),
(469,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request and on the advice of your treating physician.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical</span></b><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> </span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Certification</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose. The certification must include the date the reasonable accommodation became medically advisable, the probable duration of the reasonable accommodation, and an explanatory statement as to the medical advisability of the reasonable accommodation.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:.5in\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services</span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability DC',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-08 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-08 22:22:23',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	78,	1),
(470,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, you may be provided <span style=\"border:none\">with reasonable accommodation<span style=\"border:none\"> <span style=\"border:none\">on the advice of your treating physician.<span style=\"border:none\"> The following accommodations will be made, upon request<span style=\"border:none\">, and without additional documentation <span style=\"border:none\">required<span style=\"border:none\">:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Providing more frequent, longer, or flexible restroom breaks</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Modifying a no food<span style=\"border:none\"> or drink policy</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Providing seating or allowing you to sit more frequently if the job requires you to stand</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Restricting lifting&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">to <span style=\"border:none\">17 pounds or less</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The following accommodations may be made, upon request, unless it would cause undue hardship<span style=\"border:none\"> and may require&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">additional documentation (see below):</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Job restructuring, part-time or modified work schedule, reassignment to a vacant position, or acquiring or modifying equipment, devices, or an employee&rsquo;s work station</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Providing for temporary transfer to a less <span style=\"border:none\">strenuous or less hazardous position</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Scheduling flexibility for prenatal visits</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Providing assistance with manual labor and limits on lifting above 17 pounds</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you need any additional or different accommodations, please make your request known. We will ma<span style=\"border:none\">ke appropriate considerations based on information provided by the Washington&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Department of Labor and Industries or your attending health care provider.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical</span></b> <strong><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\">Certification</span></span></span></span></span></span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you our <i>Medical Certification Form</i> for this purpose. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability Accommodation - WA',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2017-09-12 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-12 21:08:18',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	92,	1),
(471,	'<p style=\"margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">We must keep&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">certain personnel records in order to comply with legislated record keeping and reporting requirements. <span style=\"border:none\">Many of these records you will be asked to complete upon employment. <span style=\"border:none\">These records are confidential and only made available to authorized personnel. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">The physical safety and privacy of personnel records must be secured at all times. Therefore, files are locked and/or contain special computer access codes. Entry to the files is strictly limited to authorized personnel on a need-to-know basis. <span style=\"border:none\">If you access&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">your own, or a co-worker&rsquo;s, confidential employee file without authorization, you may be subject to disciplinary action up to and including termination<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Y</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">ou, along with previous </span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">employees, may inspect and copy certain documents in the personnel files<span style=\"border:none\">. <span style=\"border:none\">We reserve the right to determine which documents you may inspect at any given time in accordance with any law. <span style=\"border:none\">These inspections are limited <span style=\"border:none\">to no more than twice <span style=\"border:none\">in a 12<span style=\"border:none\"> <span style=\"border:none\">month period, unless the request immediately follows notification to <span style=\"border:none\">you<span style=\"border:none\"> regarding newly&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">added negative information. In which case, inspection of the personnel file may happen outside of the <span style=\"border:none\">2 <span style=\"border:none\">per<span style=\"border:none\"> <span style=\"border:none\">year limit. <span style=\"border:none\">You will be informed within 10 days of any newly added negative records to your personnel file <span style=\"border:none\">which<span style=\"border:none\"> could affect your employment o<span style=\"border:none\">r result in disciplinary action. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">A request for an appointment to review the file must be submitted in writing using the </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Request to Review Personnel File Form</span></span></i></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span> </span></span></p>\r\n',	2,	'Personnel Records MA',	'PERSONNEL RECORDS',	'none',	'2017-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-15 21:22:36',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	13,	0),
(472,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are bereaved by the death of a family member, you may be provided a leave of absence. Unless there are extenuating circumstances, you must request and get approval for <span style=\"border:none\">the leave in advance. The amount of time off provided is at our discretion and is based, in large part, on the staffing needs at the time of the request. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">After you have successfully completed the orientation and training period, you may be eligible for compensation <span style=\"border:none\">for the wages lost while on the leave. Time paid for bereavement leave will not be counted as hours worked for computing overtime. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Compensation is provided according to the following provisions:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><strong>Regular Full-Time Employees</strong></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Up to a total of _<span style=\"border:none\">_____ workday(s) when a death occurs in your immediate family. A workday constitutes the number of hours you would have worked had you not been off for bereavement leave. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Up to a total of ______ workday(s) when the death of a relative occurs in your family<span style=\"border:none\">. A workday constitutes the number of hours you would have worked had you not been off for bereavement leave.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><strong>Regular Part-Time Employees</strong><br />\r\nUp to a total of ______ workday(s) when a death occurs in your immediate family. A workday constitutes the number o<span style=\"border:none\">f hours you would have worked had you not been off for bereavement leave.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Up to a total of ______ workday(s) when the death of a relative occurs in your family. A workday constitutes the number of hours you would have worked had you not been off for bereavement <span style=\"border:none\">leave.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustified\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Immediate family</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> is defined as father, mother, sister, brother, legal spouse, domestic partner</span></span></span> (<span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">who meets the NY Civil Rights Law criteria; including same-sex couples), son, daughter, step-parents, step-siblings, father-in-law, mother-in-law<span style=\"border:none\">, grandparents, and grandchildren (whether related by blood, adoption, or marriage).</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Relative</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> is defined as brotherâ<span style=\"border:none\">inâ<span style=\"border:none\">law, sisterâ<span style=\"border:none\">inâ<span style=\"border:none\">law, daughterâ<span style=\"border:none\">inâ<span style=\"border:none\">law, sonâ<span style=\"border:none\">inâ<span style=\"border:none\">law or a relative residing as a regular household member in the home of the employee<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Bereavement Leave-NY',	'BEREAVEMENT LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-10-05 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-15 21:26:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	53,	1),
(473,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><strong><i><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"color:black\">NOTE: This policy has been written in accordance with Minnesota&rsquo;s Sick and Safe Leave law. Modifications to the language up to &ldquo;Regular Full-Time Employees&rdquo; may result in the policy being out of compliance. Please check with an authorized source before making changes.</span></span></span></i></strong></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to<span style=\"border:none\"> an absence for one or more days for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\">\r\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">You or your family member is suffering from an illness, injury, or a medical condition</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\">\r\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Providing or receiving assistance to you or your family member because of sexual assault, domestic abuse, or stalking</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">ââ</span></span></span></span></span>The following definitions apply for purposes of this policy:</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\">\r\n	<p><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">The definition of family member means spouse, siblings, children (biological, adopted, stepchild, or foster child), parents, mother-in-law, father-in-law, grandchildren (biological, adopted, stepchild, or foster grandchild), grandparents and stepparents</span></span></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: \"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; border: none; font-family: \"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you must have worked at least 12 months preceding the request for an average number of hours per week equal to one-half of a full-time equivalent position.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick pa<span style=\"border:none\">y benefits will be paid for the time you normally would have been scheduled to work had you not been absent. During the orientation and training period, you do not earn paid sick leave. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Regular FullâTime Employees</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you earn ______ hours of paid sick leave<span style=\"border:none\"> for each month worked after the successful completion of the orientation and training period. Sick leave is not earned during a month where you are working less than 50 percent of the normally scheduled work hours.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Regular Part-Time Employees</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you earn __<span style=\"border:none\">____ hours of paid sick leave for each month worked after the successful completion of the orientation and training period. Sick leave is not earned during a month where you are working less than 50 percent of the normally scheduled work hours.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;p<span style=\"border:none\">aid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><strong>Notice of Absence</strong>&mdash;if you&rsquo;re going to be absent for an illness or injury, we appreciate as much advance notice as possible. At a minimum, you must notify us of your absence&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">no later than 1 hour before the start of the workday. If circumstances are such that you cannot personally notify us, please have a relative or other responsible individual handle that for you within the required timeframe. Failure to follow this procedure&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">will void the claim for paid sick leave and can be grounds for disciplinary action up to and including termination.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">During an absence because of illness, you are to notify us daily of progress unless otherwise agreed upon.</span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Please give us advance notice of your return to work after a sick leave absence to that we can manage the schedule and staff accordingly.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Physician&rsquo;s Statement</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;at our discretion, you may be required to bring a healthcare practitioner&rsquo;s certificate verifying the medical reason for y<span style=\"border:none\">our absence and your ability to return to work.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;please be sure to include any sick leave taken on your attendance record&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">so we can <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">pay you appropriately.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><strong>Leave of Absence</strong>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you ma<span style=\"border:none\">y be put on a leave of absence. Please review our </span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Leave of Absence</span></span></i></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> policy for more information. </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\">No sick leave is earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;any unused sick time will be paid once a year, on the anniversary date of employment, a<span style=\"border:none\">t your regular hourly rate of pay. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you will be not be paid for any earned and unused sick leave at the time of termination.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave MN over 21',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	21,	99999,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-15 21:37:40',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	26,	1),
(474,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is intended&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">to protect you against undue financial loss in case of an illness for one or a few days. Acceptable medical reasons include your own incapacitating illness or injury and necessary medical treatment or that of a child, parent, spouse, or domestic partner.<span style=\"border:none\"> Sick pay benefits will be paid for the time you normally would have been scheduled to work had you not been absent. During the orientation and training period, you do not earn paid sick leave. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Regular FullâTime Employees</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you earn ______ hours of paid si<span style=\"border:none\">ck leave for each month worked after the successful completion of the orientation and training period. Sick leave is not earned during a month where you are working less than 50 percent of the normally scheduled work hours.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Regular Part-Time Employees</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you<span style=\"border:none\"> earn ______ hours of paid sick leave for each month worked after the successful completion of the orientation and training period. Sick leave is not earned during a month where you are working less than 50 percent of the normally scheduled work hours.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><strong>Notice of Absence</strong>&mdash;if you&rsquo;re going to be absent for an illness or injury, we appreciate as much advance notice as possible. At a minimum, you must notify us of yo<span style=\"border:none\">ur absence no later than <span style=\"border:none\">1<span style=\"border:none\"> hour before the start of the workday. If circumstances are such that you cannot personally notify us, please have a relative or other responsible individual handle that for you within the required timeframe. Failure to follow thi<span style=\"border:none\">s procedure will void the claim for paid sick leave and can be grounds for disciplinary action up to and including termination.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">During an absence because of illness, you are to notify us daily of progress unless otherwise agreed upon.</span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Please give us advance notice of your return to work after a sick leave absence so that we can manage the schedule and staff accordingly.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Physician&rsquo;s Statement</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;at our discretion, you may be required to bring a healthcare practitioner&rsquo;s certificate verifying your ability to <span style=\"border:none\">return to work.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;please be sure to include any sick leave taken on your attendance record&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">so we can <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">pay you appropriately.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><strong>Leave of Absence</strong>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within <span style=\"border:none\">6<span style=\"border:none\"> working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. <span style=\"border:none\">Please review our </span></span></span></span></span><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Leave of Absence</span></span></i></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> policy for more information. </span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">No sick leave is earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;any unused sick time will be paid once a year<span style=\"border:none\">, on the anniversary date of employment,<span style=\"border:none\"> at your regular hourly rate of pa<span style=\"border:none\">y. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;you will be not be paid for any earned and unused sick leave at <span style=\"border:none\">the <span style=\"border:none\">time of termination.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave MN under 21',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2017-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	1,	20,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-15 21:41:06',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	25,	1),
(475,	'<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><strong><em>NOTE: choose only one of the options below, and remove the other options.&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><strong><em>Option 1</em></strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe provide a pre-tax election transportation fringe benefits program that provides commuter highway vehicle, transit or bicycling benefits consistent with applicable Internal Revenue Code. The benefit is equal to the maximum amount that may be deducted for those programs from an employee&#39;s gross income, which may vary from one year to the next. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">This benefit is available immediately upon hire. You will be provided with appropriate information of how this works. If you have questions, please let us know.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><strong><em><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Option 2</span></span></span></span></span></em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">You have an option for receiving your commuter benefits. You will need to choose one of the following:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A transit pass for a public transit system of your choosing, or</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Reimbursement of vanpool or bicycling costs in an amount at least equal to the purchase price of a transit pass for an equivalent trip on a public transit system.</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">This benefit is available immediately upon hire. You must inform us of your choice, and then we will provide the benefit accordingly. If you have questions, please let us know.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><strong><em><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Option 3</span></span></span></span></span></em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">We provide transportation for all our employees in a vanpool or bus operated by and for us. This benefit is available immediately upon hire. You will be provided with appropriate information of how this works. If you have questions, please let us know.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Commuter Benefits DC all 3',	'COMMUTER BENEFITS',	'none',	'2017-09-15 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	20,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-15 21:50:20',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	55,	1),
(476,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">A leave of absence may be granted if you are temporarily unable to work due to an illness or disability, including pregnancy or pregnancy-related conditions, or if you choose to take time off work to fulfill personal obligations due to an exceptional or emergency nature.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">after having completed 6 months of employment, <span><span><span>you</span></span></span><span><span><span> may request a leave of absence. Exceptions to the length of service requirement will be considered at </span></span></span><span><span><span>our discretion.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Request for a Leave of Absence</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;a request for a leave </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>of absence </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>must be submitted in writing at lea<span>st 30 days in advance</span></span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>,</span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span> or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Please use the </span></span></span><span><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Request for a Leave Absence Form</span></span></em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>If the reason for the leave is due to an illness or a disability, you must include medical certification from your health care provider&nbsp;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">verifying the need for leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:40.5pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Your desire to return to work and a date of return must be agreed upon in writing. We reserve the right to approve or deny any request for a leave of absence.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Length of Leave</span></strong></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;a leave of absence will be granted for a reasonable period of time, which will normally be construed as the period of the actual disability or 8 weeks, whichever is less. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Reporting on Progress</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;you are required to report directly to </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>us</span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span> on your status and your continued intention&nbsp;<span>to return to work </span></span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>a minimum of every 30 days.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Salary and Benefits</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may be required to use any paid time off benefit available. If so, the paid time off will run concurrently with the leave of absence.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical insurance benefits, if applicable, will continue until the end of the month in which the leave begins. After the initial month, you may be eligible for continuation coverage. If applicable, you will be notified of your continuation coverage rights. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>When you return from leave, benefits will again be provided according to the applicable policies and plans.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Reinstatement to Work</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;so that your return to work can be properly scheduled, please provide at least 30 days advance notice in<span> writing of the date you intend to return to work. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>If you take a leave of absence </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>because of a</span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>n</span></span></span> <span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>illness or disability</span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>, you must provide a note from your physician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties</span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span> with <span>or without restrictions. Please use the </span></span></span></span><span><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Medical Release </span></span></em></span><span><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>t</span></span></em></span><span><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>o Work Form</span></span></em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Unless applicable laws require otherwise, reinstatement cannot be guaranteed to anyone </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>returning from a leave</span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span> of absence</span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>. We will endeavor to place </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>you in your </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>former position or in a <span>position comparable in status and pay</span></span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>. This is </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>subject to budgetary restrictions, </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>our</span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span> need to fill vacancies, and the ability to find qualified temporary replacements.</span></span></span> <span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Reinstatement is at </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>our discretion.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Termination of Employment</span></strong></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>&mdash;your employment </span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>may end if any of the following occurs:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>If you accept outside or supplement employment while being on a leave of absence</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>If you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>If the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresent<span>ed</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span>If the request for a leave of absence was denied and you take time off anyway</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>W</span></span></span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>hen, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Leave of Absence - IA',	'LEAVE OF ABSENCE',	'none',	'2019-10-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IA\"]',	0,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-15 22:09:16',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	63,	1),
(477,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You will be provided an unpaid family and medical leave as outlined below.&nbsp; &nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:left\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family and medical leave, you must have worked: 1) at least 12 months within the previous 7 years*, 2) at least 1,250 hours in the 12 months immediately preceding the request for leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">*Military service or other written agreements may extend this length of time</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><strong><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></em></strong></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 12 weeks over a 12 month period (measured from the date your initial leave begins) for the following reasons: </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The birth of a child</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The placement of a child for adoption or foster care</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Your own serious health condition*</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The serious health condition* of your family member (spouse, domestic partner, child or parent)</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Any &ldquo;qualifying exigency&rdquo; (as the Secretary shall, by regulation, determine) arising out of the fact that your spouse, domestic partner, child, or parent is on active duty (or has been notified of an impending call or order to active duty) in the National Guard or Reserves in support of a contingency operation or a member of the Armed Forces who is deployed in a foreign country</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">*A serious health condition is one requiring in-patient, hospital, hospice, or residential medical care or continuing physician care.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A leave of absence may be granted up to 26 weeks over a 12 month period (measured from the date your initial leave begins) for the following reason:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">To care for your spouse, domestic partner, child, parent, or next of kin who is a member of the Armed Forces, National Guard or Reserves who is undergoing treatment for, or recuperating from, a serious injury or illness incurred in the line of duty while on active duty</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">To care for your spouse, domestic partner, child, parent, or next of kin who is a former member of the Armed Forces, National Guard or Reserves who, during the first five years following his/her discharge from military service, is undergoing treatment for, or recuperating from, a serious injury or illness incurred in the line of duty while on active duty</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">NOTE:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> During the single 12 month period in which leave is taken to care for a covered service member, if you need FMLA leave for any other reason, you are entitled to a combined total of 26 weeks. The availability of leave for another reason in any other 12 month period shall not be limited.&nbsp; </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">NOTE:</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&nbsp; Serious injury and illness includes injuries and illnesses aggravated by active duty service.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you and your spouse or domestic partner are both employed by us, you are entitled to combined leave of up to 12 weeks in a 12 month period for the birth, adoption, or placement for foster care of a child; to care for a sick child or parent; or for a &ldquo;qualifying exigency,&rdquo; and are entitled to a combined total of 26 weeks of leave to care for an injured service member as well as leave for other FMLA-qualifying reasons during the applicable 12 month period. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Intermittent </span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;leave for your own serious health condition, a&nbsp; family member&rsquo;s serious health condition, &ldquo;qualifying exigencies,&rdquo; or to care for an injured service member may be taken on an intermittent or reduced schedule basis when necessary. If you request intermittent leave or leave on a reduced schedule for a serious health condition or to care for an injured service member, we may require that you transfer to a temporary, alternative job for which you are qualified and that better accommodates the intermittent or reduced schedule leave than your regular job. The temporary position will provide pay and benefits equivalent to your regular job. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><strong>Request for Leave</strong>&mdash;a request for leave must be submitted in writing at least 30 days in advance, or as early as possible for unforeseeable events. If you have a foreseeable need for leave due to a planned course of medical treatment, you must attempt to schedule the leave to avoid unnecessary disruption.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical</span></strong><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> Certification</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need for leave due to a serious health condition of your own, the serious health condition of a covered family member, or to care for a covered service member.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><strong><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></em></strong></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash; the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may be required to use any paid time off benefit available. If so, the paid time off will run concurrently with the FMLA leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are two payment options: 1) prepayment before the leave, 2) pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. Failure to pay your share of the health insurance premium may result in a loss of coverage. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Benefits are not accumulated while on family and medical leave.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>Seniority is not lost and will continue to be accumulated while on family and medical leave.</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span><strong><em><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></em></strong></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that work can be properly scheduled.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">If you take a leave due to a personal serious health condition, <span><span><span>you must provide a note from your phys<span>ician verifying that you are able to return to work and can assume your regular work duties</span></span></span></span><span><span><span> with or without restrictions. Please use the </span></span></span><span><em><span><span>Medical Release </span></span></em></span><span><em><span><span>t</span></span></em></span><span><em><span><span>o Work Form</span></span></em></span><span><span><span>.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">When you return from leave, you will be reinstated to your former position or an equivalent position without loss of status, pay or service credits, unless a comparable position no longer exists.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><strong>Termination of Employment</strong>&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs: </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span><span><span>If you <span>accept outside or supplemental employment while being on a leave of absence</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span><span><span>If you do not </span></span></span><span><span><span>return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span><span><span>If the </span></span></span><span><span><span>purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span><span><span>If t</span></span></span><span><span><span>he request for a leave of absence </span></span></span><span><span><span>was</span></span></span><span><span><span> denied and you take<span> time off anyway</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span><span><span><span><span>When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'FMLA',	'FEDERAL FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE ACT (FMLA)',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-09-20 15:17:06',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	220,	1),
(479,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">You will be provided an unpaid new parent leave as outlined below. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"left\" class=\"bodybullet\" style=\"text-align:left; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Eligibility</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid new parent leave, you must have: 1) been employed for a total of at least 12 months (52 weeks) prior to the commencement of leave, 2) worked at least 1,250 hours during the 12 month period immediately prior to the date of leave. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Reasons for Leave</span></span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;you may be eligible to take new parent leave to: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Bond with a new child within one year of the child&rsquo;s birth, adoption, or foster placement </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Request for Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;you must request a leave at least 30 days in advance. However, if 30 days&#39; advance notice is impossible because of a change in circumstances or a medical emergency, you must give notice as soon as practicable.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Length of Leave</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 12 workweeks in a 12 month period. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">If we employ both parties of a relationship and both are eligible for leave, the new parent leave is limited to 12 workweeks in a 12 month period between the two parents. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Salary and Benefits</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;generally, the leave of absence is without pay. However, you may use any earned paid time off benefit as part of the leave. Any paid time off used will run concurrently with new parent leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are 2 payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">We reserve the right to recover the premium we paid during the leave of absence if you fail to return to work once the leave of absence is completed if the reason for your inability to report to work is unrelated to continuation, recurrence, or onset of a serious health condition or other circumstances beyond your control. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Upon returning from leave, you retain all seniority earned before your leave began for purposes of layoff, recall, promotion, job assignment, and seniority-related benefits.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Benefits earned prior to taking leave will not be reduced, other than any paid leave used during new parent leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Reinstatement to Work</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;on return from leave, you will be restored to your former position or to a position with similar duties and responsibilities and equivalent status, benefits, pay, working conditions, privileges, and other terms and conditions of employment. Upon request, we will provide this guarantee of reinstatement in writing. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">When we agree to a definite return date at the start of leave, you will be reinstated on that date. If the original return date changes during your leave, we will reinstate you within 2 business days after receiving notice of your readiness to return.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\">Termination of Employment</span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">&mdash;employment may end if any of the following occurs: </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">You do not return to work on the scheduled day of return</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">When the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">When, for business and economic reasons, the job is not available</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'New Parent Leave - CA',	'NEW PARENT LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-02-05 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	20,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-10-17 20:51:41',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	104,	1),
(480,	'<p>You may be provided an unpaid family leave as outlined below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong><!--[if supportFields]><b\r\nstyle=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\r\n\"Arial\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span></span></b><span\r\nstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif\'>xe\r\n&quot;Eligibility&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><b\r\nstyle=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\r\n\"Arial\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></span></b><![endif]-->&mdash;to qualify for an unpaid family and medical leave, you must have worked: 1) At least 12 months, 2) At least 1,000 hours in the 12 months immediately preceding the leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reasons for Leave</strong>&mdash;you can take family leave for:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Childbirth, including a child born pursuant to a valid written agreement between you and a gestational carrier</li>\r\n	<li>Adoption or foster placement of a child</li>\r\n	<li>The serious health condition of your family member</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For purposes of this policy, &ldquo;child&rdquo; means:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Biological, adopted, foster child, resource family child, stepchild, legal ward, or child of a parent;</li>\r\n	<li>Under 18 years of age; or</li>\r\n	<li>18 years of age or older but incapable of self-care because of a mental or physical impairment; or</li>\r\n	<li>A child who becomes the child of a parent pursuant to a valid written agreement between the parent and gestational carrier</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For purposes of this policy, &ldquo;family member&rdquo; means:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Child, parent, parent-in-law, sibling, grandparent, grandchild, spouse, domestic partner, or civil union partner</li>\r\n	<li>Any other individual related by blood to you</li>\r\n	<li>Any other individual that you show to have a close association with which is the equivalent of a family relationship</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For purposes of this policy, &ldquo;serious health condition&rdquo; means:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>An illness, injury, impairment, or physical or mental condition requiring inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential medical care facility or continuing treatment by a health care provider</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Request for Leave</strong><!--[if supportFields]><span\r\nstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:\r\nfield-begin\'></span>xe &quot;Leave Of Absence Request&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><span\r\nstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:\r\nfield-end\'></span></span><![endif]-->&mdash;you must provide us with notice of your intention to take leave under this policy in a manner that is reasonable and practicable. When emergent circumstances require you to begin leave sooner, you should give us as much notice as possible.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For birth, adoption, or foster placement, advance notice is considered to be 15 days&rsquo; before taking intermittent leave and 30 days&rsquo; notice before taking continuous leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please attempt to schedule the leave to avoid unduly disrupting our operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Medical</strong><strong> Certification</strong>&mdash;you may be required to provide a health care provider&rsquo;s certification of the need for leave. If possible, this medical certification must be submitted before leave begins.</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s *family medical history*, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span><strong><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span>*Family medical history may be acquired as part of the certification process for leave where an employee is asking for leave to care for a family member with a serious health condition. </span></span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Length of </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;a leave of absence may be granted up to 12 weeks over a 24 month period. Leave taken for the birth or adoption or foster placement of a child can begin at any time within a year after the date of the birth or adoption or foster placement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Intermittent </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;you can take leave intermittently. In the case of a family member with a serious health condition, intermittent leave cannot extend beyond a 12 month period for each serious health condition episode.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reduced L</strong><strong>eave</strong><strong> Schedule</strong>&mdash;you can choose to take family leave on a reduced schedule that extends over a period of up to 12 consecutive months for any one period of leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A reduced leave schedule means leave scheduled for fewer than your usual number of hours worked per week but not fewer than your usual number of hours worked per day, unless agreed to by you and us.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and </strong><strong>Benefits</strong>&mdash;the leave of absence is without pay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. There are 2 payment options: 1) Prepayment before the leave, 2) Pay as the premiums become due, which may be either monthly or quarterly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that the return to work can be properly scheduled.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon return from family leave, you will be restored to your former position or to a position with equivalent seniority, status, employment benefits, pay, and other terms and conditions of employment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you began family leave before we determined that denial of leave is necessary, you must return to work within 10 workdays of receiving notice of the denial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Termination of Employment</strong><!--[if supportFields]><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span>xe\r\n&quot;Voluntary Termination&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><span\r\nstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:\r\nfield-end\'></span></span><![endif]-->&mdash;employment may end if you do not return to work on the scheduled day of return, or when the purpose for requesting the leave was misrepresented.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Family Medical Leave NJ',	'FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	30,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-10-23 22:53:04',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	213,	1),
(481,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">I</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">f you are a veteran</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, y</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">ou may be provided with time off on Veteran&rsquo;s Day, November 11, </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">and Memorial Day, last Monday in May, <span style=\"border:none\">if </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">you would otherwise be scheduled to work</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> either of those&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">days</span></span></span></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">and you would like to participate in<span style=\"border:none\"> an exercise, parade or service</span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You will be provided with sufficient time to participate in such services in your community of residence. <span style=\"border:none\">Time off provided is without pay. Please provide reasonable notice of your<span style=\"border:none\"> intent to <span style=\"border:none\">participate in such events <span style=\"border:none\">so that we can make <span style=\"border:none\">appropriate arrangements<span style=\"border:none\"> for your absence.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Holidays for Veterans - MA',	'HOLIDAYS FOR VETERANS',	'none',	'2017-10-31 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	0,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-10-31 18:41:20',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	45,	1),
(482,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">I</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">f you are a veteran</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, y</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">ou may be provided with time off on Vetera<span style=\"border:none\">n&rsquo;s Day, November 11, </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">and Memorial Day, last Monday in May, if </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">you would otherwise be scheduled to work</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> either of those days</span></span></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">and you would like to participate in an exercise, parade or service</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You will be provided with sufficient time to participate in su<span style=\"border:none\">ch services in your community of residence. Time off provided for Memorial Day is without pay. Time off for </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Veteran&rsquo;s Day</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> is paid. Please provide reasonable notice of your intent to participate in such events so that we can make appropriate arrangements fo<span style=\"border:none\">r your absence.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Holidays for Veterans - MA 50+',	'HOLIDAYS FOR VETERANS',	'none',	'2017-10-31 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2017-10-31 18:42:48',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	46,	1),
(483,	'<p>JANUARY TESTING 1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please read</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please update</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New text added on 2/2/18</p>\r\n\r\n<p>New new text Alan Added on 2/13/2018!</p>\r\n',	4,	'January Testing 1',	'JANUARY TESTING 1',	'none',	'2018-02-15 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-01-25 23:19:06',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'disabled',	1,	0),
(484,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is <span style=\"border:none\">intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Care for or treat your own mental or physical illness, injury, or condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Preventive medical care for you or your family member </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Care for your family member with a mental or physical illness, injury or condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Maternity or paternity leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Obtain medical or mental health attention for you or your family member that is related to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Obtain assistance from a victim services organization for you or your family member that is related to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Acquire legal services or attend proceedings for you or your family member that is related to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Temporary relocation for you or your family member that is related to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For purposes of this policy, the term family member includes: </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A spouse</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&#39;s stepchild or a biological, adopted, or foster child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A child for whom the employee has legal or physical custody or guardianship</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A child for whom the employee stands in loco parentis, regardless of age</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A stepparent or a biological, adoptive, or foster parent of the employee or the employee&rsquo;s spouse</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A legal guardian of the employee</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">An individual who acted as a parent or stood in loco parentis to the employee or the employee&rsquo;s spouse when either were a minor</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A step-grandparent or a biological, adopted, or foster grandparent of the employee</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A step-grandchild or a biological, adopted, or foster grandchild of the employee</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A stepsibling or a biological, adopted, or foster sibling of the employee</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all employees who regularly work </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">12 hours or </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">more<span style=\"border:none\"> per week. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:7.8pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">1 hour of paid leave is accrued for every 30 hours worked up to a maximum of 40 hours per year</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:7.8pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:7.8pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave is not accrued if:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">During any 2 week pay period you work fewer than 24 hours total (if applicable)</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">During any 1 wee<span style=\"border:none\">k pay period you work fewer than a combined 24 hours total in the current and immediately preceding pay period (if applicable)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">During any pay period in which you are paid twice a month and you worked fewer than 26 hours in the pay period (if applicable)</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;in 1 year, you may not use more than </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">64</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours of sick leave. You are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until the </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">106</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><sup><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">th</span></span></sup></span> <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">106 </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">days of employment<span style=\"border:none\">, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave may be used in </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">the smallest amount our payroll system will allow</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span> </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;up to 40 hours of accrued and unused sick leave during a 12 month period will be carried over into the ne<span style=\"border:none\">xt year. Sick time is capped at </span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">64</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Unused sick leave that is rolled over will not affect an employee&rsquo;s ability to accrue up to 40 hours each year. For example, an employee rolls over 40 hours of sick leave and accrues 24 more hours to a cap of 64 <span style=\"border:none\">hours for the year. If the employee uses 20 hours of sick time in that same year, s/he will begin to accrue up to 16 more hours of sick time to total 40 hours of sick time actually accrued in the year. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends, for any reason, and you are<span style=\"border:none\"> rehired within 37 weeks of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued sick leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using sick leave provided you worked at least 106 days previously.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Make-up T<span style=\"border:none\">ime</span></span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours or shifts during the same or next pay period in lieu of hours or shifts missed and not have to use paid sick leave benefits. However, we cannot require you to work the extra hours<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;or shifts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;when the use of paid sick leave is foreseeable, you shall provide notice of your intention to take sick time at least </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">7</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> days in advance. If the need for paid sick leave is unforeseeable, please provide notice as soon as practicable<span style=\"border:none\">. We ask that you comply with our rules regarding notifying us of your absences and to make an attempt to schedule the use of sick time in a manner that does not unduly disrupt our operations. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave f<span style=\"border:none\">or more than 2 consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting the need for leave from your treating physician. If the need for sick leave is foreseeable and will require you to be off for more than 2 consecutive days<span style=\"border:none\">, you may be required to provide certification supporting the need for leave from your treating physician prior to sick leave commencing. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Prohibition on Retaliation and Adverse Action</span></span></span></b><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;we </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">will not retaliate or take adverse action against employees</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">who </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">need to exercise </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">their</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> right to use paid sick leave as described in this policy.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Right to Report Alleged </span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">V</span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">iolation</span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">if you believe there has been a violation of this policy or your right to sick leave, please report that to us as soon as possible so that w<span style=\"border:none\">e can rectify the problem. However, you do have the right to report violations to the Commissioner and take appropriate action from there. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Prohibition on Bad Faith Complaints</span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">employees may not make a complaint, bring an action, or testify in an action in<span style=\"border:none\"> bad faith.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">&nbsp;so we can be <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">sure to pay you appropriately.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;notice of<span style=\"border:none\"> your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave MD 15+',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-10-02 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	15,	999999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-03-01 23:12:14',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	23,	1),
(485,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Unpaid sick leave </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">may be used</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Care for or treat your own mental or physical illness, injury, or condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Preventive medical care for you or your family member </span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Care for your family member with a mental or physical illness, injury or condition</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Maternity or paternity leave</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Obtain medical or mental health attention for you or your family member that is related to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Obtain assistance from a victim services organization for you or your family member that is related to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 45.8pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Acquire legal services or attend proceedings for you or your family member that is related to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:10pt\"><span courier=\"\" new=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">Temporary relocation for you or your family member that is related to domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">For purposes of this policy, the term family member includes: </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A spouse</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">An employee&#39;s stepchild or a biological, adopted, or foster child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A child for whom the employee has legal or physical custody or guardianship</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\">A child for whom the employee stands in loco parentis, regardless of age</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A stepparent or a biological, adoptive, or foster parent of the employee or the employee&rsquo;s spouse</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A legal guardian of the employee</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">An individual who acted as a parent or stood in loco parentis to the employee or the employee&rsquo;s spouse when either were a minor</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A step-grandparent or a biological, adopted, or foster grandparent of the employee</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A step-grandchild or a biological, adopted, or foster grandchild of the employee</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal\">A stepsibling or a biological, adopted, or foster sibling of the employee</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">un</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">paid sick leave is provided to all employees who regularly work </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">12 hours or </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">more per week. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:7.8pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">1 hour of </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">un</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">paid leave is accrued for every 30 hours worked up to a maximum of 40 hours per year</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:7.8pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:7.8pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave <span style=\"border:none\">is not accrued if:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">During any 2 week pay period you work fewer than 24 hours total (if applicable)</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">During any 1 week pay period you work fewer than a combined 24 hours total in the current and immediately preceding pay period (if applicable)</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.15pt left 45.0pt 49.5pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">During any pay<span style=\"border:none\"> period in which you are paid twice a month and you worked fewer than 26 hours in the pay period (if applicable)</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;in 1 year, you may not use more than </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">64</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours of sick leave. You are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until the </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">10<span style=\"border:none\">6</span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><sup><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">th</span></span></sup></span> <span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">106 </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">days of employment, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave may be used in </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">the smallest amount our payroll system will allow</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span> </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;up to 40 hours of accrued and unused sick leave during a 12 month period will be carried over into the next year. Sick time is capped at </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">64</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Unused sick leave that is rolled over will not affect an employee&rsquo;s ability to accrue up to 40 hours<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;each year. For example, an employee rolls over 40 hours of sick leave and accrues 24 more hours to a cap of 64 hours for the year. If the employee uses 20 hours of sick time in that same year, s/he will begin to accrue up to 16 more hours of sick time <span style=\"border:none\">to total 40 hours of sick time actually accrued in the year. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends, for any reason, and you are rehired within 37 weeks of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued sick leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period<span style=\"border:none\">, upon rehiring, for using sick leave provided you worked at least 106 days previously.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Make-up Time</span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours or shifts during the same or next pay period in lieu of hours <span style=\"border:none\">or shifts missed and not have to use sick leave benefits. However, we cannot require you to work the extra hours or shifts. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;when the use of </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">un</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">paid sick leave is foreseeable, you shall provide notice of your intention to take sick time a<span style=\"border:none\">t least </span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">7</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> days in advance. If the need for </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">un</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">paid sick leave is unforeseeable, please provide notice as soon as practicable. We ask that you comply with our rules regarding notifying us of your absences and to make an attempt to schedule the use of sick ti<span style=\"border:none\">me in a manner that does not unduly disrupt our operations. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are absent on sick leave for more than 2 consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting the need for leave from your treating physician<span style=\"border:none\">. If the need for sick leave is foreseeable and will require you to be off for more than 2 consecutive days, you may be required to provide certification supporting the need for leave from your treating physician prior to sick leave commencing. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span arial=\"\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"color:black\">Prohibition on Retaliation and Adverse Action</span></span></span></b><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;we </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">will not retaliate or take adverse action against employees</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">who </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">need to exercise </span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">their</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> right to use sick leave as described in this policy.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Right to Report Alleged Violation</span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">if you believe there has been a violation<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;of this policy or your right to sick leave, please report that to us as soon as possible so that we can rectify the problem. However, you do have the right to report violations to the Commissioner and take appropriate action from there. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><b><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Prohibition<span style=\"border:none\"> on Bad Faith Complaints</span></span></span></b></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">employees may not make a complaint, bring an action, or testify in an action in bad faith.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are un<span style=\"border:none\">able to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"tab-stops:list 2.4pt left 40.5pt 91.6pt 137.4pt 183.2pt 229.0pt 274.8pt 320.6pt 366.4pt 412.2pt 458.0pt 503.8pt 549.6pt 595.4pt 641.2pt 687.0pt 732.8pt\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" style=\"font-family:\" times=\"\"><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\" narrow=\"\" style=\"font-family:\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span arial=\"\" class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" narrow=\"\" style=\"border:none; font-family:\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so <span style=\"border:none\">that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave MD less than 15',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-10-02 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	1,	14,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-03-01 23:14:40',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	24,	1),
(486,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth<span style=\"border:none\">,<span style=\"border:none\"> lactation or the need to express breastmilk<span style=\"border:none\">, you may be provided with reasonable <span style=\"border:none\">accommodation on the advice of your treating physician. The following accommodations will be made, upon request, and without additional documentation required:</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Providing more frequent, longer, or flexible restroom<span style=\"border:none\">, food, or water<span style=\"border:none\"> breaks</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Providing seating o<span style=\"border:none\">r allowing you to sit more frequently if the job requires you to stand</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Lifting restrictions<span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;of 20<span style=\"border:none\"> pounds or <span style=\"border:none\">more</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"border:none\">Providing a private, non-bathroom space for expressing breastmilk</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you need any additional or different accommodations, please make your request&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">known. We will <span style=\"border:none\">engage in a timely, good faith, interactive process to determine an effective and reasonable accommodation<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical</span></b><span class=\"Heading2Char\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-style:italic\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"> <span style=\"color:black\">Certification</span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;for a request beyond anything that is listed above, you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you our <i>Medical Certification Form</i> for this purpose. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability Accommodation - MA',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2018-03-20 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	0,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-03-20 20:29:12',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	82,	1),
(487,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Your own mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; your own need for medical diagnosis, care, or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; your own need for preventive medical care;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Care of a family member with a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; care of a family member who needs medical diagnosis, care, or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; care of a family member who needs preventive medical care;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Closure of our place of business by order of a public official due to a public health emergency or your need to care for a child whose school or place of care has been closed by order of a public official due to a public health emergency, or care for oneself or a family member when it has been determined by the health authorities having jurisdiction or by a health care provider that you or your family member&#39;s presence in the community may jeopardize the health of others because of exposure to a communicable disease, whether or not you or your family member has actually contracted the communicable disease; or</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">When you or your family member is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">For purposes of this policy, the term family member includes: </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A <span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">biological, adopted, or foster son or daughter, a stepson or stepdaughter, a legal ward, a son or daughter of a domestic partner, or a son or daughter in which you stand in loco parentis to that child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">A biological, foster, or adoptive parent, a stepparent, a legal guardian, or other person who stands in loco parentis&nbsp;to you or your spouse or domestic partner when he/she was a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A spouse or domestic partner</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Mother-in-law or father-in-law</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Grandparents</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Grandchildren</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Brother or sister, whether related through half blood, whole blood or adoption, a foster sibling, or step-sibling</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Care recipient (a person for whom you are responsible for providing or arranging health or safety related care)</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A member of your household</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:42.0pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Eligibility</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all employees<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Earning Sick Leave</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">1 hour of paid leave is accrued for every </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">35</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours worked up to a maximum of 24 hours </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">during the calendar year of 2018; </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">up to a maximum of </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">32</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> hours </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">during the calendar year of 2019</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> and up to a maximum of 40 hours per calendar year thereafter<span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Accrual of sick leave begins July 1, 2018 or at the start of hire, whichever is later. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Using Sick Leave</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;<span style=\"border:none\">while sick leave begins accruing at the start of employment, <span style=\"border:none\">y<span style=\"border:none\">ou are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until <span style=\"border:none\">after <span style=\"border:none\">90 </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">calendar days<span style=\"border:none\"> <span style=\"border:none\">of <span style=\"border:none\">employment. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">For temporary employees<span style=\"border:none\">, </span>you are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until after </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">180</span></span></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">calendar </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">days of employment</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">.</span></span></span> </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">For seasonal employees, you are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until after </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">150</span></span></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">calendar </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">days of employment.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Sick leave may be used<span style=\"border:none\"> in hourly increments<span style=\"border:none\">. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will be carried over into the next year.</span></span></span> </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">You may not use, in one <span style=\"border:none\">calendar year<span style=\"border:none\">, more than <span style=\"border:none\">24 hours <span style=\"border:none\">of sick leave </span></span></span></span>through December 31, 2018<span style=\"border:none\">; </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">more than 32 hours<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;of sick leave </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">through December 31, 2019; <span style=\"border:none\">and more than 40 hours of sick leave <span style=\"border:none\">beginning January 1, 2019<span style=\"border:none\"> and beyond</span></span></span>.&nbsp; </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If your employment ends <span style=\"border:none\">and you are rehired within <span style=\"border:none\">135 days<span style=\"border:none\"> of the date of separation, </span></span></span></span><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"border:none\">your </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">previously unused accrued sick leave will<span style=\"border:none\"> be reinstated</span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. T</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">here will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for&nbsp;using sick leave provided you worked at least </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">90 <span style=\"border:none\">calendar <span style=\"border:none\">days</span></span> previously.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;when the use of paid sick leave is foreseeable, you shall make a good faith effort&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">to provide notice</span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, orally or in writing, </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">of the need for such time to us in advance</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, this should include expected duration of the absence when possible</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. You shall make a reasonable effort to schedule the use of earned paid sick time in a manner that does<span style=\"border:none\"> not unduly disrupt our operations. When the need for sick leave is not foreseeable, please follow our procedures for notification of unexpected time off (see the </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Attendance &amp; Punctuality</span></span></i></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> policy earlier in this manual for specific call-in procedures).</span></span></span> </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">if you are absent within the two weeks prior to your scheduled final day of employment, or </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">you are absent on paid sick leave for more than 3 consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">reasonable documentation </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">supporting t<span style=\"border:none\">he need for leave</span>. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Overtime</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Attendance Record</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;record&nbsp;</span></span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">so we can be <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">sure to pay you appropriately.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;notice<span style=\"border:none\">&nbsp;of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Unused Sick Leave upon Termination</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave Accrual RI 18+',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-10-02 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	18,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-03-21 23:35:57',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	31,	1),
(488,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">We do not provide paid sick leave as a benefit at this time. If, however, you are absent due to the following reasons, your attendance record and overall performance standing with us will no<span style=\"border:none\">t be adversely affected:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Your own mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; your own need for medical diagnosis, care, or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; your own need for preventive medical care;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Care of a family member with a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; care of a family member who needs medical diagnosis, care, or treatment of a mental or physical illness, injury or health condition; care of a family member who needs preventive medical care;</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">Closure of our place of business by order of a public official due to a public health emergency or your need to care for a child whose school or place of care has been closed by order of a public official due to a public health emergency, or care for oneself or a family member when it has been determined by the health authorities having jurisdiction or by a health care provider that you or your family member&#39;s presence in the community may jeopardize the health of others because of exposure to a communicable disease, whether or not you or your family member has actually contracted the communicable disease; or</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"color:black\">When you or your family member is a victim of domestic violence, sexual assault, or stalking.</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\">&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">For purposes of this policy, the term family member includes: </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A <span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">biological, adopted, or foster son or daughter, a stepson or stepdaughter, a legal ward, a son or daughter of a domestic partner, or a son or daughter in which you stand in loco parentis to that child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"background:white\"><span style=\"color:black\">A biological, foster, or adoptive parent, a stepparent, a legal guardian, or other person who stands in loco parentis&nbsp;to you or your spouse or domestic partner when he/she was a child</span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A spouse or domestic partner</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Mother-in-law or father-in-law</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Grandparents</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Grandchildren</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Brother or sister, whether related through half blood, whole blood or adoption, a foster sibling, or step-sibling</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Care recipient (a person for whom you are responsible for providing or arranging health or safety related care)</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">A member of your household</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.5in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:42.0pt; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave Time</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;during <span style=\"border:none\">the calendar year 2018, you have up to 24 hours; during the calendar year 2019, you have up to 32 hours; and beginning on January 1 and each year thereafter, you have up to 40 hours.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">These hours do not rollover at the end of the year if not used. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"><span style=\"border:none\">Absences not related to the above reasons, or absences that exceed the aforementioned hours, may be cause for disciplinary action up to and including termination. </span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Notice of Absence</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;when the use of sick leave is foreseeable, you shall make a good faith effort&nbsp;<span style=\"border:none\">to provide notice</span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, orally or in writing, </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">of the need for such time to us in advance</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">, this should include expected duration of the absence when possible</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">. You shall make a reasonable effort to schedule the use of earned sick time in a manner that do<span style=\"border:none\">es not unduly disrupt our operations. When the need for sick leave is not foreseeable, please follow our procedures for notification of unexpected time off (see the </span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><i><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">Attendance &amp; Punctuality</span></span></i></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\"> policy earlier in this manual for specific call-in procedures).</span></span></span> </span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Certification</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;</span></span></span> <span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">if you are absent within the two weeks prior to your scheduled final day of employment, or </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">you are absent on sick leave for more than 3 consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">reasonable documentation </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">supporting<span style=\"border:none\"> the need for leave</span>. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Leave of Absence</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence. </span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-right:.5in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11ptJustifiedCharChar\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Employee&#39;s Return to Work</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">&mdash;notice of your return to work aft<span style=\"border:none\">er an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave Accrual RI under 18',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-07-06 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"RI\"]',	1,	17,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-03-21 23:38:12',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	32,	1),
(489,	'<p>Paid sick leave is intended to protect you against undue financial loss in case of an illness for one or a few days. Acceptable medical reasons include your own incapacitating illness or injury and necessary medical treatment&nbsp;or that of a child, parent, spouse, or domestic partner. Sick pay benefits will be paid for the time you normally would have been scheduled to work had you not been absent. During the orientation and training period, you do not earn paid sick leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Regular FullâTime&nbsp;Employees</strong>&mdash;you&nbsp;earn ______ hours of paid sick leave for each month worked after the successful completion of the orientation and training period. Sick leave is not earned during a month where you are working less than 50 percent of the normally&nbsp;scheduled work hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Regular Part-Time Employees</strong>&mdash;you earn ______ hours of paid sick leave for each month worked after the successful completion of the orientation and training period. Sick leave is not earned during a month where you are working less than 50 percent of the normally scheduled work hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Overtime</strong>&mdash;paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notice of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you&rsquo;re going to be absent for an illness or injury, we appreciate as much advance notice as possible. At a minimum, you must notify us of your absence no later than 1 hour before the start of the workday. If circumstances are such that you cannot personally notify us, please have a relative or other responsible individual handle that for you within the required timeframe. Failure to follow this procedure will void the claim for paid sick leave and can be grounds for disciplinary action up to and including termination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>During an absence because of illness, you are to notify us daily of progress&nbsp;unless otherwise agreed upon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please give us advance notice of your return to work after a sick leave absence so that we can manage the schedule and staff accordingly.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Physician&rsquo;s </strong><strong>Statement</strong>&mdash;at our discretion, you may be required to bring a healthcare practitioner&rsquo;s certificate verifying your ability to return to work.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attendance </strong><strong>Record</strong>&mdash;please be sure to include any sick leave taken on your attendance record&nbsp;so we can pay you appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Leave of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within&nbsp;6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Please review our Leave of Absence policy for more information. No sick leave is earned while on a leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;any unused sick time will be paid once a year, on the anniversary&nbsp;date of employment, at your regular hourly rate of pay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick Leave upon </strong><strong>Termination</strong>&mdash;you will not be paid for any earned and unused sick leave at the time of termination.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave CT under 50 (General)',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-05-01 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CT\"]',	1,	49,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-05-24 19:27:42',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	16,	1),
(490,	'<p>Testing a new required policy update for the live site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rad&nbsp;Man!!</p>\r\n',	2,	'Test Live Update',	'Test Live Update',	'none',	'2018-10-10 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MA\"]',	1000,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-10-09 23:18:09',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'disabled',	1,	0),
(491,	'<p>Paid sick leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any of the following reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Diagnosis, care, or treatment of, or recovery from, your own mental or physical illness, injury or other adverse health condition, or for your own preventive medical care</li>\r\n	<li>To aid or care for your family member during diagnosis, care, or treatment of, or recovery from, your family member&rsquo;s mental or physical illness, injury or other adverse health condition, or for your family member&rsquo;s preventive medical care</li>\r\n	<li>Circumstances resulting from you or your family member being a victim of domestic or sexual violence</li>\r\n	<li>Closure of our workplace or your child&rsquo;s school or place of care by order of a public official due to an epidemic or other public health emergency</li>\r\n	<li>Being unable to work because of the issuance by a public health authority of a determination that the presence in the community by you or a family member in need of your care would jeopardize the health of others</li>\r\n	<li>Attend a school-related conference, meeting, function or other event requested or required by your child&rsquo;s school administrator, teacher, or other professional staff member, or to attend a meeting regarding care provided to the child&nbsp;in connection with the child&rsquo;s health condition or disability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>For purposes of this policy, the term family member includes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>An employee&#39;s or a spouse&rsquo;s or a domestic partner&#39;s or a civil union partner&rsquo;s biological, adoptive, or foster child, stepchild or legal ward</li>\r\n	<li>A spouse</li>\r\n	<li>A domestic partner</li>\r\n	<li>A civil union partner</li>\r\n	<li>An employee&rsquo;s or a spouse&rsquo;s or a domestic partner&#39;s or a civil union partner&rsquo;s biological, adoptive, or foster sibling</li>\r\n	<li>An employee&rsquo;s or a spouse&rsquo;s or a domestic partner&#39;s or a civil union partner&rsquo;s biological, adoptive, or foster parent, stepparent or legal guardian or person who stood in loco parentis</li>\r\n	<li>An employee&rsquo;s or a spouse&rsquo;s or a domestic partner&#39;s or a civil union partner&rsquo;s grandparent</li>\r\n	<li>An employee&rsquo;s or a spouse&rsquo;s or a domestic partner&#39;s or a civil union partner&rsquo;s grandchild</li>\r\n	<li>Any other individual related by blood to the employee or whose close association with the employee is the equivalent of a family relationship</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;paid sick leave is provided to all employees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Benefit </strong><strong>Year</strong>&mdash;January 1 to December 31.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Date Sick Leave Accrual </strong><strong>Begins</strong>&mdash;October 29 for all employees employed as of October 29, 2018. First day of employment for all employees hired after October 29, 2018. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Earning Sick Leave</strong>&mdash;1 hour of paid leave is accrued for every 30 hours worked up to a maximum of 40 hours per benefit year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Sick </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;in 1 benefit year, you may not use more than 40 hours of sick leave. You are not eligible to use your accrued sick leave until the 120th calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial 120 days of employment, you may use your sick leave as it is accrued.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sick leave must be used in full-day increments based on what you are scheduled to work. For example, if you are scheduled to work 6 hours, sick leave must be taken for 6 hours. At our discretion, we may make exceptions and allow fewer sick time hours to be used depending on your position and the schedule.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;up to 40 hours of accrued and unused sick leave during a benefit year will be carried over into the next year. Sick time is capped at 40 hours.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unused sick leave that is rolled over will not affect your ability to accrue up to 40 hours each year. For example, you roll over 20 hours of sick leave and accrue 20 more hours to a cap of 40 hours for the benefit year. If you use 20 hours of sick time in that same year, you will begin to accrue up to 20 more hours of sick time to total 40 hours of sick time actually accrued in the benefit year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your employment ends, for any reason, and you are rehired within 180 days of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued sick leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using sick leave provided you worked at least 120 days previously.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Make-up </strong><strong>Time</strong>&mdash;upon mutual consent by you and us, you may choose to work additional hours or shifts during the same or next pay period in lieu of hours or shifts missed and not have to use paid sick leave benefits. However, we cannot require you to work the extra hours or shifts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notice of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;when the use of paid sick leave is foreseeable, you shall provide notice of your intention to take sick time at least 7 days in advance. If the need for paid sick leave is unforeseeable, please provide notice as soon as practicable. We ask that you comply with our rules regarding notifying us of your absences and to try to schedule the use of sick time in a manner that does not unduly disrupt our operations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;if you are absent on paid sick leave for 3 or more consecutive scheduled work days, you may be required to bring in certification supporting the need for leave from your treating physician. If the need for sick leave is foreseeable and will require you to be off for 3 or more consecutive days, you may be required to provide certification supporting the need for leave from your treating physician prior to sick leave commencing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Overtime</strong>&mdash;the time spent on paid sick leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attendance </strong><strong>Record</strong>&mdash;if you have earned sick leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record so we can be sure to pay you appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Leave of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid sick time is not earned while on a leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employee&#39;s Return to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Sick Leave upon </strong><strong>Termination</strong>&mdash;accrued and unused sick leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Sick Leave NJ',	'SICK LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-11-14 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	1,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-10-10 21:25:34',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	27,	1),
(492,	'<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border:none; font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"border:none; font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"border:none\">If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth<span style=\"border:none\">,<span style=\"border:none\"> lactation or the need to express breastmilk<span style=\"border:none\">, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation on the advice of your treating physician. </span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">Medical Certification</span></b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you our <i>Certification of Healthcare Provider for Pregnancy Disability Leave, Transfer and/or Reasonable Accommodation Form </i>for this purpose.<i> &nbsp;</i></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"border:solid windowtext 3.0pt; padding:1.0pt 4.0pt 1.0pt 4.0pt\">\r\n<p align=\"center\" style=\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0in; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><b><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</span></span></b></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n',	4,	'Pregnancy Disability SC 15+',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2018-11-01 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"SC\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-10-31 23:50:57',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	91,	1),
(493,	'<p><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt\">We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required meal periods, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-IL under 5',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2018-11-06 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	1,	4,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-11-05 23:27:02',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	133,	1),
(494,	'<p>Testing Policy for the Update Process. Please ignore.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bullet 1</li>\r\n	<li>Bullet 2</li>\r\n	<li>Bullet 3</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	3,	'Update Process Testing 1 2018',	'Update Process Testing 1 2018',	'none',	'2018-11-10 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"IL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-11-09 20:46:56',	'2019-12-17 20:59:52',	'disabled',	26,	0),
(495,	'<p>Washington\'s Paid Family &amp; Medical Leave Program is organized as an insurance program. Beginning on Jan. 1, 2019, we are required to collect Paid Family and Medical Leave premiums from your paychecks.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The initial premium will be 0.4% and can be adjusted annually after 2020 by the Employment Security Department, according to rules set by the statute. One-third (1/3) of the premium will be collected for Family Leave, and 2/3 of the premium for Medical Leave.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The premium is shared between us (employer = 37% and employee = 63%). Employers with fewer than 50 employees are not required to pay the employer portion of the premium but are still required to collect and remit the employee portion. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Premium payments are required to be paid quarterly. Payments are due to the department by the last day of the month following the end of the calendar quarter for which premiums are being paid.</p>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><strong><u>Paid Family and Medical Leave (Beginning January 1, 2020)</u></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>BenefitÂ </strong><strong>Period</strong>âa ârollingâ 12 month period measured backward from the date an employee uses any Paid Family and Medical Leave. Under the âârollingââ 12 month period, each time an employee takes Paid Family and Medical Leave, the remaining leave entitlement would be the balance of the 12 weeks which has not been used during the immediately preceding 12 months.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â  Example:</strong> Michael requests three weeks of medical leave to begin on July 31st. The employer looks back 12 months (from July 31st back to the previous August 1st) to see if any leave had been used. Michael had not taken any previous leave, so he is entitled to the three weeks he requested and has nine more weeks available.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>âto qualify for paid family and medical leave, you must have worked at least 820 hours or more in the qualifying period. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 820 hours you need to qualify can be accrued at more than one employer. For example, if worked 15 hours a week at two different employers, you would accrue 30 hours per week toward this programâs qualifying hours.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Qualifying Period</strong>âthe first four of the last five completed calendar quarters starting from the day you intend to take leave. If you donât qualify by that standard, the last four completed calendar quarters will be used.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Paid family leave may be granted for the following reasons: </p>\n\n<ul><li>The birth of a child</li>\n	<li>The placement of a child under 18 for adoption or foster care </li>\n	<li>The serious health condition* of your family member (spouse, domestic partner, child or parent)</li>\n	<li>Any âqualifying exigencyâ (as the Secretary shall, by regulation, determine) arising out of the fact that your spouse, domestic partner, child, or parent is on active duty (or has been notified of an impending call or order to active duty) in the National Guard or Reserves in support of a contingency operation or a member of the Armed Forces who is deployed in a foreign country</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Paid medical leave may be granted for the following reasons</p>\n\n<ul><li>Your own serious health condition*</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>*A serious health condition is an illness, injury, impairment, or physical or mental condition that involves inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential health care facility; or continuing treatment orÂ continuing supervision by a health care provider.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Length of Leave</strong>âup to 12 weeks of leave are generally available, though up to 18 weeks could be allowed in some circumstances.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Job Protection</strong>âprovided that we employ 50 or more employees and you worked at least 12 months (not continuous in some circumstances) and at least 1,250 hours in the preceding year, family or medical leave under the program is protected, meaning you must be returned to the same or comparable position at the end of the leave period.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>NotificationÂ of </strong><strong>Leave</strong>âyou must provide notification of your intention to take leave. If an event is foreseeable, you must provide 30 daysâ notice. If the event is unforeseeable, you must provide notice as soon as practicable. For example, if you have a medical procedure appointment that will be the start of your leave, you must give your employer 30 daysâ notice of your intention to take leave. <u>Your application to the Employment Security Department isnât considered notice to your employer</u>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong>âwhile on leave, you are entitled to progressive wage replacement. That means youâll get a percentage of your average weekly pay. The benefit is up to 90% of your weekly wage with a minimum of $100 per week and a maximum of $1,000 per week.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For more details about this policy, including how to apply for benefits, please ask your manager.Â </p>\n',	4,	'Paid Family Leave WA',	'PAID FAMILY AND MEDICAL LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	1,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-11-15 00:37:33',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	290,	1),
(496,	'<p style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.05in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">If you are a victim of a crime, you may be eligible for unpaid leave for the purpose attending a deposition or court proceeding related to:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.05in; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Criminal proceedings where you have a legal right or obligation to appear at the proceeding </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.05in; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Relief from abuse hearings and neglect or exploitation hearings under when you are a plaintiff </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:.05in; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Hearings concerning an order against stalking or sexual assault</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Definitions</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;for purposes of this policy, a victim of a crime is person who has:</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Obtained a relief from abuse order against a family or household member</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Obtained a court order against stalking or sexual assault </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Obtained a court order against abuse of a vulnerable adult </span></span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Sustained physical, emotional or financial injury as the direct result of a crime, and is identified as a crime victim in an affidavit filed by law enforcement</span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Eligible Employees</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;you must have worked for us an average of at least 20 hours per week for a period of six months immediately preceding the leave.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0in; margin-right:3.75pt; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Benefits</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;any other applicable benefits will continue for the duration of leave at the same level and conditions that existed prior to the leave. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin:0in; margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin-right:0in; margin-left:0in\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"color:black\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">Wages</span></strong><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Arial Narrow&quot;,sans-serif\">&mdash;leave is unpaid unless you choose to use any available paid time off benefits during the time off.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Crime Victims Leave VT',	'CRIME VICTIM\'S LEAVE',	'none',	'2018-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VT\"]',	1,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-11-15 00:40:48',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	374,	1),
(497,	'<p style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt; margin:0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\">It is our policy to provide a work environment that is free from any form of discrimination or </span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\">harassment.</span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"> Throughout <span style=\"border:none\">this <span style=\"border:none\">policy, the term harassment </span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"ArialNarrow11pt\" style=\"border: none;\"><u><span style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\">always</span></span></u><span style=\"border: none;\"><span style=\"border:none\"> includes<span style=\"border:none\"> sexual harassment.<span style=\"border:none\"> No form of harassment will be tolerated. &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Harassment can take many forms: written, verbal and non-verbal, and can occur with any type of medium: phone, email, texting, social networking, etc. In all cases, jokes, name calling, discrimination, or harassment is prohibited at all times. Everyone is required to work in a manner that prevents discrimination or harassment in the workplace. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy is one component of our commitment to a discrimination-free work environment. Harassment of any kind is against the law, and all employees have a legal right to a workplace free from discrimination or harassment. We urge you to report discrimination or harassment by filing a complaint internally with <span class=\"bulletedtextChar\">your direct supervisor, or </span>any other company supervisor/manager as soon as possible. You may also file a complaint with a government agency or in court under federal, state or local anti-discrimination laws.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">This policy applies to all employees, applicants for employment, interns (whether paid or unpaid), contractors and persons conducting business, regardless of immigration status. Everyone must follow and uphold this policy.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Discrimination and harassment will not be tolerated. Any employee or individual covered by this policy who engages in discrimination, harassment or retaliation will be subject to remedial and/or disciplinary action (e.g., counseling, suspension, termination).</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">No person covered by this Policy shall be subject to adverse action because the employee reports an incident of discrimination or harassment, provides information, or otherwise assists in any investigation of a complaint.<b> </b>We will will not tolerate such retaliation against anyone who, in good faith, reports or provides information about suspected discrimination or harassment. Any employee of ours who retaliates against anyone involved in an investigation will be subjected to disciplinary action, up to and including termination. Anyone working in the workplace who believe s/he has been subject to such retaliation should inform a supervisor or manager. Anyone who believes they have been a target of such retaliation may also seek relief in other available forums, as explained below in the section on Legal Protections.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Harassment of any kind is offensive, is a violation of our policies, is unlawful, and may subject us to liability for harm to targets of harassment. Harassers may also be individually subject to liability. Employees of every level who engage in harassment, including managers and supervisors who engage in harassment or who allow such behavior to continue, will be penalized for such misconduct.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will conduct a prompt and thorough investigation that ensures due process for all parties, whenever management receives a complaint about harassment, or otherwise knows of possible harassment occurring. We will keep the investigation confidential to the extent possible. Effective corrective action will be taken whenever harassment is found to have occurred. All employees, including managers and supervisors, are required to cooperate with any internal investigation of harassment.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" class=\"Default\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><u>What Is &ldquo;Sexual Harassment&rdquo;?</u></b></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Sexual harassment is a form of sex discrimination and is unlawful under federal, state, and (where applicable) local law. Sexual harassment includes harassment on the basis of sex, sexual orientation, self-identified or perceived sex, gender expression, gender identity and the status of being transgender.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Sexual harassment includes unwelcome conduct which is either of a sexual nature, or which is directed at an individual because of that individual&rsquo;s sex when:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Such conduct has the purpose or effect of unreasonably interfering with an individual&rsquo;s work performance or creating an intimidating, hostile or offensive work environment, even if the reporting individual is not the intended target of the sexual harassment;</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Such conduct is made either explicitly or implicitly a term or condition of employment; or</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Submission to or rejection of such conduct is used as the basis for employment decisions affecting an individual&rsquo;s employment.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">A sexually harassing hostile work environment includes, but is not limited to, words, signs, jokes, pranks, intimidation or physical violence which are of a sexual nature, or which are directed at an individual because of that individual&rsquo;s sex. Sexual harassment also consists of any unwanted verbal or physical advances, sexually explicit derogatory statements or sexually discriminatory remarks made by someone which are offensive or objectionable to the recipient, which cause the recipient discomfort or humiliation, which interfere with the recipient&rsquo;s job performance.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Sexual harassment also occurs when a person in authority tries to trade job benefits for sexual favors. This can include hiring, promotion, continued employment or any other terms, conditions or privileges of employment. This is also called &ldquo;quid pro quo&rdquo; harassment.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Any employee who feels harassed should report so that any violation of this policy can be corrected promptly. Any harassing conduct, even a single incident, can be addressed under this policy.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><u>Examples of sexual harassment</u></b></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">The following describes some of the types of acts that may be unlawful sexual harassment and that are strictly prohibited:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Physical acts of a sexual nature, such as:</span></span></span>\r\n\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Touching, pinching, patting, kissing, hugging, grabbing, brushing against another employee&rsquo;s body or poking another employee&rsquo;s body;</span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Rape, sexual battery, molestation or attempts to commit these assaults.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Unwanted sexual advances or propositions, such as:</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Requests for sexual favors accompanied by implied or overt threats concerning the target&rsquo;s job performance evaluation, a promotion or other job benefits or detriments;</span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Subtle or obvious pressure for unwelcome sexual activities.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Sexually oriented gestures, noises, remarks or jokes, or comments about a person&rsquo;s sexuality or sexual experience, which create a hostile work environment.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Sex stereotyping occurs when conduct or personality traits are considered inappropriate simply because they may not conform to other people&#39;s ideas or perceptions about how individuals of a particular sex should act or look.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Sexual or discriminatory displays or publications anywhere in the workplace, such as:</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Displaying pictures, posters, calendars, graffiti, objects, promotional material, reading materials or other materials that are sexually demeaning or pornographic. This includes such sexual displays on workplace computers or cell phones and sharing such displays while in the workplace.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Hostile actions taken against an individual because of that individual&rsquo;s sex, sexual orientation, gender identity and the status of being transgender, such as:</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Interfering with, destroying or damaging a person&rsquo;s workstation, tools or equipment, or otherwise interfering with the individual&rsquo;s ability to perform the job;</span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Sabotaging an individual&rsquo;s work;</span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Bullying, yelling, name-calling.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><u>Who can be a target of sexual harassment?</u></b></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Sexual harassment can occur between any individuals, regardless of their sex or gender. New York Law protects employees, paid or unpaid interns, and non-employees, including independent contractors, and those employed by companies contracting to provide services in the workplace. Harassers can be a superior, a subordinate, a coworker or anyone in the workplace including an independent contractor, contract worker, vendor, client, customer or visitor.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><u>Where can sexual harassment occur?</u></b></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Unlawful sexual harassment is not limited to the physical workplace itself. It can occur while employees are traveling for business or at employer sponsored events or parties. Calls, texts, emails, and social media usage by employees can constitute unlawful workplace harassment, even if they occur away from the workplace premises, on personal devices or during non-work hours.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" class=\"Default\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" class=\"Default\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><u>Retaliation</u></b></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Unlawful retaliation can be any action that could discourage a worker from coming forward to make or support a sexual harassment claim. Adverse action need not be job-related or occur in the workplace to constitute unlawful retaliation (e.g., threats of physical violence outside of work hours). </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Such retaliation is unlawful under federal, state, and (where applicable) local law. The New York State Human Rights Law protects any individual who has engaged in &ldquo;protected activity.&rdquo; Protected activity occurs when a person has:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">made a complaint of harassment, either internally or with any anti-discrimination agency; </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">testified or assisted in a proceeding involving harassment under the Human Rights Law or other anti-discrimination law; </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">opposed harassment by making a verbal or informal complaint to management, or by simply informing a supervisor or manager of harassment; </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">reported that another employee has been harassed; or </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">encouraged a fellow employee to report harassment.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Even if the alleged harassment does not turn out to rise to the level of a violation of law, the individual is protected from retaliation if the person had a good faith belief that the practices were unlawful. However, the retaliation provision is not intended to protect persons making intentionally false charges of harassment.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" class=\"Default\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><u>Reporting Harassment</u></b></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b>Preventing harassment is everyone&rsquo;s responsibility.</b> We cannot prevent or remedy harassment unless we know about it. Anyone who has been subjected to behavior that may constitute harassment is encouraged to report such behavior to a <span class=\"bulletedtextChar\">direct supervisor, or </span>any other company supervisor/manager as soon as possible. Anyone who witnesses or becomes aware of potential instances of harassment should report such behavior to a <span class=\"bulletedtextChar\">direct supervisor, or </span>any other company supervisor/manager as soon as possible.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Reports of harassment may be made verbally or in writing. A form for submission of a written complaint is attached to this policy, and all employees are encouraged to use this complaint form. If you are reporting harassment on behalf of other employees, please use the complaint form and note that it is on another employee&rsquo;s behalf.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Please see the section below on Legal Protections for other options. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" class=\"Default\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><u>Supervisory Responsibilities</u></b></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">All supervisors and managers who receive a complaint or information about suspected harassment, observe what may be harassing behavior or for any reason suspect that harassment is occurring, <b>are required </b>to report such suspected harassment to their direct supervisor or manager.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">In addition to being subject to discipline if they engaged in harassing conduct themselves, supervisors and managers will be subject to discipline for failing to report suspected harassment or otherwise knowingly allowing harassment to continue. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Supervisors and managers will also be subject to discipline for engaging in any retaliation.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" class=\"Default\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" class=\"Default\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><u>Complaint and Investigation of Harassment</u></b></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><i>All</i></b> complaints or information about harassment will be investigated, whether that information was reported in verbal or written form. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">An investigation of any complaint, information or knowledge of suspected harassment will be prompt and thorough, commenced immediately and completed as soon as possible. The investigation will be kept confidential to the extent possible. All persons involved, including complainants, witnesses and alleged harassers will be accorded due process, as outlined below, to protect their rights to a fair and impartial investigation. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Any employee may be required to cooperate as needed in an investigation of suspected harassment. We will not tolerate retaliation against employees who file complaints, support another&rsquo;s complaint or participate in an investigation regarding a violation of this policy.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"DefaultCxSpMiddle\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\">While the process may vary from case to case, investigations should be done in accordance with the following:</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li class=\"DefaultCxSpMiddle\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\">Upon receipt of complaint, we will conduct an immediate review of the allegations and take any interim actions (e.g., instructing the respondent to refrain from communications with the complainant), as appropriate. If complaint is verbal, we will encourage the individual to complete the complaint form in writing. If he or she refuses, we may prepare a complaint form based on the verbal reporting.</span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">If documents, emails or phone records are relevant to the investigation, we will take steps to obtain and preserve them. </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will request and review all relevant documents, including all electronic communications.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will interview all parties involved, including any relevant witnesses. </span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will create written documentation of the investigation (such as a letter, memo or email), which contains the following:</span></span></span>\r\n	<ul style=\"list-style-type:circle\">\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">A list of all documents reviewed, along with a detailed summary of relevant documents;</span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">A list of names of those interviewed, along with a detailed summary of their statements;</span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">A timeline of events;</span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">A summary of prior relevant incidents, reported or unreported; and</span></span></span></li>\r\n		<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">The basis for the decision and final resolution of the complaint, together with any corrective action(s).</span></span></span></li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will keep the written documentation and associated documents in a secure and confidential location.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will promptly notify the individual who reported and the individual(s) about whom the complaint was made of the final determination and implement any corrective actions identified in the written document.</span></span></span></li>\r\n	<li class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">We will inform the individual who reported of the right to file a complaint or charge externally as outlined in the next section.</span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p align=\"center\" class=\"Default\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\"><span style=\"color:black\"><b><u>Legal Protections and External Remedies</u></b></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\"><span style=\"color:black\">Harassment is not only prohibited by us but is also prohibited by state, federal, and, where applicable, local law.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\"><span style=\"color:black\">&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"margin:0in 0in 0.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"color:black\">Aside from our internal process, you may also choose to pursue legal remedies with the following governmental entities. While a private attorney is not required to file a complaint with a governmental agency, you may seek the legal advice of an attorney.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><b><u>State Human Rights Law </u></b></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">The Human Rights Law (HRL), codified as N.Y. Executive Law, art. 15, &sect; 290 et seq., applies to all employers in New York State with regard to harassment, and protects employees, paid or unpaid interns and non-employees, regardless of immigration status. A complaint alleging violation of the HRL may be filed either with the Division of Human Rights (DHR) or in New York State Supreme Court.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">Complaints with DHR may be filed any time <b>within one year</b> of the harassment. If an individual did not file at the DHR, they can sue directly in state court under the HRL <b>within three years</b> of the alleged harassment. An individual may not file with the DHR if they have already filed an HRL complaint in state court.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">An internal complaint with us does not extend your time to file with the DHR or in court. The one year or three years is counted from date of the most recent incident of harassment.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">You do not need an attorney to file a complaint with the DHR, and there is no cost to file with the DHR.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:8.0pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">The DHR will investigate your complaint and determine whether there is probable cause to believe that harassment has occurred. Probable cause cases are forwarded to a public hearing before an administrative law judge. If harassment is found after a hearing, the DHR has the power to award relief, which varies but may include requiring the employer to take action to stop the harassment, or redress the damage caused, including paying of monetary damages, attorney&rsquo;s fees and civil fines.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">The DHR&rsquo;s main office contact information is: NYS Division of Human Rights, One Fordham Plaza, Fourth Floor, Bronx, New York 10458. You may call (718) 741-8400 <span style=\"color:black\">or visit:</span> <a href=\"http://www.dhr.ny.gov\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"color:black\">www.dhr.ny.gov</span></a><span style=\"color:black\">.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"color:black\">Contact the DHR at (888) 392-3644 or visit </span><a href=\"https://dhr.ny.gov/complaint\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"color:black\">dhr.ny.gov/complaint</span></a><span style=\"color:black\"> for more information about filing a complaint. The website has a complaint form that can be downloaded, filled</span> out, notarized and mailed to the DHR. The website also contains contact information for the DHR&rsquo;s regional offices across New York State. </span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\"><b><u>Civil Rights Act of 1964</u></b></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">The United States Equal Employment Opportunity Commission (EEOC) enforces federal anti-discrimination laws, including Title VII of the 1964 federal Civil Rights Act (codified as 42 U.S.C. &sect; 2000e et seq.). An individual can file a complaint with the EEOC anytime within 300 days from the harassment. There is no cost to file a complaint with the EEOC. The EEOC will investigate the complaint, and <span style=\"color:black\">determine whether there is reasonable cause to believe that discrimination has occurred, at which point the EEOC will issue a Right to Sue letter permitting the individual to file a complaint in federal court. </span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"color:black\">The EEOC does not hold hearings or award relief, but may take other action including pursuing cases in federal court on behalf of complaining parties. Federal courts may award remedies if discrimination is found to have occurred. In general, private employers must have at least 15 employees to come within the jurisdiction of the EEOC.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">An employee alleging discrimination at work can file a &ldquo;Charge of Discrimination.&rdquo; The <span style=\"color:black\">EEOC has district, area, and field offices where complaints can be filed. Contact the EEOC by calling 1-800-669-4000 (TTY: 1-800-669-6820), visiting their website at </span><a href=\"http://www.eeoc.gov\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"color:black\">www.eeoc.gov</span></a><span style=\"color:black\"> or via email at </span><a href=\"mailto:info@eeoc.gov\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"color:black\">info@eeoc.gov</span></a><span style=\"color:black\">.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">If an individual filed an administrative complaint with the DHR, the DHR will file the complaint with the EEOC to preserve the right to proceed in federal court.</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><span style=\"page-break-after:avoid\"><b><u>Local Protections</u></b></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">Many localities enforce laws protecting individuals from harassment and discrimination. An individual should contact the county, city or town in which they live to find out if such a law exists. For example, employees who <span style=\"color:black\">work in New York City may file complaints of harassment with the New York City Commission on Human Rights. Contact their main office at Law Enforcement Bureau of the NYC Commission on Human Rights, 40 Rector Street, 10th Floor, New York, New York; call 311 or (212) 306-7450; or visit </span><a href=\"http://www.nyc.gov/html/cchr/html/home/home.shtml\" style=\"color:blue; text-decoration:underline\"><span style=\"color:black\">www.nyc.gov/html/cchr/html/home/home.shtml</span></a><span style=\"color:black\">.</span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\"><b><u>Contact the Local Police Department</u></b></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"CxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"line-height:normal\">If the harassment involves unwanted physical touching, coerced physical confinement or coerced sex acts, the conduct may constitute a crime. Contact the local police department.&nbsp;</span></span></span></p>\r\n',	6,	'Harassment NY',	'ANTI-HARASSMENT AND DISCRIMINATION',	'none',	'2018-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	1,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2018-11-15 00:48:08',	'2019-12-18 23:18:19',	'enabled',	1,	0),
