(501,	'<p>This is a testing policy. If you see this, please ignore it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Option 1</li>\r\n	<li>Option 2</li>\r\n	<li>Option 3</li>\r\n	<li>New text from 7/18/19</li>\r\n	<li>New text from 7/19/19</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',	4,	'Update Process Testing Policy Summer 2019-3',	'Update Process Testing Policy Summer 2019-3',	'none',	'2019-07-20 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"CA\"]',	1450,	1600,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-07-03 20:54:08',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'disabled',	10,	1),
(502,	'<p>All staff members should be aware that there are certain hazards common in a veterinary hospital that could cause risks to a developing fetus or to the reproductive systems of men and women seeking to have children. If you are a pregnant staff member or a staff member seeking to become pregnant or have children, you may wish to speak with the Safety Director regarding potentially harmful chemicals and exposure to radiation in your job or to review our OSHA required disclosures regarding chemicals and exposure to radiation located in the Hospital Safety Manual.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you are a pregnant staff member of this practice, you should know that there is a chance that you and your fetus will be exposed to some of the hazards common in a veterinary hospital that may pose significant risks to a developing fetus. To minimize the risks, we require that you adhere to all safety rules relevant to the procedure being performed or the product being used. You must be capable of performing the essential requirements of the position. If you cannot perform the essential requirements of your position safely, you may request a transfer to an administrative position if one is available or you may request maternity leave in accordance with our established policy on medical leave.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe realize that this decision is a personal one and every person must make his or her own choices. You can consult with your physician prior to making this decision.</p>\r\n',	5,	'Reproductive Rights',	'Workplace Issues Concerning Reproduction and Fertility',	'none',	'2019-10-03 07:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	1,	1000000,	'[\"voptional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-10-03 16:32:17',	'2019-10-03 16:32:44',	'enabled',	6,	0),
(503,	'<p>Beginning July 1, 2020, you will be provided paid family leave as outlined below.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Covered Employees</strong><!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc245634814\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc245692096\'><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc245702073\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc246323575\'><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc246841890\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc291058392\'><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc304295664\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc343247442\'></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc245634814\'><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc245692096\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc245702073\'><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc246323575\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc246841890\'><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc291058392\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc304295664\'><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc343247442\'><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'>xe &quot;Eligibility&quot;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc245634814\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc245692096\'><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc245702073\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc246323575\'><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc246841890\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc291058392\'><spanstyle=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc304295664\'><span style=\'mso-bookmark:_Toc343247442\'></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><spanstyle=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span><![endif]-->&mdash;you are covered by this policy if you spend at least 50% of the time working in the District of Columbia, or if your employment is based in the District of Columbia and you regularly spend a substantial amount of your time in the District of Columbia and not more than 50% of your time in another jurisdiction.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong><!--[if supportFields]><bstyle=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-begin\'></span></span></b><spanstyle=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'>xe&quot;Eligibility&quot;</span><![endif]--><!--[if supportFields]><bstyle=\'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\'><span style=\'font-size:11.0pt;font-family:\"Arial Narrow\",sans-serif\'><span style=\'mso-element:field-end\'></span></span></b><![endif]-->&mdash;to qualify for paid family leave, you must have been a covered employee for &nbsp;some or all of the 52 calendar weeks immediately preceding the qualifying event for which paid leave is being taken.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Parental </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;paid family leave may be granted up to 8 weeks within a 52 workweek period for the following reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The birth of a child</li>\r\n	<li>The placement of a child for adoption or foster care</li>\r\n	<li>Baby bonding</li>\r\n	<li>The placement of a child for whom you legally assume and discharge parental responsibility</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Leave must be taken within one year of the occurrence of a qualifying reason.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Family </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;paid family leave may be granted up to 6 weeks within a 52 workweek period for the following reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>To provide care or companionship to a family member due to the diagnosis or occurrence of a serious health condition</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Medical </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;paid family leave may be granted up to 2 weeks within a 52 workweek period for the following reasons:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your own diagnosis or occurrence of a serious health condition</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>A serious health condition means a physical or mental illness, injury, or impairment that requires inpatient care in a hospital, hospice, or residential health care facility, or continuing treatment or supervision at home by a health care provider or other competent individual.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For purposes of this policy, &ldquo;family member&rdquo; means:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A biological, adopted, or foster son or daughter, a stepson or stepdaughter, a legal ward, a son or daughter of a domestic partner, or a person to whom an eligible individual stand in loco parentis</li>\r\n	<li>A biological, foster, or adoptive parent, a parent-in-law, a stepparent, a legal guardian, or other person who stood in loco parentis to an eligible individual when the eligible individual was a child</li>\r\n	<li>A person to whom an eligible individual is related by domestic partnership or marriage</li>\r\n	<li>A grandparent of an eligible individual</li>\r\n	<li>A sibling of an eligible individual</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Limited </strong><strong>Duration</strong>&mdash;paid leave benefits are limited to 8 workweeks total in a 52 workweek period regardless of the number of qualifying leave events that occurred during that period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Paid Family Leave </strong><strong>Program</strong>&mdash;this program is funded through an employer payroll tax. Benefit payments are managed by the Department of Employment Services.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Paid Leave DC',	'PAID FAMILY LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"DC\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-18 22:49:37',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	60,	1),
(504,	'<p>If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, lactation or the need to express breastmilk, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following are examples of possible accommodations that can be made:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Providing more frequent or longer breaks</li>\r\n	<li>Time off to recover from childbirth</li>\r\n	<li>Acquisition or modification of equipment</li>\r\n	<li>Appropriate seating</li>\r\n	<li>Temporary transfer to a less strenuous or less hazardous position</li>\r\n	<li>Job restructuring</li>\r\n	<li>Light duty</li>\r\n	<li>Modified work schedule</li>\r\n	<li>Providing a private, non-bathroom space for expressing breastmilk</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need any additional or different accommodations, please make your request known. We will engage in a timely, good faith, interactive process to determine an effective and reasonable accommodation.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Preg Disability KY',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"KY\"]',	15,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-18 22:55:22',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	95,	1),
(505,	'<p>If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, lactation or the need to express breastmilk, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation, upon request.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will work together to determine the possible accommodations that can be made to ensure your continued employment unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Medical</strong> <strong>Certification</strong>&mdash;you may be required to submit proof verifying the need for the accommodation. We will provide you a form for this purpose.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>The Genetic Information Nondiscrimination Act of 2008 (GINA) prohibits employers and other entities covered by GINA Title II from requesting or requiring genetic information of an individual or family member of the individual, except as specifically allowed by this law. To comply with this law, we ask that you not provide any genetic information when responding to this request for medical information. &ldquo;Genetic Information&rdquo; as defined by GINA includes an individual&rsquo;s family medical history, the results of an individual&rsquo;s or family member&rsquo;s genetic tests, the fact that an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member sought or received genetic services, and genetic information of a fetus carried by an individual or an individual&rsquo;s family member or an embryo lawfully held by an individual or family member receiving assistive reproductive services.</strong></p>\r\n',	4,	'Preg Disability ME',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ME\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-18 22:57:45',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	93,	1),
(506,	'<p>If you are a veteran who needs to attend a scheduled appointment at a medical facility operated by the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs, you will be provided with time off.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The time taken will be unpaid unless you use any paid time off benefit that you have available, if applicable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please provide us notice of your need for time off as soon as reasonably possible so that we may appropriately prepare for your absence and avoid unnecessary disruptions with workflow.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Time Off for VA Appt ME over 10',	'TIME OFF FOR VA APPOINTMENTS',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ME\"]',	10,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-18 23:02:09',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	47,	1),
(507,	'<p>If you are a veteran who needs to attend a scheduled appointment at a medical facility operated by the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs, you will be provided with time off.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The time taken will be unpaid unless you use any paid time off benefit that you have available, if applicable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please provide us at least 2 weeks&rsquo; notice of the need for time off.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs provides you will less than 2 weeks&rsquo; notice of the appointment, then please provide us with notice of your need for time off as soon as reasonably possible so that we may appropriately prepare for your absence and avoid unnecessary disruptions with workflow.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Time Off for VA Appt ME under 10',	'TIME OFF FOR VA APPOINTMENTS',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ME\"]',	1,	9,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-18 23:04:13',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	48,	1),
(508,	'<p>You may be eligible for an unpaid leave of absence if you wish to donate an organ or your bone marrow to another person. To be eligible, you must have been employed for at least 12 months and worked 1,250 hours in the previous 12 months immediately preceding the beginning of leave. The following outlines the leave of absence available for each purpose:&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>O</strong><strong>rgan Donation</strong>&mdash;you may be given a leave of absence for up to 60 business days in any 12 month period for the purpose of donating an organ to another person.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Bone Marrow Donation</strong>&mdash;you may be given a leave of absence for up to 30 business days in any 12 month period for the purpose of donating bone marrow to another person.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Written Verification</strong>&mdash;if you need a leave for either of the above-listed reasons, you must provide written verification that you are an organ or bone marrow donor or that there is a medical necessity for the donation at the time the leave of absence is requested.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;leave is unpaid, unless you choose to use any paid time off benefits, if applicable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the purposes of seniority, benefits, or other terms of employment, leave taken under this policy does not constitute a break in continuous service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If applicable, we shall maintain health insurance coverage for the full duration of the leave in the same manner the coverage would have been maintained if you had been actively at work during the leave period. Therefore, if the health insurance premium is shared between us, you will be responsible for your portion each month while on leave. Failure to provide payment for your premium cost may result in health insurance being discontinued.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that work can be properly scheduled.&nbsp; Upon returning from leave you will be reinstated to the position held before the leave began, or a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.<span style=\"font-size:11pt\">&nbsp;ââââ</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Organ Bone Marrow MD 15 to 49',	'ORGAN AND BONE MARROW DONATION LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	15,	49,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-18 23:06:52',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	66,	1),
(509,	'<p>You may be eligible for an unpaid leave of absence if you wish to donate an organ or your bone marrow to another person. To be eligible, you must have been employed for at least 12 months and worked 1,250 hours in the previous 12 months immediately preceding the beginning of leave. The following outlines the leave of absence available for each purpose:&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>O</strong><strong>rgan Donation</strong>&mdash;you may be given a leave of absence for up to 60 business days in any 12 month period for the purpose of donating an organ to another person.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Bone Marrow Donation</strong>&mdash;you may be given a leave of absence for up to 30 business days in any 12 month period for the purpose of donating bone marrow to another person.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This leave does not run concurrently with Family and Medical Leave Act (FMLA) as described elsewhere in this manual.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Written Verification</strong>&mdash;if you need a leave for either of the above-listed reasons, you must provide written verification that you are an organ or bone marrow donor or that there is a medical necessity for the donation at the time the leave of absence is requested.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits</strong>&mdash;leave is unpaid, unless you choose to use any paid time off benefits, if applicable.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For the purposes of seniority, benefits, or other terms of employment, leave taken under this policy does not constitute a break in continuous service.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If applicable, we shall maintain health insurance coverage for the full duration of the leave in the same manner the coverage would have been maintained if you had been actively at work during the leave period. Therefore, if the health insurance premium is shared between us, you will be responsible for your portion each month while on leave. Failure to provide payment for your premium cost may result in health insurance being discontinued.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Reinstatement to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;if you intend to return to work sooner than originally scheduled, please give advance notice of the intended date of return so that work can be properly scheduled.&nbsp; Upon returning from leave you will be reinstated to the position held before the leave began, or a position with equivalent seniority status, benefits, pay and other terms and conditions of employment.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Organ Bone Marrow MD over 50',	'ORGAN AND BONE MARROW DONATION LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MD\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-18 23:09:18',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	67,	1),
(510,	'<p>Paid leave is intended to compensate you for wages that would have otherwise been lost due to an absence for any reason.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Benefit </strong><strong>Year</strong>&mdash;January 1 to December 31.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;paid leave is provided to all employees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Earning Paid Leave</strong>&mdash;0.01923 hours of paid leave are accrued for every 1 hour worked.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will be provided with the amount of paid leave you have accrued each payday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using Paid </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;you are not eligible to use your accrued paid leave until the 90<sup>th</sup> calendar day following commencement of your employment. After you have completed the initial 90 days of employment, you may use your paid leave as it is accrued.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Paid leave may be used in 4 hour increments and is paid based on your current rate of pay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may not use, in 1 year, more than 40 hours of paid leave.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Paid </strong><strong>Leave</strong>&mdash;up to 40 hours of accrued and unused paid leave will be carried over into the next benefit year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If your employment ends due to a layoff or discharge and you are rehired within 90 days of the date of separation, your previously unused accrued paid leave will be reinstated. There will be no waiting period, upon rehiring, for using paid leave provided you worked at least 90 days previously.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Notice of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;when the use of paid leave is foreseeable, you shall provide notice as soon as practicable, verbally or in writing, of the need to take paid leave. When possible, please provide notice at least 5 days in advance for scheduling purposes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When using paid leave for vacation purposes, we ask that you take the time off when it is most convenient for the practice. All vacations must be approved in advance to assure that scheduling needs are met. Please submit your request at least 4 weeks in advance. Vacation requests will generally be scheduled on a first come, first served basis. In the event of conflicting requests, seniority may be considered.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Overtime</strong>&mdash;the time spent on paid leave is not included as hours worked when computing overtime for the day or week.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Attendance </strong><strong>Record</strong>&mdash;if you have earned paid leave for an absence and expect to be paid, please indicate so on your attendance record so we can be sure to pay you on the next regularly scheduled payday after your leave was taken.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Leave of </strong><strong>Absence</strong>&mdash;if you are unable to return to work within 6 working days, you may be put on a leave of absence. Paid leave is not accrued while on a leave of absence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Employee&#39;s Return to </strong><strong>Work</strong>&mdash;notice of your return to work after an extended absence needs to be given in advance so that scheduling adjustments can be made.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unused Paid Leave upon </strong><strong>Termination</strong>&mdash;accrued and unused paid leave will not be paid at the time of separation.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Paid Leave NV',	'PAID LEAVE',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NV\"]',	50,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-18 23:12:51',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	59,	1),
(511,	'<p>Once you have earned sick leave, you may use your personal sick leave benefit provided by us for absences due to your family member&rsquo;s illness or injury, or for your family member to receive care from a licensed or certified health professional.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For purposes of this policy, family member means any of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Child or foster child</li>\r\n	<li>Spouse or domestic partner</li>\r\n	<li>Parent</li>\r\n	<li>Grandchild or great-grandchild</li>\r\n	<li>Grandparent or great-grandparent</li>\r\n	<li>Brother or sister</li>\r\n	<li>Niece or nephew</li>\r\n	<li>Aunt or uncle</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Eligibility</strong>&mdash;you must eligible to earn and use sick leave according to our sick leave policy. Please see our sick leave policy for further information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sick leave for family members must be used in the same manner as it would be for you, as explained in our sick leave policy.<span style=\"font-size:11pt\">&nbsp;ââââââ</span></p>\r\n',	4,	'Caregiver Leave NM',	'CAREGIVER LEAVE ACT',	'none',	'2019-12-17 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NM\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-18 23:16:27',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	286,	1),
(512,	'<p>If lunch and/or rest breaks are applicable to our office, please review the respective policies in the benefits section of this manual for details about how those specified breaks should be observed and factored into your schedule.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This policy relates to how time records are to be managed for lunch and rest breaks that have been authorized by the employer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bona fide lunch breaks are unpaid; therefore, if you are authorized to take a bona fide lunch break, please clock out on your time record. Bona fide lunch breaks are defined as lasting 30 minutes or more in which no work is performed during the entire period.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Short rest breaks that have been authorized will be paid; therefore, please do not clock out on your time record. Short rest breaks are defined as 20 minutes or less but&nbsp;<u>shall not exceed 10 minutes without&nbsp;prior permission</u>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Unauthorized extensions of rest breaks that are provided is a violation of policy, will not be paid, and may result in disciplinary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a new mom who needs additional break time to breastfeed or express milk, you will be allotted the same paid break time that everyone else receives. Any time needed beyond that will be unpaid. For example, if all employees receive 10 minutes for breaks and the new mom needs 20 minutes, the first 10 minutes will be paid and the remaining time unpaid. Therefore, please do not clock out on your time records until the break time is unpaid.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please let us know if you have questions about this or other applicable policies regarding breaks at our office.</p>\r\n',	3,	'Breaks and Time Records',	'BREAKS AND TIME RECORDS',	'none',	'2020-02-11 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"ALL\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-19 19:12:15',	'2020-02-11 18:26:03',	'enabled',	2,	0),
(513,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you or a family/household member are a victim of domestic abuse, you may be allowed to take reasonable time off from work so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Obtain or attempt to obtain any relief, including, but not limited to, a temporary or permanent restraining order or other injunctive relief to help ensure the health, safety, or welfare of you or your family/household member.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any applicable paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take time off under this policy, you must give us at least 48 hours&rsquo; advance notice of your intention to take leave unless that is impracticable and/or the situation poses imminent danger to the health or safety of you or your family/household member.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may be required to provide verification supporting your reason for being absent. If required, verification must be provided within a reasonable time after it has been requested.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will treat information the employee provides confidentially. Information will not be disclosed without your express permission, or as otherwise required by applicable federal or state law.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence MN',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"MN\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-19 22:58:26',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	267,	1),
(514,	'<p>This policy focuses on domestic violence which can infiltrate and impact you and us in many ways. Through this policy, it is our aim to provide support should domestic violence be a factor for you.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you or your child is a victim of domestic violence, you may take reasonable time off from work so that you can:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Seek medical attention for injuries caused by domestic violence</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain services from a domestic violence shelter, program, or rape crisis center as a result of domestic violence</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain psychological counseling related to an incident or incidents of domestic violence</li>\r\n	<li>Participate in safety planning and take other actions to increase safety from future incidents of domestic violence including temporary or permanent relocation</li>\r\n	<li>Obtain legal services, assist in the prosecution of the offense, or appear in court in relation to the incident or incidents of domestic violence</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Time off may be denied if it will cause undue hardship on our business.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Time off taken will be unpaid unless you choose to use any applicable paid time off benefit available at that time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Health insurance, if applicable, will continue during the leave period at the same level and under the same conditions that existed before leave began. Therefore, if the premium is shared between you and us, you are responsible for your share of the health insurance premium while on leave. Failure to pay your share of the health insurance premium may result in a loss of coverage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need to take time off under this policy, you must give us reasonable advance notice of your intention to take time off, unless advance notice is not feasible. When the need for time off is unforeseeable, we may ask you to provide certification to us within a reasonable time after the absence.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can provide certification through one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A police report indicating that you or your child were a victim of domestic violence.</li>\r\n	<li>Court protection order separating you or your child from the perpetrator of an act of domestic violence, or other evidence from the court or prosecuting attorney that you have appeared in court.</li>\r\n	<li>Documentation from a medical professional, domestic violence advocate, health care provider, or counselor that you or your child were undergoing counseling or treatment for physical or mental injuries or abuse resulting in victimization from an act of domestic violence.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>To the extent allowed by law, we will treat your status as a victim of domestic violence and any information you provide confidentially.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Domestic Violence NY',	'LEAVE RELATED TO DOMESTIC VIOLENCE',	'none',	'2019-12-18 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NY\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-11-19 23:05:07',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	273,	1),
(515,	'<p>If you are a veteran who has received an honorable discharge from the United States armed forces, you shall have a preference to not work during the 24 hours comprising Veterans Day provided that you request the time off in advance. Multiple requests from veterans for time off on this holiday may result in our inability to grant the time off to everyone depending on staffing needs. Time off is unpaid.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Veterans Day Holiday - NH',	'VETERANS DAY HOLIDAY',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NH\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-12-18 22:42:07',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	44,	1),
(516,	'<p>We provide a pre-tax election transportation fringe benefits program that provides commuter highway vehicle and transit benefits consistent with applicable Internal Revenue Code.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The benefit is equal to the maximum amount that may be deducted for those programs from an employee&#39;s gross income, which may vary from one year to the next.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A qualified transportation fringe benefit is defined as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<li>Transportation in a commuter highway vehicle for travel between the employee&rsquo;s residence and place of employment</li>\r\n	<li>Transit passes</li>\r\n	<li>Qualified parking</li>\r\n	<li>Qualified bicycle commuting reimbursement</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This benefit is available immediately upon hire. You will be provided with appropriate information of how this works. If you have questions, please let us know.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Commuter Benefits NJ',	'COMMUTER BENEFITS',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"NJ\"]',	20,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-12-18 22:44:37',	'2020-06-08 18:46:20',	'enabled',	56,	1),
(517,	'<p>We are committed to a work environment in which all individuals are treated with respect and dignity. You have the right to work in a professional atmosphere that promotes equal employment opportunities and prohibits unlawful discriminatory practices, including harassment. Therefore, we expect that all relationships among our team will be business-like and free of bias, prejudice and harassment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have developed this policy to ensure that everyone can work in an environment free from unlawful discrimination and harassment. We will make every reasonable effort to ensure that all concerned are familiar with these policies and are aware that any report in violation of such policies will be investigated and resolved appropriately.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Conduct prohibited by this policy is unacceptable in the workplace and in any work-related setting outside the workplace, such as during business trips, business meetings and business-related social events.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><u>Discrimination</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Discrimination based on race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy, sexual orientation, or gender identity), national origin, age, genetic information (including family medical history), marital status, or any other characteristic protected by law is illegal and will not be tolerated.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As noted elsewhere in this manual, we will provide reasonable accommodations to individuals who need them for medical or religious reasons, as required by law.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will not retaliate or otherwise punish anyone for reporting discrimination, participating in a discrimination investigation or lawsuit, or opposing discrimination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><u>Harassment</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Harassment can take many forms: written, verbal and non-verbal, and can occur with any type of medium: phone, email, texting, social networking, etc. In all cases, harassment is prohibited at all times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sexual harassment includes but is not limited to: verbal, physical, or visual behavior of a sexual nature; graphic or suggestive comments about an individual&#39;s dress or body, or actual or perceived sexual orientation; making unwanted sexual advances and requests for sexual favors where either (1) submission to such conduct is made an explicit or implicit term or condition of employment; (2) submission to or rejection of such conduct by an individual is used as the basis for employment decisions affecting such individual; or (3) such conduct has the purpose or effect of substantially interfering with an individual&#39;s work performance or creating an intimidating, hostile, or offensive working environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Harassment on the basis of any other protected characteristic is also strictly prohibited. Under this policy, harassment is verbal, written or physical conduct that denigrates or shows hostility or aversion toward an individual because of their race, color, religion, sex (including pregnancy, sexual orientation, or gender identity), national origin, age, genetic information (including family medical history) or any other characteristic protected by law, and that: a) has the purpose or effect of creating an intimidating, hostile or offensive work environment, b) has the purpose or effect of unreasonably interfering with an individual&rsquo;s work performance, or c) otherwise adversely affects an individual&rsquo;s employment opportunities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Harassing conduct includes epithets, slurs or negative stereotyping; threatening, intimidating or hostile acts; denigrating jokes; and written or graphic material that denigrates or shows hostility or aversion toward an individual or group that is placed on walls or elsewhere on our premises or circulated in the workplace, on company time or using company equipment by e-mail, phone (including voice messages), text messages, social networking sites or other means.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will not retaliate or otherwise punish anyone for reporting harassment, participating in a harassment investigation or lawsuit, or opposing harassment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><u>Reporting Discrimination or Harassment</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We support individuals who believe they are being subjected to such conduct to promptly advise the offender that their behavior is unwelcome and to request that it be discontinued. Often this action alone will resolve the problem. We recognize, however, that an individual may prefer to pursue the matter through reporting procedures.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We encourage reporting of all perceived incidents of discrimination or harassment, including threats, intimidation, and assault, regardless of the offender&rsquo;s identity or position. Individuals who believe that they have been the victim of such conduct should discuss their concerns with their immediate supervisor, or any other company supervisor/manager. We request that you submit this information in writing using the <em>Report of Harassment or Discrimination Form</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><u>Investigating and Responding to A Report of Discrimination or Harassment</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If discrimination or harassment is reported, we will conduct a prompt, thorough, and impartial investigation. The investigation may include individual interviews with the parties involved and, where necessary, with individuals who may have observed the alleged conduct or may have other relevant knowledge.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will protect the confidentiality of the individual who made the report, as well as those who participate in the investigation process, to the greatest possible extent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When necessary, we will take immediate corrective action with employees who have violated this policy. Corrective action includes, but is not limited to, formal written warnings, suspension without pay, and termination. The action we take will be based on the findings of the investigation and will be designed to prevent such situations in the future.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All employees reporting incidences of discrimination or harassment will be advised of the investigation, the investigation findings, and the corrective action taken.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If a party to a report of discrimination or harassment does not agree with the resolution, that party may appeal it with their immediate supervisor, or any other company supervisor/manager.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Retaliation against an individual for reporting discrimination or harassment or for participating in an investigation of a claim of harassment or discrimination is a serious violation of this policy and, like discrimination or harassment itself, will be subject to disciplinary action. Acts of retaliation should be reported immediately and will be promptly investigated and addressed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>False and malicious reports of discrimination or harassment (as opposed to reports that, even if erroneous, are made in good faith) may be subject to appropriate disciplinary action.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All incidences of discrimination or harassment will be carefully documented and retained in confidential files.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong><u>Rights of Employees </u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There is a five-year statute of limitation for filing a report alleging an unlawful employment practice of discrimination or harassment as described in this policy with the Commissioner of the Bureau of Labor and Industries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At no point may we require or coerce an employee to enter into a nondisclosure or nondisparagement agreement.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>A nondisclosure agreement is a contract by which one or more parties agree not to disclose confidential information that they have shared with each other as a necessary part of doing business together. A nondisparagement agreement is a contract between two parties that prohibits one party from criticizing the other.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You may voluntarily request to enter into a settlement, separation or severance agreement that contains one or more of the following:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A nondisclosure or nondisparagement stipulation</li>\r\n	<li>Prevents disclosure of factual information relating to a claim of discrimination or conduct that constitutes sexual assault</li>\r\n	<li>Has a no-rehire provision that prohibits you from seeking reemployment with us</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you request and enter into an agreement as described above, you have seven days after executing the agreement to revoke it.</p>\r\n',	6,	'Harassment Discrimination OR',	'ANTI-DISCRIMINATION AND HARASSMENT',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-12-18 22:55:30',	'2019-12-18 23:18:19',	'enabled',	3,	0),
(518,	'<p>If you are pregnant or you have a medical condition that is related to pregnancy, including childbirth, lactation or the need to express breastmilk, you may be provided with reasonable accommodation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The following are examples of possible accommodations that can be made:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Acquisition or modification of equipment or devices</li>\r\n	<li>More frequent or longer break periods or periodic rest</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance with manual labor</li>\r\n	<li>Modification of work schedules or job assignments</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you need any additional or different accommodations, please make your request known. We will engage in a timely, good faith, interactive process to determine an effective and reasonable accommodation unless doing so creates an undue hardship.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Preg Disability OR more than 6',	'PREGNANCY DISABILITY ACCOMMODATION',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"OR\"]',	6,	99999,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-12-18 23:00:45',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	86,	1),
(519,	'<p>Property or equipment belonging to us may not be removed from the premises without written approval. You will be responsible for the proper care and return of all property and equipment assigned to your possession.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are provided a key to the building, you are to notify us immediately if it is lost, and you are prohibited from making duplicate copies. You are not to discuss the security system or code, if applicable, with any unauthorized person. Violations may result in immediate termination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are provided with a desk or a locker for your use during work hours, you are not allowed to store items such as weapons, alcohol, illegal drugs, illegally prescribed drugs or medications, or other prohibited materials at any time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We reserve the right to conduct searches to monitor compliance with rules concerning security of company and individual property, drugs and alcohol, and possession of other contraband items. All employees may be subject to searches. Searches may include individual employees, work areas, computers, lockers or other storage devices, vehicles if driven or parked on our property or are used when conducting company business, and other personal items. These searches may occur at any time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If we allow you to have a locker or other storage area, we will either furnish the lock and keep a copy of the key or combination, or else allow you to furnish a personal lock, but you must give us a copy of the key or combination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If a search is requested, it is not an accusation of theft or other wrongdoing, but merely part of an investigation. Refusal to submit to a search may lead to immediate termination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We take no responsibility for any personal belongings that are lost, damaged, stolen or destroyed during work hours.</p>\r\n',	6,	'Property Equipment Security TX',	'PROPERTY AND EQUIPMENT SECURITY',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"TX\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"optional\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-12-18 23:05:00',	'2019-12-18 23:18:19',	'enabled',	9,	0),
(520,	'<p>We must keep certain personnel records in order to comply with legislated record keeping and reporting requirements. Many of these records you will be asked to complete upon employment. These records are confidential and only made available to authorized personnel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The physical safety and privacy of personnel records must be secured at all times. Therefore, files are locked and/or contain special computer access codes. Entry to the files is strictly limited to authorized personnel on a need-to-know basis. If you access your own, or a co-worker&rsquo;s, confidential employee file without authorization, you may be subject to disciplinary action up to and including termination.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Upon written request from a current or former employee, we will furnish a copy of all records or papers retained by us that reflect dates of employment, wages and salary, job description and title, and any injuries sustained by the employee during the course of employment with us. This shall be provided within 30 days of receipt of the written request.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We may charge a reasonable fee per page for copying these records.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Written request may be submitted using the <em>Request to Review Personnel File Form</em>.</p>\r\n',	2,	'Personnel Records VA',	'PERSONNEL RECORDS',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"VA\"]',	NULL,	NULL,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-12-18 23:07:50',	'2019-12-18 23:17:35',	'enabled',	15,	0),
(521,	'<p>We support your right to breastfeed and/or express milk. If you choose to do so during work hours, you may use lactation rooms or other private areas for this purpose up to 1 year after the birth of a child. This time shall run concurrently with state-required rest breaks, meal periods or both, when applicable. If additional time is needed, reasonable unpaid time for breaks, which is mutually agreed upon by you and us, will be provided each day to be used for breastfeeding or expressing milk. This is intended to allow new mothers to return to work more easily and to create goodwill and a more productive atmosphere. We reserve the right to modify or rescind the accommodation if it creates an undue hardship on the business.</p>\r\n',	4,	'Breastfeeding-WA under 15',	'BREASTFEEDING AND EXPRESSING MILK RIGHTS',	'none',	'2019-12-19 08:00:00',	NULL,	'[\"WA\"]',	1,	14,	'[\"required\"]',	NULL,	'[]',	'2019-12-18 23:10:37',	'2020-06-08 18:46:21',	'enabled',	201,	1),
